geSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:938,&quot;width&quot;:1456,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:625932,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;topImage&quot;:true,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F54a6bef8-fead-4f94-9f1a-421e537ce217_2000x1288.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F54a6bef8-fead-4f94-9f1a-421e537ce217_2000x1288.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F54a6bef8-fead-4f94-9f1a-421e537ce217_2000x1288.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F54a6bef8-fead-4f94-9f1a-421e537ce217_2000x1288.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" fetchpriority="high"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a><figcaption class="image-caption">Photo by √Årp√°d Czapp on Unsplash</figcaption></figure></div><p class="button-wrapper" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://timdenning.substack.com/p/nine-micro-life-hacks-i-found-on?utm_source=substack&amp;utm_medium=email&amp;utm_content=share&amp;action=share&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Share&quot;,&quot;action&quot;:null,&quot;class&quot;:null}" data-component-name="ButtonCreateButton"><a class="button primary" href="https://timdenning.substack.com/p/nine-micro-life-hacks-i-found-on?utm_source=substack&amp;utm_medium=email&amp;utm_content=share&amp;action=share"><span>Share</span></a></p><p>A lot of self-improvement is grandiose.</p><p>That‚Äôs why we dismiss the ‚Äú5 Ways to be Happy‚Äù nonsense and click the next article. I discovered a goldmine of micro life hacks on a Reddit thread called ‚ÄúLife Pro Tips,‚Äù that you can put into action without too much effort.</p><p>They‚Äôre awesome rule-of-thumbs that will save you time, money, and make you more sociable.</p><h1><strong>Say yes to more invites</strong></h1><blockquote><p><em>As an adult if new friends invite you to something say, ‚ÄúYes.‚Äù ‚Äî Vanguard Anon</em></p></blockquote><p>Children get lots of opportunities to make new friends. </p><p>As adults they don‚Äôt come around as often. One of my good friends went through a brutal divorce last year. We tried to invite him to lots of social events. He rarely says yes and prefers to play computer games.</p><p>We keep inviting him anyway because occasionally he says yes. The last time he came with us he made a new friend. </p><p>That new friend has since started going on bike rides with him that has got him out of the house. We‚Äôve noticed he‚Äôs losing weight, looking fresher, and in a better mood since.</p><p>Don‚Äôt underestimate the power of new friends. Say yes to random invitations and you‚Äôll meet new, interesting people.</p><h1><strong>Think of everything you do as progress</strong></h1><blockquote><p><em>Sent someone a meme? You progressed your relationship. Drew a doodle? You progressed your art skill. Took a bath? You progressed your mental health.</em></p><p><em>Life is a bank and any time you do anything that brings you joy you‚Äôre earning.</em></p><p><em>‚Äî Mew Brew</em></p></blockquote><p>The reason why many of us have phases in life where we feel like we‚Äôre making no progress is because we make things too big in our heads.</p><p>Of course if your goal is to make 7-figures in a year you probably won‚Äôt achieve it. But you can sell one book for $20, even if it‚Äôs to your mother. Or you can send one sales email, even if nobody reads it.</p><p>It‚Äôs important to tell yourself after every small action that you‚Äôre making progress towards a goal. That self-talk helps give you self-fulfilling motivation ‚Äî a type of motivation that will compound enormously over a year or more.</p><h1><strong>The weekend is where your future is built</strong></h1><blockquote><p>Use the weekend to build the life you want, instead of trying to escape the life you have ‚Äî Bigger_ThanLife</p></blockquote><p>When I worked a job I hated, the weekend was my escape.</p><p>I did anything I could to numb the pain. The problem is it got me nowhere. I‚Äôd be right back to hell at 9 am on Monday morning. That‚Äôs when I learned to build after hours. We‚Äôre talking micro hacks, though, so hear me out.</p><p>Do 15 minutes of a new side project every weekend. Do it for 21 days to make it a habit. Every weekend add another 15 minutes. Within a few months you‚Äôll slowly be transitioning from the life you hate to a new life with loads more possibilities. Quick transformations don‚Äôt work.</p><p>Slow transformations that start out as 15 minutes feel effortless. Effortless turns into action. Action changes your future.</p><h1><strong>Take pictures every day with your phone</strong></h1><blockquote><p><em>You may not like being in pictures or taking them, but you will hate that you have no photos of some time period when you‚Äôre older.</em></p><p><em>Take pictures even if it is out of your comfort zone occasionally, for your future self ‚Äî Squaragus_Asparagus</em></p></blockquote><p>I haven‚Äôt admitted this before so here goes‚Ä¶ </p><p>In 2011, I went from 60 KGs to over 100 KGs in weight, thanks to a personal trainer. I thought muscles would help me attract women. It did the opposite.</p><p>When I tell people this story the first thing they ask is ‚Äúcan you show me a photo?‚Äù I didn‚Äôt take a lot of photos back then as I was in a deep, dark depression and hated myself. The idea of taking photos of myself felt stupid.</p><p>Now I regret it.</p><p>During the lockdowns caused by the global health crisis, I decided to make a change. I took multiple photos (even ones with masks) to remind myself of one of the most difficult times in human history. Now I have photos to show my future post-apocalypse children.</p><p>Photos are memories. Take plenty. Keep them off Instagram.</p><h1><strong>Be awesome to non-drinkers</strong></h1><blockquote><p><em>If you offer someone an alcoholic drink and they say no, immediately tell them what non-alcoholic drinks you have. With no judgment.</em></p><p><em>They don‚Äôt owe you any explanation of recovery, medical contraindications, or whether or not they just don‚Äôt feel like it that day. ‚Äî Lemjne</em></p></blockquote><p>I haven‚Äôt had an alcoholic drink for years.</p><p>Too many times alcohol has ruined my life.</p><p>So I stay away from it but it‚Äôs bloody hard. When I worked a regular job one of the hardest things was going to a social event and being asked ‚Äúdo you want beer or wine, mate?‚Äù</p><p>The truly awesome people would then follow up with ‚Äúcan I get you a soda or a sparkling mineral water?‚Äù The knob heads would keep asking why I didn‚Äôt drink. They‚Äôd accidentally embarrass me in front of an audience.</p><p>Explaining why you don‚Äô drink is deeply personal.</p><p>I gave up due to a near-miss with cancer, my bad behavior around women when drunk, and the impulses to drink too much when life became unbearable. Explaining that in front of your boss or to a person on a first date with you is hard.</p><p>Quickly offer non-drinkers the non-alcoholic beverage options. They‚Äôll love you for it and you‚Äôll increase the chances of connecting with new people.</p><h1><strong>Ask this polite question in job interviews</strong></h1><blockquote><p><em>From here on out, make ‚ÄúWhat was your company‚Äôs 2020 response?‚Äù a standard interview question. ‚Äî PhasmaFelis</em></p></blockquote><p>Many companies did a terrible job in 2020 after the global health crisis. They treated us like bugs they could crush with their army boots.</p><p>How employers handle people during the tough times says a lot about them. If you‚Äôre deciding on a new employer and discover they did mass layoffs in March 2020, run a million miles away from them.</p><p>Compassion is the new business trend.</p><p>Every company that doesn‚Äôt get it will be scratching their heads and saying ‚Äúwhy is it so hard to hire people?‚Äù Screw them.</p><p>They deserve it for being evil to humans.</p><h1><strong>Use this to avoid the death spiral into a useless conversation about politics</strong></h1><blockquote><p><em>Next time you are stuck in a conversation about politics, ask the person ‚Äúwhat is your supported political party doing for you?‚Äù ‚Äî Roboboy3000</em></p></blockquote><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2 is-viewable-imag" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fd8113bb6-e91a-4850-a936-70283f975945_600x419.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fd8113bb6-e91a-4850-a936-70283f975945_600x419.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fd8113bb6-e91a-4850-a936-70283f975945_600x419.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fd8113bb6-e91a-4850-a936-70283f975945_600x419.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fd8113bb6-e91a-4850-a936-70283f975945_600x419.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fd8113bb6-e91a-4850-a936-70283f975945_600x419.png" width="600" height="419" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/d8113bb6-e91a-4850-a936-70283f975945_600x419.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:419,&quot;width&quot;:600,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:null,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:null,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" title="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fd8113bb6-e91a-4850-a936-70283f975945_600x419.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fd8113bb6-e91a-4850-a936-70283f975945_600x419.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fd8113bb6-e91a-4850-a936-70283f975945_600x419.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fd8113bb6-e91a-4850-a936-70283f975945_600x419.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a><figcaption class="image-caption">Image Credit‚ÄìSara Tasker via <a href="https://twitter.com/meandorla/status/1325766630266298368?s=20">Twitter</a> (WARNING: image used for demonstration only and does not reflect my political beliefs)</figcaption></figure></div><p>Most political talk leads nowhere.</p><p>It turns into a character assassination based on emotions rather than facts. Our politicians are out of touch with reality. A large proportion of them are white males over 70. It‚Äôs no wonder we lack a diversity of thought. This will hopefully change, but for now, it‚Äôs a long road.</p><p>Vote when the time comes. Don‚Äôt get too caught up in it. Instead, work on yourself. No politician is going to save you from inflation, or bring down the cost of your bills, or help you get a job. That‚Äôs the harsh truth.</p><h1><strong>Pretend other drivers are your grandmother</strong></h1><blockquote><p><em>When you don‚Äôt have all the facts, try to give people the most generous reason you can for their behavior.</em></p><p><em>Annoyingly slow driver? Maybe it‚Äôs a mom with a birthday cake in the back. This mindset will gradually make you less reactive, more compassionate and more forgiving of your own bad days.</em></p><p><em>‚Äî ContributionNarrow88</em></p></blockquote><p>I used to be a road rage maniac. I‚Äôd ride up the asses of every car on the freeway and scream ‚Äúget out of my way, pal!‚Äù</p><p>That‚Äôs what deep anxiety sounds like.</p><p>In recent years I‚Äôve used this life hack to think of other drivers as my grandmother. When she used to drive me around I‚Äôd be patient, forgive her when she made wrong turns, and be more helpful.</p><p>Grandma died a few years ago.</p><p>Her legacy lives on through the way I‚Äôve decided to treat other drivers. All of the blowing up at drivers used to drain my energy. Now I‚Äôm just a Sunday driver in a lawn bowls outfit and candy pink visor hat, sharing the roads with my fellow grandmothers and grandfathers.</p><p>Takeaway: If you knew that annoying person had just left the hospital to farewell the love of their life after dying from cancer, would you be so cruel? Of course not. Try to think that way about everyone you meet.</p><h1><strong>Do the phone survey and unlock a hidden reward</strong></h1><blockquote><p><em>If you‚Äôre asked to take a survey after a service rep/tech helps you out, take it and give them the best score possible‚Äî Stoncils</em></p></blockquote><p>I spent a good part of my career working in call centers. I had to ask every caller to do a survey.</p><p>Many of them would say no or hang up. It broke my heart.</p><p>They didn‚Äôt know how important it was. I had a KPI on how many surveys I got done. And if they left me a positive comment at the end it would get read out in team meetings.</p><p>One customer left me such a good comment after the survey that it got shared with thousands of my colleagues at a town hall meeting by our General Manager. As a result of that feedback I met my future boss who got me out of the call center and into a job I loved.</p><p>Customer service reps could do with your help. It takes 30 seconds and can help ensure they don‚Äôt have to work in the same job forever. Completing a survey is the gift of an opportunity.</p><p>You unlock the hidden reward of knowing you made a customer service rep‚Äôs day. Try it.</p><p><em>This final life hack is from me‚Ä¶</em></p><h1><strong>Don‚Äôt write controversial words on social media</strong></h1><p>It can get you banned and the platform‚Äôs machine learning/algorithms are trained to look for them.</p><p>You could be smacked in the face by the nanny police for trying to innocently share your story. They won‚Äôt tell you either. They‚Äôll either block your content or shadow-ban you.</p><p>Examples:</p><ul><li><p>S*x</p></li><li><p>Coroni-rona</p></li><li><p>P*rn</p></li></ul><p>Instead, just substitute the controversial word for one that has the same meaning and won‚Äôt trigger the nannies. Here‚Äôs an example: ‚Äúfuggit.‚Äù (Hat tilt to Sean Kernan.) See, you know what I‚Äôm saying, don‚Äôt you? Nice.</p><p>Until the web becomes decentralized this is what we have to deal with. No point complaining.</p><p>Tell me which of these life hacks you loved the most and why in the comments.</p><div><hr></div><p>P.S. 2024 is rushing to a close already.&nbsp;</p><p>Are you making the kind of money you'd like to make?</p><p><a href="https://event.webinarjam.com/register/70/ywkx0t73">If not, take a peek at my upcoming free masterclass.</a></p></body></html>	Micro life hacks save time, money, and boost sociability. Say yes to invites, view actions as progress, build your future on weekends, take daily photos, be kind to non-drinkers, and ask smart interview questions.	2024-09-05 11:04:54	2024-10-05 19:41:53.019	2024-10-10 14:04:45.21	{english}	https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F54a6bef8-fead-4f94-9f1a-421e537ce217_2000x1288.jpeg	Tim Denning	nine-micro-life-hacks-i-found-on-reddit-that-are-surprisingly-useful
19	https://timdenning.substack.com/p/your-life-is-won-or-lost-based-on	Your Life Is Won or Lost Based on Whether You Use Boredom to Your Advantage 	Or let boredom use and abuse you with a whip like a slave	<html><head></head><body><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2 is-viewable-imag" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F38e5d2f7-d0ad-4860-8a29-d7c1cd976f1b_1456x816.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F38e5d2f7-d0ad-4860-8a29-d7c1cd976f1b_1456x816.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F38e5d2f7-d0ad-4860-8a29-d7c1cd976f1b_1456x816.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F38e5d2f7-d0ad-4860-8a29-d7c1cd976f1b_1456x816.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F38e5d2f7-d0ad-4860-8a29-d7c1cd976f1b_1456x816.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F38e5d2f7-d0ad-4860-8a29-d7c1cd976f1b_1456x816.jpeg" width="1456" height="816" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/38e5d2f7-d0ad-4860-8a29-d7c1cd976f1b_1456x816.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:816,&quot;width&quot;:1456,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:239015,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;topImage&quot;:true,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F38e5d2f7-d0ad-4860-8a29-d7c1cd976f1b_1456x816.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F38e5d2f7-d0ad-4860-8a29-d7c1cd976f1b_1456x816.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F38e5d2f7-d0ad-4860-8a29-d7c1cd976f1b_1456x816.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F38e5d2f7-d0ad-4860-8a29-d7c1cd976f1b_1456x816.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" fetchpriority="high"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a><figcaption class="image-caption"><em>Image Credit-Midjourney</em></figcaption></figure></div><p class="button-wrapper" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://timdenning.substack.com/p/your-life-is-won-or-lost-based-on?utm_source=substack&amp;utm_medium=email&amp;utm_content=share&amp;action=share&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Share&quot;,&quot;action&quot;:null,&quot;class&quot;:null}" data-component-name="ButtonCreateButton"><a class="button primary" href="https://timdenning.substack.com/p/your-life-is-won-or-lost-based-on?utm_source=substack&amp;utm_medium=email&amp;utm_content=share&amp;action=share"><span>Share</span></a></p><p>Life is full of virgins.</p><p>Not in a sexual sense but in the sense that most people aren‚Äôt willing to try stuff. They refuse to take risks. They won‚Äôt consider a different point of view. They refuse to change. So their body ages but their ‚Äúself‚Äù stays the same age.</p><p>It‚Äôs why there are a lot of children living in adult bodies.</p><p>One of the biggest reasons people lose in life comes down to how they use boredom. For some of us, we‚Äôve accidentally learned to harness boredom. We don‚Äôt talk about it because a lot of us don‚Äôt even realize we do it.</p><p>Here‚Äôs a completely different perspective on boredom that‚Äôll upgrade your life.</p><h1>Boredom is a luxury</h1><p>A friend of mine lives in Africa.</p><p>His family is poor. He‚Äôs lived through famines. He‚Äôs someone I admire. When I asked him about boredom he laughed.</p><blockquote><p><em>‚ÄúOnly rich kids complain about boredom. In my village we have enough work to keep us busy for a decade. No time for boredom or you‚Äôll starve.‚Äù</em></p></blockquote><p>In one way he‚Äôs making a joke, but in another way he‚Äôs bang on.</p><p>Being bored shows a lack of gratitude. There are people battling cancer who‚Äôd love to have zero worries in the world and experience boredom.</p><h1>Consumerism needs you to be a bored ape</h1><p>Society isn‚Äôt trying to get rid of boredom.</p><p>Why? Corporations need you to be bored so they can sell you magic pills to cure it ‚Äì entertainment, sports, video games, mindless apps, etc.</p><p>Boredom has an even darker side.</p><p>I grew up around many drug addicts. One pattern I noticed is they all say they used drugs to try and cure their boredom. They wanted a thrill because they were bored.</p><p>A sniff of coke gave them a high. It also ruined their life. When I think about my own bad habits, they always get the best of me if I get too bored.</p><p>Boredom isn‚Äôt scary, but how we try to cure it is. It‚Äôs a slippery slope that can lead to an unescapable hell if you‚Äôre not careful.</p><h3>Romanticising boredom is a deadly cop out</h3><p>Boredom is a sign you‚Äôre living a life designed by someone else.</p><p>You took the traditional path. You listened too much to past, pre-internet generations. You took the default career path to nowhere to climb a corporate ladder leaning against the wrong wall.</p><p>There‚Äôs nothing worse than someone that brags about being bored. This same person lives for the weekends and they can‚Äôt stop thinking about their next escapism holiday because that‚Äôs honestly all they live for at this point in life.</p><p>Boredom is a big red blinking siren that‚Äôs trying to tell you to wake the f*ck up. And if you ignore the alert it‚Äôs the equivalent of hitting the snooze button on life for an eternity.</p><p>Boredom isn‚Äôt cool. It‚Äôs the highest form of mediocrity imaginable.</p><h1>The feeling of boredom is mislabeled</h1><p>The depth of experiences we can have as humans is vast.</p><p>We live in a world that has 100K pixel clarity. Life is fascinating if you actually choose to live it.</p><p>When people say they‚Äôre bored what they‚Äôre masking is a deep dissatisfaction for life itself. When what you do in life is so painfully useless, comfortable and lacks any sort of challenge, we wrongly call it boredom.</p><p>What we should call it is failure. Or a lack of goals. Or no passion.</p><h1>Your boredom holds your unrealized potential</h1><p>Netflix won‚Äôt make you feel better. It‚Äôs a sugar pill. It‚Äôs a fake placebo.</p><blockquote><p><em>‚ÄúReal pleasure comes from overcoming challenges, feeling confidence in your abilities, gaining fluency in skills, and experiencing the power this brings.</em></p><p><em>You develop patience. Boredom no longer signals the need for distraction, but rather the need for new challenges to conquer.‚Äù ‚Äì Robert Greene</em></p></blockquote><p>The cure for boredom is progress.</p><p>Not huge progress either. Just tiny 1%-better-each-day forms of progress. As an example, last week I felt a bit bored writing. Medium feels more stale than my daughter‚Äôs 2 week old sandwiches at the back of the couch.</p><p>So‚Ä¶I thought about how I could use this temporary boredom in my writing to harness it. The answer was lying right in front of my eyes. For the last 2 years I‚Äôve wanted to start an Instagram profile.</p><p>This week I finally did.</p><p>Now, instead of boredom, I have a new excitement for writing. It‚Äôs a new challenge. A new way of writing.</p><p>It‚Äôs more visual. I don‚Äôt know anyone on Instagram. I have no idea how to use the platform. I don‚Äôt know if I‚Äôm doing it right. I‚Äôm a pig rolling in mud and sh*t, and it feels incredible.</p><p>Boredom unlocked my potential. The next level of the writing video game has now been discovered. The truth is you can play real video games and waste your life away‚Ä¶ or you can treat real pursuits in life like a video game and level up.</p><p>In the process you‚Äôll go from being a bored ape manipulated by news/politics and whatever culture war is going on, into becoming a beast in your field of obsession.</p><p>Boredom is trying to help your hidden potential get unleashed. Most people try to numb the feeling instead of harnessing it. Sad.</p><h1>Here‚Äôs how to hack your boredom to make it work in your favor</h1><p>Time to become an outlier. You might even join the top 1%.</p><h3>1. The best antidote to boredom in history</h3><p>If you‚Äôre bored just follow your curiosity.</p><pre><code>What are you curious about? What can you not stop thinking about? What‚Äôs a childhood activity you‚Äôve given up?</code></pre><p>My answer to this is music. I was a musician until my mid-20s. I haven‚Äôt touched it for a decade. Last week my daughter got a toy drum kit on loan from the toy library. She handed me the drumsticks. I felt a wave of emotion.</p><p>I used to be one of the best drummers in the world (no exaggeration). Picking up those drumsticks again awakened a giant inside of me. Now I want to spend boring moments on the weekend showing my daughter the drums.</p><p>The cure to a boring life is right under your eyes.</p><h3>2. Play this game on hard mode</h3><p>Thinking of every pursuit in life as a video game is one of the best mental models.</p><p>Most people will play video games like Fortnite. A cooler video game to play in life is entrepreneurship. Starting a business makes everything in life better. Plus if it works to even a tiny degree, you end up with money.</p><p>Money is a resource that you can reinvest into your obsession to make it even better. I like the game of money because it‚Äôs tangible, whereas a lot of people play games to win fake prizes like points or participation trophies.</p><p>Play stupid games, win stupid prizes (as they say). Play games of obsession, like entrepreneurship, and become a different person you‚Äôll be proud of.</p><h3>3. Stop letting yourself off the hook</h3><p>People let deadly boredom run their lives because they‚Äôre not hard enough on themselves.</p><p>A mediocre life is your responsibility. If the job sucks, it‚Äôs on you. If money is always a problem, it‚Äôs on you. If every friendship or romantic relationship turns into painful loneliness, it‚Äôs on you.</p><p>The good news is when you‚Äôre to blame you can solve it. It‚Äôs how you take back control. Try being a little harder on yourself.</p><p>More discipline. A series of daily habits that are non-negotiable. An exercise routine for more energy. Less junk food that clogs up your body and steals your energy.</p><p>As long as you label bad things ‚Äúself-care‚Äù you‚Äôll keep letting the devil win.</p><h3>4. Make this powerful choice</h3><p>When boredom strikes we have two options:</p><ul><li><p>Distraction</p></li><li><p>Building</p></li></ul><p>Option one leads you to become a destroyer. To be angry. To leave nasty comments. To talk smack about successful people. To engage in mindless activities like scrolling social media at 11 PM.</p><p>Option two leads to a beautiful life. One where you solve other people‚Äôs problems. Where you become an inspiration. Where you start a movement. Where you create something new you can be proud of.</p><p>Whenever you‚Äôre bored label the feeling with either ‚ÄúI‚Äôm going to embrace distraction‚Äù or ‚ÄúI‚Äôm going to build.‚Äù I recommend the latter.</p><h1>Final Thought</h1><p>It sounds cliche as f*ck, but what you do when boredom strikes or when you have some time before or after work can either make you or destroy you.</p><p>No one tells us this though. The distraction economy doesn‚Äôt want you to know this secret because then they can‚Äôt profit off you. I have nothing to lose so I‚Äôll tell you.</p><p>Remember: The cure for boredom is progress.</p><p>Tell me which of these ideas you loved the most and why in the comments.</p><div><hr></div><p>I send this email weekly. If you would also like to receive it, join the 125,000+ other smart people who absolutely love it today.</p><p class="button-wrapper" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://timdenning.substack.com/subscribe?&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Subscribe now&quot;,&quot;action&quot;:null,&quot;class&quot;:null}" data-component-name="ButtonCreateButton"><a class="button primary" href="https://timdenning.substack.com/subscribe?"><span>Subscribe now</span></a></p><p>üëâ&nbsp;If you enjoy reading this post, feel free to share it with friends! Or feel free to click the ‚ù§Ô∏è button on this post so more people can discover it on Substack üôè</p><p class="button-wrapper" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://timdenning.substack.com/p/your-life-is-won-or-lost-based-on?utm_source=substack&amp;utm_medium=email&amp;utm_content=share&amp;action=share&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Share&quot;,&quot;action&quot;:null,&quot;class&quot;:null}" data-component-name="ButtonCreateButton"><a class="button primary" href="https://timdenning.substack.com/p/your-life-is-won-or-lost-based-on?utm_source=substack&amp;utm_medium=email&amp;utm_content=share&amp;action=share"><span>Share</span></a></p></body></html>	Boredom signals untapped potential. Harness it for progress, not distraction. Choose building over destruction. Follow curiosity to unlock hidden passions and level up in life's game.	2024-09-03 11:04:54	2024-10-05 19:41:55.058	2024-10-10 14:04:45.234	{english}	https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F38e5d2f7-d0ad-4860-8a29-d7c1cd976f1b_1456x816.jpeg	Tim Denning	your-life-is-won-or-lost-based-on-whether-you-use-boredom-to-your-advantage
20	https://timdenning.substack.com/p/all-you-need-is-a-bad-breakup-to	All You Need Is a Bad Breakup to Discover Your True Obsession and Become Wildly Successful	Breakups come in many outrageous forms	<html><head></head><body><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2 is-viewable-imag" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc1ec3b88-3e13-493d-8fe4-21d490b29631_1680x720.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc1ec3b88-3e13-493d-8fe4-21d490b29631_1680x720.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc1ec3b88-3e13-493d-8fe4-21d490b29631_1680x720.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc1ec3b88-3e13-493d-8fe4-21d490b29631_1680x720.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc1ec3b88-3e13-493d-8fe4-21d490b29631_1680x720.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc1ec3b88-3e13-493d-8fe4-21d490b29631_1680x720.jpeg" width="728" height="312" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/c1ec3b88-3e13-493d-8fe4-21d490b29631_1680x720.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:624,&quot;width&quot;:1456,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:728,&quot;bytes&quot;:241394,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;topImage&quot;:true,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc1ec3b88-3e13-493d-8fe4-21d490b29631_1680x720.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc1ec3b88-3e13-493d-8fe4-21d490b29631_1680x720.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc1ec3b88-3e13-493d-8fe4-21d490b29631_1680x720.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc1ec3b88-3e13-493d-8fe4-21d490b29631_1680x720.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" fetchpriority="high"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a><figcaption class="image-caption"><em>Image Credit: Midjourney</em></figcaption></figure></div><p class="button-wrapper" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://timdenning.substack.com/p/all-you-need-is-a-bad-breakup-to?utm_source=substack&amp;utm_medium=email&amp;utm_content=share&amp;action=share&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Share&quot;,&quot;action&quot;:null,&quot;class&quot;:null}" data-component-name="ButtonCreateButton"><a class="button primary" href="https://timdenning.substack.com/p/all-you-need-is-a-bad-breakup-to?utm_source=substack&amp;utm_medium=email&amp;utm_content=share&amp;action=share"><span>Share</span></a></p><p>She threw me out of the car in the middle of the road.</p><p>Pouring with rain. Tears pouring down my face. A car nearly hit me at 75 miles an hour. It felt scary. It felt overwhelming.</p><p>Our 4-year relationship ended in an instant. We never spoke to each other again. The future marriage ceremony by the lake, lit on fire. The unborn baby we could have had, dead. Both of them.</p><p>It felt like the worst day of my life.</p><p>My identity was tied to her. We did everything together. She was my best friend. My only friend at the time, if I‚Äôm being honest. Everyone at work knew us as the two bankers who met and fell in love.</p><p>Now what would I tell them?</p><p>I‚Äôm not sure why we broke up. It was a feeling. I had dreams of wild success. She wanted to settle down. I wanted to stay in Melbourne and she wanted to go overseas every weekend (one trip we did was 48 hours in Asia ‚Ä¶ who does that?).</p><p>Jumping on planes was exhausting. She was doing it to escape. I didn‚Äôt want to escape. I wanted to double down on my writing and be near family.</p><p>Two different people, worlds apart.</p><h1>The post breakup phase is incredible</h1><p>Once the nail was in our relationship coffin everything changed.</p><p>I became a psychopath.</p><p>People didn‚Äôt recognize me. My true obsession for writing came alive. I launched a newsletter. I wrote more. I built an online business.</p><p>I stopped living for a partner and started living for me. I built a new life. One that didn‚Äôt have to meet another person‚Äôs standards. One where I could tell my bank boss to stick his job where the sun don‚Äôt shine.</p><p>When we were together I couldn‚Äôt quit banking. It was a couple‚Äôs activity. We caught the train together. We went to the same work events. We were always together which was 99% of the problem.</p><pre><code>Obsession forces you to seek solitude.</code></pre><p>You can‚Äôt do great things if you have a needy lover handcuffed to your leg begging you to ‚Äúspend time with me, baby‚Äù every 5 seconds. Obsession changes how you do love.</p><h1>Breakups come in many outrageous forms</h1><p>The title of this story makes you think it‚Äôs all about love.</p><p>Breakups aren‚Äôt exclusive to a lover though. You can have a bad breakup with a boss, job, hobby, family member (even parent), or best friend.</p><p>I had a bad breakup with a boss in 2019. I worked with this guy in banking. He was cool. We ate steaks together. We swore a lot and sipped lattes every few days.</p><p>When I quit banking I got a new job. The role had no boss and they were hiring. I recommended this mofo for the job and he got it thanks to my endorsement. Shortly after I figured out he was the devil, worse than Hitler.</p><p>Then he fired me.</p><p>A friend no more. Traitor. It hurt bad. It took me many buckets of tears and 6 months to recover. The nice end to the story is he got fired, too, and ended up in a sh*tty job in the middle of butt-f*ck nowhere. So karma‚Äôs a b*tch, as they say.</p><p>This boss breakup changed my life.</p><p>I stopped trusting employers. I went harder on my side hustle. I got a new job but I was relentless. I said no to many boss requests. I had this carefree attitude that‚Äôd terrify most business leaders.</p><p>The bags under my eyes and the look in my pupils screamed ‚ÄúI‚Äôm here for 5 seconds then I‚Äôm gonna love ya and leave ya for my writing obsession.‚Äù</p><p>People I worked with knew my agenda. They didn‚Äôt care. Neither did I.</p><p>My side hustle was no longer a nice option. It was make-it-happen or death. No in-between. No piss-farting around. Pure relentlessness that‚Äôd rip your face off.</p><p>A breakup feels outrageous. And rage is what you need to get to the next level of life and do something you‚Äôll be proud of.</p><h1>Orchestrate a breakup</h1><p>There‚Äôs something in your life you need to break up with.</p><p>A boss, alcohol, cigarettes, drugs, a lover/spouse, bad parent, or 7-day-a-week job from hell. This story means nothing if you don‚Äôt take action.</p><p>I freaking dare you to break up with the thing you know is no good for you. I dare you to feel the fear and do it anyway. Obsession is found on the other side of breakups.</p><p>You need a catalyst to spark change. Change leads to transformation. And a good transformation needs obsession to give it rocket fuel to move forward.</p><p>When something feels like a horrible ending, it‚Äôs usually the seed of a new beginning. Only when we fall down hard and smack our face on the gutter, do we wake up and realize we‚Äôre living a groundhog day life that ends in boredom and regrets.</p><p>Wake up. Go have a break up.</p><p>Tell me if breakups have been good for you and why in the comments below.</p><div><hr></div><p>P.S. Whether you're heartbroken or not, a great place to put your energy is...</p><p>Posting daily online.&nbsp;</p><p>Have you started writing daily yet? Thinking about it?&nbsp;</p><p><a href="https://forms.gle/7LGuF6bojnHEJ4gi8">Take the "gut check" quiz here.</a></p></body></html>	A bad breakup can spark transformation. It fuels obsession, leading to personal growth and new opportunities. Embrace the pain as a catalyst for positive change.	2024-08-29 11:04:24	2024-10-05 19:42:06.013	2024-10-10 14:04:45.266	{english}	https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc1ec3b88-3e13-493d-8fe4-21d490b29631_1680x720.jpeg	Tim Denning	all-you-need-is-a-bad-breakup-to-discover-your-true-obsession-and-become-wildly-successful
21	https://timdenning.substack.com/p/it-takes-90-days-of-loneliness-to	It Takes 90 Days of Loneliness to Rediscover Who You Are	"Time alone isn‚Äôt lonely, it‚Äôs freedom"	<html><head></head><body><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2 is-viewable-imag" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F78146317-f99d-46e0-9584-a91ba8ec2607_1321x733.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F78146317-f99d-46e0-9584-a91ba8ec2607_1321x733.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F78146317-f99d-46e0-9584-a91ba8ec2607_1321x733.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F78146317-f99d-46e0-9584-a91ba8ec2607_1321x733.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F78146317-f99d-46e0-9584-a91ba8ec2607_1321x733.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F78146317-f99d-46e0-9584-a91ba8ec2607_1321x733.jpeg" width="1321" height="733" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/78146317-f99d-46e0-9584-a91ba8ec2607_1321x733.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:733,&quot;width&quot;:1321,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:308463,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;topImage&quot;:true,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F78146317-f99d-46e0-9584-a91ba8ec2607_1321x733.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F78146317-f99d-46e0-9584-a91ba8ec2607_1321x733.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F78146317-f99d-46e0-9584-a91ba8ec2607_1321x733.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F78146317-f99d-46e0-9584-a91ba8ec2607_1321x733.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" fetchpriority="high"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a><figcaption class="image-caption"><em>Image Credit-Midjourney via Reddit (Woman facing the monster of loneliness and slaying him)</em></figcaption></figure></div><p class="button-wrapper" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://timdenning.substack.com/p/it-takes-90-days-of-loneliness-to?utm_source=substack&amp;utm_medium=email&amp;utm_content=share&amp;action=share&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Share&quot;,&quot;action&quot;:null,&quot;class&quot;:null}" data-component-name="ButtonCreateButton"><a class="button primary" href="https://timdenning.substack.com/p/it-takes-90-days-of-loneliness-to?utm_source=substack&amp;utm_medium=email&amp;utm_content=share&amp;action=share"><span>Share</span></a></p><p>I‚Äôm a loner. Some say that makes me a loser.</p><p>I‚Äôve always been that way and thought it was a bad thing. In my 20s everyone wanted to go out and party. I just wanted to sit in my bedroom and make electronic music. When I tried to take that music out to nightclubs as a DJ, I crashed and burned.</p><p>I now see loneliness differently, and you will too (shortly).</p><h1>The discomfort of isolation</h1><p>Loneliness is uncomfortable.</p><p>When I worked in banking I had to say no a lot. No to after-work drinks. No to weekends away with other bankers. No to going to the AFL football (our bank was the major sponsor).</p><p>Each no made me feel like crap. Like I was letting people down or something was wrong with me. But if I didn‚Äôt, then I would never have had the headspace to be a writer.</p><p>Modern life is slowly making us go insane.</p><p>We can‚Äôt switch off. We can‚Äôt escape. We live in constant FOMO. We have headphones on 24/7 that destroy our hearing and leave us with a high-pitched ringing in our ears, that contributes to the insanity. It‚Äôs why modern life is a horror film.</p><p>When you always have other people‚Äôs voices playing in your headphones, you drown out your own voice. You forget who you are. You can‚Äôt hear yourself think. Therefore, you can‚Äôt be creative or solve big problems.</p><p>So what are you left with? Crippling boredom that requires endless entertainment to numb the pain.</p><p>Loneliness starts out as uncomfortable because most of us don‚Äôt do it. Even when we are alone we have Netflix or our phone to talk with us. We‚Äôre truly never alone.</p><p>To unlock your inner genius you must embrace isolation for a long enough time.</p><div class="pullquote"><p>‚ÄúHe moves fastest who moves alone.‚Äù ‚Äï&nbsp;Milton Friedman</p></div><h1>Lean into your dark side</h1><p>All of us have a dark side.</p><p>We unlock it when we‚Äôre alone. A recent example is Ben Affleck. He married Jennifer Lopez who he thought was the love of his life after decades of wanting one another.</p><p>Within two years they‚Äôre getting a divorce. This love affair started almost 20 years ago. Sources close to Ben say he has a dark side. He can never be fully present because he needs extended periods of solitude.</p><pre><code>It‚Äôs this alone time that has made him one of the greatest actors of our time.</code></pre><p>But his ex-wife JLO didn‚Äôt understand it. She wanted him to always be present. To always want to go away or be in the spotlight. On their honeymoon Ben and JLO had paparazzi around them all the time.</p><p>It led Ben to madness. So their marriage ended.</p><p>I can relate to this. Thankfully my wife knows I need solitude. She also likes the same alone time, so it works well for us.</p><p>In my banking days, I remember working out of a bank branch. All the other bankers would go home at 5 PM. I‚Äôd stay back. I‚Äôd finish my banking work at 5 PM and stick around to record podcasts with successful people. Or I‚Äôd stay there and write.</p><p>Most nights I wouldn‚Äôt leave before 9 or 10 PM. I stayed so late one night that I slept in my car. I was obsessed with this new life I‚Äôd found. I wanted to exit banking as quickly as possible, but knew only loneliness would get me there.</p><p>The other bankers used to make fun of me. They said I lived at the office. Bosses thought it was awesome. But no one knew I lived at the office to build my own thing, not do useless banking work like open bank accounts for customers.</p><p>Your dark side is where hidden potential is found. It comes out to play after hours.</p><blockquote><p><em>‚ÄúBeing alone is a power very few can handle‚Äù ‚Äì Aaron Will</em></p></blockquote><h1>Success isn‚Äôt complicated (but everyone thinks it is)</h1><p>When I see complicated paths to success, I see bullsh*t.</p><p>Loneliness is a powerful tool to get anything you want in life. If you do it for 90 days everything will change in your life. Here‚Äôs the thing: <em>I can‚Äôt promise you what will change because it‚Äôs different for everyone.</em></p><p>What I know is loneliness forces you to rediscover who you are.</p><p>You won‚Äôt come out the other side of 90 days of deep solitude the same person. It‚Äôs exciting. It‚Äôs breathtaking. But it takes a level of discomfort most can‚Äôt handle.</p><p>The first few days are like being 48 hours into a water fast. This memory stands out as I‚Äôm 8 weeks away from another stint in hospital. Before I go under the knife, I‚Äôll have to fast beforehand so it‚Äôs safe for the anesthetic.</p><p>As the hunger sets in so too will the darkness.</p><p>I‚Äôve been down this road since 2015. First, I‚Äôll wonder whether the cancer comes back. Then I‚Äôll stress about the hospital because I hate needles and blood. This time I‚Äôll stress harder because I have a 1 year old daughter. What if the hospital goes wrong?</p><p>But as wild as it sounds, I look forward to this darkness.</p><p>It‚Äôs deeply motivating. It interrupts my thought patterns and I come out the other side 10x more grateful than the average person who takes everything for granted.</p><p>The fasting will require solitude. The recovery in the hospital will require solitude, too. I wonder what the loneliness will teach me this time?</p><div class="pullquote"><p>‚ÄúTime alone isn‚Äôt lonely, it‚Äôs freedom‚Äù ‚Äì OrangeBook</p></div><h1>90 days is all it takes to rediscover who you are</h1><p>My challenge to you is to embrace 90 days of loneliness.</p><p>Here‚Äôs what to do in the 90 days:</p><ul><li><p>Delete all your goals. Start again.</p></li><li><p>Start writing daily online so you can use it to think deeply.</p></li><li><p>Create a new vision for your life. Dream big. Remove the limiting valves on your consciousness.</p></li><li><p>Think of one way to build a new network of people from scratch.</p></li><li><p>Read more autobiographies than you ever read before ‚Äì Steve Jobs, Winston Churchill, Arnold Schwarzenegger, Andre Agassi, and Alexander Hamilton.</p></li><li><p>Take some new risks.</p></li></ul><p>During this time get your phone out of your life.</p><p>Buy an Apple Watch if you must to escape the phone. Turn off social media. Quit all the networking events. Stop trying to be a socialite with your neighbors, The Joneses (who don‚Äôt give a f*ck about you), and just work on yourself.</p><p>90 days.<br>3 months.<br>A quarter of a year.</p><p>It‚Äôs no time at all, yet it‚Äôs a decent chunk of your life. I promise you, if you do this, your life will never be the same again. Most won‚Äôt. But the few of you who do are why I‚Äôve written this.</p><p>Tell me if this big idea resonates with you and why in the comments.</p><div><hr></div><p>I send this email weekly. If you would also like to receive it, join the 125,000+ other smart people who absolutely love it today.</p><p class="button-wrapper" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://timdenning.substack.com/subscribe?&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Subscribe now&quot;,&quot;action&quot;:null,&quot;class&quot;:null}" data-component-name="ButtonCreateButton"><a class="button primary" href="https://timdenning.substack.com/subscribe?"><span>Subscribe now</span></a></p><p>üëâ&nbsp;If you enjoy reading this post, feel free to share it with friends! Or feel free to click the ‚ù§Ô∏è button on this post so more people can discover it on Substack üôè</p><p class="button-wrapper" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://timdenning.substack.com/p/it-takes-90-days-of-loneliness-to?utm_source=substack&amp;utm_medium=email&amp;utm_content=share&amp;action=share&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Share&quot;,&quot;action&quot;:null,&quot;class&quot;:null}" data-component-name="ButtonCreateButton"><a class="button primary" href="https://timdenning.substack.com/p/it-takes-90-days-of-loneliness-to?utm_source=substack&amp;utm_medium=email&amp;utm_content=share&amp;action=share"><span>Share</span></a></p></body></html>	Embrace 90 days of solitude to rediscover yourself. Delete goals, write daily, create a new vision, build networks, read biographies, and take risks. Disconnect from technology and social events.	2024-08-27 11:04:09	2024-10-05 19:42:07.768	2024-10-10 14:04:45.279	{english}	https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F78146317-f99d-46e0-9584-a91ba8ec2607_1321x733.jpeg	Tim Denning	it-takes-90-days-of-loneliness-to-rediscover-who-you-are
22	https://timdenning.substack.com/p/how-writing-on-the-internet-made	How Writing on the Internet Made Me $1,000,000	The opposite of what you think. Not clickbait.	<html><head></head><body><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2 is-viewable-imag" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F19621110-bfed-4c14-9724-54fd8ebce91b_1500x1248.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F19621110-bfed-4c14-9724-54fd8ebce91b_1500x1248.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F19621110-bfed-4c14-9724-54fd8ebce91b_1500x1248.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F19621110-bfed-4c14-9724-54fd8ebce91b_1500x1248.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F19621110-bfed-4c14-9724-54fd8ebce91b_1500x1248.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F19621110-bfed-4c14-9724-54fd8ebce91b_1500x1248.jpeg" width="1456" height="1211" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/19621110-bfed-4c14-9724-54fd8ebce91b_1500x1248.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:1211,&quot;width&quot;:1456,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:337081,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;topImage&quot;:true,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F19621110-bfed-4c14-9724-54fd8ebce91b_1500x1248.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F19621110-bfed-4c14-9724-54fd8ebce91b_1500x1248.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F19621110-bfed-4c14-9724-54fd8ebce91b_1500x1248.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F19621110-bfed-4c14-9724-54fd8ebce91b_1500x1248.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" fetchpriority="high"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a><figcaption class="image-caption"><em>Photo by Poppy Martinez via Pexels</em></figcaption></figure></div><p class="button-wrapper" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://timdenning.substack.com/p/how-writing-on-the-internet-made?utm_source=substack&amp;utm_medium=email&amp;utm_content=share&amp;action=share&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Share&quot;,&quot;action&quot;:null,&quot;class&quot;:null}" data-component-name="ButtonCreateButton"><a class="button primary" href="https://timdenning.substack.com/p/how-writing-on-the-internet-made?utm_source=substack&amp;utm_medium=email&amp;utm_content=share&amp;action=share"><span>Share</span></a></p><p>Your first million dollars is odd.</p><p>Nothing changes and you 100% don‚Äôt feel rich, even though you should. I hit this milestone years ago from writing online. That means I get emails every day from people wanting to do the same.</p><p>Here‚Äôs my blanket response for how I made $1M from writing online.</p><h1>1. Write on social media</h1><p>Every day. Pick a topic you are crazy about. Reply to people‚Äôs comments. Have fun. Format your writing so it can be read on a phone. Ignore hateful comments.</p><h1>2. Don‚Äôt try to monetize on day one</h1><p>Focus on building a small audience first. Figure out what they want. Find their problems. When you find them, look for the pain.</p><p>Create a service to solve the problem. Promote it to your tiny audience. Make some money. Consider turning that service into a digital product to create more leverage.</p><h1>3. Have your life fall apart</h1><p>Wake up one morning and open your computer. Sip a cup of coffee. Smile at your crypto fortune. See all the Stripe emails for product sales. Think you‚Äôre a big shot. Consider ripping out a cigar and posting a selfie of you smoking it on social media.</p><p>For fun, check your digital wallet. Notice a withdrawal of more than $1M.</p><p>Fall to the floor. Nearly have a heart attack. Contact your best friend who works in crypto. Have him say ‚ÄúIt‚Äôs gone, mate.‚Äù Have coffee with him later that day. Explain how you now know why a person can jump in front of a train.</p><p>Go home. Face your wife. Tell her you love her, then share the bad news. Watch the dreams of her first home go up in smoke with the look she gives. See nuclear mushroom clouds in her eyes. The woman you loved. Heartbroken. Speechless.</p><p>Go back to your office. Write. Make money online. Feel like sh*t. <em>This is the first ripple.</em></p><p>Because you now can‚Äôt afford a home, look around for a new house to rent. Go to the open for inspections. Have your rental applications turned down. Wait in line while hundreds of people try to rent the same property as you.</p><p>Be reminded that record-high property prices are the cause. No one can afford to buy so they rent. Be reminded how $1M was supposed to exclude you from this problem. Now you‚Äôve gotta face it like everyone else.</p><p>Be humbled.</p><p>Eventually rent a new home under an airport flight path. Get woken up by helicopters flying overhead all day and night. Then, find out you‚Äôre going to be a parent. Be simultaneously joyful and terrified at the same time. Where will the baby sleep? How will the baby sleep?</p><p>Realize this is now the ripple effect at play and this is <em>the second ripple.</em></p><p>Rush your partner to the hospital. Baby is coming fast. Nurses everywhere. It‚Äôs all going to plan. Suddenly an alarm sounds. Doctors rush in. Your daughter‚Äôs heart rate is dropping. You could lose the baby. Blood everywhere. Needles. Gas.</p><p>Your daughter is born. She‚Äôs incredible. She pisses all over your new sweater and leaves a yellow stain. You smile. You kiss her. She can do no wrong. Perfection. Joy. <em>This is the third ripple.</em></p><p>Start looking for a new home (again). Go to house auctions in between writing and making money online. Lose every auction by hundreds of thousands of dollars. Be reminded again of the money that was stolen from you and what it could‚Äôve done in this situation.</p><p>Keep trying. Try to have hope when it feels like there‚Äôs none. Finally find a house. Get excited. Make an early offer. Have the owner accept it. See the smile on your partner‚Äôs face. Move in. Feel on top of the world. Paint the walls. Get the grass redone. Install a big screen TV. Feel like you‚Äôve made it.</p><p>One night, get woken up by loud music. Wonder what the hell is going on. Investigate. Discover you have a bad neighbor who believes they are above the law.</p><p>Get frustrated. Blow up. Go over and yell at them. Say things you wish you didn‚Äôt. Take them through the legal system. Sleepless nights. Waste a year of your life. Lose. Community organizations are above the law and have friends in local government. <em>This is the fourth ripple.</em></p><p>At the end of the legal battle you feel exhausted. You realize it‚Äôs taken a toll on your marriage. Your partner is not happy with you. You‚Äôve let them down. You‚Äôve spent too much time away from them dealing with this issue.</p><p>Make the difficult decision to get marriage counseling.</p><p>Feel like crap. Feel like a failed parent. Feel like you‚Äôve let your daughter down. Enter the therapist‚Äôs office and feel like you‚Äôve time-traveled back a decade, when you faced extreme mental illness. Remember the dark times. Have them haunt you.</p><p>Show up to couple‚Äôs therapy. See someone you know in the waiting area. Feel like even more of a loser. Tell no one. Keep it a secret. Pretend you‚Äôre okay. Act like a happy couple outside of therapy.</p><p>Wake up in the middle of the night with nightmares of divorce.</p><p>Imagine raising a child in a broken family in a broken 19070s home. Visualize the look on your kid‚Äôs face. Wake up the next day and commit to work on yourself. Try to find the source of the problem that led to therapy. Realize it‚Äôs you. <em>This is the fifth ripple.</em></p><p>Keep showing up to therapy. Listen. Notice the situation at home getting better. See the relief on your daughter‚Äôs face. Have the therapist make a strange comment. ‚ÄúNewly married couples with young children see me all the time. It‚Äôs normal. Getting therapy as a precaution is a sign of love, not a failing marriage.‚Äù</p><p>Feel relieved.</p><p>Late one afternoon you start writing a newsletter. You realize that everything in life is downstream of the ripple effect. One tiny event can trigger a series of other events. You can either make the ripples positive or negative. Making large sums of money has little to do with knowledge and more to do with what you‚Äôre putting out into the world each day.</p><p>You attract what you give. Create positive ripple effects for others and watch them reverberate back in your life.</p><h1>4. Publish a weekly newsletter for a year</h1><p>Build an email list so you own the distribution of your writing. Occasionally make paid offers to earn money, even if that‚Äôs just a paid newsletter.</p><div><hr></div><p><strong>Enough storytelling for today. Let's talk about you.&nbsp;</strong></p><p>How's your online writing journey going?&nbsp;</p><p>Started? Stalled? Struggling?&nbsp;</p><p><a href="https://forms.gle/AvzUvDcEdwXM5no38">Tell me the details here. I can help.</a></p></body></html>	Online writing journey leads to unexpected $1M. Life's challenges follow. Therapy, parenthood, and neighbor disputes ensue. Positive ripples create success. Weekly newsletters build audience and income.	2024-08-22 11:05:56	2024-10-05 19:42:18.886	2024-10-10 14:04:45.29	{english}	https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F19621110-bfed-4c14-9724-54fd8ebce91b_1500x1248.jpeg	Tim Denning	how-writing-on-the-internet-made-me-1000000
23	https://timdenning.substack.com/p/if-you-feel-like-an-outcast-and-nobody	If You Feel like an Outcast and Nobody Gets You, Read This	Common sense is the most common form of insanity	<html><head></head><body><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2 is-viewable-imag" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F4d9fe373-5c3d-428a-a51a-57648eb82018_970x630.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F4d9fe373-5c3d-428a-a51a-57648eb82018_970x630.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F4d9fe373-5c3d-428a-a51a-57648eb82018_970x630.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F4d9fe373-5c3d-428a-a51a-57648eb82018_970x630.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F4d9fe373-5c3d-428a-a51a-57648eb82018_970x630.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F4d9fe373-5c3d-428a-a51a-57648eb82018_970x630.jpeg" width="970" height="630" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/4d9fe373-5c3d-428a-a51a-57648eb82018_970x630.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:630,&quot;width&quot;:970,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:244904,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;topImage&quot;:true,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F4d9fe373-5c3d-428a-a51a-57648eb82018_970x630.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F4d9fe373-5c3d-428a-a51a-57648eb82018_970x630.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F4d9fe373-5c3d-428a-a51a-57648eb82018_970x630.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F4d9fe373-5c3d-428a-a51a-57648eb82018_970x630.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" fetchpriority="high"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a><figcaption class="image-caption"><em>Image Credit: ‚ÄúSay Anything‚Äù movie/ 20th Century Studios/JohnCusack</em></figcaption></figure></div><p class="button-wrapper" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://timdenning.substack.com/p/if-you-feel-like-an-outcast-and-nobody?utm_source=substack&amp;utm_medium=email&amp;utm_content=share&amp;action=share&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Share&quot;,&quot;action&quot;:null,&quot;class&quot;:null}" data-component-name="ButtonCreateButton"><a class="button primary" href="https://timdenning.substack.com/p/if-you-feel-like-an-outcast-and-nobody?utm_source=substack&amp;utm_medium=email&amp;utm_content=share&amp;action=share"><span>Share</span></a></p><p>I‚Äôm an outcast and it makes me depressed sometimes.</p><p>Most people don‚Äôt get me. Dinner parties are weird. Neighborly chats in the street feel off. ‚ÄúGoing out with friends‚Äù is a struggle.</p><p>As soon as I talk it‚Äôs like I‚Äôm an alien. It‚Äôs why I still tell people I‚Äôm a banker because if I told them what I really did, which doesn‚Äôt fit into any defined career path, they‚Äôd be so confused they‚Äôd tune out.</p><p>Being an outcast is a daily struggle.</p><p>And it‚Äôs the kind of struggle we should embrace. When I talk about being an outcast some people get confused. They think I‚Äôm talking about being a weirdo or wearing rainbow-colored pants to the supermarket sometimes. Nope.</p><p>An outcast is someone who doesn‚Äôt fit in. They‚Äôre outspoken. And most of all, they hate the mainstream narrative and avoid it like a bat virus plague.</p><p>Here‚Äôs why being an outcast is a superpower that you must embrace.</p><h1>‚ÄúFitting in‚Äù has the worst rewards in history</h1><p>When you try to fit in you become someone you‚Äôre not.</p><p>That means you‚Äôre a Hollywood actor jumping through circus hoops trying to do a strip dance for an audience of strangers. Fitting in means not being yourself, and it‚Äôs the secret goal of most people.</p><p>If you break down people‚Äôs fears, like I have through my fearless writer challenge, you realize the average person doesn‚Äôt want to rock the boat or speak out of turn.</p><p>They‚Äôre worried they‚Äôll be canceled or face a moment of public embarrassment, where their execution is televised for the world to see.</p><p>Outcasts know this powerful truth: <strong>nobody gives a sh*t.</strong></p><p>Nobody gives a sh*t about your career.<br>Nobody gives a sh*t about if you‚Äôre poor.<br>Nobody gives a sh*t about whether you‚Äôre happy.<br>Nobody gives a sh*t about what you write online.<br>Nobody gives a sh*t about whatever personal tragedy you‚Äôre facing.</p><p>All the average person gives a sh*t about is themselves.</p><p>We‚Äôre now all drowning in so many day-to-day problems we don‚Äôt have mental bandwidth to deal with anyone else‚Äôs. 24/7 news cycles, phone notifications, a full-time career, a lifetime of daily emails to open and delete, a to-do list a mile long.</p><p>The modern human is busier than ever so they don‚Äôt have time to give a damn about you. And that‚Äôs the best news you will hear for the rest of this decade.</p><h3>If you fit in you‚Äôre replaceable.</h3><p>Fitting in means copying others.</p><p>It means you walk and talk the same. It means you wear a penguin suit to work so you look like all the other penguins hoping for a big annual bonus and a juicy promotion.</p><p>It means you watch Marvel superhero movies and consume the same Netflix tv series that every other monkey in a clown suit is drowning themselves in so they can numb the pain of their normal life into next year.</p><ul><li><p>Fitting in means 6-figures of debt for a useless college degree.</p></li><li><p>Fitting in means living next to the Joneses in the suburbs and trying to one-up them every year with a house renovation or new car.</p></li><li><p>Fitting in means choosing a traditional career path, where your creativity and imagination is suppressed so hard you start to internally combust and sh*t out your mouth.</p></li><li><p>Fitting in means taking on a home loan to buy a house you can‚Äôt afford that you‚Äôll be paying off for the rest of your life. The recurring debt payments mean you can‚Äôt take lots of time off work. You must be heavily money-focused for the rest of your life. Always keeping score.</p></li><li><p>Fitting in means being less than you can be so you don‚Äôt shine too bright.</p></li></ul><p>This is a nightmare way to live that I wouldn‚Äôt wish on my worst enemy, Matt (screw you if you‚Äôre reading, matey, you piece of cr*p).</p><pre><code>The traditional path is the path to nowhere.</code></pre><p>In a world of massive technological change, artificial intelligence that leads to infinite intelligence, low cost or even $0 electricity thanks to nuclear energy, and human labor no longer needed because of robots‚Ä¶ doing what humans always did is the path to 1930s depression-like poverty and mental illness.</p><p>If you follow the conventional path you‚Äôre replaceable.</p><p>If you follow your curiosity anything is possible.</p><h1>Being an outcast creates loneliness which is a superpower</h1><p>Sometimes it‚Äôs lonely for me to be an outcast.</p><p>I feel like I don‚Äôt belong. But more and more I‚Äôm realizing solitude is a powerful habit. When you‚Äôre alone you can think deeply. My best creative work comes from periods of loneliness. Time alone lets me shut out the noise and focus.</p><p>The flow states that follow we‚Äôll knock most people to the floor.</p><p>3 years of work in a week is no joke when you embrace solitude and let it lead to flow states. Maybe the real problem is that humans need to spend too much time socializing so they feel like they belong to something.</p><p>In the process, they don‚Äôt have enough time to achieve their big goals.</p><p>Show me someone who‚Äôs okay to be lonely, and I‚Äôll show you an outcast who will go on to do great things and change the world.</p><div class="pullquote"><p>‚ÄúI used to think the worst thing in life was to end up all alone. It‚Äôs not. The worst thing in life is to end up with people who make you feel all alone.‚Äù ‚Äî Robin Williams</p></div><h1>Common sense is daylight robbery for your future</h1><p>Screw being normal.</p><p>Normal people follow the mainstream narrative. They argue over politics like it‚Äôs going to save their lives. Red versus Blue thinking in America is the worst. What if Red and Blue are both part of the same side?</p><p>Election promises are bullsh*t. When you‚Äôve only got the top job for 4 years you‚Äôll say anything. If you deliver on none of your promises there are no consequences.</p><blockquote><p>If a guy who‚Äôs in his 80s and can hardly string together two words is in charge of the greatest nation on the planet, what does that say?</p></blockquote><p>He‚Äôs not running anything. Someone is but it‚Äôs not Joe, Kamala, or Orange Man.</p><p>I don‚Äôt believe in conspiracy theories, so my best guess is the richest Americans run the U.S. and they use their money to manipulate congress through lobbying. This is why the mainstream narrative is a clown show.</p><p>All it does is outsource your control to a 3rd party where you have no control. People tell outcasts like me to follow common sense.</p><p>That means taking pharmaceutical pills, murdering loads of animals so I can eat, watching news designed to make me mad, getting into debt through toxic consumerism behaviour, and watching my savings erode to nothing thanks to underreported inflation and money printing.</p><p>Common sense is insanity.</p><p>Outcasts question everything. They even question the fact-checkers themselves.</p><h1>Being an outcast is a deep human experience that bends reality</h1><p>I never fit in at school.</p><p>There were three groups: Aussies, Europeans (Greeks/Italians), and Chinese. The Aussies rejected me because I didn‚Äôt care about driving fast muscle cars or throwing a shrimp on the barbie. No thanks, mate.</p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2 is-viewable-imag" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F290981e6-c7f0-4f6a-991c-0b2f4f5439a7_640x984.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F290981e6-c7f0-4f6a-991c-0b2f4f5439a7_640x984.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F290981e6-c7f0-4f6a-991c-0b2f4f5439a7_640x984.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F290981e6-c7f0-4f6a-991c-0b2f4f5439a7_640x984.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F290981e6-c7f0-4f6a-991c-0b2f4f5439a7_640x984.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F290981e6-c7f0-4f6a-991c-0b2f4f5439a7_640x984.jpeg" width="234" height="359.775" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/290981e6-c7f0-4f6a-991c-0b2f4f5439a7_640x984.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:984,&quot;width&quot;:640,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:234,&quot;bytes&quot;:124382,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F290981e6-c7f0-4f6a-991c-0b2f4f5439a7_640x984.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F290981e6-c7f0-4f6a-991c-0b2f4f5439a7_640x984.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F290981e6-c7f0-4f6a-991c-0b2f4f5439a7_640x984.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F290981e6-c7f0-4f6a-991c-0b2f4f5439a7_640x984.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a><figcaption class="image-caption"><em>Image credit: Wikipedia Creative Commons (1984 Paul Hogan ad for Australia)</em></figcaption></figure></div><p>I tried to fit in with the Europeans but their parents told them not to hang around Aussies like me.</p><p>Because of their racism, within 6 months of being in high school, my 3 best Italian friends would no longer speak to me. They ran away whenever I came near them. I tried with the Chinese, too, but I couldn‚Äôt speak their language so they looked at me and smiled.</p><p>By the end of high school, I decided university wasn‚Äôt for me.</p><p>My school didn‚Äôt know what to do with me. They told me to leave so I did. I ended up studying sound engineering with no prior experience. I had to lie about my age to get in at 16 years old when I should have been 18 and had a high school diploma.</p><p>In adult life, I decided to marry my wife who is from China. Aussies didn‚Äôt get it. They made fun of me. <strong>One Medium dot com article ridiculed me and said I was a s*xpat.</strong></p><p>I‚Äôd never heard this word before.</p><p>Nowadays, when I go to pick up my daughter from daycare I get all sorts of strange looks. Only mothers pick up their kids at our daycare. The dads are all at work. When I take my daughter swimming I‚Äôm the only dad. The other parents are all mothers.</p><p>They all look at me with this strange facial expression that says: ‚Äúwhy isn‚Äôt he at an office job providing for his family?‚Äù</p><p>Office jobs made me depressed. That‚Äôs why. And gender-allocated roles are silly.</p><p>When I was 6 years old my two best friends were Sri Lankan. We played cricket and ate curry every day. As a teenager many of my friends were Muslim.</p><p>I fasted with them during Ramadan. I even went to the mosque with them. Now, in my 30s, I go to Jewish Passover every year with friends and even read ancient passages.</p><p>When you don‚Äôt fit in and embrace other cultures your human experience is way more nuanced. You eat food from different parts of the world. You speak different languages. You go places others are afraid to go.</p><p>Black and white thinking and being stuck in a bubble is worse than being an outcast.</p><p>The full human experience is understanding all humans, not just the rednecks in your own backyard.</p><h1>See things differently and tell it as it is</h1><p>I don‚Äôt sugarcoat anything.</p><p>I learned this from my former buddha boss, who‚Äôs one of the most interesting outcasts I‚Äôve ever come across. He tells it how it is.</p><p>If the IT systems at the bank are blowing up, he tells you. ‚ÄúIt‚Äôs bad. Very bad.‚Äù His counterparts would try to make it sound like everything was fine which led to more devastation. Not buddha boss man.</p><pre><code>An outcast sees things differently which is why they‚Äôre often isolated or treated badly.</code></pre><p>I find hanging around outcasts useful because of this. I want to know what other viewpoints exist on a topic. If everyone is looking at an issue from the front, I like to talk to an outcast and get the upside-down view.</p><p>Growth only happens when we‚Äôre forced to stretch ourselves to the point of discomfort.</p><h1>The world is moving towards a ‚Äúcategory of one‚Äù</h1><p>There‚Äôs a logical reason why more of us feel like outcasts.</p><p>I often say to writers ‚Äúyou are the niche.‚Äù Writer Mike Goitein said to me in a chat ‚Äúwe are all a category of one.‚Äù</p><p>As more of us begin to embrace social media, we no longer fit inside of neat boxes anymore. None of us are single-topic humans. We‚Äôre not single-industry humans either. The trend of being a one-person business is catching on.</p><p>When you go from believing you‚Äôre an employee with a boss, to believing you‚Äôre a one-person with one customer (an employer) or multiple clients, your thinking starts to shift. The limitations the world wants to put on you in the form of niches, job titles, and labels don‚Äôt make sense anymore.</p><p>The more of us that go through this transformation, the more outcasts we will have.</p><h1>Being an outcast is the highest form of compliment in existence</h1><p>Let‚Äôs finish here.</p><p>Being an outcast is a massive compliment. Embrace it. It means you‚Äôre not being brainwashed. Instead, you‚Äôre programming your own mind. You‚Äôre thinking beyond the normal boundaries and daring to be yourself in all its glory.</p><p>Go out there and be an outcast with no f*cks given.</p><p>Tell me whether you are or are not an outcast and why in the comments below.</p></body></html>	Outcasts embrace uniqueness, question norms, and explore diverse perspectives. Solitude fuels creativity. Rejecting conformity opens doors to personal growth and unconventional success. Being different is a strength, not a weakness.	2024-08-20 11:05:06	2024-10-05 19:42:20.86	2024-10-10 14:04:45.302	{english}	https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F4d9fe373-5c3d-428a-a51a-57648eb82018_970x630.jpeg	Tim Denning	if-you-feel-like-an-outcast-and-nobody-gets-you-read-this
24	https://niallharbison.substack.com/p/unveiling-tinas-hospital	Unveiling Tina's Hospital 	Fit for the best girl there ever was	<html><head></head><body><p>Dear Tina,</p><p>I wanted to write to you as it was exactly a year ago today that you left us. I can‚Äôt explain how much I miss you and how often I think about you. I would say at least 50 times a day. </p><p>If I could push pause and freeze my life for a moment it would be with you in the hammock listening to <a href="https://youtu.be/yYcyacLRPNs?si=q8MeKyqgxtdO86kE&amp;t=33">this song</a> on our last day together. Your body had given up but you were so warm, so cosy and so happy. I was hiding the tears in my eyes. Me and you had known for a while this moment was coming and we hadn‚Äôt wasted a second. </p><p>You really taught me how to live life in the 6 months I knew you Tina and you left a huge impact not just on me but on the world. </p><p>You might no longer be here physically Tina but I wanted to tell you how you are still everywhere‚Ä¶</p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2 is-viewable-imag" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7d07a3a6-5b4d-4b10-be01-ad6e8e367dd5_1348x770.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7d07a3a6-5b4d-4b10-be01-ad6e8e367dd5_1348x770.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7d07a3a6-5b4d-4b10-be01-ad6e8e367dd5_1348x770.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7d07a3a6-5b4d-4b10-be01-ad6e8e367dd5_1348x770.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7d07a3a6-5b4d-4b10-be01-ad6e8e367dd5_1348x770.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7d07a3a6-5b4d-4b10-be01-ad6e8e367dd5_1348x770.png" width="1348" height="770" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/7d07a3a6-5b4d-4b10-be01-ad6e8e367dd5_1348x770.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:770,&quot;width&quot;:1348,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:2536629,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;topImage&quot;:true,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7d07a3a6-5b4d-4b10-be01-ad6e8e367dd5_1348x770.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7d07a3a6-5b4d-4b10-be01-ad6e8e367dd5_1348x770.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7d07a3a6-5b4d-4b10-be01-ad6e8e367dd5_1348x770.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7d07a3a6-5b4d-4b10-be01-ad6e8e367dd5_1348x770.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" fetchpriority="high"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a></figure></div><h3>You Made Me A Better Person</h3><p>You won‚Äôt believe how hard things got after you passed Tina. I‚Äôm sure they are all sitting beside you playing now but a week after you I also lost Snoop. A couple of months later Derek and Jumbo also left this world. It was one of the hardest few months in my life. The 4 of you were such wonderful dogs and the house was very quiet. I hope you are sharing tennis balls with the boys and all keeping each other safe. </p><p>What got me through that time and other tough moments was one thing Tina. It was thinking about you. Any challenge I‚Äôve faced this past year (there have been many) I just think of your face and your soft nature. </p><p>I think my own sobriety, depression and anxiety was already in control when I met you but you cemented the recovery. When I whispered in your ear a year ago that I would never let you or all the other dogs down it was an unbreakable promise. Iron Clad. </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2 is-viewable-imag" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F91979184-5f9b-46c3-b698-dc908b41dd22_1286x696.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F91979184-5f9b-46c3-b698-dc908b41dd22_1286x696.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F91979184-5f9b-46c3-b698-dc908b41dd22_1286x696.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F91979184-5f9b-46c3-b698-dc908b41dd22_1286x696.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F91979184-5f9b-46c3-b698-dc908b41dd22_1286x696.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F91979184-5f9b-46c3-b698-dc908b41dd22_1286x696.png" width="1286" height="696" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/91979184-5f9b-46c3-b698-dc908b41dd22_1286x696.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:696,&quot;width&quot;:1286,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:1828405,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F91979184-5f9b-46c3-b698-dc908b41dd22_1286x696.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F91979184-5f9b-46c3-b698-dc908b41dd22_1286x696.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F91979184-5f9b-46c3-b698-dc908b41dd22_1286x696.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F91979184-5f9b-46c3-b698-dc908b41dd22_1286x696.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a></figure></div><h3>We‚Äôve Operated On 20,000 Dogs Like You Since You Died</h3><p>I always remember stroking your belly and seeing the evidence of so much breeding. It‚Äôs amazing how a little memory like that can make so much change happen.</p><p>You were such a majestic dog but you were seen as an ATM machine and kept on a chain. I‚Äôm sitting here writing beside <a href="https://www.instagram.com/p/C-cy3bQvnEO/">Bowie and her 6 puppies</a> and I can‚Äôt help but think what a great mum you‚Äôd have been if you were given the chance. </p><p>You won‚Äôt believe it Tina but we‚Äôve managed to sterilise <a href="https://www.happydoggo.com/our-work">20,000 dogs since the day you passed</a>. We do it with 9 wonderful partners in 3 countries. It‚Äôs a big number to think about Tina but we estimate that might have stopped 200,000+ dogs being born into suffering like you. </p><p>It wouldn‚Äôt be right to for me and you to take credit for it Tina as there are SO SO many people involved and so much money to raise and logistics to plan. What I can say Tina is rubbing your belly helped me push to make things grow faster. You continue to inspire so much change like that Tina.</p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2 is-viewable-imag" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F20dc8adb-4846-44b1-88fa-c06159615ead_1234x714.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F20dc8adb-4846-44b1-88fa-c06159615ead_1234x714.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F20dc8adb-4846-44b1-88fa-c06159615ead_1234x714.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F20dc8adb-4846-44b1-88fa-c06159615ead_1234x714.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F20dc8adb-4846-44b1-88fa-c06159615ead_1234x714.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F20dc8adb-4846-44b1-88fa-c06159615ead_1234x714.png" width="1234" height="714" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/20dc8adb-4846-44b1-88fa-c06159615ead_1234x714.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:714,&quot;width&quot;:1234,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:1833307,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F20dc8adb-4846-44b1-88fa-c06159615ead_1234x714.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F20dc8adb-4846-44b1-88fa-c06159615ead_1234x714.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F20dc8adb-4846-44b1-88fa-c06159615ead_1234x714.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F20dc8adb-4846-44b1-88fa-c06159615ead_1234x714.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a></figure></div><h3>We‚Äôre Building A Hospital In Your Name </h3><p>I remember when I buried you beside the hammock as the last stones went on I had a moment where I just screamed into the jungle. It was a mixture of anger, sadness but also determination. I wasn‚Äôt going to let your life go to waste. </p><p>We are now officially building the hospital in your name. You can <a href="https://www.happydoggo.com/tinas-hospital">see all the details here.</a> The incredible thing is that <a href="https://www.dannyforster.com/">unbelievably talented architects</a> from America and some other wonderful partners have done this all free of charge Tina. They were so inspired by YOU that they created a building that will help all the sick dogs. </p><p>The design is so unique that it even has your grave built in and a reflective place for people to visit you. Your spirit will guide the vets and nurses who work there and your kind nature will make the sick dogs feel safe as they get X rays, surgeries and all the other treatments they need. </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2 is-viewable-imag" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F9c34072e-5038-4cbd-aa69-bb92aa8b1942_1878x1242.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F9c34072e-5038-4cbd-aa69-bb92aa8b1942_1878x1242.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F9c34072e-5038-4cbd-aa69-bb92aa8b1942_1878x1242.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F9c34072e-5038-4cbd-aa69-bb92aa8b1942_1878x1242.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F9c34072e-5038-4cbd-aa69-bb92aa8b1942_1878x1242.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F9c34072e-5038-4cbd-aa69-bb92aa8b1942_1878x1242.png" width="1456" height="963" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/9c34072e-5038-4cbd-aa69-bb92aa8b1942_1878x1242.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:963,&quot;width&quot;:1456,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:5322588,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F9c34072e-5038-4cbd-aa69-bb92aa8b1942_1878x1242.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F9c34072e-5038-4cbd-aa69-bb92aa8b1942_1878x1242.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F9c34072e-5038-4cbd-aa69-bb92aa8b1942_1878x1242.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F9c34072e-5038-4cbd-aa69-bb92aa8b1942_1878x1242.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a></figure></div><p>I made the name up last year just after you had left us as a bit of a joke. The more I thought about it though the more I realised that it was perfectly fitting. <strong>Tina‚Äôs Hospital For Dogs Who Aren‚Äôt Doing So Good</strong>. Thats exactly what it will be called. </p><p>People bought T-Shirts, they climbed mountains and donated from all over the world in your name Tina. We are more than <a href="https://www.happydoggo.com/tinas-hospital">50% of the way there to funding it already</a>. We‚Äôve already started building the road into the land so trucks and machinery can get there.</p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2 is-viewable-imag" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F5fe1dc2d-148f-463a-aea6-86e6104bc293_1324x964.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F5fe1dc2d-148f-463a-aea6-86e6104bc293_1324x964.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F5fe1dc2d-148f-463a-aea6-86e6104bc293_1324x964.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F5fe1dc2d-148f-463a-aea6-86e6104bc293_1324x964.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F5fe1dc2d-148f-463a-aea6-86e6104bc293_1324x964.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F5fe1dc2d-148f-463a-aea6-86e6104bc293_1324x964.png" width="1324" height="964" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/5fe1dc2d-148f-463a-aea6-86e6104bc293_1324x964.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:964,&quot;width&quot;:1324,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:2666136,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F5fe1dc2d-148f-463a-aea6-86e6104bc293_1324x964.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F5fe1dc2d-148f-463a-aea6-86e6104bc293_1324x964.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F5fe1dc2d-148f-463a-aea6-86e6104bc293_1324x964.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F5fe1dc2d-148f-463a-aea6-86e6104bc293_1324x964.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a></figure></div><h3>I Love You Tina</h3><p>If I‚Äôm honest Tina I haven‚Äôt stopped since you died to take time off. I stay busy every single hour of every day on this mission. I‚Äôm scared to stop and just look at pictures and videos of you. I miss you too much to do that. </p><p>I made a little <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Bs0vSPOhvmA">video about you Tina here that you‚Äôll hopefully like</a> (I got a little emotional). I think this best sums up how I genuinely feel about you. </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2 is-viewable-imag" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc79eb599-5bd2-4548-9be0-b2f5574ad2f4_1704x1086.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc79eb599-5bd2-4548-9be0-b2f5574ad2f4_1704x1086.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc79eb599-5bd2-4548-9be0-b2f5574ad2f4_1704x1086.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc79eb599-5bd2-4548-9be0-b2f5574ad2f4_1704x1086.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc79eb599-5bd2-4548-9be0-b2f5574ad2f4_1704x1086.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc79eb599-5bd2-4548-9be0-b2f5574ad2f4_1704x1086.png" width="1456" height="928" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/c79eb599-5bd2-4548-9be0-b2f5574ad2f4_1704x1086.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:928,&quot;width&quot;:1456,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:4521227,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc79eb599-5bd2-4548-9be0-b2f5574ad2f4_1704x1086.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc79eb599-5bd2-4548-9be0-b2f5574ad2f4_1704x1086.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc79eb599-5bd2-4548-9be0-b2f5574ad2f4_1704x1086.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc79eb599-5bd2-4548-9be0-b2f5574ad2f4_1704x1086.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a></figure></div><p>You would be way too modest to acknowledge it Tina but you left a huge imprint. Not just on me but also on people around the world. </p><p>I often try to think why that was. For me it boils down to 2nd chances and living life to it‚Äôs full. You‚Äôd been dealt the worst hand of cards imaginable but you didn‚Äôt let that stop you once you got your chance. You lived every second like it was your last. You loved everybody. You had no regrets. </p><p>So many of us struggle in life Tina. Over the last year I‚Äôve spoken to people with serious illness, people who themselves were dying, others with depression and lots of other illnesses and hard situations in life. In New York, Dublin, Manchester, Dubai and Thailand people have told me with tears in their eyes how you helped them. Imagine that Tina. </p><p>You couldn‚Äôt solve all the worlds problems but for a dog on a chain with only 6 months of proper living you sure crammed a lot in! </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2 is-viewable-imag" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F1de9a511-e31e-43e9-9e62-3b20d8b92816_1182x754.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F1de9a511-e31e-43e9-9e62-3b20d8b92816_1182x754.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F1de9a511-e31e-43e9-9e62-3b20d8b92816_1182x754.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F1de9a511-e31e-43e9-9e62-3b20d8b92816_1182x754.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F1de9a511-e31e-43e9-9e62-3b20d8b92816_1182x754.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F1de9a511-e31e-43e9-9e62-3b20d8b92816_1182x754.png" width="1182" height="754" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/1de9a511-e31e-43e9-9e62-3b20d8b92816_1182x754.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:754,&quot;width&quot;:1182,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:1673236,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F1de9a511-e31e-43e9-9e62-3b20d8b92816_1182x754.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F1de9a511-e31e-43e9-9e62-3b20d8b92816_1182x754.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F1de9a511-e31e-43e9-9e62-3b20d8b92816_1182x754.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F1de9a511-e31e-43e9-9e62-3b20d8b92816_1182x754.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a></figure></div><p>Life isn‚Äôt always easy helping the dogs Tina. It‚Äôs actually very hard. I see some horrible things and wish it could change quicker. I just wanted to let you know what a difference you have made in terms of speeding things up. I‚Äôm no longer scared of massive scale and I do things with a Tina attitude. Nobody or no single thing can get me down.</p><p>I ask myself every single day ‚Äúwould Tina be proud of you today‚Äù and the answer so far is yes. I miss you so much Tina but I‚Äôll always be grateful I met you because you changed everything for the better. </p><p>I‚Äôll see you somewhere one day soon,</p><p>To the best girl there ever was, I love you more than you‚Äôll ever know. </p><p>Niall</p><p>P.S</p><p>You can see <a href="https://www.happydoggo.com/tinas-hospital">the hospital plans and donate here</a> </p><p></p><p></p></body></html>	A heartfelt tribute to Tina, a rescue dog who inspired global change. Her short life sparked a mission to help thousands of dogs, including building a hospital in her name. Her legacy lives on.	2024-08-18 06:02:54	2024-10-05 19:42:43.552	2024-10-10 14:04:45.681	{english}	https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7d07a3a6-5b4d-4b10-be01-ad6e8e367dd5_1348x770.png	Niall Harbison	unveiling-tinas-hospital
123	https://babyvc.substack.com/p/new-llm-launch-ai-sales-agents-crowdfunded	New LLM Launch, AI Sales Agents, Crowdfunded Plant-based Food, and much more...	What's Up Tech? #194	<html><head></head><body><p>Welcome to our <strong>194th </strong>newsletter, written with üñ§ by <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/annika-bautista-453106168/">Annika Bautista</a> and <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/sarah-luna-mongin/">Sarah Luna Mongin</a></p><pre><code>üîç Topics we'll cover this week</code></pre><ul><li><p><strong>Fundraising &amp; general news from the week</strong>: the Artificial General Intelligence (AGI) race is heating up with landmark fundraising, and AI agents want to sell you the next big thing‚Ä¶ü§ñ </p></li><li><p><strong>Up-and-coming ventures to watch: </strong>Efficiency in production is the theme of the week ‚ú®</p></li><li><p><strong>Internships &amp; Job</strong> <strong>offers</strong> of the week </p></li><li><p><strong>In case you missed it: </strong>Our <a href="https://babyvc.substack.com/p/scaling-and-investing-in-techbio">last article</a> in the HealthTech Deep Dive series is out!  </p></li></ul><p>Enjoy the read! üíõ</p><pre><code><code>ü§ë Fundraisings of the week</code></code></pre><h3>üß† OpenAI and poolside lead the AI fundraising race with landmark rounds (üá∫üá∏üá´üá∑)</h3><p>The fight to be the leader in AGI is on. üî• <a href="https://openai.com/">OpenAI</a> announced its raise of <strong>$6.6 billion at a post-money valuation of $157 billion</strong>, led by <a href="https://thrivecap.com/">Thrive Capital</a>. According <a href="https://openai.com/index/scale-the-benefits-of-ai/">to the team</a>, the new funding round is meant to scale its efforts ‚Äúin frontier AI research, increase compute capacity, and continue building tools that help people solve hard problems.‚Äù ‚ö°Ô∏è</p><p>Meanwhile, <a href="https://poolside.ai/">poolside</a>, an AI-driven coding startup, has raised <strong>‚Ç¨500 million in Series B funding at a post-money valuation of $3 billion, </strong>led by <a href="https://baincapitalventures.com/">Bain Capital Ventures</a>. The funding will be used to train new models on 10,000 Nvidia GPUs, and strengthen their go-to-market and research efforts. While originally from the U.S., poolside relocated their headquarters to Paris in August 2023 to capitalize on France‚Äôs growing startup scene and AI funding momentum. üöÄ</p><blockquote><p><a href="https://techcrunch.com/2024/10/02/openai-raises-6-6b-and-is-now-valued-at-157b/">OpenAI Raises $6.6 billion and is now Valued at $157 billion</a></p><p><a href="https://techcrunch.com/2024/10/02/ai-coding-startup-poolside-raises-500m-from-ebay-nvidia-and-others/">AI Coding Startup Poolside Raises $500 million from eBay, Nvidia, and Others</a></p></blockquote><div><hr></div><h3>üíª Pydantic builds developer-first tools with new fund raise of ‚Ç¨12.5 million (<strong>üá¨üáß</strong>)</h3><p><a href="https://pydantic.dev/">Pydantic</a> became known for their open source data validation Python framework that‚Äôs used by developers from tech companies, such as Meta, Netflix, and OpenAI. Now, the company has secured <strong>‚Ç¨12.5 million in Series A funding</strong>, led by <a href="https://www.sequoiacap.com/">Sequoia</a>.  The funding will go towards further development of a new product - a data observability platform called <a href="https://pydantic.dev/logfire">Logfire</a>. The tool is meant to ease error spotting and enrich analysis in data-rich environments.  üî•</p><blockquote><p><a href="https://techcrunch.com/2024/10/01/sequoia-backs-pydantic-to-expand-beyond-its-open-source-data-validation-framework/">Sequoia Backs Pydantic to Expand Beyond Its Open Source Data-Validation Framework</a></p></blockquote><div><hr></div><h3>üïµÔ∏è 11x secures $50 million to scale AI-driven sales agents(üá¨üáß)</h3><p>Agentic AI, or AI-enabled products that operate on a pay-per-task model, rather than  pay-per-seat, is in full swing. <a href="https://www.11x.ai/">11x</a> is proof of that, having raised <strong>$50 million in Series B funding</strong>,<strong> </strong>led by <a href="https://a16z.com/">a16z</a>,<strong> with a post-money valuation of $350 million</strong>. üëè The company is developing a Sales Development Representative (SDR) agent to automate sales processes.</p><p>The round comes just weeks after a <a href="https://www.11x.ai/blog/series-a">$24 million Series A round announcement</a>. </p><blockquote><p><a href="https://techcrunch.com/2024/09/30/11x-ai-a-developer-of-ai-sales-reps-has-raised-50m-series-b-led-by-a16z-sources-say/">11x.ai, a Developer of AI Sales Reps, Has Raised $50 million Series B Led by A16Z, Sources Say</a></p></blockquote><div><hr></div><h3>ü•ì La Vie raised ‚Ç¨25 million to fuel innovation and growth in plant-based foods (<strong>üá´üá∑</strong>)</h3><p>French foodtech startup <a href="https://www.laviefoods.com/">La Vie</a> has secured ‚Ç¨25 million in funding to continue innovating its plant-based products. Existing investors, along with new partners like <a href="https://zintinus.com/">Zintinus</a> and <a href="https://sparkfood.com/">Sparkfood</a>, participated in this round, which also included a <strong>record-setting crowdequity campaign</strong> with over 3,000 contributors investing as little as ‚Ç¨10.</p><p>Known for its award-winning <a href="https://www.laviefoods.com/produits/bacon/">vegan bacon and ham</a>, La Vie has expanded its range to include plant-based meatballs with Italian and Asian flavors. The company which currently employs 70 people, plans to <strong>recruit an additional dozen employees</strong> by 2025 to support its projected 80% revenue growth, building on its current ‚Ç¨19 million turnover. üìà</p><blockquote><p><a href="https://www.maddyness.com/2024/10/04/la-vie-leve-25-millions-deuros-pour-poursuivre-le-developpement-de-la-charcuterie-vegetale/">La Vie Raises ‚Ç¨25 Million to Continue Developing Plant-Based Charcuterie</a></p></blockquote><div><hr></div><h3>üß¨ Kurma partners announces ‚Ç¨140 million first close for new biotech fund (<strong>üá´üá∑</strong>)</h3><p>Paris-based VC firm <a href="https://www.kurmapartners.com/en">Kurma Partners</a>, specializing in health and biotech and part of the <a href="https://www.eurazeo.com/en">Eurazeo Group</a>, has secured a ‚Ç¨140 million first close for its latest fund, with a <strong>target of ‚Ç¨250 million by 2025</strong>. This will be <strong>the firm‚Äôs largest fund</strong>, aiming to support startups developing prescription drugs for various diseases. üíä</p><p>Kurma‚Äôs previous fund (worth ‚Ç¨160 million) saw successful exits, including the ~$800 million acquisition of France-based <a href="https://www.astrazeneca.com/media-centre/press-releases/2024/acquisition-of-amolyt-pharma-completed.html">Amolyt Pharma by AstraZeneca</a> and the purchase of German cancer startup <a href="https://transkript.de/artikel/2023/eli-lilly-kauft-emergence-therapeutics-fuer-rund-350-mio-us-dollar/">Emergence Therapeutics by Eli Lilly</a>. From the new fund, Kurma plans to invest in 16-20 startups, half of which the firm has co-created by identifying promising academic research.</p><blockquote><p><a href="https://sifted.eu/articles/eurazeo-kurma-partners-fundraise-news">Eurazeo‚Äôs Kurma Partners Hits First Close of ‚Ç¨140m for Biotech Fund</a></p></blockquote><pre><code><code>üî• Up-and-coming startups to watch</code></code></pre><h3><strong>üë∑ </strong>Ameba raises ‚Ç¨6.4 million to streamline supply chain management (<strong>üá¨üáß)</strong></h3><p><a href="https://ameba.ai/">Ameba</a> has closed a <strong>‚Ç¨6.4 million seed funding</strong> led by <a href="https://www.hedosophia.com/">Hedosophia </a>to revolutionize supply chain management through automated data extraction across multiple channels, such as e-mail, WhatsApp, and online documents and spreadsheets. The startup also aims to <strong>reduce manual data entry by 30%</strong>, offering significant efficiency improvements for businesses. üôå</p><blockquote><p><a href="https://www.eu-startups.com/2024/10/london-based-ameba-raises-e6-4-million-to-transform-global-supply-chains-with-its-ai-driven-platform/">London-based Ameba Raises ‚Ç¨6.4 million to Transform Global Supply Chains with Its AI-driven Platform</a></p></blockquote><div><hr></div><h3>‚ö° NRJx raises ‚Ç¨2 million to expand and tackle global energy challenges (<strong>üá´üá∑</strong>)</h3><p>French startup <a href="https://www.nrjx.tech/">NRJx</a> has raised ‚Ç¨2 million in its first funding round, led by <a href="https://www.bpifrance.fr/nos-solutions/investissement/investissement-expertise/digital-venture">Bpifrance‚Äôs Digital Ventures</a> fund and <a href="https://www.ringcp.com/generations/">Ring Capital</a>‚Äôs impact seed fund, G√©n√©rations powered by Edhec, alongside several business angels. üëº</p><p>The funds will be used to <strong>double the team size and expand operations</strong>, with a goal of saving the energy equivalent of a city of 50,000 people by 2025, according to co-founder <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/alexandre-kipp-151392105/">Alexandre Kipp</a>. NRJx also aims to enhance its product by improving energy consumption forecasting and boosting brand awareness. </p><blockquote><p><a href="https://www.maddyness.com/2024/10/03/nrjx-leve-2-millions-deuros-pour-reduire-la-consommation-denergie-dans-les-usines/">NRJx Raises ‚Ç¨2 Million to Cut Energy Consumption in Factories</a></p></blockquote><pre><code>üì∞ News of the week</code></pre><h3>üöÄ Nvidia recently launched NVLM 1.0, a new family of open-source LLMs</h3><p>Early October 2024, Nvidia launched <a href="https://research.nvidia.com/labs/adlr/NVLM-1/">NVLM 1.0</a>, a series of advanced multi-modal language models comparable to GPT-4. Instead of competing directly with consumer AI platforms like ChatGPT, Nvidia is enabling others to build their own AI tools by making <strong>NVLM‚Äôs model weights publicly available</strong>. </p><p>Previously known for its AI hardware, Nvidia is now showcasing its strength in generative AI by providing open access to key AI development resources.</p><blockquote><p><a href="https://bgr.com/tech/nvidia-stunned-the-world-with-a-chatgpt-rival-thats-as-good-as-gpt-4o/?_bhlid=ba0f624b9e7bf7e8fd4f3b5bf83134790444a9f6">Nvidia Stunned the World with A ChatGPT Rival That‚Äôs As Good As GPT-4o</a></p></blockquote><div><hr></div><h3>‚ò¢Ô∏è Newcleo raises ‚Ç¨135 million and relocates to Paris (üá¨üáßüá´üá∑)</h3><p>Nuclear energy startup <a href="https://www.newcleo.com/">Newcleo</a> has raised <strong>‚Ç¨135 million</strong>, targeting to raise ‚Ç¨1 billion.  The funding will support the development of their innovative nuclear technology, focused on small modular reactors for sustainable energy production. </p><p>In August, the company announced its plans to <a href="https://sifted.eu/articles/nuclear-newcleo-raise-startup-france">move its holding company to Paris</a> to stay close to its fuel cycle ambitions. <strong>Landmark projects are set to happen in France</strong>, such as the construction of a prototype reactor and the creation of a reprocessed nuclear waste facility. üóëÔ∏è</p><blockquote><p><a href="https://energynews.pro/en/newcleo-relocates-to-paris-and-raises-e135-million-from-european-investors/">Newcleo Relocates to Paris and Raises ‚Ç¨135 million from European Investors</a></p></blockquote><pre><code><code>üëî Internships &amp; job offers</code></code></pre><h3>Internships</h3><p>VC Analyst - <strong>Omnes Capital </strong>(Paris)</p><blockquote><p><a href="https://france-invest.welcomekit.co/companies/omnes-capital/jobs/stage-venture-capital_paris_OC_0Waw55z?fbclid=IwY2xjawFWfURleHRuA2FlbQIxMQABHacJLDZb0m0iwee_i7eTGh-L87rIieeQuOr0I17Bc3zjbNy6kavZ5sTfzQ_aem_KvrCDfQzHJWoQntQTfWJaA">‚û§&nbsp;Job  desc.</a></p></blockquote><p>VC Analyst - <strong>Shift4Good </strong>(Paris)</p><blockquote><p><a href="https: