ne x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a></figure></div><ul><li><p><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/posts/ben-bergman-b8345925_these-are-the-19-best-female-early-stage-activity-7244419035705065474-lxPs?utm_source=share&amp;utm_medium=member_android">19 Best Female Early-Stage VCs to Watch</a> üåü </p><p>Ben Bergman highlights 19 female early-stage VCs making waves in the venture capital world and shaping the future of startups.</p></li><li><p><a href="https://www.forbes.com/sites/kjartanrist/2024/09/17/venture-capital-and-profitability-navigating-the-new-investment-paradigm/">Venture Capital and Profitability: Navigating the New Investment Paradigm</a> üìä</p><p>Forbes discusses the shifting landscape in venture capital, where profitability is becoming a priority over pure growth, changing the dynamics of investment strategies.</p></li><li><p><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/posts/davidhauser_should-investors-bet-on-the-jockey-or-the-activity-7245470714357518337-aOt-?utm_source=share&amp;utm_medium=member_android">Should Investors Bet on the Jockey or the Horse?</a> üèá</p><p>David Hauser explores the classic debate in venture capital: Should investors back the founder (the jockey) or the idea (the horse)?</p></li></ul><div><hr></div><blockquote><p>üì£Want to get your brand in front of 100k founders and investors? </p><p>If interested in sponsoring The VC Corner, reach out via email: rdominguezibar@gmail.com</p></blockquote><div><hr></div><h3>Interesting Reports üìä</h3><ul><li><p><a href="https://www.ey.com/en_gl/insights/ipo/trends">Global IPOs Modestly Grow Amid Uncertainty and Volatility</a> üìà</p><p>EY‚Äôs latest report examines the gradual growth in global IPOs, emphasizing the challenges posed by economic uncertainty and market volatility.</p></li></ul><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2 is-viewable-imag" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progre