t;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F11111a92-ed1a-47ba-bfcc-758e94fd7f52_1836x2770.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F11111a92-ed1a-47ba-bfcc-758e94fd7f52_1836x2770.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F11111a92-ed1a-47ba-bfcc-758e94fd7f52_1836x2770.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F11111a92-ed1a-47ba-bfcc-758e94fd7f52_1836x2770.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a><figcaption class="image-caption">Parodoj galima paliest ledo gabalƒÖ</figcaption></figure></div><div><hr></div><blockquote><h4>Avant Art Festival </h4></blockquote><p>Du vakarus buvau trijuose Var≈°uvos klubuose: Pardon, To Tu; Chmury ir Hydrogazadka. U≈æ ~30 eur i≈°klausiau 7 labai skirting≈≥ koncert≈≥. Nostalgi≈°kai prisiminiau prie≈° 15 m. Lenk≈≥ kult≈´ros namuose (Vilniuje) vykdavusius <a href="https://lt.wikipedia.org/wiki/A.LT">apdovanojimus A.LT</a>, kur vienoje scenoje pasirodydavo vis≈≥ ne-pop stili≈≥ muzikos atstovai. Var≈°uvoje taip pat buvo ƒØdomu stebƒóti publikƒÖ, atstovaujanƒçiƒÖ visoms tebeegzistuojanƒçios ir nykstanƒçioms subkult≈´roms, nuo sen≈≥ reiveri≈≥ iki jaun≈≥ metalist≈≥, bei tiesiog paprastam visavalgiam ≈æmogui kaip a≈°.</p><p>Taip pat galvojau apie tai, kad pas mus avangardas suprantama kaip ka≈ækas labai rimto, avangardinƒó muzika skamba kokiam nors ≈†MC, ‚ÄûJaunos muzikos‚Äú festivalyje ar bent jau ‚ÄûVilnius Jazz‚Äú. Lenki≈°kasis renginio konceptas buvo be jokio elitizmo, koncertai vyko toliau nuo centro, industriniuose klubuose/baruose/skylƒóse. Klausytoj≈≥ (ir atlikƒój≈≥) am≈æius buvo tarp 20 ir 70 met≈≥.</p><p><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=QTskdzJ1VCE&amp;ab_channel=KEXP">MABE FRATTI</a> (Gvatemala/Meksika) trio grojo violonƒçele paremtƒÖ d≈æiazƒÖ su pop/folk elementais. Po ≈°io rimto, auk≈°to lygio koncerto kiek komi≈°kai atrodƒó <a href="https://youtu.be/NtCWDoYtExQ">P√ñ</a> (Pranc≈´zija/Gana) ‚Äì labiau solo performansas nei muzika. Atlikƒója su zombio linzƒóm vaik≈°ƒçiojo tarp publikos ir priki≈°dama arti veidƒÖ gƒÖsdino vyrus (ka≈ækodƒól j≈≥ publikoj buvo daugiau). Visgi saugi performanso riba nebuvo per≈æengta, visi liko pakutenti, su nejaukiom ≈°ypsenƒólƒóm, buvo daug kƒÖ pafilmuoti, bet muzikinio ir idƒójinio turinio lyg ir neƒØ≈ævelgiau. Nepaisant tarp menƒçi≈≥ atlikƒójai i≈°tatuiruoto smuiko rakto.</p><div class="native-video-embed" data-component-name="VideoPlaceholder" data-attrs="{&quot;mediaUploadId&quot;:&quot;48ba1398-c226-45fa-82be-198bb6a5a92b&quot;,&quot;duration&quot;:null}"></div><p>Dvi persipynusios grupƒós i≈° Brazilijos paliko did≈æiausiƒÖ ƒØsp≈´dƒØ. <a href="https://youtu.be/V6vwTQ3so_0">TEST</a> ‚Äì vokalo/gitaros ir ≈æiauri≈≥ b≈´gn≈≥ duetas grojo ekperimentinƒØ metalƒÖ su grindcore / punk elementais. Turb≈´t garsiausia ir labiausiai patyrusi festivalio grupƒó <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ZIRoS-woHvA&amp;ab_channel=Lovers%26Lollypops">DEAFKIDS</a> metalƒÖ mai≈°ƒó su elektronika, noizu ir poliritmine perkusija.</p><div class="native-video-embed" data-component-name="VideoPlaceholder" data-attrs="{&quot;mediaUploadId&quot;:&quot;ab655998-df5c-4307-9f65-c0f3626f5293&quot;,&quot;duration&quot;:null}"></div><p><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ToaKh4aBVOA&amp;ab_channel=Taberculat">MASQUE NOIR</a> (Baltarusija/Lenkija) grojo free-improv d≈æiazƒÖ. Prie j≈≥ vienam ilgam gabalui pasipra≈°ƒôs prisijungƒó vietinis vokalistas, neblogai pasita≈°kƒôs ir parƒókavƒôs. Pasirodo, grupƒó propaguoja koncertus be jokio pasiruo≈°imo atsitiktinƒóse vietose su atsitiktiniais ≈æmonƒómis.</p><div class="native-video-embed" data-component-name="VideoPlaceholder" data-attrs="{&quot;mediaUploadId&quot;:&quot;eaf2a59c-0513-49ef-8f84-d65f6cfdc572&quot;,&quot;duration&quot;:null}"></div><p>SEPERSA &amp; MATEUSZ KROL (Iranas/Lenkija) eksperimentavo su ritmo ma≈°inomis, bet atrodƒó labiau besi≈æavintys technologijom nei muzika. <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bfDHv3Mocjk&amp;t=1s&amp;ab_channel=obscuredbyears">Duetas MOE</a> (Norvegija) su nenusakomo am≈æiaus ir stebƒótinos jƒógos seniuku Ikuro Takahashi (Japonija, perkusija) ≈°iek tiek priminƒó Bjork su politi≈°kais paklykavimais ir pasiraitymais tarp publikos. Bosinƒó gitara dundƒójo nuostabiai. Pabaigoje vokalistƒó sakƒó: ‚ÄûAƒçi≈´, kad leid≈æiate groti avangardƒÖ.‚Äú</p><div class="native-video-embed" data-component-name="VideoPlaceholder" data-attrs="{&quot;mediaUploadId&quot;:&quot;f9d3b8f9-5c9f-4dc2-844d-b64347d434c3&quot;,&quot;duration&quot;:null}"></div><p>(Prie grupi≈≥ pavadinim≈≥ pridedu geresni≈≥ nuorodas ƒØ geresnius video nei ≈°itie mano pigiu telefonu filmuoti.) </p><p>≈†iaip ko pasigedau, tai tik lenk≈≥ (ant scenos). Bet, kiek suprantu, organizatoriai lenkus labiau promina u≈æsienyje, o ƒØ festivalƒØ daugiau ve≈æa u≈æsienieƒçius. Mums palinkƒóƒçiau daugiau toki≈≥ tarpini≈≥ erdvi≈≥/ rengini≈≥ ‚Äì tarp elitini≈≥ sali≈≥ ir pogrindini≈≥ skyli≈≥. Ir kad alaus kainos b≈´t≈≥ labiau kaip Lenkijoj, o ne kaip ≈†vedijoj.</p><div><hr></div><blockquote><h4>girl in red</h4></blockquote><p>Dar, kad ma≈æa nepasirodyt≈≥, apsilankiau popmuzikos koncerte. 25-eri≈≥ Marie Ulven i≈° Norvegijos i≈°garsƒójo 2018 m. su singlu ‚ÄûI wanna be your girlfriend‚Äú, dabar jis perklausom nusileid≈æia vir≈° milijardo kart≈≥ perklausytai dainai ‚Äûwe fell in love in october‚Äú. 2021 m. debiutinis albumas buvo labai sƒókmingas, antrasis, pasirodƒôs ≈°iemet, jau ma≈æiau.</p><p>Nedidelƒó sporto halƒó buvo i≈°parduota (bilietƒÖ pirkau u≈æ 40eur). 90 procent≈≥ publikos sudarƒó jaunutƒós neheteronormatyvi≈°kai atrodanƒçios merginos (Marie - lesbietƒó, apie tai i≈° dalies ir jos dainos) su ≈°iurpiai trumpais sijonƒóliais, plƒó≈°ytom pƒódkelnƒóm, apsmukusiom kelnƒóm, goti≈°ku makia≈æu ir kit≈≥ stili≈≥ elementais. Koncerte buvo galima ƒØsitikinti tiesa, kad gamtoje nƒóra garsiau klykianƒçio gyv≈´no u≈æ paauglƒô mergaitƒô. Stereotipi≈°kai atrodantys vyrai ƒçia buvo nebent tƒóƒçiai arba apsauginiai. Tikrai keistas poj≈´tis b≈´ti minioj, kurioj visi ne auk≈°tesni u≈æ mane.</p><p>Marie sirgo, sakƒó: ‚Äû≈†iandien dar su niekuo nekalbƒójau, saugojau balsƒÖ, j≈´s pirmi, tai girdƒósit daug nesƒÖmoni≈≥.‚Äú Atliko Billie Eilish dainos fragmentƒÖ su ≈æod≈æiais <em>miau miau miaaauu</em>. VienƒÖ k≈´rinƒØ dedikavo ‚Äûlenki≈°kai virtuvei‚Äú. O savo ≈æavinga laisva laikysena scenoje priminƒó m≈´si≈°kƒô Beatrich ar ma≈æutƒô mielƒÖ Courtney Love. Buvo atliktas ir publikos praskyrimo stebuklas (≈ær. klipƒÖ), kai Marie atsiduria minios epicentre. Garso kokybƒó, deja, buvo ‚Äûlenki≈°ka‚Äú, o gal tiesiog mano ausys jau per senos ≈°itiems da≈æniams.</p><div id="youtube2-w9RTuUTl-40" class="youtube-wrap" data-attrs="{&quot;videoId&quot;:&quot;w9RTuUTl-40&quot;,&quot;startTime&quot;:null,&quot;endTime&quot;:null}" data-component-name="Youtube2ToDOM"><div class="youtube-inner"><iframe src="https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/w9RTuUTl-40?rel=0&amp;autoplay=0&amp;showinfo=0&amp;enablejsapi=0" frameborder="0" loading="lazy" gesture="media" allow="autoplay; fullscreen" allowautoplay="true" allowfullscreen="true" width="728" height="409"></iframe></div></div><div><hr></div><p>Tiek ƒØsp≈´d≈æi≈≥ i≈° Var≈°uvos. Raginu ten va≈æiuoti, pasijusit kaip ponai (finansine prasme). Pastaraisiais metais su lenk≈≥ kult≈´ra jauƒçiu vis didesnƒØ bendrumƒÖ, pradƒójau galvoti, kad vertƒót≈≥ jau vaduotis i≈° istorini≈≥ traum≈≥ ir pastebƒót, kas mus sieja. Daug kuo esam prana≈°esni, progresyvesni (pvz., kasdienybƒós technologijom: netgi Var≈°uvoj ne visur gali susimokƒót kortele, kai pas mus jau grynais ne visur priima; be to, lenkai labai r≈´ko senovi≈°kas cigaretes, kai pas mus seniausiai visi veipina), be to, turim geresnƒØ estetinƒØ skonƒØ. Tad nereikia jaustis kaip kokiam diƒçkio nuskriaustam vaikui.</p><div><hr></div><p><em>Kadangi ≈æmonƒós nepaliauja man si≈´lyti pinig≈≥, tai padariau jums tokiƒÖ galimybƒô. U≈æ tekstƒÖ padƒókoti ir prie mano gerovƒós prisidƒóti galite paspaudƒô mygtukƒÖ ≈æemiau ir ƒØvedƒô savo sugalvotƒÖ sumƒÖ. Taƒçiau esat laisvi to ir nedaryti. Aƒçi≈´.</em></p><p class="button-wrapper" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://buy.stripe.com/4gw7tv5Tj63OfGUdQR&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Prisidƒóti&quot;,&quot;action&quot;:null,&quot;class&quot;:null}" data-component-name="ButtonCreateButton"><a class="button primary" href="https://buy.stripe.com/4gw7tv5Tj63OfGUdQR"><span>Prisidƒóti</span></a></p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2 is-viewable-imag" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb971639e-6a68-4f72-88ac-2d1baf1283c6_4080x1836.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb971639e-6a68-4f72-88ac-2d1baf1283c6_4080x1836.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb971639e-6a68-4f72-88ac-2d1baf1283c6_4080x1836.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb971639e-6a68-4f72-88ac-2d1baf1283c6_4080x1836.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb971639e-6a68-4f72-88ac-2d1baf1283c6_4080x1836.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb971639e-6a68-4f72-88ac-2d1baf1283c6_4080x1836.jpeg" width="334" height="742.3241758241758" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/b971639e-6a68-4f72-88ac-2d1baf1283c6_4080x1836.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:3236,&quot;width&quot;:1456,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:334,&quot;bytes&quot;:5360642,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb971639e-6a68-4f72-88ac-2d1baf1283c6_4080x1836.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb971639e-6a68-4f72-88ac-2d1baf1283c6_4080x1836.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb971639e-6a68-4f72-88ac-2d1baf1283c6_4080x1836.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb971639e-6a68-4f72-88ac-2d1baf1283c6_4080x1836.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a></figure></div><p></p><p></p></body></html>	Spontani≈°ka kelionƒó ƒØ Var≈°uvƒÖ atne≈°ƒó ƒØsp≈´d≈æi≈≥ i≈° Titaniko parodos, avangardinio muzikos festivalio ir popmuzikos koncerto. Lenk≈≥ sostinƒó ≈æavi savo kontrastais, istorija ir kult≈´rine ƒØvairove. Raginama aplankyti ir patirti paƒçiam.	2024-09-28 14:02:31	2024-10-08 12:03:17.427	2024-10-09 15:08:42.402	{lithuanian}	https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/918d8b3d-ac33-4016-a201-f8ba540af388_1836x2295.jpeg	Emilija Visockaitƒó	bonus-ispudziai-is-varsuvos-22
3	https://timdenning.substack.com/p/the-greatest-book-on-money-ive-read	The Greatest Book on Money I‚Äôve Read In The Last 24 Months	Bizarrely, the book title has nothing to do with money	<html><head></head><body><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2 is-viewable-imag" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7a62ba7c-a1a4-4029-9e79-977f305a7134_1166x695.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7a62ba7c-a1a4-4029-9e79-977f305a7134_1166x695.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7a62ba7c-a1a4-4029-9e79-977f305a7134_1166x695.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7a62ba7c-a1a4-4029-9e79-977f305a7134_1166x695.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7a62ba7c-a1a4-4029-9e79-977f305a7134_1166x695.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7a62ba7c-a1a4-4029-9e79-977f305a7134_1166x695.jpeg" width="1166" height="695" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/7a62ba7c-a1a4-4029-9e79-977f305a7134_1166x695.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:695,&quot;width&quot;:1166,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:172865,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;topImage&quot;:true,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7a62ba7c-a1a4-4029-9e79-977f305a7134_1166x695.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7a62ba7c-a1a4-4029-9e79-977f305a7134_1166x695.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7a62ba7c-a1a4-4029-9e79-977f305a7134_1166x695.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7a62ba7c-a1a4-4029-9e79-977f305a7134_1166x695.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" fetchpriority="high"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a><figcaption class="image-caption"><em>Image Credit-Midjourney</em></figcaption></figure></div><p class="button-wrapper" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://timdenning.substack.com/p/the-greatest-book-on-money-ive-read?utm_source=substack&amp;utm_medium=email&amp;utm_content=share&amp;action=share&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Share&quot;,&quot;action&quot;:null,&quot;class&quot;:null}" data-component-name="ButtonCreateButton"><a class="button primary" href="https://timdenning.substack.com/p/the-greatest-book-on-money-ive-read?utm_source=substack&amp;utm_medium=email&amp;utm_content=share&amp;action=share"><span>Share</span></a></p><p>Finance nerds ruined books on money.</p><p>Technical jargon. Graphs. Lambo photos. Banking stories. Such a huge snoozer. Whenever people ask me what books to read about money it‚Äôs hard. But one book I read in the last 24 months blew my mind:</p><p><em>‚ÄúHow To Live‚Äù</em> by Derek Sivers. It doesn‚Äôt seem like a book about money but it is.</p><p>Here‚Äôs what you can learn from it.</p><h1><strong>The biggest money lesson from </strong><em>‚ÄúHow To Live‚Äù</em></h1><p>I always hated when people made lots of money.</p><p>I loved to throw mud at billionaires while sipping a one-dollar 7-Eleven coffee. Then Derek Sivers said this:</p><blockquote><p><em>"Making money is nothing more than a neutral exchange of value. Making money is proof you're adding value to people's lives. Aiming to get rich is aiming to be useful to the world."</em></p></blockquote><p>Making money is helping people.</p><p>When someone makes a lot of money it means they‚Äôve helped a lot of people, and you should at least shake their hand. You should probably also try to learn something from them. Only closed-minded losers shame wealthy people.</p><div class="pullquote"><p>"Making money isn't evil, greedy, shallow, or vain. Your biggest obstacle to getting rich is the harmful meaning you've attached to it."</p></div><h1>Money doesn‚Äôt give a f*ck about these things‚Ä¶</h1><blockquote><p><em>"Money doesn't care about your:</em></p><p><em>‚Ä¢ Race</em></p><p><em>‚Ä¢ Gender</em></p><p><em>‚Ä¢ Education</em></p><p><em>‚Ä¢ Physique</em></p><p><em>‚Ä¢ Family</em></p><p><em>‚Ä¢ Nationality</em></p><p><em>Anyone can be rich ‚Äì so it might as well be you."</em></p></blockquote><p>I suspect this one will blow up a few people‚Äôs brains.</p><p>We‚Äôre taught by society to be victims. To blame our money problems on a 3rd party or even politicians. But no president is going to save you or your bank account. They‚Äôre busy building theirs and enjoying their newfound status.</p><p>One of my good friends makes 7-figures (USD) a year. He comes from a poor village in Africa. He decided to change his family‚Äôs future.</p><p>The only thing stopping you getting wealthy are your bullsh*t excuses about why it can‚Äôt happen. Money has nothing to do with IQ, and everything to do with helpfulness.</p><h1>‚ÄúIf more information was the answer, we'd all be billionaires with perfect abs.‚Äù</h1><p>Most people drown in information. They think the information age is the future.</p><p>Wrong. It‚Äôs the past. AI screwed the information age in the butt. We‚Äôre now drowning in information. Amazon is filled with AI-written books. Social media has AI sludge all over it. Our email inboxes are the next target for AI.</p><p>What a lot of people are missing is more action.</p><p>Taking what you‚Äôve already learned and putting it to good use. Consuming more information is often nothing more than procrastination in disguise. It‚Äôs why my academy now offers execution instead of information.</p><p>Get around other people with the same goal. Take daily action.</p><h1>"Ideas are worth almost nothing.</h1><h1>Execution is everything. The world is filled with ideas, yet so few take action and make them happen."</h1><p>I met someone recently who had an idea for an AI marketplace.</p><p>They didn‚Äôt want to talk about it. They wanted me to sign an NDA. I told them ‚Äúno one gives a f*ck about another AI chatbot idea. There‚Äôs nothing unique here, just like Uber but for boats isn‚Äôt a genius idea (a bank customer once wanted me to sign an NDA over this idea, too‚Ä¶LOL).</p><p>Investors and banks don‚Äôt invest in ideas. They invest in execution.</p><p>Do you have any results? Do you have customers? Have you earned any money from it? That‚Äôs the hard part.</p><p>We don‚Äôt value Elon Musk because he had a great idea of sending rockets to Mars. We value him because he sent rockets to space and saved real astronauts who were stranded.</p><p>Become an action-taker to get wealthy. Throw your ideas in the bin. What I learned is that dumb ideas often make the most money ‚Äì life is a paradox.</p><h1>‚ÄúThe purpose of <strong>money</strong> is to trade for things that make you happy.</h1><h1>So if you can bypass <strong>money</strong> and get directly to the happy, you've saved a lot of trouble.‚Äù</h1><p>Not needing stuff is a huge money hack.</p><p>My Honda Civic is 9 years old. She still drives like a dream. I could easily replace it with a Lambo 4WD tomorrow. Yet I don‚Äôt. I don‚Äôt need another car. I have zero desire for material possessions or status. So I don‚Äôt need to earn as much money to live, which means my freedom number is 10x lower than the average person.</p><p>It also means I can retire decades earlier than most corporate rats.</p><p>What I chase is happiness. My 1 year old daughter gives me all of that for the cost of new nappies and some Bluey books with the occasional cafe smoothie.</p><p>Money can make your life complicated or simple. Choose simple.</p><h1><strong>‚ÄúWe do so many things for money whether we need it or not‚Äù</strong></h1><p>The virtue-signalling unicorns in the West love to pretend they don‚Äôt work for money.</p><p>They think they‚Äôre too good for money. They‚Äôre special. They‚Äôre driven by purpose. They‚Äôre writing the novel for the love of it. They would never dare ‚Äòmonetize‚Äô a hobby. How dare you!</p><p>I call bullsh*t.</p><p>We do things for money even if we don‚Äôt need money. Getting paid helps us feel like we‚Äôre not being exploited. Better yet‚Ä¶</p><pre><code>Money helps make our work better.</code></pre><p>When you get paid you can build a website, hire a virtual assistant, get a fancy book cover designed by a cartoonist, and buy software to make your productivity higher.</p><p>Never trust a person who says they don‚Äôt need money.</p><h1>"Making money is a skill. Learn it and practice it like you would any other."</h1><p>Some people spend their entire lives struggling with money.</p><p>I was that person too. What changed for me was when I realized making money is a skill. There‚Äôs an art to crafting offers, sending proposals, pricing your time, and gently persuading someone to get your help.</p><p>Instead of treating money as this mysterious thing you never have enough of, turn it into an art form with a set of skills attached that you can learn.</p><h1>"Don't buy too many things, too big of a house, or hire too many people.</h1><h1>Rich people who do this feel trapped and miserable. The less you buy, the more you're in control."</h1><p>As your wealth increases it‚Äôs tempting to buy more stuff.</p><p>I‚Äôm a fan of hiring people to get more of your time back and build leverage, but there‚Äôs a threshold where a team of people can become a huge burden.</p><p>Material possessions require maintenance. That needs more money. And every item occupies some mental bandwidth.</p><p>The less stuff you own, the less your stuff owns you.</p><h1>"The more something costs, the more people value it.</h1><h1>By charging more, you're actually helping them use it and appreciate it."</h1><p>How you price your products and services is psychological, too.</p><p>Some people accidentally accept a low salary because they don‚Äôt know their own value. They think they have to be the lowest-cost option to get the job.</p><p>What I found when I applied for new jobs is the higher I told them my expected salary was the more seriously they wanted to hire me. A $300K a year salesperson sounds like they‚Äôd be better than a $50K a year one.</p><p>The same applies to business. I ran a $10K service and felt guilty for the high price tag. But the customers loved it because the cost forced them to take action and get results in 30 days.</p><div class="pullquote"><p>"Charge more than is comfortable to your current self-image. Value yourself higher, then rise to fit this valuation."</p></div><h1>"To get rich, don't think about what's valuable to you. Think about what's valuable to others."</h1><p>Selfish people are broke.</p><p>When it comes to making money they always think about their selfish desires and wants. They never think about how they can be helpful. This selfishness is a disease. It comes from the current <em>me, me, me</em> culture.</p><pre><code>Harsh truth: nobody gives a f*ck about you and what you want in life.</code></pre><p>We‚Äôre all thinking about ourselves. So put others ahead and you‚Äôll be an uncommon mofo who‚Äôll make more money than feels humanly possible. I never try to guess what is valuable in my business. I ask people. I survey them. I have Zoom calls with them.</p><p>Selflessness will make you wealthy.</p><h1>‚ÄúEmotions are the enemy of good investing."</h1><p>The dumbest people I‚Äôve ever met are day traders.</p><p>They don‚Äôt understand that it‚Äôs just gambling with a s*xier label. They often trade stocks, FX or crypto and even do courses to learn this magical skill.</p><p>Anyone who has worked in finance knows that buying &amp; selling any investment in the short term is gambling.</p><p>What screws day traders are their emotions.</p><p>It‚Äôs a constant high and low rollercoaster. Ultimately they lose every dollar‚Ä¶ or they win the jackpot by accident and gamble it all back. Stay away from emotion-driven, short-term investing.</p><h1>‚ÄúThe world is full of money. There's no shortage. So capture the value you create. Charge for what you do."</h1><p>Money used to be scarce.</p><p>You were born in a country and the opportunities there defined your financial potential. If you grew up in a poor place you had to migrate to somewhere like America. It was complicated, expensive, and came with a waiting list.</p><p>Since the internet took over the planet everything has changed. It‚Äôs a borderless, global marketplace that‚Äôs open 24/7. We‚Äôre no longer limited by anything. And there are billions of dollars on the internet every day that are accessible to you.</p><p>The only limitation is whether you can attract that money to your life. That starts with ethically gaining some attention on social media, and choosing a half-decent business model.</p><p>The last one is key. Many people choose Uber slave driver income streams, like freelancing marketplaces, then wonder why their life turns to cr*ap.</p><p>Gain attention. Choose a digital income stream that‚Äôs proven to make cash. Then tell your old 9-5 boss to stick their job where the sun don‚Äôt shine (proud to have done this).</p><h1>"The world needs more boldness.</h1><h1>Refuse the comfortable addiction of a steady paycheck."</h1><p>The comfortable life is a nightmare.</p><p>It leads to mediocrity that pays the worst. You face high competition and the constant threat of the layoff boogie monster that‚Äôll bite your titties off.</p><p>I have no problem with people starting with a paycheck. What‚Äôs sad is when it ends there. The bold thing to do is go out on your own and have multiple employers (customers). It forces you to stay sharp and add value. You can‚Äôt get lost in a big organization or hide behind a department for cover and free pizza.</p><p>Since I quit my job in 2021 my skills have increased by at least 100x. I‚Äôve spent wild amounts of money on coaching, masterminds, courses, and events that have helped me gain new micro skills.</p><p>In banking, my only skill was order-taking (sales) and perhaps sending a few emails to customers with transaction fees on them.</p><p>Choose the path of growth and discomfort if you want to be wealthy.</p><h1>"Nothing destroys money faster than seeking status."</h1><p>I met a guy a few months back. Nice fellow. I wrote about him in another Substack.</p><p>He bought a BMW. He felt incredible. But the status cost him $3000 a month plus 15% a year in interest on the loan. If he invested that money in a business he would probably have quit his job by now.</p><p>When he handed over the cash to the German car company, everything at work was great. Now it isn‚Äôt. A new boss started. They micro-manage him. They took away his 6-figure bonus. Chasing status is stupid. The richest people look ordinary.</p><p>Real status is the free time to do whatever the F you want.</p><h1><strong>Closing Thought</strong></h1><p>I strongly recommend you read ‚ÄúHow To Live.‚Äù It will change your financial life.</p><p>What‚Äôs your favorite money idea above from Derek?</p><p><em>This article is for informational purposes only, it should not be considered financial, tax or legal advice. Consult a financial professional before making any major financial decisions.</em></p><div><hr></div><p>P.S. Reading about money is nice.&nbsp;</p><p>Writing to make money is even better.&nbsp;</p><p>I can show you how in next week's free masterclass</p><p><a href="https://event.webinarjam.com/register/69/gp84gs6w">Click here to reserve your seat now</a></p><p>(Limited seating)</p></body></html>	Money isn't evil - it's proof you're adding value. Anyone can be rich, regardless of background. Focus on execution, not just ideas. Simplify your life to need less. Treat making money as a skill to learn. Price yourself higher to be valued more.	2024-10-03 11:04:07	2024-10-05 19:39:31.379	2024-10-10 14:04:45.004	{english}	https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7a62ba7c-a1a4-4029-9e79-977f305a7134_1166x695.jpeg	Tim Denning	the-greatest-book-on-money-ive-read-in-the-last-24-months
14	https://niallharbison.substack.com/p/creating-a-global-movement	Creating A Global Movement	So many people now involved	<html><head></head><body><p>Most people reading this will probably know I started this mission in 2022 by feeding a single street dog myself. Her name was Lucky and <a href="https://niallharbison.substack.com/p/lucky">you can read her story here</a>. </p><p>From that single dog has grown a movement of epic proportions and I wanted to try showcase just how many people are involved and how much change is happening.</p><p>I have to pinch myself that these numbers are real‚Ä¶ </p><h3>25,000 Dogs Sterilised</h3><p>Just this week we sterilised the <a href="https://www.instagram.com/p/C_7U1w7SlLS/">25,000th dog</a>. Fittingly it was one here on the island of Koh Samui where it all started. Some of the stats around our sterilising (it means to neuter or spay) are beyond exciting‚Ä¶</p><ul><li><p>We now have <a href="https://www.happydoggo.com/our-work">8 partners in 3 countries</a> (Thailand, Sri Lanka and Indonesia)</p></li><li><p>We are now funding the sterilising of around 5000 dogs per month</p></li><li><p>Sterilising 25,000 dogs means we have stopped <strong>a quarter of a million</strong> puppies being born into suffering (counting on approx 10 puppies per dog)</p></li></ul><p>The plans to ramp this up for the rest of this year and especially into 2025 are even more ambitious. </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2 is-viewable-imag" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F59e8da2e-a312-41b6-a6a3-65025447800a_1600x900.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F59e8da2e-a312-41b6-a6a3-65025447800a_1600x900.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F59e8da2e-a312-41b6-a6a3-65025447800a_1600x900.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F59e8da2e-a312-41b6-a6a3-65025447800a_1600x900.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F59e8da2e-a312-41b6-a6a3-65025447800a_1600x900.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F59e8da2e-a312-41b6-a6a3-65025447800a_1600x900.png" width="1456" height="819" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/59e8da2e-a312-41b6-a6a3-65025447800a_1600x900.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:819,&quot;width&quot;:1456,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:202986,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;topImage&quot;:true,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F59e8da2e-a312-41b6-a6a3-65025447800a_1600x900.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F59e8da2e-a312-41b6-a6a3-65025447800a_1600x900.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F59e8da2e-a312-41b6-a6a3-65025447800a_1600x900.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F59e8da2e-a312-41b6-a6a3-65025447800a_1600x900.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" fetchpriority="high"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a></figure></div><p>While we build the partnerships and provide the funding there are close to 100 people out there on the ground doing the hard work of catching, operating on and safely returning the dogs to their communities. They are the true heroes.</p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2 is-viewable-imag" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F3315e537-ffc2-43a9-95cf-dc51d2aae75c_1162x726.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F3315e537-ffc2-43a9-95cf-dc51d2aae75c_1162x726.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F3315e537-ffc2-43a9-95cf-dc51d2aae75c_1162x726.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F3315e537-ffc2-43a9-95cf-dc51d2aae75c_1162x726.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F3315e537-ffc2-43a9-95cf-dc51d2aae75c_1162x726.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F3315e537-ffc2-43a9-95cf-dc51d2aae75c_1162x726.png" width="1162" height="726" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/3315e537-ffc2-43a9-95cf-dc51d2aae75c_1162x726.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:726,&quot;width&quot;:1162,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:1841432,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F3315e537-ffc2-43a9-95cf-dc51d2aae75c_1162x726.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F3315e537-ffc2-43a9-95cf-dc51d2aae75c_1162x726.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F3315e537-ffc2-43a9-95cf-dc51d2aae75c_1162x726.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F3315e537-ffc2-43a9-95cf-dc51d2aae75c_1162x726.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a></figure></div><h3>Dogs Number 26, 27 &amp; 28 - Billy Rusty And Sandy</h3><p>While the huge numbers are so compelling I find the individual dogs are the ones that really melt my heart. In 2024 alone we have now re-homed 28 dogs both in Thailand and around the world. </p><ul><li><p><a href="https://www.instagram.com/best_boy_billy">Billy</a>. He arrived in Singapore after his horrific slashing.</p></li><li><p><a href="https://x.com/NiallHarbison/status/1835351206337888663">Sandy and Rusty</a> Both found suffering but now snuggled up in England</p></li></ul><p>It‚Äôs really hard to explain just how many people are involved in getting them to their homes. The wonderful kind people who adopt these dogs and all the care they get during their rescues. For a dog like Billy I am not exaggerating when I say there are up to 50 people who helped him at various stages. </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2 is-viewable-imag" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fd3df3e4d-7a46-465a-9868-6abc25b3dd0a_1332x634.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fd3df3e4d-7a46-465a-9868-6abc25b3dd0a_1332x634.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fd3df3e4d-7a46-465a-9868-6abc25b3dd0a_1332x634.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fd3df3e4d-7a46-465a-9868-6abc25b3dd0a_1332x634.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fd3df3e4d-7a46-465a-9868-6abc25b3dd0a_1332x634.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fd3df3e4d-7a46-465a-9868-6abc25b3dd0a_1332x634.png" width="1332" height="634" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/d3df3e4d-7a46-465a-9868-6abc25b3dd0a_1332x634.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:634,&quot;width&quot;:1332,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:1718755,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fd3df3e4d-7a46-465a-9868-6abc25b3dd0a_1332x634.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fd3df3e4d-7a46-465a-9868-6abc25b3dd0a_1332x634.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fd3df3e4d-7a46-465a-9868-6abc25b3dd0a_1332x634.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fd3df3e4d-7a46-465a-9868-6abc25b3dd0a_1332x634.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a></figure></div><h3>Building Out A Thai Team</h3><p>I‚Äôm very conscious of the fact that I am in Thailand and we are never going to solve the dog problem here with foreign staff alone. <a href="https://www.happydoggo.com/">Happy Doggo</a> needs to be led by local people in the countries it operates in and integrate into the community. That process has started. Seeing our team in our new offices with the logo on the wall makes me so proud. </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2 is-viewable-imag" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F668eaf81-deae-4ac2-aaa5-4852b3cac81c_2048x1536.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F668eaf81-deae-4ac2-aaa5-4852b3cac81c_2048x1536.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F668eaf81-deae-4ac2-aaa5-4852b3cac81c_2048x1536.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F668eaf81-deae-4ac2-aaa5-4852b3cac81c_2048x1536.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F668eaf81-deae-4ac2-aaa5-4852b3cac81c_2048x1536.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F668eaf81-deae-4ac2-aaa5-4852b3cac81c_2048x1536.jpeg" width="1456" height="1092" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/668eaf81-deae-4ac2-aaa5-4852b3cac81c_2048x1536.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:1092,&quot;width&quot;:1456,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:270223,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F668eaf81-deae-4ac2-aaa5-4852b3cac81c_2048x1536.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F668eaf81-deae-4ac2-aaa5-4852b3cac81c_2048x1536.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F668eaf81-deae-4ac2-aaa5-4852b3cac81c_2048x1536.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F668eaf81-deae-4ac2-aaa5-4852b3cac81c_2048x1536.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a></figure></div><p>The following slide is from one of our internal decks. You can see just how fast we are trying to scale up. Most of these people will be rolling our sterilising and local operations to help more dogs on the ground as quickly as we possibly can. </p><p>You are probably as blown away by the scale of the growth as I am nervous about how to fund it all and the logistics involved. Luckily there are some outstanding people working on this behind the scenes. </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2 is-viewable-imag" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F65468ca7-8b58-4fe2-ad4a-9b099b01d455_1594x896.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F65468ca7-8b58-4fe2-ad4a-9b099b01d455_1594x896.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F65468ca7-8b58-4fe2-ad4a-9b099b01d455_1594x896.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F65468ca7-8b58-4fe2-ad4a-9b099b01d455_1594x896.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F65468ca7-8b58-4fe2-ad4a-9b099b01d455_1594x896.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F65468ca7-8b58-4fe2-ad4a-9b099b01d455_1594x896.png" width="1456" height="818" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/65468ca7-8b58-4fe2-ad4a-9b099b01d455_1594x896.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:818,&quot;width&quot;:1456,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:434711,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F65468ca7-8b58-4fe2-ad4a-9b099b01d455_1594x896.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F65468ca7-8b58-4fe2-ad4a-9b099b01d455_1594x896.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F65468ca7-8b58-4fe2-ad4a-9b099b01d455_1594x896.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F65468ca7-8b58-4fe2-ad4a-9b099b01d455_1594x896.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a></figure></div><h3>Local Support For Tina‚Äôs Hospital </h3><p>The work is really ramping up on <a href="https://www.happydoggo.com/tinas-hospital">Tina‚Äôs Hospital</a>. Not just from a design perspective with our wonderful <a href="https://www.happydoggo.com/tinas-hospital">pro bono partners</a> but also on the ground. </p><p>We had a meeting with the Mayor of Samui last week about building the public road into the hospital for us and the feedback has been excellent. Explaining our big picture thinking and seeing it so well received by key local decision makers was something I‚Äôd long been dreaming of.</p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2 is-viewable-imag" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F3bde1ed0-0f29-4127-96bd-98546f29782d_1344x742.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F3bde1ed0-0f29-4127-96bd-98546f29782d_1344x742.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F3bde1ed0-0f29-4127-96bd-98546f29782d_1344x742.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F3bde1ed0-0f29-4127-96bd-98546f29782d_1344x742.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F3bde1ed0-0f29-4127-96bd-98546f29782d_1344x742.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F3bde1ed0-0f29-4127-96bd-98546f29782d_1344x742.png" width="1344" height="742" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/3bde1ed0-0f29-4127-96bd-98546f29782d_1344x742.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:742,&quot;width&quot;:1344,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:1819775,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F3bde1ed0-0f29-4127-96bd-98546f29782d_1344x742.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F3bde1ed0-0f29-4127-96bd-98546f29782d_1344x742.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F3bde1ed0-0f29-4127-96bd-98546f29782d_1344x742.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F3bde1ed0-0f29-4127-96bd-98546f29782d_1344x742.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a></figure></div><h3>An Online Army Of Dog Lovers</h3><p>If you look through the various areas I‚Äôve outlined above there are a couple of hundred people already involved in various ways thanks to what has been created at <a href="https://www.happydoggo.com/">Happy Doggo</a>. A lot of dog lovers changing the world. A global movement.</p><p>What makes this work though is the 1000s of other people around the world supporting, sharing content and commenting with kind words and gestures. I feel it every single day and am always taken aback by people‚Äôs generosity in so many ways. </p><p>Like little Eve here and her <a href="https://www.justgiving.com/page/jade-nayyar-1723984325403">story after moving to England</a> and all who supported her recent climb. Thats one of 100 examples I could have picked.</p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2 is-viewable-imag" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F86198052-8e11-437f-88ff-7e8f1d65cee7_1338x990.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F86198052-8e11-437f-88ff-7e8f1d65cee7_1338x990.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F86198052-8e11-437f-88ff-7e8f1d65cee7_1338x990.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F86198052-8e11-437f-88ff-7e8f1d65cee7_1338x990.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F86198052-8e11-437f-88ff-7e8f1d65cee7_1338x990.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F86198052-8e11-437f-88ff-7e8f1d65cee7_1338x990.png" width="1338" height="990" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/86198052-8e11-437f-88ff-7e8f1d65cee7_1338x990.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:990,&quot;width&quot;:1338,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:2539905,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F86198052-8e11-437f-88ff-7e8f1d65cee7_1338x990.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F86198052-8e11-437f-88ff-7e8f1d65cee7_1338x990.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F86198052-8e11-437f-88ff-7e8f1d65cee7_1338x990.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F86198052-8e11-437f-88ff-7e8f1d65cee7_1338x990.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a></figure></div><p>Things are getting scarily big and very expensive and tricky to run logistically but the support online is the key element. I feel so many people want to help the dogs in any way possible even if they are half way across the world. That support takes my breath away on a daily basis. In a world with so much bad news and dark moments I think this is a little corner of the world that shows positive change can happen.</p><p>I wanted to write this update because I always get outsized credit. In comments, media coverage and in person. As you can clearly see this is a team effort and you reading this are very much part of that. </p><p>All I can do is keep dreaming even bigger and figuring out ways to save even more dogs because they are the ones suffering right now. </p><p>Thank you from the bottom of my heart. </p><p>Big Love</p><p>Niall</p><p>P.S You can always support by either <a href="https://www.happydoggo.com/donate">donating here</a> or just subscribing to this newsletter.</p><h3></h3><p></p></body></html>	A movement to help street dogs has grown exponentially, sterilizing 25,000 dogs across three countries. Local teams are expanding rapidly to scale up efforts and build a new hospital, with widespread community support.	2024-09-16 15:17:30	2024-10-05 19:41:03.066	2024-10-10 14:04:45.669	{english}	https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F3315e537-ffc2-43a9-95cf-dc51d2aae75c_1162x726.png	Niall Harbison	creating-a-global-movement
118	https://ideas.everywhere.vc/p/news-vera-launches-ai-gateway-helps-companies-safely-scale-artifical-intelligence	Vera AI Launches ‚ÄòAI Gateway‚Äô to Empower Safe and Scalable AI Deployment	Vera's AI Gateway eases the last mile of Generative AI, to ensure consistency, reliability, and cost-optimization.	<html><head></head><body><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2 is-viewable-imag" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F67322786-7e55-4414-9e56-0df027b0fbd4_1024x683.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F67322786-7e55-4414-9e56-0df027b0fbd4_1024x683.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F67322786-7e55-4414-9e56-0df027b0fbd4_1024x683.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F67322786-7e55-4414-9e56-0df027b0fbd4_1024x683.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F67322786-7e55-4414-9e56-0df027b0fbd4_1024x683.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F67322786-7e55-4414-9e56-0df027b0fbd4_1024x683.jpeg" width="1024" height="683" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/67322786-7e55-4414-9e56-0df027b0fbd4_1024x683.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:683,&quot;width&quot;:1024,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:166811,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;topImage&quot;:true,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F67322786-7e55-4414-9e56-0df027b0fbd4_1024x683.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F67322786-7e55-4414-9e56-0df027b0fbd4_1024x683.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F67322786-7e55-4414-9e56-0df027b0fbd4_1024x683.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F67322786-7e55-4414-9e56-0df027b0fbd4_1024x683.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" fetchpriority="high"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a><figcaption class="image-caption">Vera AI co-founders: Justin Norman and Liz O‚ÄôSullivan</figcaption></figure></div><p><a href="https://www.askvera.io/">Vera AI Inc</a>., a startup focused on ethical AI deployment, has officially launched its AI Gateway platform, offering businesses a robust solution for integrating AI technologies with customizable safeguards. The platform features advanced model routing and guardrail functionalities, designed to help organizations mitigate risks while adopting AI. CEO <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/lizzosullivan/">Liz O‚ÄôSullivan </a>emphasized that Vera‚Äôs technology addresses the often-overlooked complexities of AI deployment, particularly the challenges of maintaining safety, managing disinformation, and preventing content violations. The system allows companies to tailor their AI policies, balancing innovation with responsible management.</p><p>Co-founded by O‚ÄôSullivan and <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/justindnorman/">Justin Norman</a>, Vera AI is already seeing early traction, processing thousands of model requests for a growing client base. O‚ÄôSullivan, a recognized advocate for AI safety, and Norman, an expert in AI robustness, have built the platform to focus on addressing critical "last-mile" issues in AI deployment. As AI adoption continues to accelerate across industries, Vera AI's Gateway platform is set to play a key role in enabling businesses to safely scale AI technologies without compromising on security or ethical standards.</p><div><hr></div><p>Read more in <a href="https://venturebeat.com/ai/vera-ai-launches-ai-gateway-to-help-companies-safely-scale-ai-without-the-risks/">Venture Beat.</a></p><p>Check out Liz O‚ÄôSullivan in <a href="https://ideas.everywhere.vc/p/vera-liz-osullivan-justin-norman-founders">Founders Everywhere</a> and on the <a href="https://ideas.everywhere.vc/p/podcast-liz-osullivan-noah-spirakus-episode33">Venture Everywhere Podcast. </a></p></body></html>	Ethical AI deployment, helping businesses integrate AI technologies with customizable safeguards. Balancing innovation and responsible management.	2024-10-02 20:29:27	2024-10-14 08:14:24.848	2024-10-14 09:30:45.381	{vc,ai}	https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F67322786-7e55-4414-9e56-0df027b0fbd4_1024x683.jpeg	Everywhere Ventures	news-vera-launches-ai-gateway-helps-companies-safely-scale-artifical
147	https://www.eu.vc/p/understanding-board-responsibilities	Understanding board responsibilities and governance	by Roberta Tihomirova, Head of Marketing at Eleven Ventures. | Originally published on Eleven Ventures.	<html><head></head><body><p>Guest post by <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/roberta-tihomirova-20694a186/">Roberta Tihomirova</a>, Head of Marketing at <a href="https://www.11.vc/">Eleven Ventures</a>. | Originally published on <a href="https://www.11.vc/understanding-board-responsibilities-and-governance/">Eleven Ventures</a>.</p><div><hr></div><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2 is-viewable-imag" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F22452ce0-69da-4fe2-82ea-e8303bc1c1c1_1200x630.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F22452ce0-69da-4fe2-82ea-e8303bc1c1c1_1200x630.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F22452ce0-69da-4fe2-82ea-e8303bc1c1c1_1200x630.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F22452ce0-69da-4fe2-82ea-e8303bc1c1c1_1200x630.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F22452ce0-69da-4fe2-82ea-e8303bc1c1c1_1200x630.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F22452ce0-69da-4fe2-82ea-e8303bc1c1c1_1200x630.png" width="1200" height="630" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/22452ce0-69da-4fe2-82ea-e8303bc1c1c1_1200x630.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:630,&quot;width&quot;:1200,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:237967,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:null,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;topImage&quot;:true,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F22452ce0-69da-4fe2-82ea-e8303bc1c1c1_1200x630.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F22452ce0-69da-4fe2-82ea-e8303bc1c1c1_1200x630.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F22452ce0-69da-4fe2-82ea-e8303bc1c1c1_1200x630.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F22452ce0-69da-4fe2-82ea-e8303bc1c1c1_1200x630.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" fetchpriority="high"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a></figure></div><p>Before diving into the intricacies of building a world-class board, let‚Äôs pause and ask: Why even have a board?</p><p>While it seems to be a given, especially for venture funded companies, few founders or board members truly consider the actual value a board can and should provide. The answer is very specific to the type of company, the founders, and the challenge that the business needs to overcome. One possible answer is that the board is the only place where founders can navigate the inherent complexity of building a startup. They do so by having an ongoing discussion with involved people that share incentives but are not fully immersed in the day-to-day operations. As humans, we create reality by sharing with others, hence the board is a way of creating reality. If this perspective seems too abstract, consider this: the board is the place where founders can work on the company instead of in the company. It‚Äôs an opportunity to take a step back and look at the bigger picture once a quarter, gaining a sense of accomplishment and future direction. And it is a Board Member‚Äôs opportunity to provide this perspective.</p><h3><strong>Fiduciary Duties: The Cornerstone of Effective Governance<br></strong></h3><p>At the heart of a board director‚Äôs role are fiduciary duties, which serve as the bedrock of trust and integrity within the boardroom. These duties are not just ethical guidelines ‚Äì they are legal obligations that require directors to prioritize the company‚Äôs interests above all else. Here we will get you familiar with the two most important fiduciary duties* ‚Äì the duty of Care and the duty of Loyalty.</p><p><em>*A fiduciary duty is the legal responsibility to act solely in the best interest of another party. ‚ÄúFiduciary‚Äù means trust, and a person with a fiduciary duty has a legal obligation to maintain that trust.</em></p><ol><li><p><strong>Duty of Care: Informed Decision-Making</strong></p></li></ol><ul><li><p>Directors must make well-informed decisions by thoroughly understanding all relevant information.</p></li><li><p>Reliance on expert advice is permitted, but it must be reasonable and made in good faith.</p></li><li><p>Active participation in board deliberations is required, with delegation limited to specific decision-making responsibilities.</p></li></ul><ol start="2"><li><p><strong>Duty of Loyalty: Prioritizing the Company‚Äôs Interests</strong></p></li></ol><ul><li><p>Directors must act in the company‚Äôs best interests, avoiding conflicts of interest and refraining from using their position for personal gain.</p></li><li><p>This duty underscores the importance of integrity and ethical behavior in board decisions.</p></li><li><p>The Duty of Loyalty also extends to safeguarding the company‚Äôs confidential information. Directors must ensure that sensitive data is not misused or disclosed inappropriately, as this could harm the company‚Äôs competitive position.</p></li></ul><p>Beyond these, directors are also bound by the duties of:</p><ul><li><p><strong>Obedience</strong> ‚Äì directors abide by all applicable laws and regulations.</p></li><li><p><strong>Confidentiality</strong> ‚Äì directors keep certain type of information confidential.</p></li><li><p><strong>Prudence</strong> ‚Äì be aware of risks and exercise caution when making decisions; approve expenditures wisely.</p></li><li><p><strong>Disclose</strong> ‚Äì if directors have information that would influence their decisions or impact the decisions of other board members, they have a duty to make that information known.</p></li></ul><h3><strong>Navigating Conflicts of Interest: A Delicate Balance</strong></h3><p>Unfortunately, life is always messier. Although the above principles are universally accepted, most board directors serve different ‚Äúmasters‚Äù in their heads. VCs representatives prioritize their VC fund, co-founders might focus on their team or their customers, and so on. Many heated discussions and conflicts on boards arise because directors have different priorities, even though everyone assumes they are acting in the best long-term interests of the company.</p><p>To manage these conflicts effectively, directors must engage in open, honest communication. The board should establish clear guidelines for identifying and managing conflicts of interest, ensuring that all directors understand their responsibilities in this area. When conflicts arise, it‚Äôs important to address them head-on, fostering an environment where differing viewpoints can be discussed openly and resolved in a way that aligns with the company‚Äôs long-term goals.</p><h3><strong>The Role and Responsibilities of the Board: Governance in Action</strong></h3><p>The board‚Äôs role extends beyond mere oversight. While the board does not involve itself in day-to-day operations, it plays a crucial role in setting the strategic direction of the company. This responsibility is encapsulated in the principle of ‚ÄúNose in, hands out,‚Äù which suggests that while the board should be deeply informed about the company‚Äôs activities, it should refrain from micromanaging.</p><p>Key responsibilities of the board include:</p><ol><li><p><strong>Strategic Oversight</strong>: The board is responsible for guiding the company‚Äôs long-term strategy. This involves reviewing and approving major initiatives, such as market expansion, product development, and mergers or acquisitions. Directors should ensure that the company‚Äôs strategy is aligned with its mission and values and that it is adaptable to changing market conditions.<br></p></li><li><p><strong>CEO and Executive Management Oversight</strong>: One of the board‚Äôs most critical functions is the selection, evaluation, and, if necessary, replacement of the CEO. The board must also set appropriate compensation for the CEO and senior management, aligning incentives with the company‚Äôs performance and long-term goals. Regular performance reviews help ensure that the CEO and management team are executing the board‚Äôs strategic vision effectively.<br></p></li><li><p><strong>Risk Management</strong>:&nbsp;The board must oversee the company‚Äôs risk management framework, ensuring that all potential risks‚Äîfinancial, operational, legal, and reputational‚Äîare identified and mitigated. Directors should ensure that the company has adequate insurance, internal controls, and crisis management plans in place.</p></li><li><p><strong>Compliance and Ethical Oversight</strong>: Directors are responsible for ensuring that the company adheres to all relevant laws, regulations, and ethical standards. This includes setting policies on issues like environmental impact, social responsibility, and corporate governance.<br></p></li></ol><h3><strong>The Path to Effective Board Governance</strong></h3><p>Board governance is not just about ticking boxes; it‚Äôs about creating value for the company and its stakeholders. By understanding and embracing their fiduciary duties, board directors can build a foundation of trust, integrity, and strategic foresight that drives the company towards sustainable success. Effective governance requires a delicate balance of oversight and empowerment, where directors guide the company‚Äôs vision while enabling the management team to execute it.</p><p>As a board director, your role is to ensure that every decision contributes to the long-term prosperity of the company. By fostering transparency, managing conflicts of interest, and staying committed to your fiduciary duties, you can help steer the company through the complexities of growth and innovation, ensuring that it not only survives but thrives in a competitive landscape.</p><p>Coming up next ‚Äì strategic planning and execution oversight. </p><p>Stay tuned for Chapter 2!</p><div><hr></div><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc2e93607-5191-4afb-b94b-51d0b094363e_1100x220.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc2e93607-5191-4afb-b94b-51d0b094363e_1100x220.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc2e93607-5191-4afb-b94b-51d0b094363e_1100x220.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc2e93607-5191-4afb-b94b-51d0b094363e_1100x220.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc2e93607-5191-4afb-b94b-51d0b094363e_1100x220.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc2e93607-5191-4afb-b94b-51d0b094363e_1100x220.png" width="1100" height="220" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/c2e93607-5191-4afb-b94b-51d0b094363e_1100x220.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:220,&quot;width&quot;:1100,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:60754,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" cl