quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/65c92233-ba1d-494b-9908-f87f76831f5d_7728x5152.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:971,&quot;width&quot;:1456,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:9239888,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;topImage&quot;:true,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F65c92233-ba1d-494b-9908-f87f76831f5d_7728x5152.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F65c92233-ba1d-494b-9908-f87f76831f5d_7728x5152.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F65c92233-ba1d-494b-9908-f87f76831f5d_7728x5152.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F65c92233-ba1d-494b-9908-f87f76831f5d_7728x5152.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" fetchpriority="high"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a></figure></div><p>Ar Europos ≈°ali≈≥ saugumo tarnyb≈≥ darbuotojams ir kari≈°kiams jau dabar turƒót≈≥ b≈´ti u≈ædrausta netgi artintis prie kini≈°k≈≥ elektromobili≈≥? </p><p>O kaip dƒól vyriausybi≈≥ ir parlamento nari≈≥, teisƒój≈≥, policinink≈≥ ar net gydytoj≈≥? Ar jiems galima leisti va≈æinƒóti kini≈°komis elektrinƒómis transporto priemonƒómis?</p><p>Ar apskritai tokiais automobiliais turƒót≈≥ b≈´ti leista va≈æinƒóti bet kur Europoje? Ar reikƒót≈≥ riboti j≈≥ naudojimƒÖ ≈°alia karini≈≥ objekt≈≥, NATO bazi≈≥ ar netgi vadinam≈≥j≈≥ kritinƒós infrastrukt≈´ros objekt≈≥? </p><p>KokiƒÖ grƒósmƒô bet kurios ≈°alies nacionaliniam saugumui apskritai kelia kini≈°ki elektromobiliai tiesiog va≈æinƒójantys t≈≥ ≈°ali≈≥ miest≈≥ gatvƒóse? Ir kiek t≈≥ automobili≈≥ turƒót≈≥ b≈´ti, kad grƒósmƒó tapt≈≥ kritinƒó?</p><p>Jeigu manote, kad tokie klausimai skamba keistai, tai ≈æinokite, kad juos sugalvojau ne a≈°. Tokius klausimus ne vien sugalvojo, bet ir jau kurƒØ laikƒÖ labai rimtai vie≈°umoje kelia ne vien Vakar≈≥ ≈°ali≈≥ saugumo ekspertai, bet ir bent jau buvƒô ≈°i≈≥ ≈°ali≈≥ ≈ævalgyb≈≥ atstovai.</p><p>Taƒçiau Lietuvoje apie ≈°iƒÖ tikrai rimtƒÖ nacionalinio saugumo grƒósmƒô bent jau vie≈°ai i≈° viso nekalbama. </p><p>Todƒól ≈°iandien, po to, kai <a href="https://www.theguardian.com/business/2024/oct/04/eu-chinese-ev-tariffs-split-vote-germany-car-firms">Pekinui ir jƒØ ≈°iuo klausimu rƒómusioms Europos SƒÖjungos ≈°alims bent jau nepavyko sustabdyti muit≈≥ kini≈°kiems automobiliams ƒØvedimo</a>, nusprend≈æiau, kad atƒójo metas jums, mano ‚ÄúSubstack‚Äù kanalo skaitytojai, plaƒçiau papasakoti apie ≈°iƒÖ tikrai realiƒÖ grƒósmƒô. </p><p>Tiksliau papasakosiu tai, kodƒól ƒØ kini≈°kus elektromobilius ir j≈≥ importƒÖ tiesiog <a href="https://www.lrt.lt/naujienos/eismas/7/2272702/pigus-ir-geri-bet-kelia-abejoniu-ar-ateityje-visi-persesime-i-kiniskus-elektromobilius">b≈´tina ≈ævelgti net ne ekonominƒós konkurencijos</a> ar <a href="https://www.lrt.lt/naujienos/eismas/7/2305660/kiniski-elektromobiliai-europoje-kokia-itaka-jie-darys-naudotu-automobiliu-kainoms">automobili≈≥ kainos</a>, o b≈´tent kriti≈°kai svarbios nacionalinio saugumo grƒósmƒós aspektu. Nors ne vien Lietuva, bet ir visa Europos SƒÖjunga, skirtingai negu JAV, pana≈°u, tam dar nepasirengusi.</p><p></p><p></p>\n      <p>\n          <a href="https://laurinavicius.substack.com/p/pigus-kiniski-elektromobiliai-karui-6dc">\n              Read more\n          </a>\n      </p>\n   </body></html>	Kini≈°ki elektromobiliai gali kelti grƒósmƒô Europos ≈°ali≈≥ nacionaliniam saugumui. Saugumo ekspertai kelia klausimus dƒól j≈≥ naudojimo ≈°alia karini≈≥ objekt≈≥ ar kritinƒós infrastrukt≈´ros. Taƒçiau Lietuvoje ≈°is klausimas vie≈°ai neaptariamas, nors Europoje jis sulaukia vis daugiau dƒómesio.	2024-10-07 16:55:37	2024-10-09 18:14:33.953	2024-10-09 18:14:35.445	{lithuanian}	https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F65c92233-ba1d-494b-9908-f87f76831f5d_7728x5152.jpeg	Marius Laurinaviƒçius	pigus-kiniski-elektromobiliai-karui
212	https://newsletter.mcj.vc/p/zeno	Our Investment in Zeno	Comprehensive electric mobility ecosystem	<html><head></head><body><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2 is-viewable-imag" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F08d67668-6b8a-48a2-9171-00dbce108f7b_2000x1125.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F08d67668-6b8a-48a2-9171-00dbce108f7b_2000x1125.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F08d67668-6b8a-48a2-9171-00dbce108f7b_2000x1125.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F08d67668-6b8a-48a2-9171-00dbce108f7b_2000x1125.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F08d67668-6b8a-48a2-9171-00dbce108f7b_2000x1125.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F08d67668-6b8a-48a2-9171-00dbce108f7b_2000x1125.png" width="1456" height="819" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/08d67668-6b8a-48a2-9171-00dbce108f7b_2000x1125.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:819,&quot;width&quot;:1456,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:69660,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;topImage&quot;:true,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F08d67668-6b8a-48a2-9171-00dbce108f7b_2000x1125.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F08d67668-6b8a-48a2-9171-00dbce108f7b_2000x1125.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F08d67668-6b8a-48a2-9171-00dbce108f7b_2000x1125.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F08d67668-6b8a-48a2-9171-00dbce108f7b_2000x1125.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" fetchpriority="high"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a></figure></div><p>The commuter motorcycle market is enormous, with an estimated <a href="https://www.riders-share.com/blog/article/number-motorcycles-world-top-countries">600 million</a> vehicles currently on the road globally, and projections reaching <a href="https://www.iea.org/reports/global-ev-outlook-2024">1.5 billion by 2040</a>. Most of this growth will come from emerging economies, where rising demand for affordable, accessible transportation combined with rapid urbanization fuels the growing need for 100-200cc motorbikes.</p><p>While drivers prefer electric options, regions like India and East Africa remain dominated by petrol-powered bikes. Despite these bikes' high fuel cost and environmental impact in densely populated areas, petrol-powered models are often more affordable upfront than electric alternatives. At MCJ, we understand that without electric options matching the upfront cost, performance, and practicality of petrol-powered bikes, transitioning is difficult, if not impossible, for those who rely on them for their livelihoods.</p><p>That‚Äôs where <strong><a href="https://zeno.earth/">Zeno</a></strong> comes in. The company is developing a 100-200cc equivalent electric motorcycle designed to compete directly with today‚Äôs most popular internal combustion engine models. Zeno uses a battery-as-a-service subscription model, allowing customers to purchase the motorcycle upfront and subscribe to access both the battery and Zeno's charging network. MCJ is excited to participate in Zeno‚Äôs Seed round, alongside firms such as Lowercarbon, Toyota Ventures, and others. Keep reading to see why we‚Äôre thrilled to support Michael Spencer and the team at Zeno as they address the electric 2-wheel mobility and energy gap in emerging markets.</p><h1><strong>What is Zeno?</strong></h1><p>Zeno is creating a comprehensive electric mobility ecosystem from the ground up. Serving emerging markets like India and East Africa, Zeno‚Äôs product features a 100-200 cc equivalent entry-level sport utility electric motorbike engineered to rival today‚Äôs top commuter motorcycles in every aspect. Zeno‚Äôs proprietary battery-as-a-service model allows riders to avoid the high upfront cost of purchasing a bike with a built-in battery. The company‚Äôs cloud-managed swap network ensures riders have seamless access to a dependable and flexible multimodal charging system, including battery swapping, public fast charging, and at-home slow charging options. This eliminates the wait time for recharging, reduces downtime, and increases reliability, making it easier for riders to stay on the road and boost their earning potential.</p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2 is-viewable-imag" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F15565fb2-ed30-455e-ae34-3b600e9776cd_1600x1137.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F15565fb2-ed30-455e-ae34-3b600e9776cd_1600x1137.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F15565fb2-ed30-455e-ae34-3b600e9776cd_1600x1137.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F15565fb2-ed30-455e-ae34-3b600e9776cd_1600x1137.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F15565fb2-ed30-455e-ae34-3b600e9776cd_1600x1137.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F15565fb2-ed30-455e-ae34-3b600e9776cd_1600x1137.png" width="1456" height="1035" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/15565fb2-ed30-455e-ae34-3b600e9776cd_1600x1137.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:1035,&quot;width&quot;:1456,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:null,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:null,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F15565fb2-ed30-455e-ae34-3b600e9776cd_1600x1137.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F15565fb2-ed30-455e-ae34-3b600e9776cd_1600x1137.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F15565fb2-ed30-455e-ae34-3b600e9776cd_1600x1137.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F15565fb2-ed30-455e-ae34-3b600e9776cd_1600x1137.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a></figure></div><p>The primary audience for Zeno‚Äôs first product is motorbike taxi drivers, known as boda drivers in East Africa, who often cover up to 150 km daily on rugged terrain while transporting heavy loads. Current electric options are limited: low-quality pedal-assisted bikes struggle with durability, hills, and load capacity, while premium electric bikes come with built-in batteries that increase costs, require long charging times, and often need financing. Zeno provides a superior solution‚Äîoffering better quality and affordability than both the low-end and premium electric alternatives, while enhancing the riding experience compared to gas-powered bikes.</p><h1><strong>Why Did We Invest?</strong></h1><h2><strong>Competitive Landscape</strong></h2><p>Most companies tackling two-wheel electric mobility today focus on e-bikes or lower-end scooters or mopeds, however, we believe the real market opportunity lies in the 100-200cc commuter motorcycle segment. Despite accounting for 60-80% of the global market, this segment is underserved in terms of electric options. Zeno is poised to fill this gap by leveraging advancements in battery technology and its innovative battery-as-a-service subscription model, which makes electric motorcycles more cost-competitive with gas-powered models. By targeting this segment in emerging markets like East Africa and South Asia, Zeno has the potential to capture significant market share and become a key player in the global shift toward sustainable mobility.</p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2 is-viewable-imag" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F24995492-2988-4c96-9fe5-c1c4b30c663f_1600x899.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F24995492-2988-4c96-9fe5-c1c4b30c663f_1600x899.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F24995492-2988-4c96-9fe5-c1c4b30c663f_1600x899.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F24995492-2988-4c96-9fe5-c1c4b30c663f_1600x899.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F24995492-2988-4c96-9fe5-c1c4b30c663f_1600x899.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F24995492-2988-4c96-9fe5-c1c4b30c663f_1600x899.png" width="1456" height="818" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/24995492-2988-4c96-9fe5-c1c4b30c663f_1600x899.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:818,&quot;width&quot;:1456,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:null,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:null,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F24995492-2988-4c96-9fe5-c1c4b30c663f_1600x899.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F24995492-2988-4c96-9fe5-c1c4b30c663f_1600x899.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F24995492-2988-4c96-9fe5-c1c4b30c663f_1600x899.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F24995492-2988-4c96-9fe5-c1c4b30c663f_1600x899.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a><figcaption class="image-caption">Sneak peek at Zeno‚Äôs battery and motorbike</figcaption></figure></div><h2><strong>Economic and Quality of Life Benefits&nbsp;</strong></h2><p>Electric motorbikes present a significant opportunity for economic uplift and improved quality of life, especially for commercial motorbike taxis in emerging markets. Transitioning to electric motorbikes offers significant cost savings, enabling drivers to increase their take-home income by up to 50%. As a result, drivers can see an immediate improvement in their economic stability and the ability to support their families.</p><p>Beyond individual economic benefits, electric motorbikes also contribute to public health. With a reduction in air pollution compared to traditional motorbikes, the shift to electric options reduces the harmful emissions that contribute to respiratory issues and other health problems. Cleaner air leads to better health outcomes for entire communities, which is crucial in densely populated urban areas where pollution levels are particularly high.</p><p>Furthermore, Zeno‚Äôs battery infrastructure could serve as a decentralized energy source. Their distributed network of batteries could be leveraged to provide grid services through a virtual power plant, or backup power to those without reliable access to electricity. This power can used for essential activities like cooking, lighting, and other household needs, raising the overall standard of living.</p><h2><strong>Compelling Founder-Market Fit</strong></h2><p>Zeno‚Äôs Founder and CEO,<strong> <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/michael-spencer-729a6715/">Michael Spencer</a></strong>, brings a decade of experience in building climate-focused businesses across East Africa, the U.S., and Europe. Most recently, he led Model 3 production ramp-up, supercharger network deployment across the U.S. and Europe, and home energy product launch at Tesla. His previous ventures include developing affordable, sustainable housing, turning around a conservation and regenerative agriculture business, and founding two affordable healthcare companies in Kenya.</p><p>But Michael doesn‚Äôt operate alone. He has assembled a highly skilled team capable of bringing a challenger brand to market from scratch and driving sales. Michael has attracted some of the industry‚Äôs top talent, from several engineering leaders at India‚Äôs largest electric two-wheeler OEMs to executives from East Africa‚Äôs largest ride-hailing companies. We believe this team not only has the market know-how but also the technical and logistical chops to tackle the complex challenge of battery swapping logistics‚Äîan essential component to making electric mobility reliable and scalable in emerging markets. We‚Äôre excited to watch this team grow!&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Additional Resources</strong></p><ul><li><p><a href="https://techcrunch.com/2024/09/19/zeno-emerges-from-stealth-to-crib-teslas-master-plan-for-africa-and-beyond/?guccounter=1&amp;guce_referrer=aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZ29vZ2xlLmNvbS8&amp;guce_referrer_sig=AQAAADxg802NieZp0f2g93KlvS-xLuMmK0Shf6qdBrGTEd2RYN835mXf2y2-w3q5xcwlpTBeVl45QSF0isyTrtFvtZuZrNVeEy1YQXDh_gn75CieAkNzQEz6SJ63ZoRvx_DMxYxGUb_vIpP-3E86MTBuul0OQDIX8BLQOls4BIverB-M">Zeno emerges from stealth to crib Tesla‚Äôs master plan for Africa and beyond</a> [Tech Crunch]</p></li></ul><div><hr></div><p class="button-wrapper" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://newsletter.mcj.vc/p/zeno?utm_source=substack&amp;utm_medium=email&amp;utm_content=share&amp;action=share&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Share&quot;,&quot;action&quot;:null,&quot;class&quot;:null}" data-component-name="ButtonCreateButton"><a class="button primary" href="https://newsletter.mcj.vc/p/zeno?utm_source=substack&amp;utm_medium=email&amp;utm_content=share&amp;action=share"><span>Share</span></a></p><p><strong>The MCJ Newsletter</strong>&nbsp;is a free weekly email curating news, jobs,&nbsp;<a href="https://www.mcjcollective.com/media/podcast">My Climate Journey podcast episodes</a>, and other noteworthy happenings in the&nbsp;<a href="https://mcj.vc/join">MCJ Collective</a>.</p><p>üí≠ If you have feedback or items you‚Äôd like to include, feel free to&nbsp;<a href="mailto:info@mcj.vc">reach out</a>.</p><p>ü§ù If you‚Äôd like to join the MCJ Collective, <a href="https://mcj.vc/join">apply today</a>.</p><p>üí° Have a climate-related event or content topic that you'd like to see in the MCJ newsletter? Email us at&nbsp;<a href="mailto:content@mcj.vc">content@mcj.vc</a></p></body></html>	The commuter motorcycle market is enormous, with 600 million vehicles globally and projections reaching 1.5 billion by 2040. Zeno is developing a 100-200cc equivalent electric motorcycle to compete with popular internal combustion engine.	2024-10-22 13:04:54	2024-10-26 13:34:53.457	2024-10-26 14:01:31.563	{english}	https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F24995492-2988-4c96-9fe5-c1c4b30c663f_1600x899.png	MCJ	our-investment-in-zeno
214	https://parsers.substack.com/p/parsers-vc-weekly-funding-startup-e5d	Parsers VC - Weekly Funding / Startup / VC news of October 22, 2024	Venture Capital News. Funding rounds, statistics Week of October 15 - October 21: United States (52 - $3.1B), United Kingdom (12 - $209M), India (5 - $248M), Israel (4 - $74M), Canada (3 - $267M)	<html><head></head><body><h2>Most Popular Venture Capital News</h2><h3>1. <a href="https://parsers.vc/news/241016-everstage-s-30-million-leap--a-new-era-for/?utm_source=newsletter.parsers.vc&amp;utm_medium=newsletter&amp;utm_campaign=parsers-vc-weekly-funding-startup-vc-news-of-october-22-2024&amp;_bhlid=43e3213e85cb874aa088cd72c8867d30419a4764">Everstage's $30 Million Leap: A New Era for Sales Performance Management</a>&nbsp;</h3><p><em>(Cited in 24 tech media)</em></p><p>In the bustling world of SaaS, Everstage has made waves. The Chennai and Delaware-based startup recently secured $30 million in a Series B funding round led by Eight Roads Ventures. This infusion of capital brings its total funding to $45 million. It‚Äôs a significant milestone for a company that only launched in 2020.<br>Everstage specializes in sales performance management software. Think of it as a compass for sales teams, guiding them through the fog of commission structures and performance metrics. With this latest funding, Everstage aims to sharpen its tools and expand its offerings. The goal? To enhance product capabilities and boost in-house professional services.</p><h3>2. <a href="https://parsers.vc/news/241015-telecom-titans-unite-to-forge-a-new-api/?utm_source=newsletter.parsers.vc&amp;utm_medium=newsletter&amp;utm_campaign=parsers-vc-weekly-funding-startup-vc-news-of-october-22-2024&amp;_bhlid=d01505e6d9505a6cc0a8ca7806a043d9c2647756">Telecom Titans Unite to Forge a New API Frontier</a>&nbsp;</h3><p><em>(Cited in 17 tech media)</em></p><p>In a bold move, twelve of the world's leading telecom operators have banded together with Ericsson to create a joint venture aimed at revolutionizing the telecommunications landscape. This alliance is not just a handshake; it‚Äôs a seismic shift in how network resources are accessed and monetized. The new company is set to develop and monetize network Application Programming Interfaces (APIs), a market projected to reach a staggering $30 billion by 2030.<br>Imagine a world where telecom services are as easy to access as flipping a switch. This partnership aims to make that vision a reality. By leveraging network APIs, telecom operators can offer direct, dynamic, and scalable access to their resources. It‚Äôs like opening a floodgate of connectivity, allowing developers to tap into a vast reservoir of networking capabilities with just a single API call.</p><h3>3. <a href="https://parsers.vc/news/241015-dtiq-s-bold-leap--a-145-million-investment/?utm_source=newsletter.parsers.vc&amp;utm_medium=newsletter&amp;utm_campaign=parsers-vc-weekly-funding-startup-vc-news-of-october-22-2024&amp;_bhlid=30afe324bf4272a5bd546d4d3ce669ecd6d9b9c4">DTiQ's Bold Leap: A $145 Million Investment to Revolutionize Retail Analytics</a>&nbsp;</h3><p><em>(Cited in 14 tech media)</em></p><p>In the fast-paced world of retail and hospitality, data is the new gold. DTiQ Technologies, a frontrunner in SaaS-based video analytics, has just struck a deal that could reshape its future. With a hefty $145 million growth investment from Bain Capital Credit, DTiQ is poised to accelerate its innovation and expand its reach. This funding isn't just a financial boost; it's a strategic move that signals a shift towards a more robust SaaS growth model.<br>DTiQ specializes in video-based business optimization solutions tailored for the restaurant, convenience store, and specialty retail sectors. Think of them as the eyes in the sky, turning video footage into actionable insights. Their clients include heavyweights like Subway, Dunkin', and Burger King. With this new capital, DTiQ aims to enhance its AI-powered analytics and broaden its product offerings. The goal? To provide operators with tools that tackle everyday challenges, from loss prevention to improving service speed.</p><h3>4. <a href="https://parsers.vc/news/241015-the-remote-work-tug-of-war--a-new-era-of/?utm_source=newsletter.parsers.vc&amp;utm_medium=newsletter&amp;utm_campaign=parsers-vc-weekly-funding-startup-vc-news-of-october-22-2024&amp;_bhlid=c30be5047d871acbd4f5522516062b8362e2ac1e">The Remote Work Tug-of-War: A New Era of Office Dynamics</a>&nbsp;</h3><p><em>(Cited in 14 tech media)</em></p><p>The landscape of work is shifting. The pandemic pushed remote work into the spotlight, but now, the pendulum is swinging back. Companies like Amazon and Apple are calling employees back to the office. Meanwhile, Spotify stands firm, advocating for flexibility. This clash of cultures reveals deeper truths about productivity, trust, and the future of work.<br>In 2020, remote work was a lifeline. It was a necessity, a temporary fix to an unprecedented crisis. Fast forward to 2024, and the world is a different place. The pandemic is largely behind us, yet the debate over remote work rages on. Some companies are eager to return to the old ways, while others, like Spotify, are embracing a new normal.</p><h3>5. <a href="https://parsers.vc/news/241016-20vc-s-third-fund--a-bold-leap-into-the/?utm_source=newsletter.parsers.vc&amp;utm_medium=newsletter&amp;utm_campaign=parsers-vc-weekly-funding-startup-vc-news-of-october-22-2024&amp;_bhlid=7e5719390dead7ded47fe361838dc5f04e936354">20VC's Third Fund: A Bold Leap into the Future of Venture Capital </a></h3><p><em>(Cited in 12 tech media)</em></p><p>In the world of venture capital, success often hinges on timing and strategy. 20VC, a London-based investment firm led by Harry Stebbings, has struck gold with its latest fundraising effort. The firm recently announced the closing of its third fund, amassing a staggering $400 million. This is not just a number; it‚Äôs a statement. It signals confidence in a time when many firms are grappling with fundraising challenges.<br>The new fund is split into two segments: $125 million earmarked for Seed investments and $275 million for Series A funding. This structure is designed to support startups at critical stages of their growth. The scale of this fund is a remarkable 2.5 times larger than its predecessor, which raised $140 million in June 2021. This growth trajectory is a testament to 20VC‚Äôs evolving strategy and the increasing trust of its investors.</p><h3>6. <a href="https://parsers.vc/news/241018-amazon-s-nuclear-leap--powering-the-future/?utm_source=newsletter.parsers.vc&amp;utm_medium=newsletter&amp;utm_campaign=parsers-vc-weekly-funding-startup-vc-news-of-october-22-2024&amp;_bhlid=6df40e5119ff70f516d5f05e017309a871a76ae2">Amazon's Nuclear Leap: Powering the Future of AI </a></h3><p><em>(Cited in 11 tech media)</em></p><p>In a bold move, Amazon is stepping into the nuclear energy arena. The tech giant has partnered with Energy Northwest and X-Energy to harness the power of nuclear energy for its ambitious artificial intelligence (AI) projects. This partnership marks a significant shift in how major tech companies approach energy consumption, especially as they grapple with the soaring demands of AI.<br>The collaboration aims to generate a staggering 5 gigawatts (GW) of energy by 2039, with the first reactors expected to come online by 2030. Amazon's investment of $500 million in X-Energy underscores its commitment to this venture. X-Energy, a startup specializing in small modular reactors (SMRs), is set to play a crucial role in this energy transformation.</p><h3>7. <a href="https://parsers.vc/news/241016-dialpad-s-300-million-milestone--a-new-era/?utm_source=newsletter.parsers.vc&amp;utm_medium=newsletter&amp;utm_campaign=parsers-vc-weekly-funding-startup-vc-news-of-october-22-2024&amp;_bhlid=6206e4726f4bf630ef3956dbdff160da76b10d55">Dialpad's $300 Million Milestone: A New Era in AI-Powered Communications</a>&nbsp;</h3><p><em>(Cited in 11 tech media)</em></p><p>Dialpad has crossed a significant threshold, surpassing $300 million in annual recurring revenue (ARR). This achievement is not just a number; it‚Äôs a testament to the company‚Äôs vision and innovation in the realm of AI-driven communications. Dialpad stands at the forefront of a revolution, reshaping how businesses interact with their customers.<br>The company‚Äôs journey began with a bold investment in artificial intelligence back in 2018. This foresight has paid off handsomely. Dialpad‚Äôs AI capabilities are not mere enhancements; they are the backbone of its service. The platform transcribes every customer conversation in real-time, providing immediate insights and guidance. This real-time feedback loop is like having a seasoned coach in your ear during every call, ensuring that sales and support teams are always at their best.</p><h3>8. <a href="https://parsers.vc/news/241018-hometree-s-50m-boost--a-green-revolution/?utm_source=newsletter.parsers.vc&amp;utm_medium=newsletter&amp;utm_campaign=parsers-vc-weekly-funding-startup-vc-news-of-october-22-2024&amp;_bhlid=9e4b95cb1cf9b14f734b01bdfb892ab8213173f0">Hometree's ¬£50M Boost: A Green Revolution for UK Homes</a>&nbsp;</h3><p><em>(Cited in 10 tech media)</em></p><p>Hometree is on a mission. The London-based residential energy services company has secured a ¬£50 million mezzanine financing package from CPP Investments. This funding is not just a number; it‚Äôs a lifeline for homeowners seeking greener alternatives. With this capital, Hometree aims to install solar panels, batteries, and heat pumps in 35,000 homes across the UK.<br>The urgency for such initiatives is palpable. Energy prices are soaring. Ofgem‚Äôs recent announcement of a ¬£149 increase in the energy price cap has left many households reeling. The need for renewable energy solutions has never been more pressing. Last year, over 180,000 solar panel installations took place in the UK. The momentum is building, but barriers remain.</p><h2>Last week's funding rounds</h2><p><strong>149</strong> funding rounds, <strong>+29%</strong> from last week.</p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2 is-viewable-imag" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2d0aa158-b330-471c-8320-100723e99a47_600x350.gif" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_lossy/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2d0aa158-b330-471c-8320-100723e99a47_600x350.gif 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_lossy/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2d0aa158-b330-471c-8320-100723e99a47_600x350.gif 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_lossy/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2d0aa158-b330-471c-8320-100723e99a47_600x350.gif 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_lossy/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2d0aa158-b330-471c-8320-100723e99a47_600x350.gif 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_lossy/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2d0aa158-b330-471c-8320-100723e99a47_600x350.gif" width="600" height="350" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/2d0aa158-b330-471c-8320-100723e99a47_600x350.gif&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:350,&quot;width&quot;:600,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:null,&quot;alt&quot;:&