112	https://thefoundingjourney.substack.com/p/how-steven-galanis-grew-cameo-into	How Steven Galanis Grew Cameo Into a $1 Billion Unicorn 	Our second episode for the Founding Journey podcast!	<html><head></head><body><p>Each Thursday I‚Äôll interview a world-class founder about their unique paths to uncover tactical insights they've learned about how to fundraise, grow, validate, hire, scale, and lead teams.</p><p>The first <em>two</em> episodes are live right now, including this conversation with Steven Galanis from Cameo.</p><p>Steven is the co-founder and CEO of Cameo. He grew the company from 0 into a $1 billion unicorn pursued by every top VC firm. Millions of Cameos have been sent since the company was founded and they recently raised fresh capital after a few rounds of layoffs. Steven was open and candid with me about that journey.</p><p>If you prefer, you can watch on <a href="https://www.youtube.com/@foundingjourney?sub_confirmation=1">YouTube</a> or listen on <a href="https://open.spotify.com/show/4SqCLo3ruK3MGCIoJvPdbR?si=f5157619cac74722">Spotify</a>, <a href="https://podcasts.apple.com/ng/podcast/founding-journey/id1773179683">Apple</a> or your podcast platform of choice.</p><div id="youtube2-uyYdcyFLURE" class="youtube-wrap" data-attrs="{&quot;videoId&quot;:&quot;uyYdcyFLURE&quot;,&quot;startTime&quot;:&quot;1s&quot;,&quot;endTime&quot;:null}" data-component-name="Youtube2ToDOM"><div class="youtube-inner"><iframe src="https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/uyYdcyFLURE?start=1s&amp;rel=0&amp;autoplay=0&amp;showinfo=0&amp;enablejsapi=0" frameborder="0" loading="lazy" gesture="media" allow="autoplay; fullscreen" allowautoplay="true" allowfullscreen="true" width="728" height="409"></iframe></div></div><p>In the episode, we discuss:</p><p><strong>The Journey to Cameo</strong></p><ul><li><p>(01:33) ‚Äî&nbsp; Steven's 1st business: Spartan Entertainment</p></li><li><p>(04:26) ‚Äî Steven's pre-Cameo work experience</p></li><li><p>(06:33) ‚Äî Starting Cameo with Co-founder Martin Blencowe</p></li><li><p>(11:14) ‚Äî Cameo's founding story</p></li></ul><p><strong>Founder Mode</strong></p><ul><li><p>(18:43) ‚Äî Steven‚Äôs early insight on ‚Äúcameos‚Äù</p></li><li><p>(23:48) ‚Äî Overcoming the cold start problem</p></li><li><p>(25:46) ‚Äî Cameo's growth tactics</p></li><li><p>(27:28) ‚Äî Cameo's eureka moment</p></li></ul><p><strong>Challenges &amp; Opportunities</strong></p><ul><li><p>(31:39) ‚Äî Changing Cameo's idea of success</p></li><li><p>(36:30) ‚Äî Navigating headcount reductions</p></li><li><p>(38:57) ‚Äî Joining the 1871 incubator</p></li><li><p>(40:57) ‚Äî Building alongside other founders</p></li></ul><p><strong>Investor Relations &amp; Communication</strong></p><ul><li><p>(42:26) ‚Äî How to interact with investors</p></li><li><p>(44:02) ‚Äî Co-founder communication</p></li><li><p>(46:39) ‚Äî Attracting investors without fundraising</p></li><li><p>(49:00) ‚Äî Fundraising without a pitch deck</p></li><li><p>(50:33) ‚Äî Benefits of creating an unused pitch deck</p></li><li><p>(53:32) ‚Äî Cameo's Series A experience</p></li></ul><p>And here's where to find Steven:</p><ul><li><p>X ‚Üí <a href="https://x.com/Mr312">x.com/Mr312</a></p></li><li><p>LinkedIn ‚Üí <a href="https://linkedin.com/in/stevengalanis">linkedin.com/in/stevengalanis</a></p></li><li><p>Instagram ‚Üí <a href="https://instagram.com/cameo">instagram.com/cameo</a></p></li><li><p>Startup ‚Üí <a href="https://cameo.com">cameo.com</a></p></li></ul><div><hr></div><h2><strong>How We Can Help</strong></h2><p><a href="https://upgrade.foundingjourney.com">Become a member</a> to join the community, get access to our 100+ case studies and deep dives, our private founder community and more.</p><h3><strong>Content Creation</strong></h3><p>Let my team and I <a href="https://s665g04yp0s.typeform.com/to/rOXjvxHU">ghostwrite</a> for your newsletter, X, or LinkedIn.</p><h3><strong>Growth</strong></h3><p><a href="https://go.houck.news/megaphone">Grow your audience + generate leads</a> with my growth service.</p><h3><strong>Fundraising</strong></h3><p><a href="https://go.houck.news/fundraise">Share your round</a> with hundreds of investors in my personal network.</p><h3><strong>Advising</strong></h3><p><a href="https://foundingjourney.com/c/collab">I‚Äôll help solve</a> a specific challenge you‚Äôre facing with your startup.</p></body></html>	This article interviews Steven Galanis, the co-founder and CEO of Cameo, about his journey in building the company from scratch into a $1 billion unicorn.	2024-10-10 10:35:54	2024-10-14 08:11:05.041	2024-10-14 09:30:45.381	{vc}	https://api.substack.com/feed/podcast/150046324/6a387836137451745722b8b89254513a.mp3	Michael Houck	how-steven-galanis-grew-cameo
109	https://thevccorner.substack.com/p/the-ultimate-vc-pitch-deck-collection	üíº The Ultimate VC Pitch Deck Collection: Over $1B Raised üöÄ	Raising funds is one of the hardest challenges for both startup founders and venture capitalists.	<html><head></head><body><p>Raising funds is one of the hardest challenges for both startup founders and venture capitalists. Whether you're launching your first startup or building a new venture fund, the key to securing investment often lies in one thing: a compelling pitch deck. But what makes a deck stand out and get results?</p><p>In this article, I‚Äôve curated<strong> 24 of the most successful VC pitch decks</strong> that have collectively raised over <strong>$1 billion</strong>. These aren't just any slides‚Äîthey‚Äôre the proven blueprints that have captured LP interest and sealed the deal for top-tier VCs.</p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2 is-viewable-imag" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F153ea772-1394-457e-b04d-8403d1fb3741_1224x659.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F153ea772-1394-457e-b04d-8403d1fb3741_1224x659.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F153ea772-1394-457e-b04d-8403d1fb3741_1224x659.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F153ea772-1394-457e-b04d-8403d1fb3741_1224x659.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F153ea772-1394-457e-b04d-8403d1fb3741_1224x659.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F153ea772-1394-457e-b04d-8403d1fb3741_1224x659.png" width="678" height="365.0343137254902" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/153ea772-1394-457e-b04d-8403d1fb3741_1224x659.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:659,&quot;width&quot;:1224,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:678,&quot;bytes&quot;:649967,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;topImage&quot;:true,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F153ea772-1394-457e-b04d-8403d1fb3741_1224x659.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F153ea772-1394-457e-b04d-8403d1fb3741_1224x659.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F153ea772-1394-457e-b04d-8403d1fb3741_1224x659.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F153ea772-1394-457e-b04d-8403d1fb3741_1224x659.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" fetchpriority="high"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a></figure></div><div><hr></div><h3>üîç <strong>Why These Decks Matter</strong></h3><p>These pitch decks reveal how the best venture capitalists structure their investment theses, articulate the strength of their teams, and showcase their unique market opportunities. Understanding what works for the top funds can give you a head start in refining your own fundraising approach.</p><div><hr></div><h3>üí∞ <strong>Unlock the Secrets Behind Raising $1B+</strong></h3><p>The decks I‚Äôm sharing have helped top funds raise millions and solidify their positions as industry leaders. If you aim to improve your fundraising game, these examples will give you the insights and structure you need to create a resonating pitch deck.</p><p>Here are just a few of the pitch decks included:</p><ul><li><p>Awesome People Ventures Fund 2 Pitch Deck</p></li><li><p>Earl Grey Capital Fund II Pitch Deck</p></li><li><p>Long Journey Ventures Fund I Pitch Deck</p></li><li><p>Not Boring Capital Fund I Pitch Deck</p></li><li><p>Precursor Fund III Pitch Deck</p></li><li><p>Shrug Capital IV Pitch Deck</p></li><li><p>Spacecadet Ventures Pitch Deck</p></li><li><p>WorkLife Fund 2 Pitch Deck</p></li><li><p>Not Boring Capital Fund II Pitch Deck</p></li><li><p>Susa Ventures IV Pitch Deck</p></li><li><p>Todd and Rahul‚Äôs Angel Fund Pitch Deck</p></li><li><p>Weekend Fund 3.0 Pitch Deck</p><p></p><p>And more‚Ä¶</p></li></ul><div><hr></div><h3>üöÄ <strong>Are You Ready to Nail Your Next Fundraise?</strong></h3><p>These decks are the ultimate resource for understanding how top VCs close deals with LPs. Instead of starting from scratch, you can use these real-world examples to refine your own pitch and raise capital more effectively. The guidance within these decks will help you understand what LPs want to see and how to deliver it.</p><div><hr></div><h3>üí° <strong>What You‚Äôll Learn</strong></h3><p>By studying these pitch decks, you‚Äôll gain:</p><ul><li><p>A clear framework for building a standout pitch deck.</p></li><li><p>Key insights into what makes LPs say yes.</p></li><li><p>Over <strong>$1 billion</strong> worth of successful fundraising strategies.</p></li></ul><p></p><h3>Find 24 <strong>of the most successful VC pitch decks below üëá</strong></h3><p></p><blockquote><p>If you're still a free subscriber, now's the perfect time to <strong>upgrade to premium</strong> with a <strong>limited offer of 25% off forever</strong>. Don‚Äôt miss out on the chance to access not only these valuable decks but also the entire archive of exclusive content on <strong>The VC Corner</strong>.</p></blockquote><p class="button-wrapper" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://thevccorner.substack.com/subscribe?coupon=6e5adce2&amp;utm_content=150091962&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Get 25% off forever&quot;,&quot;action&quot;:null,&quot;class&quot;:&quot;button-wrapper&quot;}" data-component-name="ButtonCreateButton"><a class="button primary button-wrapper" href="https://thevccorner.substack.com/subscribe?coupon=6e5adce2&amp;utm_content=150091962"><span>Get 25% off forever</span></a></p><p></p>\n      <p>\n          <a href="https://thevccorner.substack.com/p/the-ultimate-vc-pitch-deck-collection">\n              Read more\n          </a>\n      </p>\n   </body></html>	Raising funds is a significant challenge for startups and venture capitalists. This article curates 24 successful VC pitch decks that have collectively raised over $1 billion.	2024-10-11 12:08:34	2024-10-14 08:10:58.167	2024-10-14 09:30:45.381	{vc}	https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https