117	https://ideas.everywhere.vc/p/matilda-damian-png-founders-everywhere	Founders Everywhere: Damian Png	Damian Png is the co-founder and CEO of Matilda, a tech-enabled migration agency dedicated to simplifying the process for individuals seeking Employer Sponsored and Partner Visas in Australia.	<html><head></head><body><p><em>Welcome to Founders Everywhere, where we highlight the incredible people behind the companies we‚Äôve backed at <a href="https://everywhere.vc/">Everywhere Ventures</a>, a global pre-seed fund supported by a community of 500 founders and operators.</em></p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2 is-viewable-imag" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F422cce8c-ece2-47fd-83a6-86828cb17041_2364x1700.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F422cce8c-ece2-47fd-83a6-86828cb17041_2364x1700.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F422cce8c-ece2-47fd-83a6-86828cb17041_2364x1700.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F422cce8c-ece2-47fd-83a6-86828cb17041_2364x1700.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F422cce8c-ece2-47fd-83a6-86828cb17041_2364x1700.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F422cce8c-ece2-47fd-83a6-86828cb17041_2364x1700.png" width="1456" height="1047" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/422cce8c-ece2-47fd-83a6-86828cb17041_2364x1700.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:1047,&quot;width&quot;:1456,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:1701496,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;topImage&quot;:true,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F422cce8c-ece2-47fd-83a6-86828cb17041_2364x1700.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F422cce8c-ece2-47fd-83a6-86828cb17041_2364x1700.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F422cce8c-ece2-47fd-83a6-86828cb17041_2364x1700.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F422cce8c-ece2-47fd-83a6-86828cb17041_2364x1700.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" fetchpriority="high"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a><figcaption class="image-caption">Damian Png- Co-founder and CEO of Matilda.</figcaption></figure></div><p>Australia is an immigrant nation, with almost 30 percent of its population born overseas and around 50 percent having at least one parent born abroad. Despite this rich cultural diversity, navigating the immigration process remains notoriously complex, especially for those seeking permanent residency or work sponsorships. The process is often confusing and cumbersome, leading to a frustrating experience for many. While migration experts can help, their services often come with a hefty price tag and limited guidance. In Australia alone, visas are a $4 billion industry that is ripe for change. With <a href="https://www.matildamigration.com/">Matilda</a>, those who are looking for partner visas or employer sponsored visas can use the platform to simplify and automate the visa application process.&nbsp;</p><p>Matilda co-founders <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/damian-png-australia/">Damian Png</a> and <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/niamh-mooney-b5b34364/">Niamh Mooney</a> met through mutual friends and both have been affected by migration. Damian‚Äôs father is a migrant from Singapore and Niamh is a migrant from Ireland. Damian‚Äôs experience spans investment, consulting, and early-stage startups, while Niamh brings expertise in B2C marketing and scaling her successful tele-dermatology business. Damian, the CEO, shares more about their shared vision to simplify the complex migration process in Australia using innovative technology.</p><div><hr></div><h4><strong>What inspired the creation of Matilda?</strong></h4><p>My father is a migrant from Singapore, and my co-founder, Niamh, is also a migrant from Ireland. Through my work and interactions with international friends and expats, I saw the frustrations many face with the visa process. The inefficiencies and pain points made me realize that there‚Äôs a significant opportunity to improve the system with technology.&nbsp;</p><h4><strong>What is Matilda‚Äôs North Star?</strong></h4><p>Our North Star is to transform the migration experience from a stressful and complex ordeal into an exciting new chapter in people‚Äôs lives. We are streamlining the process and making it as smooth as possible, not just for obtaining visas, but for settling into a new country.&nbsp;</p><h4><strong>What sets Matilda apart? </strong></h4><p>We‚Äôre very tech-driven in a space that traditionally hasn‚Äôt embraced innovation. There are over 5,000 registered migration agents in Australia and the majority operate as small family-run businesses or sole traders, Matilda leverages design and automation to offer the same services in a more efficient, affordable, user-friendly, and transparent manner. Our philosophy is that we will never ask our clients to do something that we can do on their behalf, and that ethos is pretty unique in this sector.</p><h4><strong>Tell us about some milestones that Matilda crushed.</strong></h4><p>We <a href="https://ideas.everywhere.vc/p/news-matilda-migration-raises-1m-automate-visa-process">raised $1 million in pre-seed funding</a> and hired a senior migration agent, which was a big win for us because within the existing culture it was hard to find someone who was open to innovation and excited to improve service standards in the industry. We also launched our beta phase and are serving a limited number of clients to refine our services.&nbsp;</p><h4><strong>Any advice for other founders? </strong></h4><p>One thing that has helped me develop my founder toolkit is being personally involved with investments, both through TechStars and personal investments. Books like <em>Zero to One</em> by Peter Thiel and Blake Masters and <em>Angel</em> by Jason Calacanis help you get into the mindset of an investor. It‚Äôs less about trying to please investors and more about understanding that investors have spent a lot of time thinking about what the blueprint for a successful company looks like. Being able to put that hat on and critically look at your business really helps you with prioritization.&nbsp;</p><div><hr></div><p>Listen to  <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/gadalia-o-bryan/">Gadalia Montoya Weinberg O'Bryan</a> with <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/arinewman/">Ari Newman</a> on the Venture Everywhere podcast: <a href="https://ideas.everywhere.vc/p/podcast-gadalia-montoya-weinberg-obryan-ari-newman-episode47">Access Granted</a>. Listen now on <a href="https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/access-granted-gadalia-montoya-weinberg-obryan-with/id1683046904?i=1000671451715">Apple </a>&amp; <a href="https://open.spotify.com/episode/6YIAPFpVTwm7l9i8uumZ13">Spotify</a> and check out to all our past episodes <a href="https://ideas.everywhere.vc/s/podcast">here</a>!</p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2" target="_blank" href="https://open.spotify.com/episode/6YIAPFpVTwm7l9i8uumZ13" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F5553b565-316e-488a-895f-911ff8a09b6c_3000x3000.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F5553b565-316e-488a-895f-911ff8a09b6c_3000x3000.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F5553b565-316e-488a-895f-911ff8a09b6c_3000x3000.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F5553b565-316e-488a-895f-911ff8a09b6c_3000x3000.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F5553b565-316e-488a-895f-911ff8a09b6c_3000x3000.jpeg" width="276" height="276" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/5553b565-316e-488a-895f-911ff8a09b6c_3000x3000.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:1456,&quot;width&quot;:1456,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:276,&quot;bytes&quot;:461661,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:&quot;https://open.spotify.com/episode/6YIAPFpVTwm7l9i8uumZ13&quot;,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F5553b565-316e-488a-895f-911ff8a09b6c_3000x3000.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F5553b565-316e-488a-895f-911ff8a09b6c_3000x3000.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F5553b565-316e-488a-895f-911ff8a09b6c_3000x3000.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F5553b565-316e-488a-895f-911ff8a09b6c_3000x3000.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div></div></div></a></figure></div></body></html>	Matilda simplifies the complex migration process in Australia using innovative technology. Co-founders Damian Png and Niamh Mooney aim to transform the migration experience from a stressful ordeal into an exciting new chapter.	2024-10-03 14:57:33	2024-10-14 08:14:23.711	2024-10-14 08:35:06.793	{vc}	https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/e7d5f7d4-7659-4e88-bfce-14d30ab3f835_2364x1700.png	Everywhere Ventures	matilda-damian-png-founders
126	https://www.newsletter.datadrivenvc.io/p/founder-compensation-and-equity-benchmarks	Founder Compensation & Equity Benchmarks	Synthesizing Insights From the Data	<html><head></head><body><p>üëã&nbsp;<em>Hi, I‚Äôm <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/andreretterath/">Andre</a> and welcome to my newsletter <a href="https://www.newsletter.datadrivenvc.io/">Data-Driven VC</a> which is all about becoming a better investor with Data &amp; AI. Join <strong>28,240 thought leaders</strong> from VCs like a16z, Accel, Index, Sequoia, and more to understand how startup investing becomes more data-driven, why it matters, and what it means for you.</em></p><p class="button-wrapper" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://www.newsletter.datadrivenvc.io/subscribe?&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Subscribe now&quot;,&quot;action&quot;:null,&quot;class&quot;:null}" data-component-name="ButtonCreateButton"><a class="button primary" href="https://www.newsletter.datadrivenvc.io/subscribe?"><span>Subscribe now</span></a></p><div><hr></div><p>Brought to you by <a href="https://vestberry.com/?utm_source=Newsletter&amp;utm_medium=DDVC">VESTBERRY</a> - Portfolio Intelligence Platform for Data-Driven VCs</p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2" target="_blank" href="https://hello.vestberry.com/ddvc-ai-portfolio-review/?utm_source=Newsletter&amp;utm_medium=DataDrivenVC" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F8809b532-7874-4994-9035-45983c354d16_2400x900.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F8809b532-7874-4994-9035-45983c354d16_2400x900.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F8809b532-7874-4994-9035-45983c354d16_2400x900.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F8809b532-7874-4994-9035-45983c354d16_2400x900.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F8809b532-7874-4994-9035-45983c354d16_2400x900.png" width="1456" height="546" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/8809b532-7874-4994-9035-45983c354d16_2400x900.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:546,&quot;width&quot;:1456,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:574835,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:&quot;https://hello.vestberry.com/ddvc-ai-portfolio-review/?utm_source=Newsletter&amp;utm_medium=DataDrivenVC&quot;,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;topImage&quot;:true,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F8809b532-7874-4994-9035-45983c354d16_2400x900.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F8809b532-7874-4994-9035-45983c354d16_2400x900.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F8809b532-7874-4994-9035-45983c354d16_2400x900.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F8809b532-7874-4994-9035-45983c354d16_2400x900.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" fetchpriority="high"></picture><div></div></div></a></figure></div><p>Watch this short video to learn how data-driven VCs automate their monthly portfolio performance reviews using ChatGPT, Vestberry, Slack, and Gmail via Make.com! Discover a new way to stay updated on your portfolio's performance and offer support to your portfolio companies when needed, all powered by AI.</p><p class="button-wrapper" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://hello.vestberry.com/ddvc-ai-portfolio-review/?utm_source=Newsletter&amp;utm_medium=DataDrivenVC&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Watch video&quot;,&quot;action&quot;:null,&quot;class&quot;:null}" data-component-name="ButtonCreateButton"><a class="button primary" href="https://hello.vestberry.com/ddvc-ai-portfolio-review/?utm_source=Newsletter&amp;utm_medium=DataDrivenVC"><span>Watch video</span></a></p><div><hr></div><p>Founder compensation benchmarks are among the most clicked links across all our INSIGHTS DIGEST episodes, indicating the importance for founders and investors alike. The problem with many studies, however, is that they only cover partial aspects, rarely painting the full picture. Therefore, the ambition with today‚Äôs episode is to bring it all together and create a comprehensive guide to founder compensation.</p><h2>Why is Founder Compensation so Complicated?</h2><p>Navigating the delicate balance between fair compensation and prudent business practices is no easy feat, especially under the scrutiny of investors. Conflicting expectations about what constitutes a reasonable salary can create significant tension‚Äîinvestors often prioritize runway preservation, while founders need sufficient income to sustain a viable lifestyle.</p><p>It's essential to remember that while lean times are part of the early startup journey, the idea of founders scraping by indefinitely is unrealistic. Founders must secure enough income to alleviate financial stress and maintain focus on building their businesses.</p><p>These challenges are made even more complicated when considering that founders often come from different backgrounds: One might be 25, single, and living in a smaller Spanish city, while another is 45, raising kids in New York City. These different living situations lead to dramatically varying financial needs, and striking the right balance is difficult.</p><p>Transparency around compensation creates trust among employees, investors, and stakeholders. The decisions founders make about their own pay can set the tone for company culture‚Äîtransparent and thoughtful compensation signals fairness and alignment with growth, which can help attract and retain talent.</p><p>In this episode, we‚Äôll look at best practices from scientific literature, and provide a snapshot of the current landscape, using real-world data to help you make informed compensation decisions. </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2 is-viewable-imag" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F6e46d74c-d587-4eb7-b0eb-82ff8bdad2b3_1676x874.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F6e46d74c-d587-4eb7-b0eb-82ff8bdad2b3_1676x874.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F6e46d74c-d587-4eb7-b0eb-82ff8bdad2b3_1676x874.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F6e46d74c-d587-4eb7-b0eb-82ff8bdad2b3_1676x874.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F6e46d74c-d587-4eb7-b0eb-82ff8bdad2b3_1676x874.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F6e46d74c-d587-4eb7-b0eb-82ff8bdad2b3_1676x874.png" width="1456" height="759" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/6e46d74c-d587-4eb7-b0eb-82ff8bdad2b3_1676x874.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:759,&quot;width&quot;:1456,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:459572,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F6e46d74c-d587-4eb7-b0eb-82ff8bdad2b3_1676x874.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F6e46d74c-d587-4eb7-b0eb-82ff8bdad2b3_1676x874.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F6e46d74c-d587-4eb7-b0eb-82ff8bdad2b3_1676x874.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F6e46d74c-d587-4eb7-b0eb-82ff8bdad2b3_1676x874.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a></figure></div><div><hr></div><div><hr></div><h2>Compensation and Equity</h2><p>One of the fundamental trends in startup compensation is the inverse relationship between equity stakes and cash compensation. As founders hold larger equity shares, their cash salaries tend to decrease (Wasserman, <a href="https://journals.aom.org/doi/10.5465/amj.2006.22798177">2006</a>). This dynamic is rooted in the concept of psychological ownership‚Äîequity provides founders with a direct, personal stake in the success of the business, fostering a focus on long-term value rather than short-term gains.</p><p>Equity ownership also aligns founders' interests with those of other shareholders, emphasizing growth and later profitability. Unlike cash compensation, which tends to encourage more conservative decision-making, founders with significant equity are often willing to pursue riskier, innovative strategies, betting on the company‚Äôs future success (Alkebsee et al., <a href="https://www.emerald.com/insight/content/doi/10.1108/JAEE-12-2020-0336/full/html">2021</a>; Atif et al., <a href="https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/abs/pii/S0927538X17303219?via%3Dihub">2020</a>; Bruton et al., <a href="https://journals.sagepub.com/doi/10.1111/j.1540-6520.2009.00309.x">2009</a>). The long-term incentives provided by equity mean that founders are more likely to prioritize visionary moves over short-term financial stability, thereby enhancing the company's potential for substantial growth.</p>\n      <p>\n          <a href="https://www.newsletter.datadrivenvc.io/p/founder-compensation-and-equity-benchmarks">\n              Read more\n          </a>\n      </p>\n   </body></html>	The importance of transparency and the balance between fair compensation and prudent business practices. Inverse relationship between equity stakes and cash compensation - and how equity ownership aligns founders' interests.	2024-10-08 06:01:15	2024-10-14 08:15:49.175	2024-10-14 09:30:45.381	{vc}	https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F6e46d74c-d587-4eb7-b0eb-82ff8bdad2b3_1676x874.png	Andre Retterath	founder-compensation-and-equity
197	https://ravenewworld.substack.com/p/the-politics-of-dancing	THE POLITICS OF DANCING 	Deconstructing toxic techno culture with investigative journalist Annabel Ross	<html><head></head><body><p>Hi sweeties! </p><p>I‚Äôve been following and documenting Singapore‚Äôs secretive<a href="https://ravenewworld.substack.com/p/singapores-neo-pagan-rave-resistance"> underground nightlife</a> and <a href="https://ravenewworld.substack.com/p/singapore-stoner">drug cultures</a> for years, and it‚Äôs been a dream to create a short documentary about my beautiful, weird, and kinda <a href="https://ravenewworld.substack.com/p/singapores-nonsensical-nightlife">fucked-up hometown</a> with some super talented raver-friends. Our 15-minute film is about a queer, cyberpunk rave in the business district of Singapore called <a href="https://www.instagram.com/bussytemple/p/CocJL2OhyIy/?img_index=1">Bussy Temple,</a> and it will debut on October 24th at Canal Projects in New York City. We‚Äôre also gonna screen <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=NtGIKQHlRvU">The Last Year of Darkness</a>‚Äîa documentary that follows a group of DJs, drag queens, and other assorted club kids as their lives revolve around a nightclub in Chengdu, China. It‚Äôs the best depiction of contemporary techno culture I‚Äôve seen in a long time, and I‚Äôm super stoked to share it. </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2 is-viewable-imag" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fae48038a-1bbf-444f-ab1c-640b288ef12d_1244x1067.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fae48038a-1bbf-444f-ab1c-640b288ef12d_1244x1067.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fae48038a-1bbf-444f-ab1c-640b288ef12d_1244x1067.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fae48038a-1bbf-444f-ab1c-640b288ef12d_1244x1067.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fae48038a-1bbf-444f-ab1c-640b288ef12d_1244x1067.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fae48038a-1bbf-444f-ab1c-640b288ef12d_1244x1067.jpeg" width="1244" height="1067" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/ae48038a-1bbf-444f-ab1c-640b288ef12d_1244x1067.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:1067,&quot;width&quot;:1244,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:1388821,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;topImage&quot;:true,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fae48038a-1bbf-444f-ab1c-640b288ef12d_1244x1067.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fae48038a-1bbf-444f-ab1c-640b288ef12d_1244x1067.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fae48038a-1bbf-444f-ab1c-640b288ef12d_1244x1067.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fae48038a-1bbf-444f-ab1c-640b288ef12d_1244x1067.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" fetchpriority="high"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a></figure></div><p>Spots for our event are already overcapacity (lol), but we‚Äôre working on solutions to get everyone in! <a href="https://www.canalprojects.org/library/montez-press-radioo/rave-new-world-singapore-the-last-year-of-darkness-a-screening-on-asia-s-rising-rave-scenes">RSVP here</a>, and if the screening is too lit, you can always just join the afterparty at Montez Press Radio‚Äôs studio a couple blocks away, where DJs will be spinning weirdo tunes and music from the Asian underground. </p><p>PS: We want turn this into a docu-series on raves around the world, particularly in politically fraught and unexpected places. If you can think of a possible collaborator or supporter for this kind of thing, please feel free to forward this on to them! </p><p class="button-wrapper" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://ravenewworld.substack.com/p/the-politics-of-dancing?utm_source=substack&amp;utm_medium=email&amp;utm_content=share&amp;action=share&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Share&quot;,&quot;action&quot;:null,&quot;class&quot;:null}" data-component-name="ButtonCreateButton"><a class="button primary" href="https://ravenewworld.substack.com/p/the-politics-of-dancing?utm_source=substack&amp;utm_medium=email&amp;utm_content=share&amp;action=share"><span>Share</span></a></p><div><hr></div><h2>THE POLITICS OF DANCING </h2><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2 is-viewable-imag" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0ba84e12-a565-41b1-bea1-be36572a598a_1280x720.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0ba84e12-a565-41b1-bea1-be36572a598a_1280x720.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0ba84e12-a565-41b1-bea1-be36572a598a_1280x720.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0ba84e12-a565-41b1-bea1-be36572a598a_1280x720.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0ba84e12-a565-41b1-bea1-be36572a598a_1280x720.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0ba84e12-a565-41b1-bea1-be36572a598a_1280x720.jpeg" width="1280" height="720" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/0ba84e12-a565-41b1-bea1-be36572a598a_1280x720.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:720,&quot;width&quot;:1280,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:78208,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0ba84e12-a565-41b1-bea1-be36572a598a_1280x720.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0ba84e12-a565-41b1-bea1-be36572a598a_1280x720.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0ba84e12-a565-41b1-bea1-be36572a598a_1280x720.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0ba84e12-a565-41b1-bea1-be36572a598a_1280x720.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a></figure></div><p><em>Annabel Ross is an investigative journalist</em> <em>who‚Äôs</em> <em>broken some of the most important stories</em> <em>about sexual assault in the dance music industry</em>. <em>Her reporting has</em> <em>uncovered long trails of rape and assault charges against some of the biggest DJs/producers in the game, including</em> <em><a href="https://mixmag.net/feature/erick-morillo-accusers-stories-arrested-death-dj">Erick Morillo</a>, <a href="https://ra.co/features/3828">Derrick May</a>, and <a href="https://ra.co/features/4325">Kamaal Williams</a>.</em> <em>Annabel recently launched an excellent Substack, called <a href="https://politicsdancingxyz.substack.com/">The Politics of Dancing,</a> which covers the intersection of raves and politics. She recently reached out to me for advice, and I suggested that we just cross-interview each other, because I wanted to know more about her work too‚Äîparticularly what price she‚Äôs paid for speaking up, and the costs it‚Äôs had on her mental health. </em></p><p><em>Annabel ended up sharing some pretty real (and sometimes shocking) details about what goes on behind the scenes of her reporting. We also chatted at length about the recent passing of Jackmaster‚Äîanother dance music giant who faced sexual harassment charges, and whose legacy <a href="https://ra.co/features/4390">many are now struggling with</a>. </em></p><p><em>Check out my convo with Annabel below, and head over to The Politics of Dancing to read her interview of yours truly. (I also recommend reading the rest of her posts‚Äîincluding <a href="https://politicsdancingxyz.substack.com/p/glitter-washing-in-tel-aviv-with">this one</a> on how Tel Aviv‚Äôs nightlife scene has been ‚Äúglitter-washing‚Äù Israel‚Äôs occupation of the West Bank.) As always, thank you for supporting independent journalists like us!! </em></p><p class="button-wrapper" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://ravenewworld.substack.com/subscribe?&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Subscribe now&quot;,&quot;action&quot;:null,&quot;class&quot;:null}" data-component-name="ButtonCreateButton"><a class="button primary" href="https://ravenewworld.substack.com/subscribe?"><span>Subscribe now</span></a></p><p><strong>Michelle: You went viral a couple years ago when Carl Craig got you banned from Movement festival for writing <a href="https://ra.co/features/3780">two</a> <a href="https://ra.co/features/3828">bombshell reports</a> on Derrick May, who was accused of sexual assault by over a dozen women, and is mentor to Craig. Are you still banned from Movement?</strong>&nbsp;</p><p>Annabel: Ugh, god. They did let me go and review it last year, so no, I believe I am no longer banned.&nbsp;</p><p><strong>I thought of your reporting while watching Craig‚Äôs avant-garde jazz set at Movement this year. It was transcendental, but I have such ambivalent feelings. Trying to silence journalists to protect your bro code just reeks of this Detroit techno cabal of powerful men who‚Äôve been historized as icons‚Äîand somehow in this narrative, an idea has emerged that these men are also untouchable, which is dangerous.</strong>&nbsp;</p><p>Look, I understand wanting to protect the myth of Detroit techno. When you start to criticize someone like Derrick May, who is one of the Belleville Three, there is the fear that the whole foundation will crumble. I know there are a lot of people who are rolling their eyes like fuck, can‚Äôt we just enjoy the music? Why do you have to kill the vibe?&nbsp;</p><p><strong>One of the most asinine perspectives of dance music is that it‚Äôs an apolitical, one-love kind of culture. Scooter Braun, the former manager of Ariana Grande and Justin Bieber, produced this <a href="https://www.novaexhibition.com/">immersive art exhibition about the Nova festival attack</a>, where they are displaying bullet-ridden porta-potties taken from the massacre site in Israel, as well as fake voice messages from Hamas terrorists bragging about killing Jews. It‚Äôs currently showing in Los Angeles, and people were protesting outside when it debuted in New York. But Scooter‚Äôs like, ‚Äúthis exhibit is not political.‚Äù He tried to compare Nova festival to Governor‚Äôs Ball or Coachella, and position it as being about music as a universal language. It‚Äôs so dumb, there‚Äôs no way else to put it.&nbsp;</strong></p><p>The Nova exhibition is fucking mental. Grief and mourning is valid, but to turn it into a traveling trauma porn exhibition that functions more as Israeli propaganda than memorial‚Ä¶ it‚Äôs fucking weird.&nbsp;</p><p>As far as the sexual assault stuff goes, I hate that I can no longer enjoy Carl Craig or Derrick May‚Äôs music. I hate that I groan every time I hear ‚ÄúStrings of Life.‚Äù I hate that I haven‚Äôt listened to Omar S voluntarily in three years, especially not after his alleged assault of [Detroit singer/songwriter] <a href="https://www.metrotimes.com/music/detroit-music-scene-blasts-omar-s-following-alleged-assault-on-supercoolwicked-34571600">Supercoolwicked</a>. The number of DJs that I‚Äôve heard things about, whose music I can no longer appreciate‚Ä¶ it‚Äô sucks.&nbsp;</p><p><strong>There's still a lot of fear about speaking out against these people who have the backing of powerful institutions. For example, at Movement, I wanted to interview a Black female DJ and discuss some of the stuff we‚Äôve been talking about. The publicist said no, they can‚Äôt do that, because they‚Äôre playing on Carl Craig‚Äôs stage. How do we tell the full picture if we‚Äôre ignoring key details about what‚Äôs going on behind the scenes?&nbsp;</strong></p><p><strong>But I think there's more public acknowledgement now of the complexity of the techno origin story. There‚Äôs more of a discussion that some of the pioneering DJs were quite homophobic, and the early Detroit techno scene in the 80s came from an upper-middle class milieu that was <a href="https://infinitespeeds.substack.com/p/transcendentental-time-technologies">quite self-conscious </a>about the music not being portrayed as too ‚Äúhood.‚Äù So there was a bit of elitism involved as well.</strong>&nbsp;</p><p>I don‚Äôt know if the complexity of the Detroit techno origin story is widely acknowledged. It‚Äôs become this myth that people are reluctant to dig deeper into. We want the Black innovators to be recognized, and for that not to be taken away from them, but at the same time, there's more to the prevailing story.&nbsp;</p><p><strong>There is a post-woke reckoning in the culture right now‚Äîa bit of a recalibration going on, like let‚Äôs complexify instead of painting everything in a purely identitarian framework.</strong>&nbsp;</p><p>I‚Äôve been thinking about Jackmaster, who passed away over the weekend. There was an outpouring of grief, but it was different to when Erick Morillo died and everyone was posting glowing tributes, ignoring that he was due to face court on rape charges in three days. I still don‚Äôt know exactly what happened with the assault allegations against Jackmaster‚Äîit was pretty murky and handled badly. I‚Äôve heard a couple of other rumors, but I haven‚Äôt spoken to anyone directly so I can‚Äôt confirm anything.&nbsp;</p><p>But we do know that after initially denying his bad behavior at Love Saves The Day in 2018, he eventually owned it and apologized to everyone involved. He went to rehab and seemed to genuinely want to make amends for what he had done, but his career never really recovered. Why people didn‚Äôt go out to bat harder for him, I don‚Äôt know. Maybe there was more to it, or they were worried they‚Äôd be tarred with the same dirty brush for sticking up for him. He had a substance abuse issue long before the 2018 incident, but it can‚Äôt have been easy for him going from being king of the world to being this kind of stained person who fell from grace.&nbsp;</p><p>Now he‚Äôs dead at 38 and that‚Äôs really tragic. If people say sorry and own up to their shit and are genuine about it, I‚Äôm all for rehabilitation and rewarding that kind of accountability. I believe in restorative justice.</p><p><strong>You‚Äôre one of the only journalists doing this kind of investigative work, and I imagine it can be quite lonely sometimes. A lot of journalists don‚Äôt want to write these kinds of articles because they want to hang out backstage and be cool, right? They want to be friends with the artists they love. But once you start doing articles like this, you get banned, you get blacklisted, you get smeared on trashy gossip websites. So you have to give up some of the fun, clout-y things about being a music journalist.&nbsp;</strong></p><p>Fortunately, I've been doing this for a while. I just turned 40. Back in Australia, I was an arts and entertainment reporter and did the whole celebrity thing. When I moved to Paris in 2017 and first started writing about electronic music, I was excited to go to all the festivals and parties. But that fun stuff comes at a cost‚Äîyou get flown to cover a festival, and they expect a good review. That‚Äôs not journalism, that‚Äôs PR. And the more I learned about how things really work and what‚Äôs going on behind the scenes, I was like, well someone needs to talk about this. I think I‚Äôd already had my fun when I first fell into reporting about sexual assault in 2020. And look, as a freelance journalist, it‚Äôs not like I was thriving to begin with. So it‚Äôs sort of like, fuck it, if this means that people will avoid commissioning me for work in some cases, I‚Äôd rather be able to tell the truth.</p><p><strong>Your most recent <a href="https://ra.co/features/4325">investigation into Kamaal Williams,</a> how did that come about?</strong></p><p>I can't go into too much detail, but basically, it was quite a few years ago that I started investigating and speaking to people. There was a roadblock that stymied reporting on it for a while, but the piece that came out for RA found a way around it. After the publication of that piece, I've never had so many women come forward saying that they had a similar experience with this guy. What you read is just the tiniest, tiniest fraction of what's been happening. There are so many details that can't ever be published for various reasons. Kamaal is an example of a serial offender who has been getting away with it for over a decade, and that's largely because the industry has protected him.&nbsp;</p><p><strong>What do you mean by ‚Äúthe industry has protected him‚Äù?</strong></p><p>A big part of the problem are the teams of enablers willing to overlook and minimize bad behavior for the sake of their clients‚Äô career. When I was investigating Derrick May, his female manager at the time sent me all of these crazy explicit photos and videos of women who had allegedly sent them to Derrick. Exactly what she hoped that would achieve, I don‚Äôt know. She knew full well what Derrick was like. So many women in the industry who protect predators, and I‚Äôm just about ready to name them because it makes me sick.&nbsp;</p><p>People have known for years about Derrick May and Kamaal Williams. They heard stories or witnessed something or it happened to their friends. But they continue to support these people, book these people, manage these people, and allow them to enjoy this celebrity status. It‚Äôs all about the money.&nbsp;</p><p>We‚Äôre seeing it now with Diddy. This guy is a fucking monster ‚Äî and he&nbsp; was also very close with both Morillo and Guy Gerber, who, by the way, <a href="https://ra.co/news/78535">has also been accused of rape</a>. Diddy has gotten away with truly depraved, evil things, because no one around him did anything to stop it. In many cases they helped make it happen.&nbsp;</p><p><strong>How do you even go about unpicking such a complex web in the music industry that fosters this kind of complicity? </strong>&nbsp;</p><p>For a long time women were just seen as fair game, because there were so few of us in positions of power in the industry. There are thousands more women and femme DJs today than there were ten years ago.Gender parity and representation does matter. Straight white men are still running things to a large extent. And a lot of women feel that they have to play the game to get ahead and that means not rocking the boat and staying on side with the boys.&nbsp; If there was more diversity, especially in senior positions in the industry, it would encourage a culture that would be less accepting of that kind of thing.&nbsp;</p><p><strong>I saw an interesting take on Twitter that abusers don‚Äôt just groom their victims‚Äîthey groom everyone around them to become reliant on them for favors. It‚Äôs all about power, so that when the allegations come out, people are afraid of toppling this one figure, because it would also reduce their own power.</strong></p><p>That‚Äôs absolutely true. People are generally self-interested ‚Äî just look at Palestine and how few people are willing to speak up about it so as not to risk their careers in any way.&nbsp; Why do men who attain power feel the need to abuse it? I'm not sure. But you do also see that the more fame and money people have, it buys them a lot of protection.&nbsp;</p><p><strong>I want to come back to your mental health, because I‚Äôm confident that doing this work is pretty grueling. Do you feel dispirited, disillusioned, cynical? How do you take care of yourself?</strong>&nbsp;</p><p>I do feel all of those things in waves, yeah. How do I take care of myself? I don't know, probably not very well. Honestly, there have been a couple of times where I‚Äôve just broken down crying hearing these women‚Äôs stories‚Ä¶ I don‚Äôt think most people realize that this trauma can last for years, and sometimes for a lifetime.&nbsp;</p><p>People also don‚Äôt realize the enormous amount of work that goes into investigating and reporting these stories. I‚Äôve been working on a few of them for years, and as a freelancer, I may never get a cent for any time spent on them. So many people come to me for help, but I just can‚Äôt do it all, especially when I‚Äôm not getting paid for 90% of it.&nbsp;</p><p>But it‚Äôs rewarding to be able to help survivors tell their stories in a way that they‚Äôre comfortable with and feel good about. There is a feeling that hopefully all this work won‚Äôt be for nothing, and we‚Äôll start to see some change, even though change is very slow. Sometimes it feels like two steps forward, one step back. Or even one step forward, two steps back.</p><p></p><p></p></body></html>	Singapore's underground nightlife and drug cultures. Documentary about a queer, cyberpunk rave called Bussy Temple.	2024-10-17 11:19:50	2024-10-20 19:37:13.418	2024-10-21 05:57:34.845	{english}	https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0ba84e12-a565-41b1-bea1-be36572a598a_1280x720.jpeg	Michelle Lhooq	the-politics-of
162	https://babyvc.substack.com/p/the-eu-startup-entity-carbon-storing	The EU Startup Entity, Carbon-Storing Construction, Smart Farming, and much more...	What's Up Tech? #195	<html><head></head><body><p>Welcome to our <strong>195th </strong>newsletter, written with üñ§ by <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/annika-bautista-453106168/">Annika Bautista</a> and <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/sarah-luna-mongin/">Sarah Luna Mongin</a></p><pre><code>üîç Topics we'll cover this week</code></pre><ul><li><p><strong>Fundraising &amp; general news from the week</strong>: the biggest AI database for biology, climate-friendly construction material, and the one EU startup entity to rule them all  üëÄ</p></li><li><p><strong>Up-and-coming ventures to watch: </strong>reinventing the humble camera with the latest tech</p></li><li><p><strong>Internships &amp; Job</strong> <strong>offers</strong> of the week </p></li><li><p><strong>In case you missed it: </strong>access our full HealthTech Deep Dive series <a href="https://babyvc.substack.com/p/scaling-and-investing-in-techbio?r=3z1h8j">here</a>!  </p></li></ul><p>Enjoy the read! üíõ</p><pre><code><code>ü§ë Fundraisings of the week</code></code></pre><h3>üå±&nbsp;Basecamp Research is building the ultimate foundational models for biology with Series B funding of $60 million (üá¨üáß)</h3><p>Led by <a href="https://singular.vc/">Singular</a>, <a href="https://basecamp-research.com/">Basecamp Research</a> has just raised <strong>$60 million</strong> <strong>in Series B funding</strong> towards developing ‚Äú<strong>a GPT for Biology</strong>.‚Äù  They believe that the creation of a powerful foundational model can unlock discoveries in areas, such as novel proteins and therapeutics. üíä</p><p>The basis of the company‚Äôs foundational models is their proprietary dataset, which includes 100 times more advanced biological systems than current public databases. They also claim that their BaseFold model<a href="https://techcrunch.com/2024/10/09/basecamp-research-taps-60m-to-build-a-gpt-for-biology/"> can outperform DeepMind‚Äôs AlphaFold 2 </a>in predicting complex proteins. üî¨</p><blockquote><p><a href="https://sifted.eu/articles/basecamp-research-60m-series-b">Basecamp Research Raises $60 million Series B to Scale Its AI-powered Database of Life</a></p></blockquote><div><hr></div><h3>üåæ <strong>xFarm Technologies secures ‚Ç¨36 million in Europe's largest smart farming deal</strong> (üá®üá≠<strong>üáÆüáπ</strong>)</h3><p>Swiss-Italian startup <a href="https://xfarm.ag/en">xFarm Technologies</a> has raised <strong>‚Ç¨36 million in a Series C round</strong> led by <a href="https://partechpartners.com/news/xfarm-technologies-the-european-leader-in-the-digitalisation-of-the-agri-food-sector-raises-36-million">Partech</a>, marking Europe's largest smart farming deal to date. </p><p>With 450,000 farms across Europe already using its digital tools, xFarm helps farmers manage expenses and crops, and integrates sensor and satellite data for high-tech farming. Looking ahead, xFarm plans to <strong>expand into Brazil and India</strong>, while also exploring innovative fintech products like parametric insurance. üë©‚Äçüåæ</p><blockquote><p><a href="https://sifted.eu/articles/xfarm-startup-raise-news">xFarm Raises ‚Ç¨36M to Build Superapp for Farmers&nbsp;</a></p></blockquote><div><hr></div><h3>üå¨Ô∏è <strong>Paebbl raises $25 million Series A to scale CO2-storing building materials</strong>(üá≥üá±)</h3><p><a href="https://paebbl.com/">Paebbl</a>, a company focused on turning captured CO2 into carbon-storing materials for the construction industry, has secured <strong>$25 million in Series A funding</strong>. This funding will help Paebbl scale its efforts in <strong>carbon storage through building materials</strong>, positioning the built environment as a crucial solution to climate change. üå™Ô∏è</p><p>Paebbl, with hubs in Helsinki, Rotterdam, and Stockholm, has already moved from lab tests to a pilot unit producing 250kg of CO2-storing materials daily and aims to ramp up production with a new plant by 2025. The goal is to <strong>sequester</strong> <strong>one ton of CO2 daily</strong>, setting the stage for commercial deployment and sustainable construction worldwide. üåç</p><blockquote><p><a href="https://tech.eu/2024/10/09/paebbl-raises-25m-to-supercharge-carbon-storage-in-the-built-environment/">Paebbl Raises $25M to Supercharge Carbon Storage in the Built Environment</a></p></blockquote><div><hr></div><h3>ü¶æ Tensor Ventures fuels deep tech in Czech Republic with ‚Ç¨50 million fundraise (<strong>üá®üáø</strong>)</h3><p><a href="https://tensor.ventures/">Tensor Ventures</a> announced the launch of its new fund worth <strong>‚Ç¨50 million</strong>. The <a href="https://www.eif.org/index.htm">European Investment Fund</a>, one of the most influential funds in Europe, is one of their key investors, contributing ‚Ç¨20 million. Their primary focus will be in <strong>deep tech areas</strong> such as quantum technologies, biotech, and climate tech. Half of the fund will be invested in Czech startups, while the rest will be on global ventures.  </p><p>Their previous fund <a href="https://startupkitchen.community/new-tensor-ventures-fund-targets-size-of-eur-50-million-giving-investors-access-to-the-most-attractive-deep-tech-startups-in-the-czech-republic-and-beyond/">had two notable acquisitions</a> ‚Äî UltimateSuite (process mining startup), acquired by <a href="https://www.servicenow.com/">ServiceNow</a>, and Neuronix AI (AI-based computer vision startup), acquired by <a href="https://www.microchip.com/">Microchip Technology</a>. üí∞</p><blockquote><p><a href="https://tech.eu/2024/10/11/tensor-ventures-launches-eur50m-fund-a-boost-for-quantum-biotech-and-climate-tech-startups/">Tensor Ventures Launches ‚Ç¨50 million Fund: A Boost for Quantum, Biotech, and Climatetech Startups</a></p></blockquote><pre><code><code>üî• Up-and-coming startups to watch</code></code></pre><h3><strong>üì∏&nbsp;Muybridge is set to change the game of computer vision and cameras with new fundraise of ‚Ç¨8 million (üá≥üá¥)</strong></h3><p><a href="https://www.muybridge.com/">Muybridge</a> is advancing computer vision tech with <a href="https://thenextweb.com/news/norwegian-startup-muybridge-funding-software-defined-camera">an innovative ‚Äúvirtual camera‚Äù system</a>, made up of multiple small sensors and adaptive software. This compact system <strong>can simulate different perspectives</strong> without the need for physical adjustments. </p><p>The funding round was led by <a href="https://fairpoint.se/">Fairpoint Capital</a>. The funds will be used to expand product offerings, partner engagement, and grow their workforce, particularly in marketing and sales roles. üôã‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è</p><blockquote><p><a href="https://www.finsmes.com/2024/10/muybridge-raises-e8m-in-funding.html">Muybridge Raises ‚Ç¨8 million in Funding </a></p></blockquote><pre><code>üì∞ News of the week</code></pre><h3>üëÄ&nbsp;A big week for Elon: Tesla Cybercab reveal and SpaceX reusable rocket test</h3><p>It was a big test for Elon Musk last week. The Tesla We, Robot event featured one of the most anticipated announcements ‚Äî the <a href="https://www.largus.fr/actualite-automobile/tesla-cybercab-et-robovan-voici-les-voiture-et-bus-autonomes-promis-pour-2026-30036502.html">Tesla Cybercab</a>, a self-driving taxi expected to launch before 2027 for under $30,000. üöï</p><p>Meanwhile, millions of people streamed as SpaceX successfully caught Starship, the <strong>first reusable megarocket booster</strong>, after a test flight. This engineering milestone could be pivotal news for space travel. Over a decade later, SpaceX is shaping up to be a formidable leader in rocket flight, now <a href="https://www.science.org/content/article/spacex-now-dominates-rocket-flight-bringing-big-benefits-and-risks-nasa">powering two-thirds of NASA‚Äôs launches</a>. üöÄ</p><blockquote><p><a href="https://techcrunch.com/storyline/tesla-robotaxi-event-follow-elon-musks-big-reveals-here/">Tesla We, Robot Event: Everything Elon Musk Just Showed, including the Cybercab, Robovan, and More</a></p><p><a href="https://www.bbc.com/news/videos/ce3zek7xqk4o">Watch: Why is the Latest Space X Rocket Test a Big Deal?</a></p></blockquote><div><hr></div><h3>üë©‚Äçüíª <strong>Mountside Ventures creates an accelerator to transform fundraising for emerging VCs</strong></h3><p><a href="https://www.mountsideventures.com/">Mountside Ventures</a> has announced the launch of its inaugural VC accelerator program aimed at <strong>empowering emerging VC managers in Europe</strong>. The program seeks to address the significant funding gap faced by new and developing VC firms, which have proven to be top performers in the asset class, <a href="https://tech.eu/2024/10/14/mountside-ventures-pioneers-vc-accelerator-programme-for-early-stage-managers/">accounting for 72% of the best-returning funds.</a></p><p>With applications now open for its first cohort scheduled to begin in Q1 2025, this initiative aims to tackle the challenges associated with fundraising in the venture capital space by offering a comprehensive package that includes <strong>workshops</strong>, <strong>connections</strong> to Limited Partners (LPs), and <strong>mentorship</strong> tailored for VCs raising their Funds. ü§ù</p><blockquote><p><a href="https://sifted.eu/articles/europe-vc-accelerator-mountside">Europe‚Äôs First Accelerator for VCs Launches</a></p></blockquote><div><hr></div><h3>üöÄ <strong>European scaleups and VCs call for a unified legal entity to enhance startup growth</strong></h3><p>Leading European scaleups and venture capital firms have signed an open letter advocating for the creation of a new pan-European legal entity named ‚Äú<a href="https://www.eu-inc.org/">EU Inc.</a>‚Äù </p><p>This initiative aims to <strong>simplify operations for startups</strong> by providing a single set of business rules applicable across all 27 EU countries. Prominent supporters include founders of companies like <a href="https://www.deepl.com/en/translator">DeepL</a>, <a href="https://www.pigment.com/">Pigment</a> and <a href="https://wise.com/">Wise</a>, as well as GPs from <a href="https://seedcamp.com/">Seedcamp </a>and <a href="https://www.indexventures.com/">Index Ventures</a>.</p><p>The proposed ‚ÄúEU Inc‚Äù entity seeks to standardize investment processes, streamline cross-border operations, and create a unified framework for employee stock options. </p><blockquote><p><a href="https://sifted.eu/articles/deepl-personio-index-seedcamp-europe-business-laws">DeepL, Personio, Index, Seedcamp Call for Sweeping Reform to Pan-European Business Laws</a></p></blockquote><pre><code><code>üëî Internships &amp; job offers</code></code></pre><h3>Internships</h3><p>Investment &amp; Deal Flow Analyst - <strong>Station F </strong>(Paris)</p><blockquote><p><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/view/4046169272/">‚û§&nbsp;Job  desc.</a></p></blockquote><p>Visiting Analyst - <strong>PT1 </strong>(Berlin)</p><blockquote><p><a href="https://jcrml3owcx0.typeform.com/to/D5xWrNXL?typeform-source=www.linkedin.com">‚û§&nbsp;Job  desc.</a></p></blockquote><p>Growth Intern - <strong>Revyze </strong>(Paris)</p><blockquote><p><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/view/4047586228/">‚û§&nbsp;Job  desc.</a></p></blockquote><p></p><h3>Jobs</h3><p>Investment Manager / Principal - <strong>PT1 </strong>(Berlin)</p><blockquote><p><a href="https://join.com/companies/proptech1/12660958-investment-manager-principal-m-f-d?utm_source=venturecapitalcareers">‚û§&nbsp;Job desc.</a></p></blockquote><p>Investment Manager - <strong>Wellington Partners Life Sciences</strong> (Munich)</p><blockquote><p><a href="https://join.com/companies/wellington-partners/12579004-investment-manager-f-m-d-wellington-partners-life-sciences?utm_source=venturecapitalcareers">‚û§&nbsp;Job desc.</a></p></blockquote><p>Product Marketing Manager - <strong>Lovable</strong> (Paris)</p><blockquote><p><a href="https://lovable.dev/careers/product-marketing-manager/">‚û§&nbsp;Job desc.</a></p></blockquote><pre><code><code>üëÄ In case you missed it</code></code></pre><p>üß™ Our HealthTech Deep Dive series is over.. but  don‚Äôt worry if you missed it! Check them out here:</p><p>ü©∫ <a href="https://babyvc.substack.com/p/scaling-and-investing-in-digital?r=9bzuc">Digital Health newsletter</a></p><p>üíä <a href="https://babyvc.substack.com/p/investing-in-therapeutic-ventures?r=9bzuc">Therapeutics newsletter</a></p><p>üè• <a href="https://babyvc.substack.com/p/investing-in-medical-technology?r=9bzuc">MedTech newsletter</a></p><p>üî¨ <a href="https://babyvc.substack.com/p/scaling-and-investing-in-techbio?r=9bzuc">TechBio newsletter</a></p><div><hr></div><p>üëâ If you‚Äôd like to discover more internship &amp; job offers, you can check our LinkedIn Fridays‚Äô post<strong><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/posts/babyvc_heres-a-list-of-the-latest-vc-and-startup-activity-7247847955871756288-ADYo?utm_source=share&amp;utm_medium=member_desktop"> here</a></strong>!</p><p>You can also read more about baby vc on <strong><a href="https://www.babyvc.co/">our website</a></strong> and follow our updates on <strong><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/company/30734593/">LinkedIn</a></strong>, or directly reach out to us at <strong>hello@baby-vc.co</strong>! ü§ù</p><h4></h4><p>The whole baby vc crew üñ§</p><p></p><p class="button-wrapper" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://babyvc.substack.com/subscribe?&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Subscribe now&quot;,&quot;action&quot;:null,&quot;class&quot;:null}" data-component-name="ButtonCreateButton"><a class="button primary" href="https://babyvc.substack.com/subscribe?"><span>Subscribe now</span></a></p><p class="button-wrapper" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://babyvc.substack.com/p/the-eu-startup-entity-carbon-storing/comments&quot;,&quot;text&quot;: