188	https://www.eu.vc/p/going-public-ep-1-with-evercores	üé• Going Public Ep. 1 with Evercore's Glenn Schorr	by Michael Sidgmore, Co-founder & Partner at Broadhaven Ventures. | Originally published on Alt Goes Mainstream.	<html><head></head><body><p>Guest post by <a href="https://email.mg-d0.substack.com/c/eJxUkDmO3DAURE9DZiOIuxQwcKJrCJ_kl5oYLg0u3ZjbG20ndlZAoR4eysPAu7YfezXErzcmXzPSYLWASwWKlhm2C6aYNhQzxHTeWLDBwHDC-KdVu6EP6wB1MDuwDbzym1hBaXEZNCC8vpyn0fKVy1VzxZjgUi9i2VaptZQ7A3fBpsTSX74atlUi13x_hXXp0_UB_nvxNdPYz4_rx8WONpEm-xjj2Yn4RfhB-PF-v5cUyzeGWD4Lwo9YCD9y9A_A1GO4c21I-EGf052-5jxLHD8nFnAJw1_qc7oUPYxYyxmD5UJvu6HNPmG06CMQueJcXp726ULNEIuFNO6K_ZP7aAiZjv9vnR3bHxgXWnGzS_qy_HcAAAD__6khfxA">Michael</a><strong><a href="https://email.mg-d0.substack.com/c/eJxUkDmO3DAURE9DZiOIuxQwcKJrCJ_kl5oYLg0u3ZjbG20ndlZAoR4eysPAu7YfezXErzcmXzPSYLWASwWKlhm2C6aYNhQzxHTeWLDBwHDC-KdVu6EP6wB1MDuwDbzym1hBaXEZNCC8vpyn0fKVy1VzxZjgUi9i2VaptZQ7A3fBpsTSX74atlUi13x_hXXp0_UB_nvxNdPYz4_rx8WONpEm-xjj2Yn4RfhB-PF-v5cUyzeGWD4Lwo9YCD9y9A_A1GO4c21I-EGf052-5jxLHD8nFnAJw1_qc7oUPYxYyxmD5UJvu6HNPmG06CMQueJcXp726ULNEIuFNO6K_ZP7aAiZjv9vnR3bHxgXWnGzS_qy_HcAAAD__6khfxA"> </a></strong><a href="https://email.mg-d0.substack.com/c/eJxUkDmO3DAURE9DZiOIuxQwcKJrCJ_kl5oYLg0u3ZjbG20ndlZAoR4eysPAu7YfezXErzcmXzPSYLWASwWKlhm2C6aYNhQzxHTeWLDBwHDC-KdVu6EP6wB1MDuwDbzym1hBaXEZNCC8vpyn0fKVy1VzxZjgUi9i2VaptZQ7A3fBpsTSX74atlUi13x_hXXp0_UB_nvxNdPYz4_rx8WONpEm-xjj2Yn4RfhB-PF-v5cUyzeGWD4Lwo9YCD9y9A_A1GO4c21I-EGf052-5jxLHD8nFnAJw1_qc7oUPYxYyxmD5UJvu6HNPmG06CMQueJcXp726ULNEIuFNO6K_ZP7aAiZjv9vnR3bHxgXWnGzS_qy_HcAAAD__6khfxA">Sidgmore</a>, Co-founder &amp; Partner at <a href="https://email.mg-d0.substack.com/c/eJxUkLuu3SAURL_GdBfxxhQUac5vWNuw7YNijMXD1v376CRNbjfSaEZLK0DHvdRvv1XErwePUDKS6I2ETUeCnlvuJNfcWIIZ0rHseGKFjnGB_l-rnSVvL2fFtOabsEKiicZuoFx0YJwwwLQjyQsmFDNCcy6FMlTSmSljlHIc1g1mLWm7Q7F8LpNief-KjLaxtg7hNw0lk9SWD-uHxfc6kBz-3fvVJvlrEq9JvJ7noWstEN9w40nvMIkXuca6hJLzOFP_XvCE9cD4b3-N9UgBeirnkqIX0szOkuov6DWFBJNiOOgdSBtrLBnS6eHoe8H2ya1XhEz6T4GjYf17JqTRwjpFbi_-BAAA__-R9HXH">Broadhaven Ventures</a>. | Originally published on <a href="https://altgoesmainstream.substack.com/p/going-public-ep-1-with-evercores">Alt Goes Mainstream</a>.</p><div><hr></div><p>Today marks the launch of a new show on Alt Goes Mainstream: Going Public with <a href="https://www.evercore.com/our-business-and-capabilities/equities/research/">Evercore</a>‚Äôs <a href="https://www.evercore.com/team/glenn-schorr/">Glenn Schorr</a>.</p><p>17 years ago, there wasn‚Äôt a single alternative asset manager that was part of the public markets. Today, not only are a number of the industry‚Äôs largest firms public, but in 2024, the industry‚Äôs largest alternative asset manager, Blackstone, entered the S&amp;P 500.</p><div><hr></div><p class="button-wrapper" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/going-public-ep-1-with-evercores-glenn-schorr/id1556172088?i=1000672380384&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Listen on Apple Podcasts&quot;,&quot;action&quot;:null,&quot;class&quot;:&quot;button-wrapper&quot;}" data-component-name="ButtonCreateButton"><a class="button primary button-wrapper" href="https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/going-public-ep-1-with-evercores-glenn-schorr/id1556172088?i=1000672380384"><span>Listen on Apple Podcasts</span></a></p><p class="button-wrapper" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://open.spotify.com/episode/3WFtOmk7YBWuP8E0i6jEKD?si=3ca5d9defb694051&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Listen on Spotify&quot;,&quot;action&quot;:null,&quot;class&quot;:&quot;button-wrapper&quot;}" data-component-name="ButtonCreateButton"><a class="button primary button-wrapper" href="https://open.spotify.com/episode/3WFtOmk7YBWuP8E0i6jEKD?si=3ca5d9defb694051"><span>Listen on Spotify</span></a></p><p class="button-wrapper" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://share.transistor.fm/s/ddbe0905&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Listen on Transistor&quot;,&quot;action&quot;:null,&quot;class&quot;:&quot;button-wrapper&quot;}" data-component-name="ButtonCreateButton"><a class="button primary button-wrapper" href="https://share.transistor.fm/s/ddbe0905"><span>Listen on Transistor</span></a></p><div><hr></div><p>Just ten years ago, alternative asset managers accounted for only a small portion of financial services market capitalization in public markets, representing 4% of the $2.3T 2014 aggregated market cap figure in 2014. Today, the publicly traded alternative asset managers represent 12% of the current $3.4T financial services market capitalization, a 5x increase from 2014, as this chart from <a href="https://d1io3yog0oux5.cloudfront.net/_d615dfa3849eb15910c0b7a177cde5b6/apollo/db/2224/21725/pdf/Apollo+2024+Investor+Day+Presentation+.pdf">Apollo‚Äôs recent Investor Day </a>illustrates.</p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2 is-viewable-imag" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fbe94c9ed-7b83-4047-b3d6-1360a26057a5_2056x1158.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fbe94c9ed-7b83-4047-b3d6-1360a26057a5_2056x1158.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fbe94c9ed-7b83-4047-b3d6-1360a26057a5_2056x1158.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fbe94c9ed-7b83-4047-b3d6-1360a26057a5_2056x1158.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fbe94c9ed-7b83-4047-b3d6-1360a26057a5_2056x1158.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fbe94c9ed-7b83-4047-b3d6-1360a26057a5_2056x1158.png" width="518" height="291.7307692307692" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/be94c9ed-7b83-4047-b3d6-1360a26057a5_2056x1158.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:820,&quot;width&quot;:1456,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:518,&quot;bytes&quot;:null,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:null,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:true,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" title="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fbe94c9ed-7b83-4047-b3d6-1360a26057a5_2056x1158.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fbe94c9ed-7b83-4047-b3d6-1360a26057a5_2056x1158.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fbe94c9ed-7b83-4047-b3d6-1360a26057a5_2056x1158.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fbe94c9ed-7b83-4047-b3d6-1360a26057a5_2056x1158.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy" fetchpriority="high"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a></figure></div><p>Understanding the inner workings, strategic moves, and financial performance of the industry‚Äôs largest players can help to explain many of the trends that are making alternatives become mainstream and why these firms are becoming mainstays in the financial services ecosystem.</p><h4>Making private markets more public ‚Äî with expert analysis</h4><p>To do this, Alt Goes Mainstream has partnered with an expert who has seen the evolution of alternative asset managers from their early days.</p><p><a href="https://www.evercore.com/team/glenn-schorr/">Glenn Schorr</a> is a Senior MD and Senior Research Analyst at <a href="https://www.evercore.com/our-business-and-capabilities/equities/research/">Evercore ISI</a>, where he covers brokers, banks, asset managers, and trust banks as an analyst.</p><p>He has covered financials since 2000 and started coverage of alternative asset managers when the first firms went public.</p><p>He‚Äôs consistently come up as one of the most thoughtful and well-respected analysts in the space. He balances deep research with a creative flair (just read one of the titles of his research reports and you can see his love of the game). He‚Äôs been named to <em>Institutional Investor‚Äôs</em> All-America Research Team for his coverage, most recently ranking #2 and runner up in 2023, #1 and #2 in 2022. Prior to Evercore, Glenn was a Senior MD at Nomura, serving as the lead financials analyst.</p><p>Listen in as Glenn shares market stories, the evolution of alternative asset managers as businesses, the biggest and most exciting trends in private markets based on what the industry‚Äôs largest players are doing, and we go ‚Äúaround the horn‚Äù for his analysis on the publicly traded firms.&nbsp;</p><p>I‚Äôm excited to launch this new show with Glenn as we make private markets more public.</p><p><em>Note: This episode was recorded shortly after Q2 earnings came out.</em></p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2 is-viewable-imag" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F4f4af6a4-0e46-42f0-a7b3-da3ceed58364_1024x512.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F4f4af6a4-0e46-42f0-a7b3-da3ceed58364_1024x512.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F4f4af6a4-0e46-42f0-a7b3-da3ceed58364_1024x512.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F4f4af6a4-0e46-42f0-a7b3-da3ceed58364_1024x512.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F4f4af6a4-0e46-42f0-a7b3-da3ceed58364_1024x512.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F4f4af6a4-0e46-42f0-a7b3-da3ceed58364_1024x512.png" width="1024" height="512" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/4f4af6a4-0e46-42f0-a7b3-da3ceed58364_1024x512.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:512,&quot;width&quot;:1024,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:121612,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" title="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F4f4af6a4-0e46-42f0-a7b3-da3ceed58364_1024x512.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F4f4af6a4-0e46-42f0-a7b3-da3ceed58364_1024x512.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F4f4af6a4-0e46-42f0-a7b3-da3ceed58364_1024x512.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F4f4af6a4-0e46-42f0-a7b3-da3ceed58364_1024x512.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a></figure></div><h4>Show Notes</h4><ul><li><p>00:38 Introduction to the Going Public Series and award-winning Wall Street Analyst, Glenn Schorr</p></li><li><p>01:54 Glenn's Career Journey</p></li><li><p>03:08 The Early Days of Alts Managers Going Public</p></li><li><p>03:26 Skepticism and Challenges in Going Public</p></li><li><p>04:06 Investor Skepticism and Challenges</p></li><li><p>07:00 Transformation and Tipping Points</p></li><li><p>09:03 Structural Tailwinds and Market Trends</p></li><li><p>10:57 The Decision to Go Public vs. Staying Private</p></li><li><p>12:39 Ambition and Vision in Asset Management</p></li><li><p>14:51 The Distribution vs. Manufacturing Debate</p></li><li><p>17:03 Lessons from Traditional Asset Management</p></li><li><p>18:55 Discipline and Growth in the Alts Market</p></li><li><p>20:03 The Future of Public and Private Markets</p></li><li><p>20:50 The Role of Distribution in Asset Management</p></li><li><p>21:59 Success Stories and Acquisition Strategies</p></li><li><p>23:02 Manufacturing Competency vs. Acquisitions</p></li><li><p>24:40 The Rise of Private Markets</p></li><li><p>26:07 How Alternative Managers Make Money</p></li><li><p>27:02 Valuation Factors for Alternative Managers</p></li><li><p>28:44 Profitability and Margins in Asset Management</p></li><li><p>29:23 Building a Business: Costs and Competitive Advantages</p></li><li><p>29:50 The Moat of Success in Business</p></li><li><p>30:15 Challenges for Traditional Asset Managers</p></li><li><p>30:56 The Importance of Vision and Technology</p></li><li><p>31:22 Scaling a Business with Proven Success</p></li><li><p>31:40 Insurance Asset Management: Strategic Moves and Structural Advantages</p></li><li><p>32:17 Structural Advantages in Asset Management</p></li><li><p>33:05 The Rise of Private Credit Managers</p></li><li><p>34:43 The Impact of Interest Rates on Private Credit Managers</p></li><li><p>35:32 Navigating Rate Sensitivity in Capital Markets</p></li><li><p>38:25 Deployment and Monetization in Asset Management</p></li><li><p>39:08 The Challenge of Dry Powder in Private Equity</p></li><li><p>41:14 The Role of Deployment in Investment Success</p></li><li><p>41:46 The Resilience of Publicly Traded Alts Managers</p></li><li><p>43:26 Spotlight on Blackstone's Growth and Innovation</p></li><li><p>46:38 KKR's Global Expansion and Innovation</p></li><li><p>48:41 Apollo's Market Leadership and Challenges</p></li><li><p>50:11 Blue Owl's Strategic Investments and Challenges</p></li><li><p>53:56 TPG's Public Transition and Growth</p></li><li><p>55:11 Carlyle‚Äôs Progress and Future Challenges</p></li><li><p>56:11 Looking Ahead: Key Trends and Expectations</p></li></ul><div><hr></div><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc2e93607-5191-4afb-b94b-51d0b094363e_1100x220.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc2e93607-5191-4afb-b94b-51d0b094363e_1100x220.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc2e93607-5191-4afb-b94b-51d0b094363e_1100x220.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc2e93607-5191-4afb-b94b-51d0b094363e_1100x220.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc2e93607-5191-4afb-b94b-51d0b094363e_1100x220.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc2e93607-5191-4afb-b94b-51d0b094363e_1100x220.png" width="1100" height="220" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/c2e93607-5191-4afb-b94b-51d0b094363e_1100x220.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:220,&quot;width&quot;:1100,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:60754,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" title="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc2e93607-5191-4afb-b94b-51d0b094363e_1100x220.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc2e93607-5191-4afb-b94b-51d0b094363e_1100x220.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc2e93607-5191-4afb-b94b-51d0b094363e_1100x220.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc2e93607-5191-4afb-b94b-51d0b094363e_1100x220.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div></div></div></a><figcaption class="image-caption"><strong>Wanna be featured on eu.vc? Learn how <a href="https://www.eu.vc/p/submit-your-contribution-to-unfiltered">here.</a></strong></figcaption></figure></div></body></html>	Alternative asset managers are becoming mainstream, with a growing presence in public markets. The industry has seen a 5x increase in market capitalization since 2014, now representing 12% of the financial services market.	2024-10-16 23:11:55	2024-10-20 19:35:24.794	2024-10-21 05:58:33.887	{vc}	https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F4f4af6a4-0e46-42f0-a7b3-da3ceed58364_1024x512.png	anon	going-public-ep-1-with
161	https://thevccorner.substack.com/p/a-collection-of-the-best-89-vc-and	A Collection of the Best 89 VC and Founder Essays 	For this week's edition, I‚Äôve curated a collection of the best essays on startups, written by the most respected founders and venture capitalists worldwide.	<html><head></head><body><p>For this week's edition, I‚Äôve curated a collection of the best essays on startups, written by the most respected founders and venture capitalists worldwide.</p><p>Starting, executing, and scaling a startup is anything but a ride in the park, and learning from those who have been in the trenches (and come out on top) is a great way to keep inspired and get insights on what it takes to make a startup successful.</p><p>I‚Äôve divided the collection into five categories:</p><ol><li><p><strong>Startup Ideation and Execution</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>Fundraising and Investor Relations</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>Scaling and Growth</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>Team and Culture</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>Failure and Lessons Learned</strong></p></li></ol><p>Each of these categories has a variety of essays by the featured authors listed below, some of which are the co-founders of Y Combinator, PayPal, LinkedIn, and tier-one VCs like Vinod Khosla and Garry Tan. If there‚Äôs anyone to learn from - it‚Äôs these guys!</p><p>I hope you enjoy this curated collection and that it helps you on your startup journey.</p><h1>Featured authors:</h1><ol><li><p><strong>Paul Graham</strong></p><p>Paul Graham is a co-founder of Y Combinator.</p></li><li><p><strong>Jessica Livingston</strong></p><p>Jessica Livingston is a co-founder of Y Combinator and author of <em>Founders at Work</em>.</p></li><li><p><strong>Naval Ravikant</strong></p><p>Naval Ravikant is the co-founder of AngelList and a prolific investor in startups like Twitter and Uber.</p></li><li><p><strong>Michael Seibel</strong></p><p>Michael Seibel is a Managing Director at Y Combinator and former CEO of both <a href="http://Justin.tv">Justin.tv</a> (which became Twitch) and Socialcam.</p></li><li><p><strong>Balaji Srinivasan</strong></p><p>Balaji Srinivasan is a former CTO of Coinbase, General Partner at Andreessen Horowitz, and co-founder of startups like Counsyl.</p></li><li><p><strong>Vinod Khosla</strong></p><p>Vinod Khosla is the founder of Khosla Ventures and a co-founder of Sun Microsystems.</p></li><li><p><strong>Sam Altman</strong></p><p>Sam Altman is the former president of Y Combinator and the current CEO of OpenAI.</p></li><li><p><strong>Marc Andreessen</strong></p><p>Marc Andreessen is the co-founder of Andreessen Horowitz, a leading VC firm, and a pioneer in the tech industry, known for co-creating the Mosaic web browser and co-founding Netscape.</p></li><li><p><strong>Garry Tan</strong></p><p>Garry Tan is the co-founder of Initialized Capital and a former partner at Y Combinator.</p></li><li><p><strong>Andrew Chen</strong></p><p>Andrew Chen is a General Partner at Andreessen Horowitz and has deep expertise in growth marketing. He previously led growth at Uber.</p></li><li><p><strong>Peter Thiel</strong> ‚Äì Peter Thiel is the co-founder of PayPal and Palantir. He is known for being an early investor in Facebook.</p></li><li><p><strong>Chris Dixon</strong> ‚Äì A general partner at Andreessen Horowitz, Chris Dixon focuses on investments in crypto, Web3, and emerging technologies. He is also known for co-founding Hunch and SiteAdvisor.</p></li><li><p><strong>Reid Hoffman</strong> ‚Äì Co-founder of LinkedIn and a partner at Greylock Partners, Reid Hoffman is a prominent VC who has invested in Airbnb and Facebook.</p></li><li><p><strong>Fred Wilson</strong> ‚Äì A well-known VC and managing partner at Union Square Ventures, Fred Wilson has invested in companies like Twitter, Tumblr, and Etsy.</p></li><li><p><strong>Keith Rabois</strong> ‚Äì A VC and entrepreneur, Keith Rabois is known for his roles in companies like PayPal, LinkedIn, and Square, and is currently a general partner at Founders Fund.</p></li><li><p><strong>Brian Chesky</strong> - Co-founder of Airbnb</p></li></ol><h1>A Collection of 89 Essays üëá</h1><p class="button-wrapper" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://thevccorner.substack.com/subscribe?coupon=6e5adce2&amp;utm_content=150302502&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Get 25% off forever&quot;,&quot;action&quot;:null,&quot;class&quot;:null}" data-component-name="ButtonCreateButton"><a class="button primary" href="https://thevccorner.substack.com/subscribe?coupon=6e5adce2&amp;utm_content=150302502"><span>Get 25% off forever</span></a></p>\n      <p>\n          <a href="https://thevccorner.substack.com/p/a-collection-of-the-best-89-vc-and">\n              Read more\n          </a>\n      </p>\n   </body></html>	This curated collection features the best essays on startups by respected founders and venture capitalists, covering ideation, fundraising, scaling, team, and lessons learned.	2024-10-16 11:42:29	2024-10-16 14:47:15.613	2024-10-16 14:52:53.735	{vc}	https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/24c4e9ae-31e7-415c-895a-de75dffeb417_1200x1500.png	Ruben Dominguez Ibar	a-collection-of-the-best-89-vc
164	https://parsers.substack.com/p/parsers-vc-weekly-funding-startup-838	Parsers VC - Weekly Funding / Startup / VC news of October 15, 2024	Venture Capital News. Funding rounds, statistics Week of October 8 - October 14: United States (40 - $4.47B), United Kingdom (4 - $296M), India (5 - $694M)	<html><head></head><body><h2>Most Popular Venture Capital News</h2><h3>1. <a href="https://parsers.vc/news/241008-the-uk-s-bold-leap-into-cultivated-meat--a/?utm_source=newsletter.parsers.vc&amp;utm_medium=newsletter&amp;utm_campaign=parsers-vc-weekly-funding-startup-vc-news-of-october-15-2024&amp;_bhlid=bac25b9c3f580127b50d11a1731af5da1636d3ba">The UK‚Äôs Bold Leap into Cultivated Meat: A Regulatory Revolution </a></h3><p><em>(Cited in 16 tech media)</em></p><p>The UK government is stepping into the future of food with a ¬£1.6 million investment aimed at revolutionizing the cultivated meat industry. This move is not just a financial commitment; it‚Äôs a declaration of intent. The establishment of a regulatory ‚Äòsandbox‚Äô signals a new era for food innovation, where safety meets creativity.<br>In the wake of Brexit, the UK is eager to carve out its niche in the global food landscape. The newly created sandbox by the Food Standards Agency (FSA) is designed to accelerate the approval process for cultivated meat products. This initiative is crucial. It aims to streamline regulations that have historically stifled innovation. The sandbox will provide a controlled environment for startups and researchers to test their products, ensuring safety while fostering creativity.</p><h3>2. <a href="https://parsers.vc/news/241009-oil-prices-surge-amid-middle-east-tensions/?utm_source=newsletter.parsers.vc&amp;utm_medium=newsletter&amp;utm_campaign=parsers-vc-weekly-funding-startup-vc-news-of-october-15-2024&amp;_bhlid=2e71fc0c2248d95a71392b00a9eec141a4203346">Oil Prices Surge Amid Middle East Tensions: A Ripple Effect on Global Markets</a>&nbsp;</h3><p><em>(Cited in 14 tech media)</em></p><p>Oil prices are like a pendulum, swinging wildly with the winds of geopolitical conflict. Recently, they surged, marking the largest weekly gains in over a year. The catalyst? Escalating tensions in the Middle East. The threat of a regional war looms large, sending ripples through global markets.<br>On October 8, 2024, Brent crude futures climbed by 43 cents, settling at $78.05 per barrel. Meanwhile, US West Texas Intermediate (WTI) crude rose by 67 cents, closing at $74.38 per barrel. These figures tell a story of uncertainty and speculation, where every tick in price reflects the pulse of global politics.<br>The backdrop of this surge is a volatile situation involving Israel and Iran. Israel's vow to retaliate against Iran after a missile attack has sent shockwaves through the oil market. This retaliation follows the assassination of a Hezbollah leader, a move that has escalated tensions further. Analysts are sounding alarms, warning of potential consequences if the conflict widens.</p><h3>3. <a href="https://parsers.vc/news/241010-the-double-edged-sword-of-ai-in-innovation/?utm_source=newsletter.parsers.vc&amp;utm_medium=newsletter&amp;utm_campaign=parsers-vc-weekly-funding-startup-vc-news-of-october-15-2024&amp;_bhlid=6866cb7ba752d31d289bed7d545c99b782e0e69f">The Double-Edged Sword of AI in Innovation and Security</a><a href="https://parsers.vc/news/240419-uniqus-consultech--a-rising-star-in-the/?utm_source=newsletter.parsers.vc&amp;utm_medium=newsletter&amp;utm_campaign=parsers-vc-weekly-funding-startup-vc-news-of-october-15-2024&amp;_bhlid=92fa1cd119f1c298bc7ea7af4431fc889df09c31"> </a></h3><p><em>(Cited in 13 tech media)</em></p><p>Artificial Intelligence (AI) is a double-edged sword. On one side, it fuels innovation, sparking creativity and new ideas. On the other, it raises significant security concerns, especially in software development. Recent studies reveal a complex landscape where AI's potential is both celebrated and scrutinized.<br>A study by Wazoku and King‚Äôs Business School shows that 85% of global innovators are using Generative AI (GenAI) for research and learning. This statistic is not just a number; it reflects a seismic shift in how ideas are generated. Almost half of the surveyed innovators reported using GenAI to craft innovative solutions over the past year. The Wazoku Crowd, a diverse network of 700,000 problem solvers, includes scientists, engineers, and business leaders. Their collective intelligence is harnessed to tackle challenges posed by major enterprises like NASA and AstraZeneca.</p><h3>4. <a href="https://parsers.vc/news/241008-crypto-showdown--crypto-com-takes-on-the/?utm_source=newsletter.parsers.vc&amp;utm_medium=newsletter&amp;utm_campaign=parsers-vc-weekly-funding-startup-vc-news-of-october-15-2024&amp;_bhlid=abc66a2f65bc599e7ddcbe16de9ff6424ecdae97">Crypto Showdown: Crypto.com Takes on the SEC</a>&nbsp;</h3><p><em>(Cited in 13 tech media)</em></p><p>In the world of cryptocurrency, battles are fought not just in the market but in the courtroom. The latest skirmish involves Crypto.com, a major player in the crypto exchange arena, and the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC). This legal clash is a significant moment for the crypto industry, which has been grappling with regulatory uncertainty.<br>Crypto.com has filed a lawsuit against the SEC and its chair, Gary Gensler, after receiving a Wells Notice. This notice is a warning that the SEC is considering enforcement actions against the company. It‚Äôs like a storm cloud on the horizon, signaling trouble ahead. The lawsuit aims to challenge what Crypto.com describes as the SEC's "unauthorized overreach" and "unlawful rulemaking." The stakes are high, as the outcome could shape the future of cryptocurrency regulation in the United States.</p><h3>5. <a href="https://parsers.vc/news/241008-the-electric-surge--tesla-and-lg-energy/?utm_source=newsletter.parsers.vc&amp;utm_medium=newsletter&amp;utm_campaign=parsers-vc-weekly-funding-startup-vc-news-of-october-15-2024&amp;_bhlid=696fab86c8ea31ed2a8e4fac94a529d7b2be79b0">The Electric Surge: Tesla and LG Energy Solution Powering the Future </a></h3><p><em>(Cited in 12 tech media)</em></p><p>The electric vehicle (EV) landscape is evolving rapidly. Two giants, Tesla and LG Energy Solution, are at the forefront of this transformation. Their recent moves highlight the momentum and challenges in the EV market.<br>Tesla recently unveiled impressive statistics about its Supercharger network. In just one quarter, the company delivered a staggering 1.4 terawatt-hours (TWh) of energy. This is enough to power millions of homes for a month. The third quarter saw the opening of 2,800 new Supercharger stations, marking a 23% increase from the previous year. Tesla is expanding its network like a tree spreading its branches. Yet, there‚Äôs a twist. The pace of new station openings has slowed. Compared to the third quarter of 2023, the rollout dropped by 7.4%.</p><h3>6. <a href="https://parsers.vc/news/241014-purplle-s-bold-leap--a-new-era-in-beauty/?utm_source=newsletter.parsers.vc&amp;utm_medium=newsletter&amp;utm_campaign=parsers-vc-weekly-funding-startup-vc-news-of-october-15-2024&amp;_bhlid=febb3d2f6b28946dbe48afa79e85419dd23b4c17">Purplle's Bold Leap: A New Era in Beauty Funding</a>&nbsp;</h3><p><em>(Cited in 11 tech media)</em></p><p>Purplle is on the rise. The beauty and personal care platform recently closed its Series F funding round, securing a hefty Rs 1,500 crore, or about $180 million. This investment was led by a subsidiary of the Abu Dhabi Investment Authority (ADIA), with existing investors like Premji Invest and Blume Ventures stepping up their stakes. New players, such as Sharrp Ventures, have also joined the fray. This infusion of capital marks a significant milestone for Purplle, propelling it further into the competitive beauty marketplace.<br>Founded in 2012, Purplle has carved a niche in the beauty industry, competing with giants like Nykaa and Reliance-backed Tira. The company operates through a dual model: a marketplace for various brands and its own private labels, including Good Vibes and Faces Canada. This strategy has allowed Purplle to tap into the growing demand for beauty products across India, especially in Tier II and III cities.</p><h3>7. <a href="https://parsers.vc/news/241010-suki-s-70-million-leap--revolutionizing/?utm_source=newsletter.parsers.vc&amp;utm_medium=newsletter&amp;utm_campaign=parsers-vc-weekly-funding-startup-vc-news-of-october-15-2024&amp;_bhlid=64d97da92f021f87c62e72f0056d372c8c6d73b0">Suki's $70 Million Leap: Revolutionizing Healthcare with AI</a>&nbsp;</h3><p><em>(Cited in 10 tech media)</em></p><p>In the fast-paced world of healthcare, Suki is making waves. The company recently secured $70 million in funding, pushing its total to $165 million. This investment, led by Hedosophia and backed by Venrock and other existing investors, aims to enhance Suki's AI-driven solutions. The goal? To ease the administrative burden on clinicians and allow them to focus on what truly matters: patient care.<br>Suki is not just another tech company. It‚Äôs a voice AI innovator, transforming how healthcare professionals interact with technology. Imagine a world where clinicians can dictate notes, retrieve patient information, and navigate electronic health records (EHRs) without lifting a finger. That‚Äôs the promise of Suki Assistant. This AI-powered voice assistant is designed to streamline clinical documentation, making the process faster and more efficient. Reports suggest that Suki can help health systems complete notes up to 72% faster.</p><h3>8. <a href="https://parsers.vc/news/241010-venture-capital--the-pulse-of-innovation-in/?utm_source=newsletter.parsers.vc&amp;utm_medium=newsletter&amp;utm_campaign=parsers-vc-weekly-funding-startup-vc-news-of-october-15-2024&amp;_bhlid=45eabf2be4957f5c82a3feb7ea2bdc31ad5de621">Venture Capital: The Pulse of Innovation in Asia</a>&nbsp;</h3><p><em>(Cited in 10 tech media)</em></p><p>In the bustling world of venture capital, Asia is a vibrant landscape. It's a place where ideas bloom and investments flow like rivers. Recent reports reveal a surge in funding across the region, showcasing the relentless drive for innovation. From Hong Kong to Singapore, the momentum is palpable.<br>MindWorks Capital, a prominent player in this arena, has just raised USD 220 million for its latest fund. This isn't just a number; it's a beacon of hope for startups across the Greater Bay Area and beyond. With this new fund, MindWorks now manages a staggering USD 1.4 billion. The firm‚Äôs strategy is clear: invest in the future. The investors backing this fund include sovereign wealth funds, family offices, and entrepreneurs eager to tap into Asia's burgeoning tech scene.</p><h2>Last week's funding rounds</h2><p><strong>115</strong> funding rounds, <strong>+50%</strong> from last week.</p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2 is-viewable-imag" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fe8f7885a-e3c2-436d-9675-3c584a821f79_600x350.gif" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_lossy/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fe8f7885a-e3c2-436d-9675-3c584a821f79_600x350.gif 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_lossy/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fe8f7885a-e3c2-436d-9675-3c584a821f79_600x350.gif 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_lossy/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fe8f7885a-e3c2-436d-9675-3c584a821f79_600x350.gif 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/ima