ndustries. Subscribe now to stay ahead of the curve. (<a href="https://www.particl.com/newsletters/exploding-trends?utm_source=social&amp;utm_medium=Newsletter&amp;utm_campaign=Houck">Link</a>)*</p></li><li><p>A helpful tip when hiring at an early-stage startup (<a href="https://x.com/ankurnagpal/status/1843668118813716628">Link</a>)</p><div><hr></div></li></ul><h3>üí° <strong>Opportunity: Custom Evaluator for Buying a Business</strong></h3><p>Buying a business is a big decision, and it pays to have someone watching your blindspots.</p><p>But getting those people to evaluate a deal can be expensive, especially if you want to cover all your bases.</p><p>With OpenAI‚Äôs o1 model, you could create an agent that does it at a thousandth of the cost (and might even do a better job).</p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2 is-viewable-imag" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F3e56d636-25ab-43bd-927d-c1fd8c4a5ad4_1158x1454.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F3e56d636-25ab-43bd-927d-c1fd8c4a5ad4_1158x1454.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F3e56d636-25ab-43bd-927d-c1fd8c4a5ad4_1158x1454.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F3e56d636-25ab-43bd-927d-c1fd8c4a5ad4_1158x1454.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F3e56d636-25ab-43bd-927d-c1fd8c4a5ad4_1158x1454.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F3e56d636-25ab-43bd-927d-c1fd8c4a5ad4_1158x1454.png" width="1158" height="1454" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/3e56d636-25ab-43bd-927d-c1fd8c4a5ad4_1158x1454.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:1454,&quot;width&quot;:1158,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:190896,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F3e56d636-25ab-43bd-927d-c1fd8c4a5ad4_1158x1454.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F3e56d636-25ab-43bd-927d-c1fd8c4a5ad4_1158x1454.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F3e56d636-25ab-43bd-927d-c1fd8c4a5ad4_1158x1454.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F3e56d636-25ab-43bd-927d-c1fd8c4a5ad4_1158x1454.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a></figure></div><p><a href="https://x.com/garrytan/status/1842100905778544903">Link to Post</a></p><p>This is something that a site like <a href="http://acquire.com">acquire.com</a> could build or, ironically, you could sell it to them.</p><h3>üß†<strong> Framework: Smallest Enterprise Strategy</strong></h3><p><a href="https://pmarchive.com/guide_to_startups_part5.html">Marc Andreessen said</a> that startups shouldn‚Äôt sell to enterprise customers because deals take too long, require too much time and functionality built right away, and can go south for reasons outside the startup‚Äôs control.</p><p>So how can b2b startups who know they‚Äôll be able to anticipate the needs of enterprise customers, or even know they‚Äôll be able to service them in the future at all?</p><p><a href="https://x.com/anshublog/status/1843741351390916657">The Smallest Enterprise strategy says</a> founders should identify the smallest companies with comparable problems, processes, and tools that larger (true enterprise) customers have.</p><p>This can help founders frame the opportunity in front of them ‚Äî if your smallest enterprise is still quite large, the opportunity is that much riskier to pursue.</p><h3><strong>üõ† Tool: <a href="https://www.remofirst.com/">Remofirst</a></strong></h3><p>Founders these days can employ the best talent around the world when scaling their teams, with the help of an Employer of Record provider.</p><p><a href="https://www.remofirst.com/">Remofirst</a> is an Employer of Record that allows businesses to employ talent in 180+ countries the most affordable way, without needing local entities.</p><p>They take on the responsibility of global payroll, international HR, compliance with local laws, and more, bringing the best talent in the world to your fingertips.</p><p>As a Founding Journey reader, you‚Äôll <a href="https://www.remofirst.com/">get 2 months free</a> on your first global hire, in any country.*</p><h3>üìà<strong> Trend: AI‚Äôs Impact on Software</strong></h3><p>I‚Äôve written a lot about how AI is already disrupting SaaS, to the point where questioning the role of SaaS in the startup ecosystem is not as crazy as it would have sounded a few years ago.</p><p>But that‚Äôs not the only opportunity that‚Äôs emerged:</p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2 is-viewable-imag" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F50620f4a-cc9d-4ba4-bbc5-3435047977a7_1162x1012.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F50620f4a-cc9d-4ba4-bbc5-3435047977a7_1162x1012.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F50620f4a-cc9d-4ba4-bbc5-3435047977a7_1162x1012.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F50620f4a-cc9d-4ba4-bbc5-3435047977a7_1162x1012.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F50620f4a-cc9d-4ba4-bbc5-3435047977a7_1162x1012.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F50620f4a-cc9d-4ba4-bbc5-3435047977a7_1162x1012.png" width="1162" height="1012" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/50620f4a-cc9d-4ba4-bbc5-3435047977a7_1162x1012.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:1012,&quot;width&quot;:1162,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:103993,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F50620f4a-cc9d-4ba4-bbc5-3435047977a7_1162x1012.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F50620f4a-cc9d-4ba4-bbc5-3435047977a7_1162x1012.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F50620f4a-cc9d-4ba4-bbc5-3435047977a7_1162x1012.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F50620f4a-cc9d-4ba4-bbc5-3435047977a7_1162x1012.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a></figure></div><p><a href="https://x.com/tanayj/status/1843411855882236372">Link to Post</a></p><p>I like Tanay‚Äôs framing of the two viewpoints but disagree that they‚Äôre divergent ‚Äî it‚Äôs likely some version of both will occur.</p><p>In the past, customers wanted software to make them more efficient ‚Äî now they don‚Äôt really care about incremental efficiency gains and, instead, just want to pay for the work itself to be done.</p><p>Whether that work is done by an AI agent or personal, on-demand software is irrelevant to the end user. As a result, the right solution will depend on the problem.</p><p>The struggle will be between startups that try to tackle either end of a market with one of these two approaches, and the incumbents who have an inherent advantage in terms of training data to build them themselves.</p><p>Startups will need to move fast in order to actually cause disruption.</p><h3>üí¨<strong> Quote: The Personal Touch</strong></h3><p>A change happened in San Francisco around 2017-2018.</p><p>I was living there at the time and remember that, all of a sudden, <a href="https://www.businessinsider.com/brex-corporate-card-for-startups-covers-san-francisco-with-billboards-2018-8">billboards around the city started popping up for this startup called Brex</a>.</p><p>I didn‚Äôt really know what they did (I was working at Airbnb at the time and had no need for a startup credit card) but I distinctly knew them as <em>that company with the billboards</em>.</p><p>This wasn‚Äôt uncommon, and the billboards are legitimately a big part of their early story that many startups have tried to copy ever since. Go around SF now and <em>every</em> billboard is for a startup or big tech company.</p><p>Anyway, it turns out Brex was just as thoughtful with sales as they were with marketing:</p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2 is-viewable-imag" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F333b9e0a-132e-4842-9422-e73ae92a2e5f_1292x1232.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F333b9e0a-132e-4842-9422-e73ae92a2e5f_1292x1232.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F333b9e0a-132e-4842-9422-e73ae92a2e5f_1292x1232.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F333b9e0a-132e-4842-9422-e73ae92a2e5f_1292x1232.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F333b9e0a-132e-4842-9422-e73ae92a2e5f_1292x1232.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F333b9e0a-132e-4842-9422-e73ae92a2e5f_1292x1232.png" width="1292" height="1232" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/333b9e0a-132e-4842-9422-e73ae92a2e5f_1292x1232.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:1232,&quot;width&quot;:1292,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:652217,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F333b9e0a-132e-4842-9422-e73ae92a2e5f_1292x1232.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F333b9e0a-132e-4842-9422-e73ae92a2e5f_1292x1232.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F333b9e0a-132e-4842-9422-e73ae92a2e5f_1292x1232.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F333b9e0a-132e-4842-9422-e73ae92a2e5f_1292x1232.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a></figure></div><p class="button-wrapper" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://thefoundingjourney.substack.com/subscribe?&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Subscribe now&quot;,&quot;action&quot;:null,&quot;class&quot;:null}" data-component-name="ButtonCreateButton"><a class="button primary" href="https://thefoundingjourney.substack.com/subscribe?"><span>Subscribe now</span></a></p><div><hr></div><h2><strong>How I Can Help</strong></h2><p><a href="https://upgrade.foundingjourney.com">Become a member</a> to get full access to our case study library, private founder community, and more.</p><p>We can also help your startup in a few other ways:</p><h3><strong>Content Creation</strong></h3><p>Let my team and I <a href="https://s665g04yp0s.typeform.com/to/rOXjvxHU">ghostwrite</a> for your newsletter, X, or LinkedIn.</p><h3><strong>Growth</strong></h3><p><a href="https://go.houck.news/megaphone">Grow your audience + generate leads</a> with my growth service.</p><h3><strong>Fundraising</strong></h3><p><a href="https://go.houck.news/fundraise">Share your round</a> with hundreds of investors in my personal network.</p><h3><strong>Advising</strong></h3><p><a href="https://go.houck.news/advising">I‚Äôll help solve</a> a specific challenge you‚Äôre facing with your startup.</p><p>Advertise in this newsletter to <a href="https://go.houck.news/partner">get in front of 60,000+ founders</a>.</p></body></html>	Custom AI-powered evaluator for buying a business at low cost. Identify the smallest enterprise customers with similar needs as larger enterprises.	2024-10-15 20:19:26	2024-10-16 14:47:34.842	2024-10-16 14:52:53.735	{vc}	https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/314cf37d-0827-4f92-91ce-7f7c365b151f_1456x1048.png	Michael Houck	ais-impact-on
170	https://newsletter.mcj.vc/p/sidd-mallannagari	The Need for Alternatives to Lithium-Ion Batteries in Stationary Energy Storage	by Sidd Mallannagari	<html><head></head><body><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2 is-viewable-imag" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F82ccc73f-48ad-41c9-b78c-0fbc9382dd42_2000x1294.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F82ccc73f-48ad-41c9-b78c-0fbc9382dd42_2000x1294.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F82ccc73f-48ad-41c9-b78c-0fbc9382dd42_2000x1294.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F82ccc73f-48ad-41c9-b78c-0fbc9382dd42_2000x1294.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F82ccc73f-48ad-41c9-b78c-0fbc9382dd42_2000x1294.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F82ccc73f-48ad-41c9-b78c-0fbc9382dd42_2000x1294.png" width="1456" height="942" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/82ccc73f-48ad-41c9-b78c-0fbc9382dd42_2000x1294.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:942,&quot;width&quot;:1456,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:2786362,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;topImage&quot;:true,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F82ccc73f-48ad-41c9-b78c-0fbc9382dd42_2000x1294.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F82ccc73f-48ad-41c9-b78c-0fbc9382dd42_2000x1294.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F82ccc73f-48ad-41c9-b78c-0fbc9382dd42_2000x1294.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F82ccc73f-48ad-41c9-b78c-0fbc9382dd42_2000x1294.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" fetchpriority="high"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a></figure></div><p>The electricity generation sector contributes <a href="https://www.cbo.gov/publication/58419#:~:text=The%20electric%20power%20sector%20accounts,the%20most%20common%20greenhouse%20gas.">30% of US</a> and about <a href="https://worldemissions.io/">25% of worldwide</a> CO2 emissions making it a crucial target towards net zero goals. While wind and solar power are the most affordable renewable energy options, their intermittent nature creates challenges. Energy storage plays a key role in addressing this intermittency with the International Energy Agency (IEA) estimating that to meet net zero targets <em>non-hydropower</em> energy storage will have to increase from <a href="https://www.iea.org/data-and-statistics/charts/global-installed-energy-storage-capacity-by-scenario-2023-and-2030">87GW in 2023 to about 1200 GW in 2030</a>. This rapid increase in energy storage is essential to manage the variability of wind and solar power. It allows excess energy produced during periods of high generation (like daytime for solar) to be stored and used during times of low generation (such as nighttime when solar isn't producing). This ability to shift energy from when it's generated to when it's needed is key to supporting the transition to renewable energy sources.</p><p>Our current reliance on lithium-ion (Li-ion) batteries to meet energy storage needs presents 3 major limitations.</p><h3><strong>Potential supply shortages.</strong> </h3><p>One of the main risks is that the demand for lithium and other critical materials used in Li-ion batteries is exceeding supply and is expected to last through the next decade. According to McKinsey, the <a href="https://www.mckinsey.com/~/media/mckinsey/industries/automotive%20and%20assembly/our%20insights/battery%202030%20resilient%20sustainable%20and%20circular/svg-battery-2030-ex01-v4.svgz?cq=50&amp;cpy=Center">global demand for Li-ion cells</a> will grow 6X from 2022 (~700 GWh) to 2030 (~4700 GWh). Albemarle the world's largest lithium producer is <a href="https://www.reuters.com/markets/commodities/lithium-producers-warn-global-supplies-may-not-meet-electric-vehicle-demand-2023-06-22/#:~:text=Still%2C%20it%20expects%20global%20lithium,warn%20of%20a%20looming%20shortage">forecasting a shortage</a> by 2030 as are other industry players and analysts. The US Department of Energy‚Äôs (DOE) <a href="https://www.energy.gov/sites/default/files/2023-07/doe-critical-material-assessment_07312023.pdf">critical minerals assessment</a> has rated the supply risk of lithium, nickel, cobalt, graphite and copper, all used in Li-ion batteries as critical between 2025-2035 (see Figure 1). This supply shortage will negatively impact stationary energy storage as the needs of EVs will take precedence given the market power and market size of the automotive industry and the value premium of mobility over stationary energy storage. The lack of adequate build-out of stationary energy storage will lead to curtailing of wind and solar and continuing use of fossil fuel power plants to meet the nighttime energy demand.</p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2 is-viewable-imag" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ff85268ff-6047-4ebf-a218-b4038820960b_554x548.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ff85268ff-6047-4ebf-a218-b4038820960b_554x548.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ff85268ff-6047-4ebf-a218-b4038820960b_554x548.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ff85268ff-6047-4ebf-a218-b4038820960b_554x548.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ff85268ff-6047-4ebf-a218-b4038820960b_554x548.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ff85268ff-6047-4ebf-a218-b4038820960b_554x548.png" width="554" height="548" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/f85268ff-6047-4ebf-a218-b4038820960b_554x548.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:548,&quot;width&quot;:554,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:null,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:null,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ff85268ff-6047-4ebf-a218-b4038820960b_554x548.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ff85268ff-6047-4ebf-a218-b4038820960b_554x548.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ff85268ff-6047-4ebf-a218-b4038820960b_554x548.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ff85268ff-6047-4ebf-a218-b4038820960b_554x548.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a><figcaption class="image-caption">(Figure 1)</figcaption></figure></div><h3><strong>Supply chain security concerns</strong>. </h3><p>Beyond demand outstripping supply, the security of Li-ion supply chains also presents significant risks. The sources of supply and processing of Lithium and other critical minerals are highly concentrated <a href="https://iea.blob.core.windows.net/assets/ef6396c7-950a-4d60-8304-c210627a1512/CriticalMineralsMarketReviewLaunchPresentation.pdf">according</a> to the IEA (see Figure 2). The concentration of supply and processing for lithium and other critical minerals, coupled with geopolitical tensions, heightens the vulnerability of Li-ion supply chains, which are essential for the energy transition in key markets such as the US, Europe, and India.</p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2 is-viewable-imag" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb924cd0c-18ab-42ef-a5b3-1c35667b8b3b_808x480.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb924cd0c-18ab-42ef-a5b3-1c35667b8b3b_808x480.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb924cd0c-18ab-42ef-a5b3-1c35667b8b3b_808x480.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb924cd0c-18ab-42ef-a5b3-1c35667b8b3b_808x480.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb924cd0c-18ab-42ef-a5b3-1c35667b8b3b_808x480.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb924cd0c-18ab-42ef-a5b3-1c35667b8b3b_808x480.png" width="808" height="480" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/b924cd0c-18ab-42ef-a5b3-1c35667b8b3b_808x480.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:480,&quot;width&quot;:808,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:null,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:null,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb924cd0c-18ab-42ef-a5b3-1c35667b8b3b_808x480.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb924cd0c-18ab-42ef-a5b3-1c35667b8b3b_808x480.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb924cd0c-18ab-42ef-a5b3-1c35667b8b3b_808x480.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb924cd0c-18ab-42ef-a5b3-1c35667b8b3b_808x480.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a><figcaption class="image-caption">(Figure 2)</figcaption></figure></div><h3><strong>Challenges for longer duration storage.</strong></h3><p><a href="https://www.nrel.gov/analysis/tech-lcoe-documentation.html">Levelized Cost of Energy</a> (LCOE) is a widely used metric to compare the economics of energy technologies. The LCOE of utility solar in the first half of 2023 was ~$45/MWh, onshore wind was $42/MWh and Lithium-ion based batteries was $155/MWh <a href="https://about.bnef.com/blog/cost-of-clean-energy-technologies-drop-as-expensive-debt-offset-by-cooling-commodity-prices/">as reported by BNEF</a>. Li- ion batteries, though 3 times as expensive as solar or wind, are cost-effective for short durations of a few hours primarily due to two <a href="https://arpa-e.energy.gov/news-and-media/blog-posts/why-long-duration-energy-storage-matters">value streams</a> unique to shorter durations below ~8 hours of storage.</p><p>The first is grid services to maintain demand-supply matching for very short time horizons ranging from a few seconds to about an hour. The second is energy arbitrage in which the energy storage system charges (buying electricity) at the low-price hours of the day and discharges (selling electricity) at the higher price hours.&nbsp; This energy arbitrage is not available for longer durations and the cost of Li-ion is too expensive to be profitable beyond 8 hrs (see Figure 3).&nbsp;</p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2 is-viewable-imag" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0d4242c4-b879-48e8-aa03-a2469b0c4223_618x504.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0d4242c4-b879-48e8-aa03-a2469b0c4223_618x504.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0d4242c4-b879-48e8-aa03-a2469b0c4223_618x504.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0d4242c4-b879-48e8-aa03-a2469b0c4223_618x504.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0d4242c4-b879-48e8-aa03-a2469b0c4223_618x504.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0d4242c4-b879-48e8-aa03-a2469b0c4223_618x504.png" width="618" height="504" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/0d4242c4-b879-48e8-aa03-a2469b0c4223_618x504.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:504,&quot;width&quot;:618,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:null,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:null,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0d4242c4-b879-48e8-aa03-a2469b0c4223_618x504.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0d4242c4-b879-48e8-aa03-a2469b0c4223_618x504.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0d4242c4-b879-48e8-aa03-a2469b0c4223_618x504.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0d4242c4-b879-48e8-aa03-a2469b0c4223_618x504.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a><figcaption class="image-caption">(Figure 3)</figcaption></figure></div><p>Increasing electrification of energy needs and deployment of intermittent solar and wind power will increase the need for longer duration storage. <a href="https://www.ldescouncil.com/assets/pdf/LDES-brochure-F3-HighRes.pdf">Analysis </a>by the Long Duration Energy Storage (LDES) Council indicates that newer technologies being developed for longer durations would be more cost-effective than Li-ion for durations beyond 6-8 hrs. </p><blockquote><p><em>It is a $4 trillion marketplace for LDES. This is a huge opportunity, and that's even a conservative number. If we're going to scale to this, we have a long ways to go."</em> </p><p>- Julia Souder</p><p class="button-wrapper" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://mcj.news/jsouder&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;üéôÔ∏è LDES Council, Julia Souder&quot;,&quot;action&quot;:null,&quot;class&quot;:null}" data-component-name="ButtonCreateButton"><a class="button primary" href="https://mcj.news/jsouder"><span>üéôÔ∏è LDES Council, Julia Souder</span></a></p></blockquote><p>The supply constraints of critical Li-ion materials, the security of the Li-ion supply chains and the lack of profitability of Li-ion-based storage for the coming longer duration needs are driving the development of alternatives.</p><blockquote></blockquote><p>The US Department of Energy's <a href="https://www.energy.gov/eere/long-duration-storage-shot">Long Duration Storage Shot</a> initiative exemplifies the push for more cost-effective and secure long-duration energy storage solutions. This initiative aims to develop technologies that can store energy for 10 hours or more at a cost of $50/MWh or less by 2030. By exploring alternative chemistries, mechanical or thermal-based solutions, or combinations thereof, we can create a more secure and sustainable future for energy storage.&nbsp;</p><p>Some of the solutions in various stages of development are Sodium-ion, Nickel-hydrogen and Zinc-ion based electro-chemistries, redox flow batteries, compressed air energy storage (CAES), gravity-based storage as well as hydrogen-based energy storage.</p><blockquote></blockquote><p>Energy storage is a key enabler of the decarbonization of the energy sector which is critical to our net zero efforts. The need for developing innovative, cost-effective energy storage solutions based on secure supply chains presents a tremendous opportunity to entrepreneurs, investors, governments and the broader climate tech community. Let's seize this opportunity.</p><div><hr></div><h3>üçø The Lean Back</h3><h5><strong>Learn about <a href="https://mcj.news/radiant">Radiant</a>‚Äôs micro-nuclear reactors in this <a href="https://mcj.news/radiant">MCJ Startup Series</a> episode.</strong></h5><div id="youtube2-6VRG77IVWdY" class="youtube-wrap" data-attrs="{&quot;videoId&quot;:&quot;6VRG77IVWdY&quot;,&quot;startTime&quot;:null,&quot;endTime&quot;:null}" data-component-name="Youtube2ToDOM"><div class="youtube-inner"><iframe src="https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/6VRG77IVWdY?rel=0&amp;autoplay=0&amp;showinfo=0&amp;enablejsapi=0" frameborder="0" loading="lazy" gesture="media" allow="autoplay; fullscreen" allowautoplay="true" allowfullscreen="true" width="728" height="409"></iframe></div></div><div><hr></div><h3>üéôÔ∏è MCJ Podcast</h3><p><strong>üèõÔ∏è <a href="https://mcj.news/degraff">Russell Kenneth DeGraff</a></strong> spent 18 years as a staffer on Capitol Hill, including 12 years as the Chief Climate and Technology Advisor to Nancy Pelosi, notably during her second term as Speaker of the House. This is a special conversation going deep into the backstory of how things work in Washington and how these once-in-a-generation climate policies came to be realized.&nbsp;Listen to the episode <strong><a href="https://mcj.news/degraff">here</a></strong>. </p><p>‚ö°Ô∏è <strong><a href="https://mcj.news/hgen">Molly Yang, CEO and Co-founder of Hgen</a></strong>, discussed her company‚Äôs alkaline electrolyzer technology to make hydrogen with a smaller footprint and lower cost, using a modular, mass-manufacturable design. She also offers her thoughts to other climate tech startup founders and climate tech investors about how to approach a market. Listen to the Startup Series <strong><a href="https://mcj.news/hgen">here</a></strong>.</p><div><hr></div><h3>üë©‚Äçüíª Climate Jobs</h3><p><em>For more open positions, check out the&nbsp;<a href="https://my-climate-journey.slack.com/archives/CQGMZ9K38">#j-climatejobs channel</a>&nbsp;in MCJ Slack as well as our <a href="https://jobs.mcjcollective.com/jobs">MCJ Job Board</a>.</em></p><ul><li><p><a href="https://jobs.mcj.vc/companies/arcadia/jobs/41366310-associate-general-counsel-platform#content">Associate General Council</a> at Arcadia (Remote) </p></li><li><p><a href="https://jobs.ashbyhq.com/Crusoe/ff4ef5ed-d49a-4c97-8036-32c83e4c4227?utm_source=MCJ+job+board&amp;utm_medium=getro.com&amp;gh_src=MCJ+job+board">Director of Marketing</a> at Crusoe (SF Bay Area)</p></li><li><p><a href="https://jobs.ashbyhq.com/heirloomcarbon/8c4beffd-03da-40d0-bd6c-221db7e898fb?utm_source=vrMJrWO2aM">Senior Controls Engineer</a> and <a href="https://jobs.ashbyhq.com/heirloomcarbon/9f7cd138-8b63-4b2c-8058-f1d65d607c43?utm_source=vrMJrWO2aM">Head of Supply Chain</a> at Heirloom (SF Bay Area)</p></li><li><p><a href="https://jobs.mcj.vc/companies/levelten-energy/jobs/41357792-salesforce-administrator#content">Salesforce Administrator</a> at LevelTen Energy (Remote) </p></li><li><p><a href="https://jobs.polymer.co/mantel-capture-inc/32140?utm_source=MCJ+job+board&amp;utm_medium=getro.com&amp;gh_src=MCJ+job+board">Senior Project Engineer</a> at Mantel (Cambridge, MA)</p></li><li><p><a href="https://jobs.mcj.vc/companies/overstory-2/jobs/41359885-engineering-manager#content">Engineering Manager</a> at Overstory (Remote) </p></li><li><p><a href="https://app.dover.com/apply/Paces/fa7efc3f-5450-4bc6-b031-3c05a13412d4/?rs=76643084">Marketing Specialist</a> at Paces (Brooklyn, NY)</p></li><li><p><a href="https://job-boards.greenhouse.io/quilt/jobs/4518138007">Head of Communications</a> and <a href="https://job-boards.greenhouse.io/quilt/jobs/4526675007">Operations Associate</a> at Quilt (SF Bay Area)</p></li><li><p><a href="https://jobs.lever.co/SublimeSystems/fe56b607-0e60-43ec-9a6b-f058b35b80c2">Project Controller</a> at Sublime Systems (Somerville, MA) </p></li></ul><div><hr></div><h3>üë©‚Äçüíª Events</h3><p><strong>üö∫ <a href="https://events.zoom.us/ev/AmutbavdjOBGXQHIqtVxDK4Uk_BKq5NoCDBCl3w6