219	https://babyvc.substack.com/p/8b-fund-for-global-startups-green	$8B Fund for Global Startups, Green AI Infrastructure, Zero-Checkout Retail, and much more...	What's Up Tech? #197	<html><head></head><body><p>Welcome to our <strong>197th </strong>newsletter, written with üñ§ by <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/annika-bautista-453106168/">Annika Bautista</a> and <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/sarah-luna-mongin/">Sarah Luna Mongin</a></p><pre><code>üîç Topics we'll cover this week</code></pre><ul><li><p><strong>Fundraising &amp; general news from the week</strong>: another billion for General Catalyst‚Äôs new fund, a new investment vehicle in Europe, and a French fund‚Äôs shakeup  üëÄ</p></li><li><p><strong>Up-and-coming ventures to watch: </strong>sustainable infrastructure and energy to support AI, and a startup moving from seed to IPO real quick üí®</p></li><li><p><strong>Internships &amp; Job</strong> <strong>offers</strong> of the week </p></li></ul><p>Enjoy the read! üíõ</p><pre><code><code>ü§ë Fundraisings of the week</code></code></pre><h3>üí∏ ‚Å†General Catalyst launches $8 billion fund to fuel global startup innovation (üá∫üá∏) </h3><p>Major US venture capital firm <a href="https://www.generalcatalyst.com/">General Catalyst</a> has announced a new <strong>$8 billion fund</strong> aimed at <strong>early-stage startups across sectors and regions</strong>. This capital includes $4.5 billion for its core VC funds, focusing on seed and growth equity funding; $1.5 billion for its ‚Äúcreation strategy,‚Äù designed to help proven founders build new companies; and $2 billion in special investment vehicles for single institutional investors.</p><p>The firm CEO <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/hemanttaneja/">Hemant Taneja</a> wants to drive transformation in sectors like AI, defense, climate, energy, healthcare, and fintech. A quarter of the fund is allocated to Europe, with General Catalyst‚Äôs European head, <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/jeannette-zu-f%C3%BCrstenberg-a4227a17a/">Jeannette zu F√ºrstenberg</a>, emphasizing the firm's strategy to support early-stage talent. Post its merger with European VC firm <a href="https://www.lafamiglia.vc/">La Famiglia</a>, the company is doubling down on <strong>pre-seed and seed investments in Europe. üá™üá∫</strong></p><blockquote><p><a href="https://techcrunch.com/2024/10/24/general-catalyst-raises-8b-in-fresh-funds-to-back-startups-globally/">General Catalyst Raises $8B in Fresh Funds to Back Startups Globally</a></p></blockquote><div><hr></div><h3>üöÄ <strong>Resurge Growth Partners launches one of Europe‚Äôs first-ever ‚Äúventure equity vehicles‚Äù with ¬£120 million raise (</strong>üá¨üáß<strong>)</strong></h3><p><a href="https://resurgegrowth.com/">Resurge Growth Partners</a> is on the lookout for ‚Äú<strong>venture graduates</strong>‚Äù ‚Äî companies that aren‚Äôt quite ready for private equity, but have outgrown the venture capital funding model. üéì&nbsp;</p><p>According to <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/oren-peleg-142690118/">Oren Peleg</a>, the fund‚Äôs Founder and Portfolio Manager, 60% of venture-backed portfolio companies don‚Äôt hit the multiples needed to return the fund. With an additional operational push though, some of them could make for great private equity exits. Their goal is to <strong>acquire operational control </strong>of European and Israeli firms making at least ‚Ç¨7 million in revenue. Resurge is planning to invest between <strong>‚Ç¨10-25 million per company</strong>, aiming to profit from steady, short-term growth.&nbsp;</p><blockquote><p><a href="https://sifted.eu/articles/resurge-growth-partners-invest-vc-news?">Resurge Growth Partners is Raising ‚Ç¨120 million to Turn Around VC Orphans</a></p></blockquote><div><hr></div><h3>üõçÔ∏è <strong>dmg ventures raises ¬£50 million to back consumer startups (</strong>üá¨üáß<strong>)</strong></h3><p><a href="https://www.dmgventures.co.uk/">dmg ventures</a> remains unfazed in its mission to support consumer startups, <a href="https://sifted.eu/articles/dmg-ventures-new-fund-news">announcing </a><strong><a href="https://sifted.eu/articles/dmg-ventures-new-fund-news">two new ¬£25 million funds</a></strong>: the early-stage Headline fund and the growth-stage Scale fund. </p><p>DMG has a unique investment model, <strong>combining capital and media expertise and credits</strong> as the firm‚Äôs sole LP is media giant <a href="https://www.dmgt.com/">DMGT</a> (owner of Daily Mail and Metro). They‚Äôre focusing on consumer products that resonate with DMGT's audience, such as <a href="https://drink-trip.com/">Trip</a>, a CBD-infused drinks company. ü•Ç</p><blockquote><p><a href="https://medium.com/dmg-ventures/dmg-ventures-announces-50m-in-fresh-capital-backs-burgeoning-food-and-beverage-brands-trip-and-8b45ec590a3c">dmg ventures Announces ¬£50 million in Fresh Capital, Backs Burgeoning Food and Beverage Brands TRIP and Blue Stripes, and Makes Two Promotions to Partner</a></p></blockquote><div><hr></div><h3>üéÅ Moneybox raises ¬£70 million in Series E welcoming new investors on board (üá¨üáß)</h3><p>UK-based savings and investing platform <a href="https://www.moneyboxapp.com/">Moneybox</a> has raised <strong>¬£70 million</strong> in fresh funding, welcoming new investors <a href="https://apis.pe/">Apis Global</a> Growth Fund III and <a href="https://about.amundi.com/">Amundi</a>. This funding, primarily from a secondary share sale allowing existing investors to <strong>sell 10-15% of their shares</strong>, adds to Moneybox‚Äôs strong investor lineup.</p><p>Moneybox offers a wide range of financial services designed to help individuals save, invest, buy homes, and prepare for retirement. With over one million customers, the platform recently <strong>surpassed ¬£10 billion</strong> in Assets Under Administration (AUA) and achieved a <strong>168% revenue increase</strong> in the past fiscal year. ü§ë</p><blockquote><p><a href="https://fintech.global/2024/10/23/moneybox-raises-70m-in-new-investment-valuation-hits-550m/">Moneybox Raises ¬£70M in New Investment, Valuation Hits ¬£550M</a></p></blockquote><div><hr></div><h3>üí°<strong>Oriole Networks secures $22 million in Series A funding for energy-efficient LLM Training (</strong>üá¨üáß<strong>)</strong></h3><p>We‚Äôre seeing some light at the end of the tunnel when it comes to AI‚Äôs energy problem. ‚ö°Ô∏è</p><p>With this latest funding round led by <a href="https://pluralplatform.com/">Plural</a>, <a href="https://www.oriolenetworks.com/">Oriole Networks</a> has raised a total of <strong>$35 million</strong> to train large language models <strong>up to 100 times faster</strong> with photonic-based technology. The firm aims to create a ‚Äúphotonic AI network‚Äù by 2025.</p><blockquote><p><a href="https://tech.eu/2024/10/21/oriole-networks-raises-22m-to-reduce-energy-consumption-of-ai-data-centres/?utm_source=techeu&amp;utm_medium=email&amp;utm_campaign=TechEU+Daily+Newsletter">Oriole Networks Raises $22 million to Reduce Energy Consumption of AI Data Centers</a></p></blockquote><div><hr></div><h3>üõí Sensei raises ‚Ç¨15 million in Series A to launch 1,000 autonomous stores by 2026 (üáµüáπ) </h3><p>Say good-bye to checkouts with Portuguese retail tech company <a href="https://www.sensei.tech/">Sensei</a>. üëã The firm has raised <strong>‚Ç¨15 million in Series A funding</strong> to scale its autonomous retail platform, aiming to open 1,000 checkout-free stores by 2026. This funding supports Sensei's goal of transforming the shopping experience and optimizing retail operations on a global scale. üõçÔ∏è</p><p>Using AI-powered sensors, computer vision, and real-time algorithms, Sensei‚Äôs technology enables shoppers to <strong>skip checkout lines</strong> entirely, with items automatically added to their virtual cart. The platform also provides retailers with real-time data on inventory and store operations, addressing issues like stock-outs and checkout costs. </p><blockquote><p><a href="https://tech.eu/2024/10/24/sensei-secures-eur15m-to-expand-autonomous-retail-vision/">Sensei Secures ‚Ç¨15M to Expand Autonomous Retail Vision</a></p></blockquote><pre><code><code>üî• Up-and-coming startups to watch</code></code></pre><h3>‚ôªÔ∏è <strong>DataCrunch.io raises ‚Ç¨13 million in Seed funding to build sustainable, AI-focused cloud infrastructure (</strong>üá´üáÆ<strong>)</strong></h3><p><a href="http://DataCrunch.io">DataCrunch.io</a> is in the race to be <strong>Europe‚Äôs first hyperscaler.</strong> They raised <strong>‚Ç¨13 million</strong> led by <a href="https://www.byfounders.vc/">byFounders</a> to develop renewable-energy-powered AI infrastructure based in Finnish and Icelandic data centers. The company has taken a significant amount of debt (40% of raise) from <a href="https://www.lahitapiola.fi/henkilo/">LokalTapiola</a> and <a href="https://www.nordea.com/en">Nordea</a>, leveraging on the high liquidity potential of their hardware capital expenditure. They aim to offer efficient AI services for high-compute workloads. The funding will be used to build their own data centers come 2025. üèóÔ∏è</p><blockquote><p><a href="https://techcrunch.com/2024/10/21/datacrunch-wants-to-be-europes-first-ai-cloud-hyperscaler-powered-by-renewable-energy/">DataCrunch Wants to Be Europe‚Äôs First AI Cloud Hyperscaler ‚Äî Powered by Renewable Energy</a></p></blockquote><div><hr></div><h3>üí®&nbsp;Dunia secures $11.5 million to accelerate green material discovery with AI-driven lab (üá©üá™)</h3><p><a href="https://dunia.ai/our-dunia">Dunia Innovations</a>, a UK-based advanced materials scaleup, has raised <strong>$11.5 million</strong> in funding co-led by <a href="https://www.elaia.com/">Elaia</a> and <a href="https://www.redalpine.com/">redalpine</a>. With its AI-powered approach, Dunia reimagines the traditionally slow ‚Äúdesign, make, test, analyze‚Äù cycle, <strong>reducing it from decades to under three years</strong>.</p><p>Founded in 2022, Dunia combines AI with a proprietary self-driving lab to revolutionise materials discovery, focusing on <a href="https://www.elaia.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/PR-Dunia.pdf">power-to-x electrocatalysts</a> for sustainable fuel and chemical production. By targeting critical materials like green hydrogen catalysts, Dunia aims to tackle bottlenecks in the clean energy transition. üå±</p><blockquote><p><a href="https://tech.eu/2024/10/23/dunia-ai-raises-11-5m-for-low-carbon-fuels-and-chemicals/">Dunia.ai Raises $11.5 million for Low-Carbon Fuels and Chemicals</a></p></blockquote><div><hr></div><h3>ü§ñ <strong>LightOn prepares for IPO to expand bespoke B2B GenAI services (</strong>üá´üá∑<strong>)</strong></h3><p>From Seed funding straight into IPO, <a href="https://www.lighton.ai/">LightOn</a> is set to go public on<strong> Euronext Growth</strong>. They aim to raise <strong>‚Ç¨10 million</strong> to create enterprise-focused AI models, building on top of open-sourced large language models. Instead of raising through venture funding, LightOn wants to protect its independence. The company is bullish that consumer knowledge on AI will drive significant public interest. With a<strong> ‚Ç¨50 million valuation target</strong>, LightOn plans to grow its European and Middle Eastern presence. üó∫Ô∏è</p><blockquote><p><a href="https://sifted.eu/articles/lighton-ipo-50m-news">Paris-based GenAI Startup LightOn to IPO at a ‚Ç¨50 million Valuation</a></p></blockquote><pre><code>üì∞ News of the week</code></pre><h3>üåä French VC firm Newwave taken over by Xavier Niel‚Äôs holding amid leadership shakeup </h3><p><a href="https://www.newwave.vc/">Newwave</a> was founded back in 2020 by <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/piadiribarne/">Pia d‚ÄôIribarne</a> and <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/jeandlr/">Jean de La Rochebrochard</a> and is now being <strong>acquired by NJJ Holding</strong>, owned by billionaire Xavier Niel. The acquisition follows significant leadership changes, as d‚ÄôIribarne announced her departure to pursue new investment opportunities. De La Rochebrochard, who was ousted from Newwave earlier this year, will now return to manage the fund.</p><p>Newwave has invested in high-profile startups, including AI firms <a href="https://mistral.ai/">Mistral</a>, <a href="https://poolside.ai/">Poolside</a>, and carbon accounting platform <a href="https://www.sweep.net/">Sweep</a>. üöÄ</p><blockquote><p><a href="https://sifted.eu/articles/newwave-xavier-niel-france-vc-news">French VC Firm Newwave is Being Taken Over by Billionaire Xavier Niel‚Äôs Holding Company</a></p></blockquote><div><hr></div><pre><code><code>üëî Internships &amp; job offers</code></code></pre><h3>Internships</h3><p>Stage Programmes French Tech/France 2030 - <strong>La Mission French Tech </strong>(Paris)</p><blockquote><p><a href="https://www.pass.fonction-publique.gouv.fr/offre/stage-chargee-de-mission-programmes-french-techfrance-2030-2">‚û§&nbsp;Job  desc.</a></p></blockquote><p>Founder's Associate Intern - <strong>CoCrafter (YC W24) </strong>(Munich)</p><blockquote><p><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/view/4061516620/">‚û§&nbsp;Job  desc.</a></p></blockquote><p>Part-Time Visiting Analyst - <strong>Backing Minds </strong>(Stockholm)</p><blockquote><p><a href="https://backingminds.teamtailor.com/jobs/5119735-part-time-visiting-analyst-spring-2025?utm_source=venturecapitalcareers">‚û§&nbsp;Job  desc.</a></p></blockquote><h3>Jobs</h3><p>Investment Manager - <strong>Navigare Ventures </strong>(Stockholm)</p><blockquote><p><a href="https://venturecapitalcareers.com/job/1589792-investment-manager-navigare-ventures">‚û§&nbsp;Job desc.</a></p></blockquote><p>Principal - <strong>Movens Capital</strong> (Warsaw)</p><blockquote><p><a href="https://venturecapitalcareers.com/job/1589278-principal-movens-capital">‚û§&nbsp;Job desc.</a></p></blockquote><p>Venture Lead - <strong>Voodoo </strong>(Paris)</p><blockquote><p><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/view/4060385043">‚û§&nbsp;Job desc.</a></p></blockquote><p></p><div><hr></div><p>üëâ If you‚Äôd like to discover more internship &amp; job offers, you can check our LinkedIn Fridays‚Äô post<strong><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/posts/babyvc_baby-vc-substack-activity-7255465662267953152-h6VB?utm_source=share&amp;utm_medium=member_desktop"> here</a></strong>!</p><p>You can also read more about baby vc on <strong><a href="https://www.babyvc.co/">our website</a></strong> and follow our updates on <strong><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/company/30734593/">LinkedIn</a></strong>, or directly reach out to us at <strong>hello@baby-vc.co</strong>! ü§ù</p><h4></h4><p>The whole baby vc crew üñ§</p><p></p><p class="button-wrapper" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://babyvc.substack.com/subscribe?&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Subscribe now&quot;,&quot;action&quot;:null,&quot;class&quot;:null}" data-component-name="ButtonCreateButton"><a class="button primary" href="https://babyvc.substack.com/subscribe?"><span>Subscribe now</span></a></p><p class="button-wrapper" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://babyvc.substack.com/p/8b-fund-for-global-startups-green/comments&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Leave a comment&quot;,&quot;action&quot;:null,&quot;class&quot;:null}" data-component-name="ButtonCreateButton"><a class="button primary" href="https://babyvc.substack.com/p/8b-fund-for-global-startups-green/comments"><span>Leave a comment</span></a></p><p class="button-wrapper" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://babyvc.substack.com/p/8b-fund-for-global-startups-green?utm_source=substack&amp;utm_medium=email&amp;utm_content=share&amp;action=share&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Share&quot;,&quot;action&quot;:null,&quot;class&quot;:null}" data-component-name="ButtonCreateButton"><a class="button primary" href="https://babyvc.substack.com/p/8b-fund-for-global-startups-green?utm_source=substack&amp;utm_medium=email&amp;utm_content=share&amp;action=share"><span>Share</span></a></p></body></html>	General Catalyst raises $8 billion fund for early-stage startups globally, Resurge Growth Partners launches a ¬£120 million "venture equity vehicle" in Europe.	2024-10-29 08:01:10	2024-10-30 06:25:27.064	2024-10-30 07:51:30.763	{vc}	https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/05452546-b749-4fe3-899f-49c9be2901bd_1120x1120.jpeg	Sarah Luna Mongin	8b-fund-for-global-startups
131	https://parsers.substack.com/p/parsers-vc-weekly-funding-startup-43e	Parsers VC - Weekly Funding / Startup / VC news of October 1, 2024	Venture Capital News. Funding rounds, statistics Week of September 24 - September 30: United States (35 - $1.5B), India (9 - $614M), United Kingdom (11 - $226M), Canada (7 - $119M)	<html><head></head><body><h2>Most Popular Venture Capital News</h2><h3>1. <a href="https://parsers.vc/news/240924-celestia-foundation-secures-100-million-to/?utm_source=newsletter.parsers.vc&amp;utm_medium=newsletter&amp;utm_campaign=parsers-vc-weekly-funding-startup-vc-news-of-october-1-2024&amp;_bhlid=57a1f544b00c45146a674744f8642c29d181eb3a">Celestia Foundation Secures $100 Million to Revolutionize Blockchain Scalability </a></h3><p><em>(Cited in 19 tech media)</em></p><p>In the fast-paced world of blockchain technology, innovation is the lifeblood. The Celestia Foundation has just injected a fresh wave of energy into this ecosystem by securing $100 million in funding. This substantial investment, led by Bain Capital Crypto, signals a robust vote of confidence in Celestia's vision for modular blockchain networks. With this latest round, the total funding for Celestia has reached an impressive $155 million.<br>Celestia is not just another player in the blockchain arena. It is pioneering a modular blockchain architecture designed to tackle the scalability challenges that have plagued traditional networks. The essence of Celestia's approach lies in its separation of layers. By decoupling the consensus and data layers from the execution layer, Celestia allows developers to craft their own transaction rules. This flexibility is akin to giving a chef the freedom to create a unique recipe rather than following a rigid menu.</p><h3>2. <a href="https://parsers.vc/news/240925-the-encryption-arms-race--safeguarding-ai/?utm_source=newsletter.parsers.vc&amp;utm_medium=newsletter&amp;utm_campaign=parsers-vc-weekly-funding-startup-vc-news-of-october-1-2024&amp;_bhlid=bf1f14ef09d004f79bea028f0a7aae5018f0fa2c">The Encryption Arms Race: Safeguarding AI Models in a Digital Battlefield</a>&nbsp;</h3><p><em>(Cited in 16 tech media)</em></p><p>In the world of artificial intelligence, large language models (LLMs) are the titans of the digital age. They are the engines driving innovation, creativity, and automation. Yet, as their power grows, so do the threats surrounding them. The encryption of these models is no longer a mere technical consideration; it has become a matter of survival in a landscape riddled with legal battles, intellectual property theft, and cyber warfare.<br>Imagine a fortress. Its walls are high, its gates are fortified. But what happens when the enemy finds a way to breach those walls? This is the dilemma facing companies like OpenAI, NVIDIA, and Microsoft. They are locked in a race not just to innovate but to protect their intellectual property from a barrage of attacks. The stakes are high, and the methods of attack are evolving.</p><h3>3. <a href="https://parsers.vc/news/240924-torq-s-70m-funding--a-leap-into-the-future/?utm_source=newsletter.parsers.vc&amp;utm_medium=newsletter&amp;utm_campaign=parsers-vc-weekly-funding-startup-vc-news-of-october-1-2024&amp;_bhlid=54fd9546f138b007e6f07c73d79bb66c2bf6f4f1">Torq's $70M Funding: A Leap into the Future of Cybersecurity</a><a href="https://parsers.vc/news/240419-uniqus-consultech--a-rising-star-in-the/?utm_source=newsletter.parsers.vc&amp;utm_medium=newsletter&amp;utm_campaign=parsers-vc-weekly-funding-startup-vc-news-of-october-1-2024&amp;_bhlid=449bb923004ff3c7023643a486e2945ac13aa03e"> </a></h3><p><em>(Cited in 14 tech media)</em></p><p>In the fast-paced world of cybersecurity, Torq has just made a significant move. The New York City-based company has raised $70 million in Series C funding. This infusion of capital brings its total funding to a striking $192 million. The stakes are high, and Torq is ready to play.<br>Led by Evolution Equity Partners, the funding round also saw participation from notable players like Bessemer Venture Partners, Notable Capital, Greenfield Partners, and Strait Capital. With this financial backing, Torq aims to expand its reach across Europe, the Middle East, and the Asia-Pacific region. The company is not just looking to grow; it‚Äôs gearing up to enhance its generative AI capabilities.</p><h3>4. <a href="https://parsers.vc/news/240924-huawei-s-bold-leap--harmonyos-takes-center/?utm_source=newsletter.parsers.vc&amp;utm_medium=newsletter&amp;utm_campaign=parsers-vc-weekly-funding-startup-vc-news-of-october-1-2024&amp;_bhlid=36ade3bf97bd0856e75245808dad23b911d1601a">Huawei's Bold Leap: HarmonyOS Takes Center Stage </a></h3><p><em>(Cited in 13 tech media)</em></p><p>In a world where tech giants battle for dominance, Huawei is making a bold move. The company plans to abandon Windows for its own operating system, HarmonyOS. This shift is not just a business decision; it‚Äôs a declaration of independence. The head of Huawei‚Äôs consumer business, Yu Chengdong, has announced that the company will stop producing PCs with Windows. Instead, it will embrace HarmonyOS, a system designed to be faster and more secure.<br>HarmonyOS is not just another player in the crowded OS market. It boasts a new kernel that stands apart from Linux. This independence could be its secret weapon. However, the success of HarmonyOS hinges on one crucial factor: software support. Without a robust ecosystem of applications, even the best operating system can falter. Game developers, in particular, hold the key. If they embrace HarmonyOS, it could flourish. If not, it may struggle to gain traction.</p><h3>5. <a href="https://parsers.vc/news/240925-the-rising-tide-of-ai-threats--navigating/?utm_source=newsletter.parsers.vc&amp;utm_medium=newsletter&amp;utm_campaign=parsers-vc-weekly-funding-startup-vc-news-of-october-1-2024&amp;_bhlid=36aac9a433ac86d634ea5b745e7bbf3a7ea3cb12">The Rising Tide of AI Threats: Navigating the Deepfake and Malware Landscape</a>&nbsp;</h3><p><em>(Cited in 12 tech media)</em></p><p>In the digital age, artificial intelligence (AI) is a double-edged sword. It empowers innovation but also fuels new threats. The emergence of deepfakes and AI-generated malware is reshaping the cybersecurity landscape. Businesses and individuals alike must adapt or risk being swept away by this rising tide.<br>Deepfakes are not just a buzzword; they are a reality that poses significant risks. A recent survey revealed that 80% of executives see deepfakes as a threat to their organizations. Yet, only 29% have taken action to counter this menace. This disconnect is alarming. As AI technology evolves, so do the tactics of cybercriminals. They are using AI to create sophisticated impersonations, undermining trust and security.</p><h3>6. <a href="https://parsers.vc/news/240926-helaina-s-45-million-leap--revolutionizing/?utm_source=newsletter.parsers.vc&amp;utm_medium=newsletter&amp;utm_campaign=parsers-vc-weekly-funding-startup-vc-news-of-october-1-2024&amp;_bhlid=b54175c06e1c3bf79dd40ac42a8a37444c255b49">Helaina's $45 Million Leap: Revolutionizing Nutrition with Human Lactoferrin</a>&nbsp;</h3><p><em>(Cited in 10 tech media)</em></p><p>In the bustling world of biotechnology, Helaina stands out like a lighthouse in a storm. This New York-based startup has just raised $45 million in a Series B funding round, a significant boost that brings its total equity funding to $83 million. The money will fuel the launch of effera, the first human lactoferrin product on the market. This bioactive protein, derived from precision fermentation, is poised to disrupt the nutrition landscape, targeting women‚Äôs health, active nutrition, and healthy aging.<br>Helaina‚Äôs journey began in 2019, and since then, it has carved a niche in the competitive realm of functional foods. The company‚Äôs innovative approach leverages precision fermentation, a method that genetically engineers microbes to produce specific proteins. In this case, Helaina is producing human lactoferrin, a protein traditionally sourced from cow‚Äôs milk. The shift from bovine to human lactoferrin is not just a matter of preference; it‚Äôs about efficacy and tolerability.</p><h3>7. <a href="https://parsers.vc/news/240924-the-gut-health-revolution--viscera-3-and/?utm_source=newsletter.parsers.vc&amp;utm_medium=newsletter&amp;utm_campaign=parsers-vc-weekly-funding-startup-vc-news-of-october-1-2024&amp;_bhlid=2af8e4675226023cba6b7ee1985ec77539264016">The Gut Health Revolution: Viscera-3¬Æ and the Rise of Sodium Butyrate</a>&nbsp;</h3><p><em>(Cited in 10 tech media)</em></p><p>In the world of wellness, gut health is the new gold standard. As we step into 2024, the spotlight shines brightly on a groundbreaking supplement: Viscera-3¬Æ. This product, featuring time-released sodium butyrate in the form of tributyrin, promises to revolutionize how we think about digestive health. It‚Äôs not just a trend; it‚Äôs a necessity.<br>The gut health market is booming. It‚Äôs projected to soar from $55.7 billion in 2023 to $68.17 billion by 2030. This surge is fueled by a growing awareness of the gut's role in overall well-being. Consumers are no longer satisfied with mere fiber; they want results. Viscera-3¬Æ stands out as a beacon of hope in this crowded landscape.</p><h3>8. <a href="https://parsers.vc/news/240924-docker-and-monitoring--a-developer-s/?utm_source=newsletter.parsers.vc&amp;utm_medium=newsletter&amp;utm_campaign=parsers-vc-weekly-funding-startup-vc-news-of-october-1-2024&amp;_bhlid=c9a1880e28a31b174260aee721edf7a5ec4f62c9">Docker and Monitoring: A Developer's Toolkit for Success</a>&nbsp;</h3><p><em>(Cited in 10 tech media)</em></p><p>In the world of software development, efficiency is king. Developers crave tools that streamline processes and enhance productivity. Enter Docker, a game-changer in application development and deployment. Docker is like a magic box that holds everything an application needs to run. It packages applications into containers, ensuring they work seamlessly across different environments.<br>Imagine a world where you can run your application without worrying about the underlying infrastructure. That‚Äôs Docker. It isolates applications in containers, using the host operating system. Unlike traditional virtual machines, containers share the host OS, making them lightweight and fast. This is the essence of Docker: simplicity and speed.</p><h2>Last week's funding rounds</h2><p><strong>155</strong> funding rounds, <strong>-2%</strong> from last week.</p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2 is-viewable-imag" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ff3e5b7ed-9d30-4c58-a6c2-683419727244_600x350.gif" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_lossy/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ff3e5b7ed-9d30-4c58-a6c2-683419727244_600x350.gif 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_lossy/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ff3e5b7ed-9d30-4c58-a6c2-683419727244_600x350.gif 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_lossy/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ff3e5b7ed-9d30-4c58-a6c2-683419727244_600x350.gif 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_lossy/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ff3e5b7ed-9d30-4c58-a6c2-683419727244_600x350.gif 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_lossy/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ff3e5b7ed