179	https://stellifivc.substack.com/p/back-to-office-battle	Back-to-Office Battle	How companies shifting from hybrid working models will impact the office asset class	<html><head></head><body><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2 is-viewable-imag" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ff878601e-33f0-46d7-8037-3d0004063e8b_1456x662.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ff878601e-33f0-46d7-8037-3d0004063e8b_1456x662.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ff878601e-33f0-46d7-8037-3d0004063e8b_1456x662.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ff878601e-33f0-46d7-8037-3d0004063e8b_1456x662.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ff878601e-33f0-46d7-8037-3d0004063e8b_1456x662.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ff878601e-33f0-46d7-8037-3d0004063e8b_1456x662.jpeg" width="1456" height="662" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/f878601e-33f0-46d7-8037-3d0004063e8b_1456x662.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:662,&quot;width&quot;:1456,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:null,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;Five ideas to make use of empty office space&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;Five ideas to make use of empty office space&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:null,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;topImage&quot;:true,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="Five ideas to make use of empty office space" title="Five ideas to make use of empty office space" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ff878601e-33f0-46d7-8037-3d0004063e8b_1456x662.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ff878601e-33f0-46d7-8037-3d0004063e8b_1456x662.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ff878601e-33f0-46d7-8037-3d0004063e8b_1456x662.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ff878601e-33f0-46d7-8037-3d0004063e8b_1456x662.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" fetchpriority="high"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a></figure></div><p>The battle over remote and hybrid work is intensifying as companies summon employees back to their desks. While this trend offers a lifeline to struggling office landlords, the question remains whether it‚Äôs too little too late.</p><p><strong>Still Struggling<br></strong>Since the pandemic, office building <a href="https://www.axios.com/2024/03/13/office-building-value-commercial-real-estate">valuations have plummeted</a>, driven by the high vacancy rates they‚Äôve experienced as a result of the remote work trend. Office owners and their lenders tried to ‚Äúextend and pretend‚Äù, but after two years of rising interest rates, owners are still struggling to refinance.&nbsp;</p><p>Rate cuts are surely helpful, but they won‚Äôt deliver the magnitude of relief that is needed. It‚Äôs a long road ahead, but we‚Äôre starting to see some signs of hope for landlords and their lenders.</p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2 is-viewable-imag" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0bfbf7b9-306b-4372-9efa-da98cb5f3cdd_790x585.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0bfbf7b9-306b-4372-9efa-da98cb5f3cdd_790x585.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0bfbf7b9-306b-4372-9efa-da98cb5f3cdd_790x585.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0bfbf7b9-306b-4372-9efa-da98cb5f3cdd_790x585.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0bfbf7b9-306b-4372-9efa-da98cb5f3cdd_790x585.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0bfbf7b9-306b-4372-9efa-da98cb5f3cdd_790x585.png" width="790" height="585" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/0bfbf7b9-306b-4372-9efa-da98cb5f3cdd_790x585.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:585,&quot;width&quot;:790,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:null,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:null,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0bfbf7b9-306b-4372-9efa-da98cb5f3cdd_790x585.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0bfbf7b9-306b-4372-9efa-da98cb5f3cdd_790x585.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0bfbf7b9-306b-4372-9efa-da98cb5f3cdd_790x585.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0bfbf7b9-306b-4372-9efa-da98cb5f3cdd_790x585.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a></figure></div><p><strong>Time to Return<br></strong>The future of work remains a heated topic of debate. Most companies initially embraced hybrid and remote models. There have even been some studies that show the hybrid model can increase productivity. Employers, evidently, aren‚Äôt all convinced that hybrid work is a workable long-term solution. A growing number of corporations are now enforcing strict in-office policies.&nbsp;</p><p>Twitter and Tesla were among the first to require employees to return to the office. More recently, Amazon's CEO, Andy Jassy, announced a <a href="https://www.cnbc.com/2024/09/16/amazon-jassy-tells-employees-to-return-to-office-five-days-a-week.html">mandatory five-day workweek</a>, sparking pushback from employees. <a href="https://www.mysanantonio.com/business/article/dell-return-to-office-19831525.php">Dell followed suit</a>, prompting a scramble among staff to adjust their routines on short notice.&nbsp;</p><p>The purpose and rationale for these announcements are <a href="https://www.inc.com/jprocopio/are-return-to-office-mandates-really-just-mass-layoffs-in-disguise/90983360">open to interpretatio</a>n, but broadly speaking they are examples of a broader shift that appears to be positively impacting the office market.</p><p><strong>On the Plus Side<br></strong>The data is moving in the right direction for landlords:</p><ul><li><p>South Florida is leading the way with <a href="https://www.globest.com/2024/09/17/south-florida-leading-the-country-in-office-revival/?utm_source=newsletter.credaily.com&amp;utm_medium=newsletter&amp;utm_campaign=banks-high-volatility-cre-loans-surge-20-in-q2-2024&amp;_bhlid=2366c474207f517f369cb57f671a2c9391ab8c2e&amp;slreturn=20240920112336">over 90% of employees</a> in the region back in the office. That‚Äôs 20% higher than the national average.</p></li><li><p>CBRE's net absorption index <a href="https://www.globest.com/2024/09/17/south-florida-leading-the-country-in-office-revival/?utm_source=newsletter.credaily.com&amp;utm_medium=newsletter&amp;utm_campaign=banks-high-volatility-cre-loans-surge-20-in-q2-2024&amp;_bhlid=2366c474207f517f369cb57f671a2c9391ab8c2e&amp;slreturn=20240920112336">turned positive</a> for the first time in two years during Q2 of this year. What‚Äôs more, this trend isn‚Äôt confined to one market. The majority of markets measured in the index moved in the positive direction.</p></li><li><p>Most recently, <a href="https://www.us.jll.com/en/trends-and-insights/research/office-market-statistics-trends?mkt_tok=ODIzLUlOWi0zMTAAAAGWGzq_dMMb7OvPRckV9YbNd7FBrwAis7mbCE0VkgKySSlrgh9KgHyqC-QT6RA0R-mnGcKhgDH8W_CsecTo_ajahARyMY6Dwf86wjj9rmHgC2xF5A">JLL‚Äôs Q3 report</a> noted that while absorption was still negative, leasing activity continued to tick up and we saw the sharpest decline in availability since 2018 driven by office-to-housing conversions.</p></li></ul><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2 is-viewable-imag" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F8d5edf3a-dde7-4462-88c8-d8817180ec2b_778x586.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F8d5edf3a-dde7-4462-88c8-d8817180ec2b_778x586.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F8d5edf3a-dde7-4462-88c8-d8817180ec2b_778x586.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F8d5edf3a-dde7-4462-88c8-d8817180ec2b_778x586.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F8d5edf3a-dde7-4462-88c8-d8817180ec2b_778x586.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F8d5edf3a-dde7-4462-88c8-d8817180ec2b_778x586.png" width="778" height="586" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/8d5edf3a-dde7-4462-88c8-d8817180ec2b_778x586.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:586,&quot;width&quot;:778,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:null,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:null,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F8d5edf3a-dde7-4462-88c8-d8817180ec2b_778x586.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F8d5edf3a-dde7-4462-88c8-d8817180ec2b_778x586.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F8d5edf3a-dde7-4462-88c8-d8817180ec2b_778x586.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F8d5edf3a-dde7-4462-88c8-d8817180ec2b_778x586.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a></figure></div><p><strong>What‚Äôs Next?<br></strong>While delinquency and special servicing rates still look poor, these data points are good leading indicators of progress on the long road to recovery for office spaces. Investors are starting to <a href="https://www.commercialsearch.com/news/you-bought-an-office-building-now-what/">sniff out opportunities</a>, with many believing that the bottom is near or here. They are snatching up office buildings, hoping to capitalize on repositioning and conversion opportunities.</p><p>Existing property owners are still hoping for brighter days ahead, whether through sales, refinancing, or managing their way through the recovery. It‚Äôs going to be an uphill battle, whether you‚Äôre a current owner or buying in today. Nonetheless, the signs of recovery provide a glimmer of hope for a brighter future.</p></body></html>	The article discusses the ongoing battle over remote and hybrid work, which has led to a decline in office building valuations.	2024-10-18 16:50:39	2024-10-20 19:33:56.985	2024-10-21 05:59:52.902	{vc}	https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ff878601e-33f0-46d7-8037-3d0004063e8b_1456x662.jpeg	Gilberto Orozco	back-to-office
239	https://www.newcomer.co/p/silicon-valley-cant-look-away-from	Silicon Valley Can't Look Away from the Election 	Plus, we dig into General Catalyst's $8 billion fundraising haul on the latest episode of the Newcomer podcast	<html><head></head><body><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2 is-viewable-imag" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F28731894-49bd-4213-8e47-29ac6f8c2f33_1920x1080.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F28731894-49bd-4213-8e47-29ac6f8c2f33_1920x1080.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F28731894-49bd-4213-8e47-29ac6f8c2f33_1920x1080.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F28731894-49bd-4213-8e47-29ac6f8c2f33_1920x1080.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F28731894-49bd-4213-8e47-29ac6f8c2f33_1920x1080.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F28731894-49bd-4213-8e47-29ac6f8c2f33_1920x1080.jpeg" width="1456" height="819" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/28731894-49bd-4213-8e47-29ac6f8c2f33_1920x1080.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:819,&quot;width&quot;:1456,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:1039583,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;topImage&quot;:true,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F28731894-49bd-4213-8e47-29ac6f8c2f33_1920x1080.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F28731894-49bd-4213-8e47-29ac6f8c2f33_1920x1080.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F28731894-49bd-4213-8e47-29ac6f8c2f33_1920x1080.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F28731894-49bd-4213-8e47-29ac6f8c2f33_1920x1080.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" fetchpriority="high"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2"><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a></figure></div><p>We‚Äôre in the home stretch. Silicon Valley‚Äôs political nightmare could <em>hopefully</em> soon be over. In the latest episode of the <em>Newcomer podcast</em>, we dig into all of the tech industry‚Äôs burning political takes.</p><p>There was <strong>Josh Wolfe‚Äôs</strong> endorsement waffling. <strong>Jeff Bezos‚Äô </strong>editorial intervention. And the general sense that everyone is losing their minds leading up to what should be Trump‚Äôs last run at the presidency. </p><p>Later in the episode, we break down General Catalyst‚Äôs massive fundraise haul and its transition into a ‚Äúcompany.‚Äù We also discuss Stripe‚Äôs billion-dollar acquisition of Bridge.</p><p><em>Episode produced by <a href="https://x.com/CGates123">Christopher Gates</a></em></p><p><strong>Timestamps:&nbsp;</strong></p><p>00:00 ‚Äî Intro</p><p>04:13 ‚Äî The VC political divide</p><p>09:27 ‚Äî The Washington Post‚Äôs editorial debacle</p><p>12:25 ‚Äî General Catalyst raises $8B</p><p>15:38 ‚Äî Stripe acquires Bridge</p><p><em><strong>Note for our listeners:</strong> We‚Äôll be back with a couple episodes of the Cerebral Valley Podcast starting next week, so stay tuned.</em> </p></body></html>	Tech elites navigate political chaos amid Trump's likely final run. VC firms make big moves with fundraising and acquisitions in uncertain times.	2024-10-29 15:07:39	2024-10-30 07:44:17.111	2024-10-30 07:51:30.763	{ai}	https://chrt.fm/track/71FD71/api.substack.com/feed/podcast/150876382/3962b4854dd54c6e897d7b272ee46c8b.mp3	Eric Newcomer	silicon-valley-cant-look-away
110	https://www.newsletter.datadrivenvc.io/p/founder-personality-and-entrepreneurial	Founder Personality and Entrepreneurial Outcomes	Use Twitter Profiles to Predict Personality to Predict Startup Success	<html><head></head><body><p>üëã&nbsp;<em>Hi, I‚Äôm <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/andreretterath/">Andre</a> and welcome to my newsletter <a href="https://www.newsletter.datadrivenvc.io/">Data-Driven VC</a> which is all about becoming a better investor with Data &amp; AI. Join <strong>28,280 thought leaders</strong> from VCs like a16z, Accel, Index, Sequoia, and more to understand how startup investing becomes more data-driven, why it matters, and what it means for you.</em></p><p class="button-wrapper" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://www.newsletter.datadrivenvc.io/subscribe?&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Subscribe now&quot;,&quot;action&quot;:null,&quot;class&quot;:null}" data-component-name="ButtonCreateButton"><a class="button primary" href="https://www.newsletter.datadrivenvc.io/subscribe?"><span>Subscribe now</span></a></p><div><hr></div><p>Brought to you by <a href="https://www.deckmatch.com/">Deckmatch</a>&nbsp;- Agentic Workflows and APIs for Data-Driven VCs</p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2" target="_blank" href="https://www.deckmatch.com/" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F55555c7f-d5c6-44d8-af44-3db71f9527c9_1632x830.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F55555c7f-d5c6-44d8-af44-3db71f9527c9_1632x830.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F55555c7f-d5c6-44d8-af44-3db71f9527c9_1632x830.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F55555c7f-d5c6-44d8-af44-3db71f9527c9_1632x830.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F55555c7f-d5c6-44d8-af44-3db71f9527c9_1632x830.png" width="1456" height="740" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/55555c7f-d5c6-44d8-af44-3db71f9527c9_1632x830.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:740,&quot;width&quot;:1456,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:634482,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:&quot;https://www.deckmatch.com/&quot;,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;topImage&quot;:true,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" title="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F55555c7f-d5c6-44d8-af44-3db71f9527c9_1632x830.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F55555c7f-d5c6-44d8-af44-3db71f9527c9_1632x830.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F55555c7f-d5c6-44d8-af44-3db71f9527c9_1632x830.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F55555c7f-d5c6-44d8-af44-3db71f9527c9_1632x830.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" fetchpriority="high"></picture><div></div></div></a></figure></div><p>Connect your top-of-funnel to Deckmatch and <em>transform pitch decks and URLs into structured and insightful data</em>. Get detailed firmographic and people data, in-depth competitive and market analysis, and personalized investment memo without lifting a finger. The&nbsp;cherry on the cake? It's all seamlessly synced to your preferred tools like Affinity through our API integrations.</p><p>Never miss a deal, ditch the donkey work, and build meaningful relationships faster.</p><p class="button-wrapper" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://www.deckmatch.com/&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Try Deckmatch&quot;,&quot;action&quot;:null,&quot;class&quot;:null}" data-component-name="ButtonCreateButton"><a class="button primary" href="https://www.deckmatch.com/"><span>Try Deckmatch</span></a></p><div><hr></div><h2>90% of Startups Fail Because of Team Issues</h2><p>I‚Äôve heard this statement in one form or another from mostly every tenured angel and VC investor when asking them about reasons for startup failure. With over 27y of firm history, our team at Earlybird has invested in hundreds of companies and we‚Äôve conducted regular post-mortems on the failed ones, all confirming above statement: <strong>Team is the most prominent reason for failure</strong>. </p><p>Double-clicking on team as the primary reason for failure, we find everything from lack of execution to hiring mistakes. Yet, the <strong>most frequent reason for failure is team conflicts</strong>. </p><p>As a result, experienced investors spend significant time with team DD, be it by spending time together with the founders and their leadership or by referencing them across their networks. In the absence of quantitative and tangible performance data, this is particularly true in the earlier stages.</p><p>Obviously, these team DDs are rarely clear cut and it‚Äôs a lot about gut feeling. While red flags are rare, it‚Äôs incredibly important to be sensible for yellow/orange flags. How does the team interact with each other? Does one always talk and give direction? Do they disagree, and if so, how? </p><p>Being a more quantitative person by nature, getting a sense for team dynamics and trusting my gut has been one of the areas where I probably learned the most as an investor. Despite the learning curve, however, I continued to ask myself over the years whether there was a more objective approach to this problem‚Ä¶</p><p>Fast forward to summer 2022, I joined a panel at a research conference and learned about two interesting research streams that sparked my interest:</p><ol><li><p>Prof Youyou Wu presented her groundbreaking work on how to predict big five character trades for people based on their social media profiles. Thankfully, she agreed to present this work again to our community at our 2024 Virtual Data-Driven VC Summit in May. Recordings can be accessed <a href="https://www.datadrivenvc.io/community">here via ‚ÄúThe Lab‚Äù</a>.</p></li></ol><p class="button-wrapper" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://www.datadrivenvc.io/community&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Access all recordings&quot;,&quot;action&quot;:null,&quot;class&quot;:null}" data-component-name="ButtonCreateButton"><a class="button primary" href="https://www.datadrivenvc.io/community"><span>Access all recordings</span></a></p><ol start="2"><li><p>Someone referenced Prof John Gottman‚Äôs work on marriage research and the ability to predict divorce with 90% accuracy based on conflict behaviour and character trades.</p></li></ol><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2 is-viewable-imag" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2764a226-be22-4934-88dd-99d6fa589332_1000x1222.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2764a226-be22-4934-88dd-99d6fa589332_1000x1222.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2764a226-be22-4934-88dd-99d6fa589332_1000x1222.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2764a226-be22-4934-88dd-99d6fa589332_1000x1222.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2764a226-be22-4934-88dd-99d6fa589332_1000x1222.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2764a226-be22-4934-88dd-99d6fa589332_1000x1222.png" width="1000" height="1222" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/2764a226-be22-4934-88dd-99d6fa589332_1000x1222.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:1222,&quot;width&quot;:1000,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:null,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;Marriage and Couples - Research | The Gottman Institute&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:null,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="Marriage and Couples - Research | The Gottman Institute" title="Marriage and Couples - Research | The Gottman Institute" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2764a226-be22-4934-88dd-99d6fa589332_1000x1222.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2764a226-be22-4934-88dd-99d6fa589332_1000x1222.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2764a226-be22-4934-88dd-99d6fa589332_1000x1222.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2764a226-be22-4934-88dd-99d6fa589332_1000x1222.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a></figure></div><p>Combining these two research streams, I was wondering whether it would be possible to 1. leverage social media profiles of founders to predict their big five character trades (should be straight forward as proven in Youyou Wu‚Äôs work) and then 2. test whether specific character trades (or combinations thereof) among founding teams would predict team conflicts (just like they did in John Gottman‚Äôs marriage work), and thus indirectly startup failure.</p><p>I took this idea to my team at Earlybird and we started a large-scale project with our Engineering (social media profiles to big five character trades) and our portfolio value creation teams (big five character trades to conflicts). Months after emerging into the project, I was lucky that Sebastian, one of our interns, pointed me to a recent paper </p>\n      <p>\n          <a href="https://www.newsletter.datadrivenvc.io/p/founder-personality-and-entrepreneurial">\n              Read more\n          </a>\n      </p>\n   </body></html>	Experienced investors spend significant time on team due diligence, as team conflicts are the most frequent reason for startup failure.	2024-10-10 06:02:10	2024-10-14 08:10:59.657	2024-10-14 09:30:45.381	{vc}	https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ffc0c9505-a984-416a-bfa2-7b76c5d71d60_2266x1174.png	Andre Retterath	founder-personality-and
