6b-8456-0ccf22a1726c_700x40.webp 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0ec2817e-7d9e-456b-8456-0ccf22a1726c_700x40.webp 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0ec2817e-7d9e-456b-8456-0ccf22a1726c_700x40.webp 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div></div></div></a></figure></div><p><strong><a href="https://www.eu.vc/p/from-viral-videos-to-a-250b-empire">From viral videos to a $250B empire: the rise and future of the creator economy</a></strong><br>by <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/laetitia-exertier/?originalSubdomain=uk">Laetitia Exertier</a>, Summer Intern at <a href="https://www.referencecap.com/">Reference Capital</a> | Originally published on üî• <a href="https://medium.com/@ReferenceCapital/reference-newsflash-bb1579e20803">Reference Newsflash.</a></p><p><strong>Why it matters: </strong>The creator economy has grown into a $250B industry, projected to reach $450B by 2027. The sector‚Äôs rapid rise is fueled by Gen Z‚Äôs drive for authenticity and democratized content but faces challenges as investment cools and monetization issues remain. </p><p>Startups are now expected to offer robust off-platform monetization options to ensure creators‚Äô income stability while attracting top talent and managing rapid content turnover. As ‚Äúinfluencers‚Äù and digital creators continue to influence sectors from finance to news, the future hinges on regulatory support and platforms addressing critical needs.</p><p><a href="https://www.eu.vc/p/from-viral-videos-to-a-250b-empire">Read the article here.</a></p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-pos