c%2Fimages%2F504ffc74-ea92-4d48-9470-2c6bd05e9123_3480x1944.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F504ffc74-ea92-4d48-9470-2c6bd05e9123_3480x1944.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F504ffc74-ea92-4d48-9470-2c6bd05e9123_3480x1944.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2"><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a><figcaption class="image-caption">Beijing</figcaption></figure></div><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2 is-viewable-imag" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fba43b8ae-1c6e-4a11-9dfa-d3fd18df39b6_3480x1942.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fba43b8ae-1c6e-4a11-9dfa-d3fd18df39b6_3480x1942.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fba43b8ae-1c6e-4a11-9dfa-d3fd18df39b6_3480x1942.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fba43b8ae-1c6e-4a11-9dfa-d3fd18df39b6_3480x1942.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fba43b8ae-1c6e-4a11-9dfa-d3fd18df39b6_3480x1942.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fba43b8ae-1c6e-4a11-9dfa-d3fd18df39b6_3480x1942.png" width="1456" height="813" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/ba43b8ae-1c6e-4a11-9dfa-d3fd18df39b6_3480x1942.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:813,&quot;width&quot;:1456,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:12403722,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fba43b8ae-1c6e-4a11-9dfa-d3fd18df39b6_3480x1942.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fba43b8ae-1c6e-4a11-9dfa-d3fd18df39b6_3480x1942.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fba43b8ae-1c6e-4a11-9dfa-d3fd18df39b6_3480x1942.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fba43b8ae-1c6e-4a11-9dfa-d3fd18df39b6_3480x1942.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2"><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a><figcaption class="image-caption">Guangzhou-Shenzhen-Hong Kong</figcaption></figure></div><p>You can view any area of the world as seen by Bismarck Brief <a href="https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/1/edit?mid=1FZ22qJhJFj5C5pvpedwLkUCnSc631vE&amp;usp=sharing">here</a>. If you aren‚Äôt already a paid subscriber to Bismarck Brief, I warmly invite you to become one and join us as we create the first-ever atlas of institutions, industries, and live players, with a new in-depth investigation in your inbox every Wednesday at 2pm GMT sharp:</p><p class="button-wrapper" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://brief.bismarckanalysis.com/subscribe?&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Subscribe now&quot;,&quot;action&quot;:null,&quot;class&quot;:null}" data-component-name="ButtonCreateButton"><a class="button primary" href="https://brief.bismarckanalysis.com/subscribe?"><span>Subscribe now</span></a></p><h2><strong>Measuring the Magnitude of Institutional Influence</strong></h2><p>The long-term project of investigating all of the world‚Äôs most strategically relevant institutions is valuable and worthy in and of itself. But it also creates the possibility for new kinds of insights into industries, societies, and civilization as a whole, as compounding case studies result in comparisons and observations that have never been made before, giving rise to useful and illuminating <a href="https://brief.bismarckanalysis.com/p/raytheon-is-now-run-under-the-portfolio">new models and theories</a> in sociology, political science, and economics.</p><p>For example, consider the common assumption that the wealthy exert an undue influence on society through spending lots of money. By this same metric, it is not wealthy individuals who are exerting the greatest influence on society, but government bureaucracies, banks, advertisers, and universities:</p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2 is-viewable-imag" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F07547717-f8f4-4311-811c-ded9dcf1c93f_3597x2396.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F07547717-f8f4-4311-811c-ded9dcf1c93f_3597x2396.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F07547717-f8f4-4311-811c-ded9dcf1c93f_3597x2396.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F07547717-f8f4-4311-811c-ded9dcf1c93f_3597x2396.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F07547717-f8f4-4311-811c-ded9dcf1c93f_3597x2396.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F07547717-f8f4-4311-811c-ded9dcf1c93f_3597x2396.png" width="1456" height="970" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/07547717-f8f4-4311-811c-ded9dcf1c93f_3597x2396.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:970,&quot;width&quot;:1456,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:1166509,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F07547717-f8f4-4311-811c-ded9dcf1c93f_3597x2396.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F07547717-f8f4-4311-811c-ded9dcf1c93f_3597x2396.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F07547717-f8f4-4311-811c-ded9dcf1c93f_3597x2396.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F07547717-f8f4-4311-811c-ded9dcf1c93f_3597x2396.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2"><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a><figcaption class="image-caption">Figure 1. Estimated yearly spending by select institutions, industries, and individuals circa 2024.</figcaption></figure></div><p>Spending by wealthy individuals is quite literally just a drop in the bucket in comparison. Even if Elon Musk‚Äîthe world‚Äôs wealthiest person‚Äîcommitted to spending every last cent of his fortune over the next 25 years, he would still spend less per year than the U.S. federal government is estimated to spend on food aid for sweetened drinks and sodas each year.&nbsp;</p><p>Elite universities spend a staggering $183 billion per year. The prestige print media‚Äîincluding the <a href="https://brief.bismarckanalysis.com/p/the-new-york-times-is-a-family-business">New York Times Company</a>, <em>Wall Street Journal</em>, and Cond√© Nast's publications like <em>Vanity Fair</em> and <em>The New Yorker</em>‚Äîspends at least $9 billion per year on its operations. This is more than Bill Gates spends to influence the world through the <a href="https://brief.bismarckanalysis.com/p/the-gates-foundations-blind-spot">Gates Foundation</a> and far more than any other individual.</p><p>The reason spending by wealthy individuals is put under a microscope is that they comparatively spend too <em>little</em> money. Institutions like bureaucracies, banks, or universities spend enough to be politically indispensable, hiring legions of employees, making or breaking legions of careers, molding the worldviews of legions of educated people, ultimately securing their privileges in law and ritual. In comparison, spending by wealthy people is not just minimal but diffuse, as their particular goals and worldviews diverge widely.</p><p>Individual spending is made in large part by the idiosyncratic decision-making process of a single person or small group, allowing it to be uniquely effective or disruptive. Institutional spending is all done by committee and custom. A large part of perceived influence on society is therefore psychologically miscategorized as coming from the quantity of spending, rather than the quality and unconventionality of it.</p><p>Wealthy individuals who wish to change society must ensure their spending is not a minor trickle feeding into a roaring river of institutional spending that would exist regardless of the spending decisions of individuals. Rather, it is only through creating new, innovative, and unconventional flows that an individual might succeed at altering the landscape of ideas, organizations, and ultimately outcomes. This capability for experimentation is the unique advantage and key societal function of individual spending, and why individuals can exert any influence at all despite the overwhelming‚Äîbut static‚Äîflows of spending that make up society. Far greater effects could be achieved if more wealthy individuals understood this and liberally used their spending power accordingly.</p><p>Another surprising fact about the U.S. economy is that non-profit organizations spend $2.42 trillion every year‚Äîthis is nearly 10% of U.S. GDP and more than the Pentagon and revenues of all the large software companies combined:</p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2 is-viewable-imag" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F619c4a5e-7310-4e58-b721-d33bc80e5e91_3143x2222.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F619c4a5e-7310-4e58-b721-d33bc80e5e91_3143x2222.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F619c4a5e-7310-4e58-b721-d33bc80e5e91_3143x2222.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F619c4a5e-7310-4e58-b721-d33bc80e5e91_3143x2222.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F619c4a5e-7310-4e58-b721-d33bc80e5e91_3143x2222.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F619c4a5e-7310-4e58-b721-d33bc80e5e91_3143x2222.png" width="1456" height="1029" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/619c4a5e-7310-4e58-b721-d33bc80e5e91_3143x2222.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:1029,&quot;width&quot;:1456,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:734119,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F619c4a5e-7310-4e58-b721-d33bc80e5e91_3143x2222.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F619c4a5e-7310-4e58-b721-d33bc80e5e91_3143x2222.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F619c4a5e-7310-4e58-b721-d33bc80e5e91_3143x2222.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F619c4a5e-7310-4e58-b721-d33bc80e5e91_3143x2222.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2"><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a><figcaption class="image-caption">Figure 3. Estimated size of financial flows of select institutions, industries, and individuals circa 2024.</figcaption></figure></div><p>This figure presumably includes many hospitals, universities, and religious organizations, not only think tanks or activist groups. Much of the spending is funded by government grants. But <a href="https://x.com/bismarckanlys/status/1840781279198929182">with</a> 35-45% of U.S. GDP spent by the public sector and perhaps up to another 10% spent by nonprofits, it is possible that a majority of U.S. GDP is spent outside of the market, without regard to market signals or forces. It is perhaps time to rethink what we call this economic system.</p><p>My goal is to exhaustively investigate the entire global landscape of live players, key institutions, new technologies, and important industries. This does not mean, however, that the Brief must have a definite end-point. The world is not static, and many future Briefs will undoubtedly be updates on institutions and live players investigated before. As a rule of thumb, I aim for a Brief to be immediately relevant for two years after being issued, and due for an update after four years. Though we are still at least a year away from the four-year anniversary of our very first Briefs, I am already looking forward to again investigating the progress of <a href="https://brief.bismarckanalysis.com/p/the-long-march-into-space">China‚Äôs space industry</a>, <a href="https://brief.bismarckanalysis.com/p/photovoltaics-give-credibility-to">the ongoing revolution in solar power</a>, <a href="https://brief.bismarckanalysis.com/p/turkeys-drone-industry-changes-airpower">Turkey‚Äôs innovative drones</a>, and more.</p><p>If you aren‚Äôt already a paid subscriber, I warmly invite you to become one and join us as we create the first-ever atlas of institutions, industries, and live players, with a new in-depth investigation in your inbox every Wednesday at 2pm GMT sharp:</p><p class="button-wrapper" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://brief.bismarckanalysis.com/subscribe?&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Subscribe now&quot;,&quot;action&quot;:null,&quot;class&quot;:null}" data-component-name="ButtonCreateButton"><a class="button primary" href="https://brief.bismarckanalysis.com/subscribe?"><span>Subscribe now</span></a></p><p>If you haven‚Äôt already, I also warmly invite you to read our recent analyses of <a href="https://brief.bismarckanalysis.com/p/bismarck-brief-outperforms-the-stock">how Bismarck Brief outperforms the S&amp;P 500</a> and <a href="https://brief.bismarckanalysis.com/p/the-theory-of-civilization-behind">how Great Founder Theory informs</a> every Bismarck Brief.</p><p>Sincerely,</p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc315e815-d2c6-4a37-b867-337d1b83c48d_768x432.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc315e815-d2c6-4a37-b867-337d1b83c48d_768x432.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc315e815-d2c6-4a37-b867-337d1b83c48d_768x432.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc315e815-d2c6-4a37-b867-337d1b83c48d_768x432.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc315e815-d2c6-4a37-b867-337d1b83c48d_768x432.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc315e815-d2c6-4a37-b867-337d1b83c48d_768x432.png" width="360" height="202.5" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/c315e815-d2c6-4a37-b867-337d1b83c48d_768x432.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:432,&quot;width&quot;:768,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:360,&quot;bytes&quot;:29331,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc315e815-d2c6-4a37-b867-337d1b83c48d_768x432.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc315e815-d2c6-4a37-b867-337d1b83c48d_768x432.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc315e815-d2c6-4a37-b867-337d1b83c48d_768x432.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc315e815-d2c6-4a37-b867-337d1b83c48d_768x432.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div></div></div></a></figure></div><p></p><p>Samo Burja</p><p>Founder and President, Bismarck Analysis</p></body></html>	Global institutions wield massive influence through trillion-dollar budgets. Interactive maps reveal networks of power across industries and organizations worldwide.	2024-10-28 15:01:37	2024-10-30 07:44:10.72	2024-10-30 07:51:30.763	{ai}	https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F1c6fd1c5-3dbe-43b6-8dde-509fc65cd7b2_3500x1928.png	Samo Burja	the-atlas-of-live-players-and
237	https://tidyfirst.substack.com/p/background-work	Background Work	First published Dec 8, 2021.	<html><head></head><body><blockquote><p>First published Dec 8, 2021. The topic of background work came up in the context of the way LLMs make such work so much cheaper than it used to be. The same rabbit hole that would have taken a week to explore can now be excavated in an hour or a minute. Background work should become more prevalent.</p></blockquote><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7429fc0a-1776-4fe5-9284-c8082dbdc617_300x200.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7429fc0a-1776-4fe5-9284-c8082dbdc617_300x200.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7429fc0a-1776-4fe5-9284-c8082dbdc617_300x200.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7429fc0a-1776-4fe5-9284-c8082dbdc617_300x200.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7429fc0a-1776-4fe5-9284-c8082dbdc617_300x200.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7429fc0a-1776-4fe5-9284-c8082dbdc617_300x200.jpeg" width="300" height="200" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/7429fc0a-1776-4fe5-9284-c8082dbdc617_300x200.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:200,&quot;width&quot;:300,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:null,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;Archaeologist working carefully&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:null,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;topImage&quot;:true,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="Archaeologist working carefully" title="Archaeologist working carefully" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7429fc0a-1776-4fe5-9284-c8082dbdc617_300x200.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7429fc0a-1776-4fe5-9284-c8082dbdc617_300x200.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7429fc0a-1776-4fe5-9284-c8082dbdc617_300x200.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7429fc0a-1776-4fe5-9284-c8082dbdc617_300x200.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" fetchpriority="high"></picture><div></div></div></a></figure></div><p>A student had a code review where the reviewer said, ‚ÄúThis variable needs to be explicitly initialized to nil.‚Äù The usual course for a junior engineer would be to change the code. Instead, the student did some research, then responded, ‚ÄúAccording to the language spec, the variable is initialized automatically.‚Äù That research was more work than strictly called for but it created value for both parties.</p><p>‚ÄúBackground Work‚Äù is the work you do over and above what is strictly required to complete a task. It may be done for learning, to satisfy curiosity, or just because you forgot to stop working when you were done. I‚Äôve noticed that the most accomplished programmers make a habit of background work.</p><p>When I saw the exchange above it brought to mind times when I have seen engineers I admire dig into the background of a topic. ‚ÄúI wrote a little prototype PHP-to-JavaScript translator and here‚Äôs the performance data,‚Äù ‚ÄúI thought this might come up, so I re-read Knuth on the topic,‚Äù ‚ÄúI wasn‚Äôt sure what I thought so I wrote this essay.‚Äù</p><p>At first I was going to call this, ‚Äúextra work,‚Äù conjuring visions of late nights and weekends, but on reflection that‚Äôs a misleading name. First, leaders seem good at managing their energy, so if they do some background work ‚Äúoff the clock‚Äù, they find ways to recharge. Background work also has a habit of paying off quickly, so that the leader accomplishes more in the ensuing day or week or month.</p><p>My own experience of background work, though, is that sometimes my curiosity gets the best of me at inopportune times, like 4 AM, and I need to just go do the work. Greek rhetoric teaches that persuasion comes from a combination of ethos, logos, and pathos, appealing to listeners on the basis of personal credibility, logic, and emotion. Background work levels up logos but I think its biggest effect is in establishing credibility, ethos. Someone who habitually digs deeper than strictly necessary is worth listening to. When they know, they will speak with authority. When they don‚Äôt know, they‚Äôll say so and then, if they are curious, go do the work to find out.</p></body></html>	Going beyond minimum requirements builds expertise. Extra research and curiosity-driven exploration create lasting value. Deep diggers earn respect and credibility.	2024-10-28 13:40:50	2024-10-30 07:44:01.249	2024-10-30 07:51:30.763	{ai}	\N	Kent Beck	background
186	https://www.eu.vc/p/why-social-impact-investing-needs	Why social impact investing needs a radical rethink for true change	Guest post by Til Klein, Founding Partner at identity.vc.	<html><head></head><body><p>Guest post by <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/tilklein/">Til Klein</a>, Founding Partner at <a href="https://identity.vc/">identity.vc.</a> | Originally published on <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/pulse/why-social-impact-investing-needs-radical-rethink-klein--snc1e/?trackingId=VwCJmZp2SMauXGHcraqS6A%3D%3D">Linkedin</a>.</p><div><hr></div><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2 is-viewable-imag" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F20b5c01d-cc18-4d9f-afd2-4658935d6f8c_1920x1080.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F20b5c01d-cc18-4d9f-afd2-4658935d6f8c_1920x1080.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F20b5c01d-cc18-4d9f-afd2-4658935d6f8c_1920x1080.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F20b5c01d-cc18-4d9f-afd2-4658935d6f8c_1920x1080.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F20b5c01d-cc18-4d9f-afd2-4658935d6f8c_1920x1080.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F20b5c01d-cc18-4d9f-afd2-4658935d6f8c_1920x1080.png" width="1456" height="819" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/20b5c01d-cc18-4d9f-afd2-4658935d6f8c_1920x1080.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:819,&quot;width&quot;:1456,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:1358709,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;topImage&quot;:true,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F20b5c01d-cc18-4d9f-afd2-4658935d6f8c_1920x1080.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F20b5c01d-cc18-4d9f-afd2-4658935d6f8c_1920x1080.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F20b5c01d-cc18-4d9f-afd2-4658935d6f8c_1920x1080.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F20b5c01d-cc18-4d9f-afd2-4658935d6f8c_1920x1080.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" fetchpriority="high"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a></figure></div><p>Everyone is talking about ESG investment. But let‚Äôs be honest: most of the excitement is focused on the ‚ÄúE‚Äù‚Äîthe environment. Billions of dollars are flowing into climate tech, clean energy, and sustainability initiatives, creating a tidal wave of innovation. Meanwhile, the ‚ÄúS‚Äù for social impact remains in the shadows, struggling to gain momentum.</p><p>But I‚Äôm not talking about charitable causes or philanthropic efforts. I‚Äôm talking about economically motivated investments aimed at driving real social change. Social impact, in this context, is about creating fair representation for minorities and equal opportunities for disadvantaged groups. It‚Äôs about ensuring that women, LGBTQ+ individuals, immigrants, and people with disabilities have the same opportunities in the economy as everyone else.</p><p>Yet, despite the urgency and potential for transformation, social impact investing lags far behind green investing. So why isn‚Äôt social investing taking off?</p><h3>The Flawed Theory of Change</h3><p>One major reason is the flawed theory of change that guides most social impact investors. The prevailing approach is to invest only in companies whose core business is directly focused on social issues. For example, these might be companies that address specific health disparities for minorities, or platforms that help underrepresented groups access the labor or financial markets. These ventures are important, and their work is undeniably worthy of support.</p><p>But there‚Äôs a limit to how far these companies can go. These businesses often scale slowly, constrained by their niche focus, and while they address symptoms of inequality, they rarely tackle the underlying structural problems that perpetuate it. As a result, their economic attractiveness is limited, and so is their overall social impact.</p><h3>The Real Leverage Lies Elsewhere</h3><p>If social impact investors want to create both substantial social change and achieve strong returns, they need to shift their focus. The real leverage lies in supporting underrepresented and disadvantaged groups within the mainstream economy.</p><p>Instead of restricting investment to businesses that directly focus on social issues, investors should back companies with diverse leadership teams, invest in founders from underrepresented backgrounds, and support organizations that integrate diversity into their operations. This approach creates a win-win: it is not only economically attractive but also drives meaningful, systemic change.</p><h3>Why This Approach Works</h3><p>Studies consistently show that diverse teams perform better. Research has found that companies with greater gender, ethnic, and racial diversity in their leadership teams are more likely to outperform their peers financially. Investing in diversity is not just the right thing to do‚Äîit‚Äôs a smart business decision.</p><p>Supporting diverse founders and teams doesn‚Äôt just help the individuals involved. It creates ripple effects throughout society. By ensuring that underrepresented and disadvantaged groups are fairly represented in leadership positions and mainstream businesses, we address the root causes of inequality. These investments can shift industries, influence corporate cultures, and create broader opportunities for the next generation of entrepreneurs and workers.</p><h3>The Future of Social Impact Investing</h3><p>To unlock this potential, social impact investors need to rethink their theory of change. It‚Äôs not enough to focus on niche solutions or businesses that operate on the fringes of the economy. The real transformation comes from making diversity and inclusion a core part of investment decisions across all sectors.</p><p>Imagine a world where social impact is not confined to niche projects but is integrated into the DNA of every business. A world where diverse leadership is the norm, and where underrepresented founders have equal access to capital and resources. This is the future we should be investing in‚Äînot only because it‚Äôs the right thing to do but because it makes good economic sense.</p><h3>The Breakthrough</h3><p>For social impact investing to truly take off, we need to expand the scope of what social change looks like. Investors must realize that supporting diversity in the mainstream economy holds the greatest potential for both financial returns and lasting social impact. By shifting their theory of change, social impact investors can create a broader, more inclusive economy that benefits everyone.</p><div><hr></div><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc2e93607-5191-4afb-b94b-51d0b094363e_1100x220.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc2e93607-5191-4afb-b94b-51d0b094363e_1100x220.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc2e93607-5191-4afb-b94b-51d0b094363e_1100x220.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc2e93607-5191-4afb-b94b-51d0b094363e_1100x220.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc2e93607-5191-4afb-b94b-51d0b094363e_1100x220.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc2e93607-5191-4afb-b94b-51d0b094363e_1100x220.png" width="1100" height="220" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/c2e93607-5191-4afb-b94b-51d0b094363e_1100x220.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:220,&quot;width&quot;:1100,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:60754,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" title="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc2e93607-5191-4afb-b94b-51d0b094363e_1100x220.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc2e93607-5191-4afb-b94b-51d0b094363e_1100x220.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc2e93607-5191-4afb-b94b-51d0b094363e_1100x220.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc2e93607-5191-4afb-b94b-51d0b094363e_1100x220.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div></div></div></a><figcaption class="image-caption"><strong>Wanna be featured on eu.vc? Learn how <a href="https://www.eu.vc/p/submit-your-contribution-to-unfiltered">here.</a></strong></figcaption></figure></div></body></html>	Social impact investing needs to shift its focus from niche solutions to supporting diversity in the mainstream economy for greater financial returns and lasting social impact.	2024-10-16 23:17:36	2024-10-20 19:34:57.84	2024-10-20 19:51:05.858	{vc}	https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F20b5c01d-cc18-4d9f-afd2-4658935d6f8c_1920x1080.png	anon	why-social-impact-investing
143	https://www.eu.vc/p/the-aec-tech-internet-index-by-foundamental	The AEC-Tech Internet Index by Foundamental	by Patric Hellermann, General Partner at Foundamental. | Originally published on Foundamental.	<html><head></head><body><p>Guest post by <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/aecvc/">Patric Hellermann</a>, General Partner at <a href="https://www.foundamental.com/">Foundamental</a>. | Originally published on <a href="https://www.foundamental.com/perspectives/internetindex">Foundamental</a>.</p><div><hr></div><p>The largest web traffic and trends analysis for ventures in architecture, engineering, and construction (AEC) technology ever done worldwide. Contains hundreds of the most-funded AEC-Tech startups and scale-ups. </p><p>The index is published monthly, and you can see a preview below. For the complete and updated version of the index, please <a href="https://www.foundamental.com/perspectives/internetindex">read the full version on Foundamental blog</a>.</p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2 is-viewable-imag" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7548ac34-1ce3-4072-b771-0f441ba87359_800x533.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7548ac34-1ce3-4072-b771-0f441ba87359_800x533.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7548ac34-1ce3-4072-b771-0f441ba87359_800x533.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7548ac34-1ce3-4072-b771-0f441ba87359_800x533.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7548ac34-1ce3-4072-b771-0f441ba87359_800x533.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7548ac34-1ce3-4072-b771-0f441ba87359_800x533.png" width="800" height="533" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/7548ac34-1ce3-4072-b771-0f441ba87359_800x533.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:533,&quot;width&quot;:800,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:21907,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:null,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;topImage&quot;:true,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7548ac34-1ce3-4072-b771-0f441ba87359_800x533.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7548ac34-1ce3-4072-b771-0f441ba87359_800x533.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7548ac34-1ce3-4072-b771-0f441ba87359_800x533.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7548ac34-1ce3-4072-b771-0f441ba87359_800x533.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" fetchpriority="high"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a></figure></div><h4><strong>The AEC-Tech Internet Index:&nbsp;What It Does</strong></h4><p>We use data to shine light on AEC-Technology-related trends we focus on. Here, our data is objective internet traffic for hundreds of startups and scale-ups in architecture, engineering and construction (AEC) technology. Internet traffic gives us non-arbitrary, transparent and robust data points we can use to estimate various trends in AEC-Technology and Construction-Tech, eg. how widespread demand, mindshare and even brand is for venture categories and specific companies in AEC-Tech.</p><p>We hope the community takes the ideas, builds on them, makes them better. We ignore arbitrary 'best-of' lists and 'market maps' propagated by venture pundits.</p><div><hr></div><h3><strong>Risers of the Month</strong></h3><p><em>As a monthly summary, the following charts show the 10 fastest rising AEC ventures in web traffic in the last month, and the most consistently growing AEC ventures over the past 12 months.</em></p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2 is-viewable-imag" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ff17e33dd-28cd-436a-bd52-88d50fc662db_969x729.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ff17e33dd-28cd-436a-bd52-88d50fc662db_969x729.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ff17e33dd-28cd-436a-bd52-88d50fc662db_969x729.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ff17e33dd-28cd-436a-bd52-88d50fc662db_969x729.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ff17e33dd-28cd-436a-bd52-88d50fc662db_969x729.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ff17e33dd-28cd-436a-bd52-88d50fc662db_969x729.png" width="969" height="729" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/f17e33dd-28cd-436a-bd52-88d50fc662db_969x729.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:729,&quot;width&quot;:969,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:77446,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ff17e33dd-28cd-436a-bd52-88d50fc662db_969x729.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ff17e33dd-28cd-436a-bd52-88d50fc662db_969x729.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ff17e33dd-28cd-436a-bd52-88d50fc662db_969x729.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ff17e33dd-28cd-436a-bd52-88d50fc662db_969x729.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a></figure></div><div><hr></div><h3><strong>Category Trends</strong></h3><p><em>For each of our AEC-Tech categories, the following charts identify venture Stars and Dogs in terms of their absolute web traffic scale in the last month mapped against their average monthly growth rate in web traffic.</em></p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2 is-viewable-imag" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2faf621a-1662-4051-be26-0e905b24d07a_954x682.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2faf621a-1662-4051-be26-0e905b24d07a_954x682.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2faf621a-1662-4051-be26-0e905b24d07a_954x682.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2faf621a-1662-4051-be26-0e905b24d07a_954x682.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2faf621a-1662-4051-be26-0e905b24d07a_954x682.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2faf621a-1662-4051-be26-0e905b24d07a_954x682.png" width="954" height="682" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/2faf621a-1662-4051-be26-0e905b24d07a_954x682.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:682,&quot;width&quot;:954,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:114576,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2faf621a-1662-4051-be26-0e905b24d07a_954x682.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2faf621a-1662-4051-be26-0e905b24d07a_954x682.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2faf621a-1662-4051-be26-0e905b24d07a_954x682.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2faf621a-1662-4051-be26-0e905b24d07a_954x682.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a></figure></div><div><hr></div><h3><strong>Venture Trends</strong></h3><p><em>For each of our AEC-Tech categories, the following charts identify the trending web traffic per AEC venture from today, over the last 6 months and over the last 12 months.</em></p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2 is-viewable-imag" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F42f3f7ff-3b83-4b62-a634-801173281745_944x710.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F42f3f7ff-3b83-4b62-a634-801173281745_944x710.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F42f3f7ff-3b83-4b62-a634-801173281745_944x710.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F42f3f7ff-3b83-4b62-a634-801173281745_944x710.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F42f3f7ff-3b83-4b62-a634-801173281745_944x710.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F42f3f7ff-3b83-4b62-a634-801173281745_944x710.png" width="944" height="710" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/42f3f7ff-3b83-4b62-a634-801173281745_944x710.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:710,&quot;width&quot;:944,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:81940,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F42f3f7ff-3b83-4b62-a634-801173281745_944x710.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F42f3f7ff-3b83-4b62-a634-801173281745_944x710.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F42f3f7ff-3b83-4b62-a634-801173281745_944x710.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F42f3f7ff-3b83-4b62-a634-801173281745_944x710.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a></figure></div><div><hr></div><h3><strong>Mindshare Winners</strong></h3><p><em>For each of our AEC-Tech categories, the following charts identify the share of web traffic per AEC venture in its category.</em></p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2 is-viewable-imag" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F48ce1df1-b9a9-49fc-8b59-8a0c3b3ceaa5_979x716.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F48ce1df1-b9a9-49fc-8b59-8a0c3b3ceaa5_979x716.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F48ce1df1-b9a9-49fc-8b59-8a0c3b3ceaa5_979x716.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F48ce1df1-b9a9-49fc-8b59-8a0c3b3ceaa5_979x716.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F48ce1df1-b9a9-49fc-8b59-8a0c3b3ceaa5_979x716.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F48ce1df1-b9a9-49fc-8b59-8a0c3b3ceaa5_979x716.png" width="979" height="716" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/48ce1df1-b9a9-49fc-8b59-8a0c3b3ceaa5_979x716.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:716,&quot;width&quot;:979,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:89056,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F48ce1df1-b9a9-49fc-8b59-8a0c3b3ceaa5_979x716.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F48ce1df1-b9a9-49fc-8b59-8a0c3b3ceaa5_979x716.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F48ce1df1-b9a9-49fc-8b59-8a0c3b3ceaa5_979x716.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F48ce1df1-b9a9-49fc-8b59-8a0c3b3ceaa5_979x716.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a></figure></div><div><hr></div><h3><strong>Previous Editions: Archive</strong></h3><p>Preserved for posterity, you can access all previous Editions from past months and years of the AEC-Tech Internet Index here:</p><p><a href="https://foundamental.com/InternetIndex/archive">foundamental.com/InternetIndex/archive</a></p><div><hr></div><h3><strong>Methodology</strong></h3><p><strong>Scope</strong>: Foundamental's AEC-Tech Internet Index includes AEC-Tech startups and scale-ups across the globe from North America, Asia (exc. China), Oceania, Europe, Africa and Latin America. founded in 2010 or after, who raised at least a publicly-known total of $25 Million in equity funding. and who did not exit or deadpool before 2019. The Index excludes ventures that are predominantly prop-tech, building operations or logistics-only, or those that have a massive share of their online traffic/visits through an app (instead of website). If the venture is direct-to-consumer (D2C) in AEC, it must show service-components to be considered in scope - eg. Houzz is not in scope for this reason.</p><p><strong>Sources</strong>: The primary data source for the AEC-Tech Internet Index is un-altered Semrush data. The data is updated monthly around the 10th day of each month. Semrush is widely regarded as accurate and reliable in web traffic analysis. While no web traffic analysis is perfectly correct - not even your own instance of Google Analytics - Semrush provides one of the most accurate estimates across the web. The latest version of Foundamental's AEC-Tech Internet Index is always available on <a href="http://foundamental.com/InternetIndex">foundamental.com/InternetIndex</a>, and is also published monthly on Patric Hellermann's Linkedin at <a href="http://linkedin.com/in/aecvc/">linkedin.com/in/aecvc/</a>.</p><div><hr></div><h3><strong>List: AEC-Tech Ventures Contained in this Edition</strong></h3><p>011h.com, adaptive.build, aeroaggna.com, alicetechnologies.com, ambar.tech, andpad.jp, arisinfra.com, assemblyosm.com, assignar.com, billd.com, biomason.com, blockrenovation.com, blokable.com, boringcompany.com, bosscathome.com, boxabl.com, brimstone.com, briq.com, buildcover.com, buildots.com, buildxact.com, builtrobotics.com, capmo.com, carboncure.com, cleanfiber.com, clearstory.build, companycam.com, convex.com, cosuno.com, cove.tools, curbio.com, diamondage3d.com, disperse.io, doxel.ai, dozr.com, dustyrobotics.com, dvele.com, earthgrid.io, ecoworks.tech, enter.de, equipmentshare.com, ergeon.com, factoryos.com, fieldwire.com, finalcad.com, forgeco.com, forteraglobal.com, fyld.ai, getbuilt.com, gobridgit.com, hammertech.com, hero-software.de, higharc.com, homebound.com, hover.to, iconbuild.com, infra.market, inspectpoint.com, jobnimbus.com, join.build, katerra.com, klarx.de, livspace.com, locusview.com, maderenovation.com, manomano.com, materialbank.com, materrup.com, metalbook.co.in, mightybuildings.com, moglix.com, monumental.co, mosaic.us, neustark.com, nexii.com, ofbusiness.com, onsiteiq.io, openspace.ai, permitflow.com, petra.cc, planradar.com, plantprefab.com, powerus.de, pro.com, reconstructinc.com, reibus.com, remihq.com, renorun.com, rhumbix.com, rombit.com, roofr.com, safeai.ai, samara.com, schuettflix.com, screeningeagle.com, sealed.com, sensat.co, siteaware.com, sitetracker.com, snaptrude.com, solidiatech.com, spacemakerai.com, stackct.com, sublime-systems.com, tenderd.com, terraco2.com, trunktools.com, urbint.com, usekojo.com, veev.com, versatile.ai, volue.com, welcomehomes.com, xyzreality.com, zetwerk.com</p><div><hr></div><h3><strong>AEC-Tech Categories Explained</strong></h3><p><strong>Digital General Contractors and Standardized Building Development:</strong> This AEC-Tech category contains ventures that focus on digital platforms to streamline the construction process and standardize building methods for enhanced efficiency and repeatability.</p><p><strong>Financial Services and Embedded Finance:</strong> This AEC-Tech category contains ventures that offer financial solutions, such as project financing, material financing, invoice financing, payment processing, and insurance, specifically tailored for the AEC industry and sometimes integrated into existing workflows.</p><p><strong>Marketplaces:</strong> This AEC-Tech category contains ventures that create tech-enabled platforms connecting buyers and suppliers of construction materials, equipment, labor and services to facilitate and fulfill easier procurement and bidding processes.</p><p><strong>Outcome-as-a-Service (OaaS):</strong> This AEC-Tech category contains ventures that provide performance-based services where clients pay for specific outcomes, such as energy efficiency or building design services, rather than SaaS-only.</p><p><strong>Resource-Efficient Materials and Processes:</strong> This AEC-Tech category contains ventures that develop innovative materials and processes designed to reduce CO2, GHG, waste, and overall enhance sustainability in construction and its supply chains.</p><p><strong>Robotics and (Autonomous) Hardware:</strong> This AEC-Tech category contains ventures that focus on developing robots, autonomous machinery, telematics and other hardware to automate and optimize various construction tasks.</p><p><strong>SaaS - Enterprise and Mid-Market - As-Built &amp; Inspection:</strong> This AEC-Tech category contains ventures that provide software solutions for capturing as-built conditions and managing inspections throughout the construction lifecycle.</p><p><strong>SaaS - Enterprise and Mid-Market - Design &amp; Planning:</strong> This AEC-Tech category contains ventures that develop software platforms to assist in the design and planning phases of construction projects, including CAD, BIM, 3D, 2D and scheduling tools.</p><p><strong>SaaS - Enterprise and Mid-Market - Procurement &amp; Estimation:</strong> This AEC-Tech category contains ventures that offer software to streamline the procurement process and improve cost estimation accuracy for large and mid-sized construction firms.</p><p><strong>SaaS - Enterprise and Mid-Market - Workflows &amp; Resources:</strong> This AEC-Tech category contains ventures that provide software solutions aimed at enhancing project management, resource allocation, and workflow management across the construction industry.</p><p><strong>SaaS - Small Businesses and Freelancers:</strong> This AEC-Tech category contains ventures that develop software tools specifically tailored to the needs of small construction businesses and independent contractors, with a focus on modularity, ease of use and often a deep verticalization.</p><div><hr></div><h3><strong>About Foundamental</strong></h3><p>We here at <a href="https://www.foundamental.com/">Foundamental</a> are the largest global venture investor for AEC-Technology. We currently manage $250M+ in venture capital and we invest in AEC-Technology, including Construction-Tech, since 2019, currently from our third fund. We invest globally across US, APAC, EU.</p><p>As on early backer of AEC category creating ventures such as eg. <a href="https://infra.market/">InfraMarket</a>, <a href="https://snaptrude.com/">Snaptrude</a>, <a href="https://rayon.design/">Rayon</a>, <a href="https://www.monumental.co/">Monumental</a>, <a href="https://enter.de/">Enter</a>, <a href="https://www.mightybuildings.com/">Mighty Buildings</a>, <a href="https://www.safeai.ai/">SafeAI</a>, <a href="https://welcomehomes.com/">Welcome</a>, <a href="https://www.permitflow.com/">Permitflow</a>, <a href="https://www.011h.com/">011h</a> or <a href="https://graneet.com/">Graneet</a>, we have seen our share of trends, categories and data across the AEC&nbsp;startup and technology landscape. We use our global investor perspective to shine light on technology-related trends in the AEC-Tech Internet Index.</p><div><hr></div><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc2e93607-5191-4afb-b94b-51d0b094363e_1100x220.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc2e93607-5191-4afb-b94b-51d0b094363e_1100x220.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc2e93607-5191-4afb-b94b-51d0b094363e_1100x220.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc2e93607-5191-4afb-b94b-51d0b094363e_1100x220.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc2e93607-5191-4afb-b94b-51d0b094363e_1100x220.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc2e93607-5191-4afb-b94b-51d0b094363e_1100x220.png" width="1100" height="220" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/c2e93607-5191-4afb-b94b-51d0b094363e_1100x220.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:220,&quot;width&quot;:1100,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:60754,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" title="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc2e93607-5191-4afb-b94b-51d0b094363e_1100x220.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc2e93607-5191-4afb-b94b-51d0b094363e_1100x220.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc2e93607-5191-4afb-b94b-51d0b094363e_1100x220.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc2e93607-5191-4afb-b94b-51d0b094363e_1100x220.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div></div></div></a><figcaption class="image-caption"><strong>Wanna be featured on eu.vc? Learn how <a href="https://www.eu.vc/p/submit-your-contribution-to-unfiltered">here.</a></strong></figcaption></figure></div></body></html>	Comprehensive data and analysis on the largest web traffic and trends for ventures in architecture, engineering, and construction (AEC) technology.	2024-10-11 14:22:58	2024-10-14 08:19:44.426	2024-10-14 09:20:44.198	{vc}	https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7548ac34-1ce3-4072-b771-0f441ba87359_800x533.png	anon	the-aec-tech-internet-index-by
142	https://www.eu.vc/p/maternity-in-venture-capital-7-in	Maternity in Venture Capital: 7 in 10 Women Concerned About the Return to Work	by Sophie Winwood, co-founder & CEO of WVC:E.	<html><head></head><body><p>Guest post by <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/sophie-winwood-92526241/">Sophie Winwood</a>, co-founder &amp; CEO of <a href="https://www.wvce.tech/">WVC:E</a>. </p><div><hr></div><p><strong>Key highlights from the report:</strong></p><ul><li><p>A new report from WVC:E shares the untold stories of mothers in venture capital.&nbsp;</p></li><li><p>120 women in VC from almost 20 countries and funds ranging from less than ‚Ç¨50M to upwards of ‚Ç¨500M were surveyed for the report - 80 per cent of whom are already mothers.</p></li><li><p>Respondents' top three main concerns were career progression, the long-term sustainability of working in VC as a parent and establishing boundaries around work.&nbsp;</p></li><li><p>84 per cent of women surveyed shared that parental leave, both time off and the level of pay, was a concern.</p></li></ul><div><hr></div><p><strong>London, UK. 10th October 2024: </strong><a href="https://www.wvce.tech/">WVC:E</a> has shared a critical report and survey results into motherhood and venture capital. <em>‚Äò<a href="https://www.wvce.tech/maternityreport24">Investing in Women: The Untold Stories of Mothers in VC</a>‚Äô</em> has gathered insights and data from women across European venture capital, analysed parental leave and pay policies across Europe, and interviewed 20 female VCs to present the challenges of navigating VC as a mother.&nbsp;</p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2 is-viewable-imag" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F174e0deb-cc1a-4c1a-99fb-b0050578139f_603x868.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F174e0deb-cc1a-4c1a-99fb-b0050578139f_603x868.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F174e0deb-cc1a-4c1a-99fb-b0050578139f_603x868.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F174e0deb-cc1a-4c1a-99fb-b0050578139f_603x868.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F174e0deb-cc1a-4c1a-99fb-b0050578139f_603x868.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F174e0deb-cc1a-4c1a-99fb-b0050578139f_603x868.png" width="603" height="868" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/174e0deb-cc1a-4c1a-99fb-b0050578139f_603x868.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:868,&quot;width&quot;:603,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:357082,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;topImage&quot;:true,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F174e0deb-cc1a-4c1a-99fb-b0050578139f_603x868.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F174e0deb-cc1a-4c1a-99fb-b0050578139f_603x868.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F174e0deb-cc1a-4c1a-99fb-b0050578139f_603x868.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F174e0deb-cc1a-4c1a-99fb-b0050578139f_603x868.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" fetchpriority="high"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a></figure></div><p class="button-wrapper" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://www.wvce.tech/maternityreport24&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Read the report here&quot;,&quot;action&quot;:null,&quot;class&quot;:null}" data-component-name="ButtonCreateButton"><a class="button primary" href="https://www.wvce.tech/maternityreport24"><span>Read the report here</span></a></p><p>Data from 120 respondents from 20 European countries and various fund sizes has revealed the following.</p><ul><li><p>Over two-thirds (71 per cent) of women planning on having children or more children were concerned about returning to work in venture capital, and one in five respondents (20 per cent) were very concerned.&nbsp;</p></li><li><p>Almost 80 per cent of respondents felt there was room for improvement in their return to work process, and just over one in three (38 per cent) said there was considerable room for improvement.</p></li><li><p>The top three concerns shared by respondents were career progression/promotion opportunities (32 per cent), the long-term sustainability of working in VC and parenting (25 per cent), and establishing boundaries, e.g., evening events (23 per cent).</p></li><li><p>84 per cent of respondents were concerned about parental leave (the amount of time off or the pay level).&nbsp;</p></li></ul><p>The venture capital industry remains male-dominated despite relatively rapid progress in recent decades. Women comprise 16 per cent of European General Partners, and women comprise only a third of investing teams. In the UK, there has been no change in the gender composition of teams since 2019, with female representation flat at 30 per cent.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Sophie Winwood, CEO of WVC:E, said: </strong></p><div class="pullquote"><p>‚ÄúThe findings in this report shine a light on the unique challenges women face in venture capital, especially when balancing motherhood with the demands of the industry. </p><p>Our goal is not to place blame but to foster understanding and inspire meaningful change. By sharing these experiences, we hope to offer valuable insights, spark important conversations, and drive action across the wider ecosystem ‚Äî in workplaces, homes, and communities. </p><p>It's time to rethink how we support women and build an environment where they can thrive without choosing between career and family.‚Äù</p></div><p><strong>Ruth Foxe Blader, GP of Foxe Capital and Chair of WVC:E, said:</strong></p><div class="pullquote"><p>‚ÄúMaternity and early childcare policy is critical infrastructure needed to rectify employment and pay inequity. But it‚Äôs totally taboo!&nbsp; </p><p>The social dimension is almost more important than the statutory. This report talks about it honestly and all of its complexity.‚Äù</p></div><p><strong>Check Warner, co-founding Partner Ada Ventures and co-founder of Diversity VC, said:</strong></p><div class="pullquote"><p>‚ÄúThe concerning stats in this report should be a wake-up call for the VC industry where parents, particularly women, have been massively let down. Unfortunately, the findings in this report chime with the stories of numerous women who have children when working in VC and have felt completely unsupported by the funds they work for. This is a big missed opportunity, as VC should be compatible with having a family. </p><p>If we as an industry don‚Äôt fix this, we will miss out on the best talent and, therefore, the best returns for investors.‚Äù&nbsp;</p></div><p>The report explores women‚Äôs concerns around parental leave and the differences between men's and women‚Äôs leave, returning to work and setting boundaries regarding policies and practices. It highlights some of these challenges' impacts and offers practical tips on navigating them. The report concludes with recommendations for partners, colleagues, General Partners and the community to improve the status quo for women, men and the industry overall.&nbsp;</p><div><hr></div><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc2e93607-5191-4afb-b94b-51d0b094363e_1100x220.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc2e93607-5191-4afb-b94b-51d0b094363e_1100x220.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc2e93607-5191-4afb-b94b-51d0b094363e_1100x220.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc2e93607-5191-4afb-b94b-51d0b094363e_1100x220.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc2e93607-5191-4afb-b94b-51d0b094363e_1100x220.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc2e93607-5191-4afb-b94b-51d0b094363e_1100x220.png" width="1100" height="220" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/c2e93607-5191-4afb-b94b-51d0b094363e_1100x220.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:220,&quot;width&quot;:1100,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:60754,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" title="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc2e93607-5191-4afb-b94b-51d0b094363e_1100x220.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc2e93607-5191-4afb-b94b-51d0b094363e_1100x220.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc2e93607-5191-4afb-b94b-51d0b094363e_1100x220.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post