234	https://fintechbusinessweekly.substack.com/p/news-you-need-to-know-before-money2020	News You Need To Know Before Money2020: Goldman & Apple Hit With CFPB Enforcement Actions	Open Banking Rule Already Faces Legal Challenge, Synapse Bankruptcy Update, SoLo Funds Hit With Putative Class Action Suit	<html><head></head><body><p>Hey all, Jason here.</p><p>When this hits your inbox, I‚Äôll presumably have already been awake for hours, thanks to the jet lag that comes with traveling from Amsterdam to Las Vegas.</p><p>Still, it‚Äôs worth it for the biggest event in US fintech, Money2020. I‚Äôll be recording two live podcasts, one with <strong>Navan‚Äôs Michael Sindicich</strong>, Tuesday at 11:55am (<a href="https://us.money2020.com/agenda/schedule#/agenda/event/fintech-business-weekly-the-expense-management-wars-with-navans-michael-sindicich-e103-62294">details here</a>), and the other with my <strong>podcasting partner-in-crime Alex Johnson, of Fintech Takes</strong>, Tuesday at 3:45pm (<a href="https://us.money2020.com/agenda/schedule#/agenda/event/fintech-recap-the-latest-fintech-news-live-from-money2020-e103-62296">details here</a>.)</p><p>Also looking forward to a slew of happy hours and dinners, including with my friends at Baselayer, Knot, Taktile, LoanPro, Sardine, Visa, Plaid, and numerous others ‚Äî if you see me this week, feel free to say hello!</p><pre><code><code>If you enjoy reading this newsletter each Sunday and find value in it, please consider supporting me (and finhealth non-profits!) by signing up for a paid subscription. It wouldn‚Äôt be possible to do what I do without the support of readers like you!</code></code></pre><p class="button-wrapper" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://fintechbusinessweekly.substack.com/subscribe?simple=true&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Subscribe or Upgrade to Paid&quot;,&quot;action&quot;:null,&quot;class&quot;:&quot;button-wrapper&quot;}" data-component-name="ButtonCreateButton"><a class="button primary button-wrapper" href="https://fintechbusinessweekly.substack.com/subscribe?simple=true"><span>Subscribe or Upgrade to Paid</span></a></p><h2>Goldman And Apple To Pay Nearly $90 Million Combined In CFPB Consent Order</h2><p>As Goldman Sachs continues to dismantle its consumer business, it will have to reckon with decisions and risks that, at the time, it must have deemed to be worth it.</p><p>Goldman took a hit of <a href="https://www.pymnts.com/news/banking/2024/report-goldman-sachs-to-sell-gm-credit-card-business-to-barclays/">approximately $400 million</a> on the sale of loan portfolios, comprised primarily of GM credit card loans, due to higher than excepted credit losses.</p><p>The GM loan book, though, is estimated at only approximately $2 billion.</p><p>That means that Goldman has about $18 billion in outstanding balances for its Apple Card program ‚Äî and a 6.9% annualized net charge-off rate for its overall consumer loan book, per its third quarter earnings presentation.</p><p>The industry-wide charge off rate on credit card loans, <a href="https://fred.stlouisfed.org/series/CORCCACBS">according to</a> Federal Reserve data, was 4.49% in Q2, the most recent data available.</p><p>This suggests any potential deal with JPMorgan Chase, who has been reported to be <a href="https://www.cnbc.com/2024/09/17/apple-jpmorgan-creditcard-goldman-sachs.html">negotiating with</a> Goldman and Apple to take over the program, may involve a significant write down on outstanding credit card receivables for Goldman.</p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2 is-viewable-imag" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F17b1feae-529e-4500-be5e-304998a75eb0_2292x1288.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F17b1feae-529e-4500-be5e-304998a75eb0_2292x1288.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F17b1feae-529e-4500-be5e-304998a75eb0_2292x1288.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F17b1feae-529e-4500-be5e-304998a75eb0_2292x1288.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F17b1feae-529e-4500-be5e-304998a75eb0_2292x1288.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F17b1feae-529e-4500-be5e-304998a75eb0_2292x1288.png" width="684" height="384.2802197802198" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/17b1feae-529e-4500-be5e-304998a75eb0_2292x1288.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:818,&quot;width&quot;:1456,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:684,&quot;bytes&quot;:447624,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F17b1feae-529e-4500-be5e-304998a75eb0_2292x1288.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F17b1feae-529e-4500-be5e-304998a75eb0_2292x1288.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F17b1feae-529e-4500-be5e-304998a75eb0_2292x1288.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F17b1feae-529e-4500-be5e-304998a75eb0_2292x1288.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2"><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a><figcaption class="image-caption">Image: Goldman Sachs <a href="https://www.goldmansachs.com/pressroom/press-releases/current/pdfs/2024-q3-earnings-results-presentation.pdf">Q3 2024 earnings presentation</a>.</figcaption></figure></div><p>Now, Goldman Sachs and its partner, Apple, have entered into consent orders with the CFPB over handling of customer disputes and deceptive practices related to the Apple Card Monthly Installments (ACMI) program.</p><p>Of the consent orders, CFPB Director Rohit Chopra <a href="https://www.consumerfinance.gov/about-us/newsroom/cfpb-orders-apple-and-goldman-sachs-to-pay-over-89-million-for-apple-card-failures/">said</a> (emphasis added):</p><blockquote><p>‚ÄúApple and Goldman Sachs illegally sidestepped their legal obligations for Apple Card borrowers. <strong>Big Tech companies and big Wall Street firms should not behave as if they are exempt from federal law.</strong> The CFPB is banning Goldman Sachs from offering a new consumer credit card unless it can demonstrate that it can actually follow the law.‚Äù</p></blockquote><p>Specifically, the CFPB <a href="https://files.consumerfinance.gov/f/documents/cfpb_goldman-sachs-bank-usa-consent-order_2024-10.pdf">found that</a> Goldman:</p><ul><li><p>violated the Truth in Lending Act and Regulation Z by failing to send acknowledgement notices and resolution letters within the required periods;</p></li><li><p>making adverse reports to consumer reporting agencies regarding amounts disputed in billing error notices prior to completing the requirements for billing error resolution;</p></li><li><p>failing to conduct reasonable investigations for disputes that qualified as billing error notices;</p></li><li><p>and holding consumers liable for amounts at issue in claims of unauthorized use before conducting a reasonable investigation.</p></li></ul><p>The CFPB further found that Goldman‚Äôs inadequate handling of consumer disputes violated the CFPA‚Äôs prohibition on unfair and deceptive acts or practices (UDAAPs).</p><p>Separately, the CFPB found that Goldman and Apple‚Äôs Apple Card Monthly Installments, which offered 0% APR financing on purchases of certain Apple devices with an Apple Card, misled consumers into believing they would automatically be enrolled in such plans, which was not the case.</p><p>The CFPB also found that Goldman misled consumers about how refunds for ACMI purchases would be applied in cases where a cardholder had both ACMI and non-ACMI balances.</p><p>The consent order requires Goldman to make approximately $19.8 million in redress to impacted consumers and pay a civil money penalty of $45 million.</p><p>Notably, the CFPB separately took action against Apple, which entered into a consent order with the Bureau, ‚Äúfor its role in marketing, offering, and servicing the Apple Card.‚Äù</p><p>According to the Apple consent order, the company ‚Äúis a ‚Äòservice provider‚Äô under the CFPA because it ‚Äòprovides a material service‚Äô to Goldman ‚Äòin connection with the offering or provision‚Äô of Apple Card, and ‚Äòparticipates in designing, operating, or maintaining‚Äô Apple Card.‚Äù</p><p>Apple, which controls the Apple Card user interface via its iOS operating system and Wallet app, failed to consistently send proper billing error notices to Goldman, which meant, in those cases, Goldman did not investigate customers‚Äô billing disputes or send legally required notices.</p><p>In cases where notice was not properly transmitted, cardholders did not receive credits for disputed transactions and may have had adverse information inappropriately reported to the credit bureaus.</p><p>In Apple‚Äôs role as service provider to Goldman, its failure to consistently and accurately transmit billing error disputes and the resulting consumer harm constitutes an unfair act or practice, the Bureau argues in the consent order.</p><p>Apple also was responsible for designing and implementing the advertising and user experience for Apple Card Monthly Installments, which ‚Äúemphasized the ease and simplicity of Apple Card and the ACMI enrollment process.‚Äù</p><p>However, the checkout process did not clearly and adequately explain that consumers needed to affirmatively opt in to the ACMI offer, and, per the consent order, Apple‚Äôs ‚Äúcustomer service representatives informed some consumers that iPhones purchased with an Apple Card would be automatically enrolled in ACMI.‚Äù</p><p>According to the consent order, Apple also unreasonably interfered with users‚Äô ability to choose ACMI by not displaying it as an option on browsers other than Apple‚Äôs own Safari or Safari in ‚Äúprivate‚Äù mode.</p><p>Apple‚Äôs actions regarding ACMI violate the CFPA‚Äôs prohibitions on UDAAP, the Bureau argues.</p><p>As part of the consent order, Apple will pay a $25 million civil money penalty.</p><h2>CFPB Introduces Final Open Banking Rule; Big Bank Trade Group Immediately Sues To Block It</h2><p>More or less exactly a year since CFPB Director Chopra <a href="https://fintechbusinessweekly.substack.com/p/money1033-top-takeaways-from-this">introduced</a> the proposed personal financial data rights rule at Money2020, he announced the final version at last week‚Äôs Philadelphia Federal Reserve 8th Annual Fintech Conference (which, sadly, I couldn‚Äôt make it to this year.)</p><p>The <a href="https://files.consumerfinance.gov/f/documents/cfpb_personal-financial-data-rights-final-rule_2024-10.pdf">594-page final rule</a>, commonly known as ‚Äú1033‚Äù in reference to the section of Dodd-Frank which created the consumer data right, is largely unchanged vs. last year‚Äôs proposed version. </p><p>Notable <a href="https://www.consumerfinancialserviceslawmonitor.com/2024/10/cfpb-issues-final-section-1033-open-banking-rule-legal-challenge-filed-immediately/#:~:text=Under%20the%20final%20rule%2C%20consumers,collection%20and%20use%20upon%20revocation.">changes include</a> exempting depository institutions with less than $850 million in assets from complying with the rule and an extended and tiered timeline for compliance by covered institutions. <em>(For a fuller breakdown of the final rule, I recommend <a href="https://fintechtakes.com/articles/2024-10-25/final-open-banking-rule/">Alex Johnson‚Äôs analysis here</a>.)</em></p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2 is-viewable-imag" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F6a48071c-2b44-4fdf-98ee-f6f60f6f3f8e_1076x581.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F6a48071c-2b44-4fdf-98ee-f6f60f6f3f8e_1076x581.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F6a48071c-2b44-4fdf-98ee-f6f60f6f3f8e_1076x581.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F6a48071c-2b44-4fdf-98ee-f6f60f6f3f8e_1076x581.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F6a48071c-2b44-4fdf-98ee-f6f60f6f3f8e_1076x581.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F6a48071c-2b44-4fdf-98ee-f6f60f6f3f8e_1076x581.png" width="1076" height="581" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/6a48071c-2b44-4fdf-98ee-f6f60f6f3f8e_1076x581.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:581,&quot;width&quot;:1076,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:null,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:null,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F6a48071c-2b44-4fdf-98ee-f6f60f6f3f8e_1076x581.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F6a48071c-2b44-4fdf-98ee-f6f60f6f3f8e_1076x581.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F6a48071c-2b44-4fdf-98ee-f6f60f6f3f8e_1076x581.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F6a48071c-2b44-4fdf-98ee-f6f60f6f3f8e_1076x581.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2"><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a><figcaption class="image-caption">Image: <a href="https://www.akerman.com/en/perspectives/cfpb-finalizes-1033-open-banking-rule.html">Akerman</a></figcaption></figure></div><p>The final rule allows for limited secondary use of consumer permissioned data, something a variety of stakeholders, including academics and researchers, had pushed for. However, entities that access users‚Äô data as permitted by the rule must obtain annual express reauthorization from consumers to continue accessing their data.</p><p>Still, some concern remains that data providers are permitted under the rule to reject third parties for a wide variety of risk management reasons, including for information security risks, and that they may do so inconsistently or for bad faith reasons.</p><p>Asked about this in a phone interview on Friday, CFPB Director Chopra said, ‚ÄúWe are always worried about pretextual denials that create roadblocks for challengers.‚Äù Chopra continued to say, ‚ÄúWe do expect there to be ongoing work in this area. It has been a topic of constant conversation between me and the other regulators. I do hope we will be able to provide even more information over time on this, to ensure we don‚Äôt have pretextual denials.‚Äù</p><p>In <a href="https://www.consumerfinance.gov/about-us/newsroom/prepared-remarks-of-cfpb-director-rohit-chopra-at-the-federal-reserve-bank-of-philadelphia-on-the-personal-financial-data-rights-rule/">his remarks</a> last week at the Philadelphia Federal Reserve, Director Chopra began <a href="https://www.consumerfinance.gov/about-us/newsroom/prepared-remarks-of-cfpb-director-rohit-chopra-at-the-federal-reserve-bank-of-philadelphia-on-the-personal-financial-data-rights-rule/">by saying</a>, ‚ÄúThe rule will provide more freedom, promote decentralization, and spur greater competition.‚Äù</p><p>Chopra touted the potential for open banking to facilitate increased competition by making it easier for consumers to switch accounts, thereby earning higher rates of interest on their savings or switching to less expensive borrowing products, for example.</p><p>Director Chopra further touted the potential for open banking-enabled account-to-account payments, also referred to as pay-by-bank, to ‚Äúmake payment options like ACH and FedNow more mainstream,‚Äù thereby competing with omnipresent card networks. He also touted the potential for consumer-permissioned to ‚Äúhelp supplement and improve the accuracy of traditional credit histories and help more people obtain credit on better terms.‚Äù</p><p>While these are <em>possible</em> outcomes from open banking, they are by no means guaranteed.</p><p>Comparison sites for savings rates and credit cards and loans have long existed ‚Äî whether or not open banking eliminates or at least lowers the barriers to users switching to an economically more optimal product or service is far from a sure thing.</p><p>Other countries that have codified open banking regulations, or even gone further to promote account portability through current (checking) account switch services, have not necessarily seen meaningful changes in user behavior.</p><p>Even if users do opt to switch banks, there‚Äôs no guarantee that their behavior will promote a more ‚Äúdecentralized‚Äù financial system, as Chopra hopes it will.</p><p>Indeed, in the UK, according to statistics from the country‚Äôs current account switch service, large incumbents, like NatWest, Lloyds, and RBS were some of the biggest net gainers, while newer entrants, like Chase‚Äôs UK offering, Monzo, and Virgin Money were net losers.</p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2 is-viewable-imag" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F28e0ee29-9c84-40a2-af47-d00f3e33e81e_968x938.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F28e0ee29-9c84-40a2-af47-d00f3e33e81e_968x938.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F28e0ee29-9c84-40a2-af47-d00f3e33e81e_968x938.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F28e0ee29-9c84-40a2-af47-d00f3e33e81e_968x938.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F28e0ee29-9c84-40a2-af47-d00f3e33e81e_968x938.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F28e0ee29-9c84-40a2-af47-d00f3e33e81e_968x938.png" width="542" height="525.202479338843" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/28e0ee29-9c84-40a2-af47-d00f3e33e81e_968x938.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:938,&quot;width&quot;:968,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:542,&quot;bytes&quot;:130429,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F28e0ee29-9c84-40a2-af47-d00f3e33e81e_968x938.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F28e0ee29-9c84-40a2-af47-d00f3e33e81e_968x938.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F28e0ee29-9c84-40a2-af47-d00f3e33e81e_968x938.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F28e0ee29-9c84-40a2-af47-d00f3e33e81e_968x938.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2"><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a><figcaption class="image-caption">Image: <a href="https://www.wearepay.uk/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/CASS-Dashboard-Q2-2024-V4.pdf">Current Account Switch Service Quarterly Dashboard</a></figcaption></figure></div><p>In our interview on Friday, Director Chopra acknowledged the impacts on competitive dynamics would vary by product for deposits and payments vs. credit and lending, and emphasized that there is ‚Äúno question that people will have more choices if they‚Äôre able to use their financial transaction data as part of their loan application. That will have a meaningful effect in how people are able not just to use that data with their existing deposit account provider or existing credit card provider, but really use it across the board.‚Äù</p><p>The US‚Äôs largest banks are far better equipped, with both funding and talent, to develop and execute on strategies that leverage open banking to benefit their bottom lines.</p><p>Mega regional PNC, which has <a href="https://fintechbusinessweekly.substack.com/p/fidelity-and-pnc-lead-akoyas-open">resisted allowing</a> aggregators like Plaid and Finicity to access its customers‚Äô data, has said as much, with its CEO Bill Demchak <a href="https://www.bankingdive.com/news/pnc-demchak-open-banking-growth-corporate-deposit/726606/">remarking that</a> PNC would ‚Äúpull share out of smaller banks who won‚Äôt have the technology to be able to take advantage of open banks.‚Äù</p><p>Demchak added that all open banking regulation is ‚Äúgoing to do is drain [small] banks of accounts, by big banks who have the technology.‚Äù</p><h4>Bank Policy Institute, Kentucky Bankers Association, Forcht File Suit Challenging Rule</h4><p>Although the rule is ‚Äúfinal,‚Äù it still faces challenges: the same day Chopra introduced it, the Bank Policy Institute, together with the Kentucky Bankers Association and Forcht Bank, filed <a href="https://bpi.com/banks-challenge-cfpb-rule-jeopardizing-security-and-privacy-of-consumer-financial-data/">a legal challenge</a> against it.</p><p>Their suit argues that the final rule, as written, requires no oversight of third parties using bank data, that the rule will increase the likelihood of fraud and scams, that it allows unsafe practices like screen scraping to persist, that it fails to hold third parties accountable, that it allows third parties to profit, at no cost, from systems built and maintained by banks, and that the rule has an unreasonable implementation timeline.</p><p>The plaintiffs argue that the CFPB‚Äôs proposed rule exceeds the statutory authority granted by 1033 and that the CFPB is ‚Äúinjecting itself into a developing, well-functioning ecosystem that is thriving under private initiatives,‚Äù which will ‚Äúcut off that private development and replace it with a complicated, expensive, mandatory regulatory framework that Congress never authorized.‚Äù</p><p>The statutory authority that the BPI suit references, section 1033 of Dodd-Frank, comprises less than one page of the 2010 bill‚Äôs 849 pages, with the operative section amounting to little more than a sentence:</p><blockquote><p>‚ÄúSubject to rules prescribed by the Bureau, a covered person shall make available to a consumer, upon request, information in the control or possession of the covered person concerning the consumer financial product or service that the consumer obtained from such covered person, including information relating to any transaction, series of transactions, or to the account including costs, charges and usage data. The information shall be made available in an electronic form usable by consumers.‚Äù</p></blockquote><p>In a post-Chevron world, and one in which, thanks to the Corner Post decision, timelines to challenge regulatory rulemakings are, essentially, infinite, it is difficult to predict what kind of reception BPI‚Äôs challenge to 1033 will get in the judiciary.</p><p>There is a certain amount of irony that BPI, which counts the nation‚Äôs largest banks, including <strong>Bank of America, Citibank, JPMorgan Chase, Wells Fargo, Truist, Capital One, and PNC <a href="https://bpi.com/about-us/#membership">as its members</a></strong>, is leading the charge to challenge open banking ‚Äî when <strong>representatives of those same banks <a href="https://financialdataexchange.org/FDX/About/About-FDX.aspx?a315d1c24e44=2#a315d1c24e44">sit on the board</a> of the Financial Data Exchange</strong>, seemingly the only body in contention to be certified as a standard setting organization under 1033.</p><p>Director Chopra was unable to comment on BPI‚Äôs suit, but regarding FDX, he acknowledged hearing ‚Äúchatter‚Äù in the fintech community around concern about who controls any standard setting organizations, and that the Bureau takes those concerns ‚Äúvery seriously.‚Äù Regarding FDX‚Äôs application specifically, Chopra added, ‚ÄúThere‚Äôs obviously a host of issues that we have to suss out with respect to this application.‚Äù</p><h2>Unlicensed P2P Payday Lender SoLo Funds Faces Putative Class Action</h2><p>SoLo Funds, an unlicensed peer-to-peer payday lender, has won plaudits from outlets as varied as <a href="https://www.americanbanker.com/news/solo-funds-breaks-million-customer-mark-challenges-the-status-quo">American Banker</a>, <a href="https://www.fastcompany.com/90605796/payday-loan-alternative-solo-funds">Fast Company</a>, <a href="https://techcrunch.com/2023/02/28/serena-ventures-solo-funds-1m-registered-users/">TechCrunch</a>, and <a href="https://www.cnbc.com/2020/04/15/solo-funds-offers-interest-free-microloans-to-millions-of-americans.html">CNBC</a>, even being named to the news site‚Äôs <a href="https://www.cnbc.com/2023/05/09/solo-funds-disruptor-50.html">Disruptor 50 list</a> in 2023.</p><p>The praise came despite <a href="https://fintechbusinessweekly.substack.com/p/tips-and-donations-can-reach-1916">long-standing</a>, <a href="https://fintechbusinessweekly.substack.com/p/techstars-backed-solo-funds-sued">known</a>, and <a href="https://fintechbusinessweekly.substack.com/p/california-dc-cite-solo-funds-for">well-documented</a> risks in the company‚Äôs business model, including that it has operated without required licenses, may operate as an unlicensed and unregistered credit reporting agency, and leverages deceptive ‚Äúdark patterns‚Äù to charge rates equivalent to APRs as high as 4,280%, even in states where such costly forms of credit are illegal.</p><p>The company has faced legal and regulatory challenges in numerous jurisdictions, including in Washington, DC, Connecticut, Minnesota, and California.</p><p>SoLo Funds is being sued by the CFPB for, the Bureau alleges, use of ‚Äúdark patterns‚Äù to deceive borrowers about the total cost of credit.</p><p>SoLo Funds has said the CFPB‚Äôs suit is ‚Äúselective‚Äù and <a href="https://solofunds.com/blog/cfpb-attacks-solo-funds-a-community-finance-platform-that-has-saved-over-40m-in-fees-for-underserved-americans/">that</a> the company believes that <strong>‚Äúregulators have worked hard to stifle innovation and prevent underserved communities from accessing better financial products.‚Äù</strong></p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2 is-viewable-imag" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ffe3b7f72-5e56-4ce9-9a6f-6d64ec993fcb_1179x1495.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ffe3b7f72-5e56-4ce9-9a6f-6d64ec993fcb_1179x1495.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ffe3b7f72-5e56-4ce9-9a6f-6d64ec993fcb_1179x1495.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ffe3b7f72-5e56-4ce9-9a6f-6d64ec993fcb_1179x1495.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ffe3b7f72-5e56-4ce9-9a6f-6d64ec993fcb_1179x1495.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ffe3b7f72-5e56-4ce9-9a6f-6d64ec993fcb_1179x1495.png" width="342" height="433.6641221374046" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/fe3b7f72-5e56-4ce9-9a6f-6d64ec993fcb_1179x1495.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:1495,&quot;width&quot;:1179,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:342,&quot;bytes&quot;:956307,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ffe3b7f72-5e56-4ce9-9a6f-6d64ec993fcb_1179x1495.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ffe3b7f72-5e56-4ce9-9a6f-6d64ec993fcb_1179x1495.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ffe3b7f72-5e56-4ce9-9a6f-6d64ec993fcb_1179x1495.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ffe3b7f72-5e56-4ce9-9a6f-6d64ec993fcb_1179x1495.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2"><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a><figcaption class="image-caption">Image: SoLo Fund‚Äôs since-deleted tweet</figcaption></figure></div><p>Now, SoLo Funds is facing a putative class action suit, <em>Danielle Cofield v. SoLo Funds, Inc.</em>, over similar issues, filed in US District Court for the Central District of California on October 16, 2024.</p><p>The suit alleges that ‚ÄúSoLo entices consumers to apply for loans through its platform by falsely representing in its advertisements that a consumer could obtain financing at zero interest,‚Äù when, in reality, the suit says, ‚Äú[v]irtually all consumers who receive loans incur a tip fee, a donation fee, or both. These fees result in a cost of credit that is both unlawful, and not disclosed to the consumer.‚Äù </p><p>The putative class action suit alleges violations of the Truth in Lending Act, California‚Äôs Unfair Competition Law, California‚Äôs Consumer Legal Remedies Act, California‚Äôs False Advertising Law, and Ohio‚Äôs Consumer Sales Practices Act.</p><p>The plaintiff is seeking certification of class status, injunctive relief, disgorgement and restitution, attorneys‚Äô fees and costs, and actual, consequential, punitive, statutory and treble damages.</p><h2>Evolve‚Äôs End Game In Synapse Bankruptcy Comes Into Focus</h2><p>Last week‚Äôs status hearing in the ongoing Synapse saga was disheartening, to say the least.</p><p>End users who dialed in to speak to the court are, understandably immensely frustrated; the Chapter 11 trustee, former FDIC Chair Jelena McWilliams, sounded resigned to the situation; and Judge Barash sounded defeated.</p><p>Barash and McWilliams are constrained it what they are empowered to do by the scope of the bankruptcy process, and those limitations have become increasingly clear.</p><p>McWilliams‚Äô status report, filed in advance of the hearing, had scant new information. </p><p>Since the last report, Evolve distributed an additional approximately $169,575 in DDA funds; the remaining DDA funds Evolve holds are associated with fintech programs that the bank has been unable to establish communication with.</p><p>The remaining DDA funds Lineage holds, approximately $55,000, belong to fintech programs themselves, rather than end users.</p><p>A total of about $53.5 million in FBO funds, about $46.9 million of which are held by Evolve, remain to be distributed.</p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2 is-viewable-imag" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fccc16294-f627-4c6c-b4cd-2dc00fc721a4_1962x540.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fccc16294-f627-4c6c-b4cd-2dc00fc721a4_1962x540.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fccc16294-f627-4c6c-b4cd-2dc00fc721a4_1962x540.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fccc16294-f627-4c6c-b4cd-2dc00fc721a4_1962x540.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fccc16294-f627-4c6c-b4cd-2dc00fc721a4_1962x540.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fccc16294-f627-4c6c-b4cd-2dc00fc721a4_1962x540.png" width="1456" height="401" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/ccc16294-f627-4c6c-b4cd-2dc00fc721a4_1962x540.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:401,&quot;width&quot;:1456,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:156954,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fccc16294-f627-4c6c-b4cd-2dc00fc721a4_1962x540.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fccc16294-f627-4c6c-b4cd-2dc00fc721a4_1962x540.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fccc16294-f627-4c6c-b4cd-2dc00fc721a4_1962x540.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fccc16294-f627-4c6c-b4cd-2dc00fc721a4_1962x540.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2"><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a><figcaption class="image-caption">Image: Chapter 11 Trustee‚Äôs Eleventh Status Report</figcaption></figure></div><p>According to Evolve‚Äôs status report and its attorney‚Äôs statements in court, Evolve  completed reconciliation on October 18th ‚Äî though this did not yield the answers that end users expected it to, based on reactions during the status conference.</p><p>McWilliams cautioned that including Lineage‚Äôs and Evolve‚Äôs reports as appendices to her filing did not constitute an endorsement, writing that ‚Äú[t]he inclusion of these reports as appendices is not an endorsement by the Trustee of positions taken by any particular Partner Bank and is solely for informational purposes.‚Äù</p><p>While many expected the completion of Evolve‚Äôs months-long reconciliation efforts to provide clarity about the size and cause of any shortfall, this turned out not to be the case.</p><p>Neither Evolve‚Äôs filing nor its counsel in the status hearing commented on the status of the approximately $35 million in reserves the bank holds, which it has previously said it would distribute to end users ‚Äúif the reconciliation indicates‚Äù it is appropriate to do so.</p><p>Nor did Evolve comment in its filing or the hearing on allegations from former Synapse CEO Sankaet Pathak about various causes of the shortfall, though an FAQ on its site specifies it disputes Pathak‚Äôs allegations.</p><div class="pullquote"><p>‚Äú<strong>The information shared by Evolve is the information they shared with us, we don‚Äôt have anything more than that</strong>‚Äù ‚Äî Synapse Chapter 11 Bankruptcy Trustee, former FDIC Chair Jelena McWilliams, during last week‚Äôs status conference.</p></div><p>Rather, according to Evolve, the third-party consultant it hired, Ankura, calculated only users‚Äô aggregate balances across all Synapse banks and the amount, if any, held at Evolve ‚Äî but <em>not</em> specific amounts held at <em>other</em> banks, nor the size and cause of any shortfall.</p><p>Per <a href="https://reconciliationbyevolve.com/FAQ">an FAQ</a> on its site, Ankura (emphasis added throughout) ‚Äú<strong>reconstructed</strong> <strong>end user balances (i) at Evolve</strong> and (ii) across the entire Synapse ecosystem, regardless of which other ecosystem bank may hold their funds. Accordingly, for some end users, this second balance ‚Äî <strong>the Synapse ecosystem balance ‚Äî may be comprised of funds held at Evolve and at other institutions</strong>. The reconciliation <strong>did not subdivide the Synapse ecosystem balance by institution, with the exception of the Evolve balance</strong>, because Ankura did not have access to transaction-level data from other Synapse ecosystem banks.‚Äù</p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2 is-viewable-imag" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc3c29f2c-246b-42ed-b359-6694f5941e02_1266x898.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc3c29f2c-246b-42ed-b359-6694f5941e02_1266x898.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc3c29f2c-246b-42ed-b359-6694f5941e02_1266x898.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc3c29f2c-246b-42ed-b359-6694f5941e02_1266x898.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc3c29f2c-246b-42ed-b359-6694f5941e02_1266x898.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc3c29f2c-246b-42ed-b359-6694f5941e02_1266x898.png" width="624" height="442.61611374407585" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/c3c29f2c-246b-42ed-b359-6694f5941e02_1266x898.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:898,&quot;width&quot;:1266,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:624,&quot;bytes&quot;:1223703,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc3c29f2c-246b-42ed-b359-6694f5941e02_1266x898.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc3c29f2c-246b-42ed-b359-6694f5941e02_1266x898.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc3c29f2c-246b-42ed-b359-6694f5941e02_1266x898.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc3c29f2c-246b-42ed-b359-6694f5941e02_1266x898.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2"><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a><figcaption class="image-caption">Evolve‚Äôs FAQ website includes a video message from the embattled bank‚Äôs chairman, Scot Lenoir.</figcaption></figure></div><p>On <a href="https://reconciliationbyevolve.com/Home/portalid/0">its website</a> for impacted end users, Evolve says that, on November 4th <em>(the day before perhaps the most contentious election in modern American history)</em>, once authenticated, users will be able to access ‚Äútheir <strong>Synapse ecosystem balance</strong> as well as the <strong>amount of any of their funds that </strong><em><strong>Evolve holds</strong></em> and will be disbursing to them.‚Äù</p><p>End users will then be able to select a payment method for how they‚Äôd like to receive their funds.</p><p>But, to reiterate: Evolve will tell end users their ‚Äútotal‚Äù balance that existed across all of Synapse partner banks and the ‚Äúamount of any of their funds that <strong>Evolve</strong> holds‚Äù ‚Äî <strong>but what happens if these amounts don‚Äôt match?</strong></p><p>In the status conference, Evolve‚Äôs attorney referenced a process for end users to dispute the amounts Evolve has calculated but didn‚Äôt provided any additional detail about how that process would actually work or who would adjudicate the claims.</p><p>The FAQs on Evolve‚Äôs site don‚Äôt mention such a process, and representatives for Evolve did not respond to a request for additional explanation of how this process would work.</p><p>In an unrelated motion, Grabr, parent company to fintech program GrabrFi, requested that the court order Lineage to produce personnel for an oral examination and documents that speak to balance details, communications between Lineage and Synapse, reconciliation efforts, funds shortfalls, and related topics.</p><p>Judge Barash granted the motion but clarified, in response to questions from Lineage‚Äôs attorney during the hearing, that the bank can seek an order of protection that would effectively block the request.</p><h2>FT Partners: September Saw $4.4B In Funding Across 322 Deals</h2><p>The frothy days of 2021 are well behind us, but deals are still getting done.</p><p><a href="https://a16z.com/newsletter/october-2024-fintech-newsletter-fintech-isnt-dead-ai-is-driving-a-new-beginning/">Some investors</a> are banking on AI to drive a ‚Äúnew beginning‚Äù for fintech, and, while you can always count on VCs to talk their own book, it remains far from certain that AI will significantly improve the prospects and profitability of certain fintech business models.</p><p>That said, based on a review of this week‚Äôs <a href="https://us.money2020.com/agenda">Money2020 agenda</a>, AI hype promises to be inescapable ‚Äî hopefully AI firms, flush with cash, and their deep-pocketed investors at least throw some good parties. </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2 is-viewable-imag" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F6c6477a0-2f14-4778-91ff-2ac1db89da16_2438x1370.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F6c6477a0-2f14-4778-91ff-2ac1db89da16_2438x1370.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F6c6477a0-2f14-4778-91ff-2ac1db89da16_2438x1370.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F6c6477a0-2f14-4778-91ff-2ac1db89da16_2438x1370.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F6c6477a0-2f14-4778-91ff-2ac1db89da16_2438x1370.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F6c6477a0-2f14-4778-91ff-2ac1db89da16_2438x1370.png" width="1456" height="818" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/6c6477a0-2f14-4778-91ff-2ac1db89da16_2438x1370.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:818,&quot;width&quot;:1456,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:2068151,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F6c6477a0-2f14-4778-91ff-2ac1db89da16_2438x1370.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F6c6477a0-2f14-4778-91ff-2ac1db89da16_2438x1370.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F6c6477a0-2f14-4778-91ff-2ac1db89da16_2438x1370.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F6c6477a0-2f14-4778-91ff-2ac1db89da16_2438x1370.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2"><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a><figcaption class="image-caption">Image: <a href="https://ftpartners.docsend.com/view/z39e8ptt7x5quij6">FT Partners</a></figcaption></figure></div><h2>Other Good Reads</h2><p>Are We Getting Steak or Sizzle from Government Actions on Payments Competition? (<strong><a href="https://openbanker.beehiiv.com/p/arewegettingsteakorsizzleinpaymentscompetition?utm_campaign=are-we-getting-steak-or-sizzle-from-government-actions-on-payments-competition&amp;utm_medium=newsletter&amp;utm_source=openbanker.beehiiv.com">Matt Janiga for Open Banker</a></strong>)</p><p>Early Thoughts On The Final Open Banking Rule (<strong><a href="https://fintechtakes.com/articles/2024-10-25/final-open-banking-rule/">Fintech Takes</a></strong>)</p><p>Consumer AI Agents in Fintech (<strong><a href="https://www.fintechbrainfood.com/p/ai-agents">Fintech Brainfood</a></strong>)</p><h2>About Fintech Business Weekly</h2><p>Looking to work with me in any of the following areas? <a href="mailto:jason@fintechbusinessweekly.com">Email me</a>.</p><ul><li><p>Pre-order my book, <em><strong>Banking as a Service: Opportunities, Challenges and Risks of New Banking Business Models</strong></em>, <a href="https://www.koganpage.com/accounting-finance-banking/banking-as-a-service-9781398617889">here</a></p></li><li><p>Vendor, partner &amp; investment opportunity advice and due diligence</p></li><li><p>Fintech advising &amp; consulting</p></li><li><p>Sponsoring this newsletter</p></li><li><p>News tip or story suggestion ‚Äî <strong>reach me on Signal at +1-316-512-1571</strong></p></li></ul></body></html>	Vegas fintech event kicks off. Goldman and Apple face CFPB penalties. Open banking rule sparks legal battle. Synapse bankruptcy drama continues. Funding stays robust.	2024-10-27 12:59:49	2024-10-30 07:43:37.532	2024-10-30 07:51:30.763	{ai}	https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F17b1feae-529e-4500-be5e-304998a75eb0_2292x1288.png	Jason Mikula	news-you-need-to-know-before
187	https://www.eu.vc/p/the-consumerisation-of-climate-part	The Consumerisation of Climate (Part 1)	by Estia Ryan, Principal & Head of Research at Eka Ventures. | Originally published on Eka Ventures Newsletter.	<html><head></head><body><p>Guest post by <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/estia-ryan/">Estia Ryan</a>, Principal &amp; Head of Research at <a href="https://www.ekavc.com/">Eka Ventures</a>. | Originally published on <a href="https://ekavc.substack.com/p/the-consumerisation-of-climate-part">Eka Ventures Newsletter</a>.</p><div><hr></div><p>After exploring Consumer Health &amp; UK Consumer, we‚Äôre now turning to the Consumerisation of Climate.</p><p>At Eka, we think <em>a</em> <em>lot</em> about Sustainable Consumption. In recent weeks, we‚Äôve seen more Sustainable Consumption signals including eBay‚Äôs slashing of UK seller fees to keep up with competition, rumours of Vinted‚Äôs secondary round fuelled by continued resale growth, or even Rent the Runway‚Äôs strategic pivot earlier in the year towards resale.</p><p><strong>What better time to unpack the Consumerisation of Climate?</strong></p><p>In this series, we‚Äôll be exploring three sub-themes: (1) Circular consumption (i.e. Vinted, eBay, Rent the Runway), (2) Sustainable brands (i.e. Patagonia, Hylo, Oddmuse), and (3) Enabling Technologies (i.e. Hived, Axle, UseAgain).</p><p>We know that consumer supply chains contribute a high percentage of total environmental impacts across carbon, land &amp; water use, and material use. In the UK, consumption emissions are close to <a href="https://www.ons.gov.uk/economy/environmentalaccounts/methodologies/measuringukgreenhousegasemissions#:~:text=Footprint%20(consumption)%20emissions%20cover%20consumption,a%2036%25%20reduction%20since%201990.)">750 million tonnes of CO2</a> annually. There are a few ways to shift this.</p><p>Firstly, we can keep goods in circulation for longer so that our linear economy becomes more circular. This is what we‚Äôll be exploring in this weeks edition. Other strategies include creating more sustainable brands from the outset which can better slot into a circular economy (i.e. designing goods with better inputs and with an ability to be recycled more easily).</p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2 is-viewable-imag" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7ac95c75-fd85-4488-8b7f-18426c47fae2_1839x760.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7ac95c75-fd85-4488-8b7f-18426c47fae2_1839x760.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7ac95c75-fd85-4488-8b7f-18426c47fae2_1839x760.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7ac95c75-fd85-4488-8b7f-18426c47fae2_1839x760.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7ac95c75-fd85-4488-8b7f-18426c47fae2_1839x760.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7ac95c75-fd85-4488-8b7f-18426c47fae2_1839x760.png" width="1456" height="602" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/7ac95c75-fd85-4488-8b7f-18426c47fae2_1839x760.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:602,&quot;width&quot;:1456,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:null,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:null,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;topImage&quot;:true,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" title="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7ac95c75-fd85-4488-8b7f-18426c47fae2_1839x760.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7ac95c75-fd85-4488-8b7f-18426c47fae2_1839x760.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7ac95c75-fd85-4488-8b7f-18426c47fae2_1839x760.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7ac95c75-fd85-4488-8b7f-18426c47fae2_1839x760.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" fetchpriority="high"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a></figure></div><div><hr></div><h2>Introducing circular consumption üóûÔ∏è</h2><h3>Linear vs. circular consumption: what‚Äôs the difference?</h3><p><strong>Linear consumption</strong> means that products are created using raw materials, purchased, and then discarded once their use has ended. This process not only consumes vast amounts of natural resources, but also generates significant waste, contributing to overflowing landfills and pollution.</p><p><strong>Circular consumption</strong> offers an alternative. Instead of discarding goods after use, these are kept in circulation for as long as possible through reselling, renting, repairing, and recycling. This model reduces the need for new resources, lowers waste, and minimizes the environmental impact of production.</p><p>We lay out a few high profile examples of linear, re-use, and rental companies below across core consumer categories.</p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2 is-viewable-imag" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F18801551-0fb5-4aa6-be38-07e3e1347338_696x267.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F18801551-0fb5-4aa6-be38-07e3e1347338_696x267.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F18801551-0fb5-4aa6-be38-07e3e1347338_696x267.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F18801551-0fb5-4aa6-be38-07e3e1347338_696x267.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F18801551-0fb5-4aa6-be38-07e3e1347338_696x267.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F18801551-0fb5-4aa6-be38-07e3e1347338_696x267.png" width="636" height="243.98275862068965" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/18801551-0fb5-4aa6-be38-07e3e1347338_696x267.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:267,&quot;width&quot;:696,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:636,&quot;bytes&quot;:40770,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" title="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F18801551-0fb5-4aa6-be38-07e3e1347338_696x267.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F18801551-0fb5-4aa6-be38-07e3e1347338_696x267.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F18801551-0fb5-4aa6-be38-07e3e1347338_696x267.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F18801551-0fb5-4aa6-be38-07e3e1347338_696x267.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a></figure></div><h3>Peer-to-peer platforms: eBay, Vinted, Vinterior, Back Market, Depop</h3><p>Peer to peer platforms connect individual buyers and sellers (typically consumers rather than businesses) to trade goods on a platform. Several P2P platforms are pioneering the circular consumption model by facilitating the exchange of secondhand goods and offering rental services. Examples include:</p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2 is-viewable-imag" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fa74eae8c-7247-4bbe-ac36-d5b269919796_730x500.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fa74eae8c-7247-4bbe-ac36-d5b269919796_730x500.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fa74eae8c-7247-4bbe-ac36-d5b269919796_730x500.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fa74eae8c-7247-4bbe-ac36-d5b269919796_730x500.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fa74eae8c-7247-4bbe-ac36-d5b269919796_730x500.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fa74eae8c-7247-4bbe-ac36-d5b269919796_730x500.png" width="631" height="432.1917808219178" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/a74eae8c-7247-4bbe-ac36-d5b269919796_730x500.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:500,&quot;width&quot;:730,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:631,&quot;bytes&quot;:89656,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" title="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fa74eae8c-7247-4bbe-ac36-d5b269919796_730x500.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fa74eae8c-7247-4bbe-ac36-d5b269919796_730x500.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fa74eae8c-7247-4bbe-ac36-d5b269919796_730x500.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fa74eae8c-7247-4bbe-ac36-d5b269919796_730x500.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a></figure></div><h3>Monetising circular economy platforms</h3><p>Peer to peer platforms are typically monetised using a combination of ads, seller fees, buyer fees, and posting fees. We‚Äôll explore this in more detail in an edition later down the line. Ebay‚Äôs <strong>seller fees</strong> were in the press last week after the company decided to slash fees in response to competition.</p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F6a03262f-8c9b-4cd0-84c0-3f82f495f8f8_2650x972.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F6a03262f-8c9b-4cd0-84c0-3f82f495f8f8_2650x972.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F6a03262f-8c9b-4cd0-84c0-3f82f495f8f8_2650x972.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F6a03262f-8c9b-4cd0-84c0-3f82f495f8f8_2650x972.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F6a03262f-8c9b-4cd0-84c0-3f82f495f8f8_2650x972.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F6a03262f-8c9b-4cd0-84c0-3f82f495f8f8_2650x972.png" width="615" height="225.5563186813187" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/6a03262f-8c9b-4cd0-84c0-3f82f495f8f8_2650x972.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:534,&quot;width&quot;:1456,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:615,&quot;bytes&quot;:1686320,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" title="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F6a03262f-8c9b-4cd0-84c0-3f82f495f8f8_2650x972.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F6a03262f-8c9b-4cd0-84c0-3f82f495f8f8_2650x972.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F6a03262f-8c9b-4cd0-84c0-3f82f495f8f8_2650x972.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F6a03262f-8c9b-4cd0-84c0-3f82f495f8f8_2650x972.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div></div></div></a></figure></div><p>Previously, sellers had been required to pay fees for each item they list, and eBay would take a percentage of the final sale price when the transaction is completed. You can still see the US site‚Äôs list price here based on the <a href="https://www.ebay.com/help/selling/fees-credits-invoices/selling-fees?id=4822">various consumer categories</a>. Now, eBay lets sellers list items for free.</p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2 is-viewable-imag" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2da9b23a-6ef6-47a5-a9cc-3ac464d0771b_1744x1200.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2da9b23a-6ef6-47a5-a9cc-3ac464d0771b_1744x1200.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2da9b23a-6ef6-47a5-a9cc-3ac464d0771b_1744x1200.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2da9b23a-6ef6-47a5-a9cc-3ac464d0771b_1744x1200.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2da9b23a-6ef6-47a5-a9cc-3ac464d0771b_1744x1200.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2da9b23a-6ef6-47a5-a9cc-3ac464d0771b_1744x1200.png" width="573" height="394.33104395604397" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/2da9b23a-6ef6-47a5-a9cc-3ac464d0771b_1744x1200.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:1002,&quot;width&quot;:1456,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:573,&quot;bytes&quot;:1881756,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" title="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2da9b23a-6ef6-47a5-a9cc-3ac464d0771b_1744x1200.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2da9b23a-6ef6-47a5-a9cc-3ac464d0771b_1744x1200.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2da9b23a-6ef6-47a5-a9cc-3ac464d0771b_1744x1200.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2da9b23a-6ef6-47a5-a9cc-3ac464d0771b_1744x1200.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a></figure></div><p>On the P2P sites, there is typically a lot of customer education which happens in the flow (this will be a recurring feature in other marketplaces). Here, eBay walks us through how we can list, price, and send our items.</p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2 is-viewable-imag" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/htt